category.name: 4GD
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: 4GD_BOM_EndItemForAssign
preference.preference_description: Specifies the end item for assigning the unit number effectivity to a BOM Line when a Design Component is assigned from a 4GD subset definition to an MBOM assembly.

preference.name: 4GD_Search_Limit
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of objects that can be loaded in Search Results View with no Out of Memory error. The default size is 100000.

preference.name: 4GD_massupdaterealization_update_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Defines the batch size for updating realizations found by 'Mass Update Realization' in My Teamcenter and Change Manager application. It is advisable to set the batch size based on network parameters between Teamcenter client and server such as latency, bandwidth etc. A value of 0 or less than 0 indicates that there is no maximum batch size and that all the realizations will be fetched in single batch. Any positive integer value indicates the maximum batch size and thus the realizations selected by the user will be updated in multiple batches as per the batch size specified by this preference.

preference.name: 4G_SubsetItem_view_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of BOM view revision which is used by the subset Item revision while mapping Design Component to PSOccurrences.

preference.name: BOM_MARKUP_ADD_FONT_STYLE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the text font style when a user adds a markup to a BOM line in Structure Manager or a markup space in 4G Designer. Valid Values: 0 (plain text) 1 (bold text) 2 (italic text) 3 (bold and italic text)

preference.name: BOM_MARKUP_ADD_FOREGROUND
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color of the markup text added to a BOM line by a user in Structure Manager or in a markup space in 4G Designer. Valid Values: Specifies three color values in order of precedence in the format N1,N2,N3, where each value is an integer in the range 0 to 255. Enter color values in red, green, blue (RGB) code, where, for example, 0, 0, 0 represents the color black and 0, 255, 255 represents the color aqua.

preference.name: BOM_MARKUP_STRIKE_FOREGROUND
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color of the strikethrough marking if a user deletes a BOM line or edits a property in Structure Manager or removes an object in a markup space in 4G Designer. Valid Values: Specify three color values in order of precedence in the format N1,N2,N3, where each value is an integer in the range 0 to 255. Enter color values in red, green, blue (RGB) code, where, for example, 0, 0, 0 represents the color black and 0, 255, 255 represents the color aqua.

preference.name: CPD_ContentSearch_SavedQueries
preference.preference_description: Lists the names of saved queries that are available in the 4G Designer attribute search. Valid Values: Any valid saved query name.

preference.name: CPD_IntroSavedQueryTypeList
preference.preference_description: Populates the list of available saved queries in a blank Content Explorer. Valid Values: Any valid saved query name.It can be empty also.

preference.name: CPD_Realization_AssignToPartition_bl_attr
preference.preference_description: Teamcenter uses this property when assigning subordinates to partitions during realization of an item assembly or its subsequent update. Valid Values: Any BOMLine property whose value is an alphanumeric string containing one or more partition IDs. Multiple IDs must be separated by comma characters (,). For example, PTN000001,PTN000002.

preference.name: CPD_SearchOptions_ContextMenu
preference.preference_description: Contains the internal names of the context menu commands displayed when you right-click search results in the Content Search view of the 4G Designer application. Valid Values: Any valid option names in the transfer option set defined in the CPD_SearchOptions_TransferOptionSet preference.

preference.name: CPD_SearchOptions_TransferOptionSet
preference.preference_description: Contains the name of the transfer option set that loads related objects when you right-click search results in the Content Search view of the 4G Designer application. Valid Values: Any valid transfer option set name.

preference.name: CPD_Workset_Type
preference.preference_description: Default workset type for Generate Design Context

preference.name: CPD_find_num_increment_value
preference.preference_description: Defines the increment value for newly generated find numbers in Workset in the 4GD application.

preference.name: DefaultLoadCountIncreaseRate
preference.preference_description: Sets the percentage increase of the size of each successive page in a result set from a 4GD cacheless search. The percentage is a ratio of each page to its successive page. For example, 120 (e.g. ratio of 100:120) will mean a 20% increase in results in each successive page. Valid Values: Any valid integer. 100 maintains the same page size.

preference.name: DefaultMaximumLoadSize
preference.preference_description: Sets the maximum page size of a result set from a 4GD cacheless search. Valid Values: Any valid integer. The larger the number, the longer the page takes to load.

preference.name: ItemRealization_skip_type_list
preference.preference_description: Defines item types that are skipped when an item assembly is realized into a collaborative design or an existing realization is updated. You must use NX 10.0.1 or later, or NX may display error messages. Valid Values: The names of closure rule names that are used during realization. The closure rules control the item types realized.

preference.name: MDL_CARRY_FORWARD_EFFECTIVITY_SAVEAS_REVISE
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to carry forward the selected effectivity expression to a new revision of a 4GD revisable object or to a new object created by SaveAs action.Its default value is "true".

preference.name: MDL_Default_RevRule
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default revision rule used to configure the contents of the Content Explorer. Valid Values: Name of a Revision Rule that is valid for usage in an Application Model and defined in the database.

preference.name: MDL_Snapshot_Default_RevRule
preference.preference_description: Defines the default revision rule used during the creation of a Snapshot of an Application Model. A valid value is the name of a revision rule that is valid for usage in an Application Model and defined in the database.

preference.name: MDL_default_attribute_group_load_count
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of model element objects that can be loaded in one server call when loading attribute groups in the 4G Designer application. Valid Values: Any integer value.

preference.name: MDL_default_attribute_group_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of managed attribute group types available to a specific user role. Valid Values: A list of internal type names of attribute groups and managed attribute groups that are defined in the 4G Designer application. For example: Cpd9PipingManagedAttrGrp Cpd9HVacManagedAttrGrp Cpd9CabinManagedAttrGrp Cpd9DeckManagedAttrGrp Mdl9AttributeGroup

preference.name: MDL_effectivity_shown_columns
preference.preference_description: Specifies if unit, date or all columns are shown in the Effectivity view of the application. Valid Values: DateOnly - The date effectivity columns are shown in the Effectivity view. UnitOnly - The unit number effectivity columns are shown in the Effectivity view. All - The date effectivity and unit number effectivity columns are both shown in the Effectivity view.

preference.name: MDL_enable_preproduction_promote_to_history
preference.preference_description: Promote to history behavior will be removed from Teamcenter 11.2.3. It must not be enabled for production use. When this preference is set to false, access to promote to history will be blocked.

preference.name: MDL_export_search_results_dataset_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the type/reference of the dataset created for the MS Excel file generated by exporting the search results in the dataset_type.reference format. The default value is MSExcel.excel. If the specified dataset type/reference is invalid, the default value is used.

preference.name: MDL_include_attribute_group_inherit_properties
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of inherited properties available when viewing attribute groups and managed attribute groups in the Content Explorer. By default, the Content Explorer displays only the properties directly defined on an attribute group or managed attribute group. Use this preference to list additional properties from the parent hierarchy of attribute group or managed attribute group. The defined properties are available in the Column Management wizard of the Content Explorer, allowing you to add them to your display.For example, the object_string property is inherited from the workspace object. To make object_string available for attribute groups, add the property name to this preference. Valid Values: A list of valid property names.

preference.name: MDL_saved_query_for_SOA_getConnectivityContents
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the saved query that will be passed to SOA getConnectivityContents. The saved query must return Geometric Connectivity Group.

preference.name: PSECopyAbsOccDuringVICreation
preference.preference_description: Controls copy of Absolute occurrence data from generic assembly to variant item on creation of a variant item. Valid Values: * false: Absolute Occurrence data is not copied on variant item creation. * true: Absolute Occurrence data is copied on variant item creation.

preference.name: PSECopyArrangementsDuringVICreation
preference.preference_description: Controls copy of Arrangements data from generic assembly to variant item on creation of a variant item. This preference is honored only if the preference PSECopyAbsOccDuringVICreation is set to true. Valid Values: * false: Arrangements data is not copied on variant item creation. * true: Arrangements data is copied on variant item creation.

preference.name: PTN_Allow_To_Add_Realized_Partition_As_Local_Partition
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether a realized partition can be added as a local partition in a target model when copying. Valid Values: true or false

preference.name: PTN_Allow_Top_Level_Partitions_Cache
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the "TOPLEVELPARTITIONCACHE" table can be used to populate the top level Partitions.

preference.name: PTN_Default_Partition_RevRule
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default revision rule for partitions within a model. Valid Values: The name of any valid Teamcenter revision rule, for example, Any Status; No Working.

preference.name: PTN_IntroSavedQueryTypeList
preference.preference_description: Defines the saved query types that Teamcenter uses for the quick search within the partitionable model Content Explorer introduction panel. Valid Values: Any valid saved query types that teamcenter can use for the quick search within the partitionable model content explorer introduction panel. Example: __PartitionTemplate __ProductArchModel

preference.name: PTN_MRU_Display_Scheme
preference.preference_description: Stores the most recently used partition scheme type used whenever the user has opened an Application Model that supports partitioning. Do not modify the preference value manually.

preference.name: PTN_Recursively_Replay_Dynamic_Partitions
preference.preference_description: Indicates if partition recipies are replayed recursively.

preference.name: PTN_Replay_Dynamic_Partitions_After_DEs_Updated
preference.preference_description: Partitions recipe are replayed after count of updated DEs meet the provided value. The default count is 1000

preference.name: PTN_disable_hierarchy_caching
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to disable the caching of Partition hierarchy for Subset content.

preference.name: PTN_disable_variant_solve_for_partition
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to bypass variant configuration when computing partition hierarchy for expansion in a Subset.

preference.name: PTN_get_dynamic_members_for_all_revisions
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether dynamic members to be persisted for dynamic partitions.

preference.name: PTN_search_results_by_partition_maximum_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of objects returned by a search operation that can be organized according to a Partition Scheme. If the number of found objects is greater than the given value, the objects will be returned as a flat list without being organized by Partition Scheme.

preference.name: PartitionableModelHistoryUIDList
preference.preference_description: Contains the history of last 20 objects opened within the "Content Explorer" view for a Partition Template and its contents. The objects are recorded as UIDs. This preference is populated internally and is not meant to be modified by users.

preference.name: Ptn0PartitionTemplateModel_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of properties that can be displayed as children of a Partition Template node.

preference.name: TC_Default_Solve_Type
preference.preference_description: Defines the default solve type value that Teamcenter uses when setting effectivity configurations. Valid values are 1 - Mismatch. Conditions that do not match the solve criteria. 2 - Explicit. Conditions that explicitly match the solve criteria. 4 - Coprime. Conditions that may match the solve criteria. The term coprime means the condition depends on variant option families that are not present in the criteria. 8 - True. Conditions that always satisfy the solve criteria because they are equivalent to the Boolean constant TRUE. 16 - False. Conditions that never satisfy the solve criteria because they are equivalent to the Boolean constant FALSE. 32 - Condition. Conditions that are nonconstant because they are not equivalent to the Boolean constants TRUE or FALSE. 64 - Error check. Conditions that return an error in the solve process. Configurations using this mode should never return any data. 128 - No condition. No conditions. Finds objects that support configuration conditions but do not have one. 256 - No configuration behavior. Objects that do not support configuration behavior in the solve process. 512 - Invert. Inverts the filter results.

preference.name: TC_EffectivityConfigurable_MaxCacheSize
preference.preference_description: The Teamcenter server caches effectivity data for configurable objects to prevent repeated frequent database queries for the same set of configurable objects. Use this preference to limit the size of the cache to optimize the balance between memory footprint of the tcserver process and the performance impact of an increased database SQL query count.The cache is automatically purged on a last-accessed basis. Cached values are automatically refreshed for loaded and up-to-date objects when a cached value is accessed and the cached has changed since it was cached. Valid Values: Any integer value that specifies the number of configurable objects for which effectivity data is cached. If the value is equal to or less than zero, or if the preference is not defined, Teamcenter applies the default value.

preference.name: TC_Fnd0Booleansolve_EffectivityDateRangeFromTo
preference.preference_description: 4th Generation Design and Product Configurator can display effectivity date ranges in one of two ways:Inclusive date ranges, where the end date is included (a from/to paradigm). Objects whose effective date range is displayed in a format such as Date=2011-04-01..2011-04-30are effective until the end of the last day, in this case, 2011-04-30. Similarly, if the date range is displayed as 2011-04-01..2011-04-30T17, the objects are effective until the end of hour 17 on the specified day, Date=2011-04-30. Set this preference to TRUE to use this display format. Half open ranges, where the end date is excluded (an effect in/effect out paradigm). Objects whose effective date range is displayed in a format such as Date=2011-04-01..2011-05-01 are not effective for the end date, in this case, Date=2011-05-01. Set this preference to FALSE to use this display format.Dates must be formatted to ISO 8601 using the server time zone. For example, a display value of 2011-04-30T17 means 2011-04-30T15:00:00Z if the Teamcenter server is located in the MET time zone. Valid Values: TRUE or FALSE.

preference.name: TC_Fnd0Booleansolve_EffectivityIntegerRangeFromTo
preference.preference_description: 4th Generation Design can display effectivity ranges in one of two ways:Inclusive unit ranges, where the end value is included (a from/to paradigm). Objects whose effective unit range is displayed in a format such as Unit=1..10are effective for the end unit, in this case, 10. Set this preference to TRUE to use this display format.Half open ranges, where the end value is excluded (an effect in/effect out paradigm). Objects whose effective unit range is displayed in a format such as Unit=1..10 are not effective for the end unit. Set this preference to FALSE to use this display format. Valid Values: TRUE or FALSE.

preference.name: TC_config_rule_name
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default revision rule used when selecting the product context based on the chosen product item. If not defined, Latest Working/Any Release Status is used. Valid Values: One or more strings as values; each string must be a valid revision rule.

preference.name: TC_configurator_relationship
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relationship used to navigate from an application model (for example, a collaborative design) to a related item revision. Teamcenter uses this relationship to derive information about the relevant product name (item ID) and product namespace (item revision ID) from the item revision. It uses this information to initialize the internal effectivity configurator.If you use an external configurator, Teamcenter associates an Effectivity In Model object with the application model and it is not necessary to set this preference. Valid Values: The name of any valid relation between an Application Model and an Item Revision that represents a Variant Configurator context.

category.name: Action Manager Daemon

preference.name: TC_actionmgrd_sleep_minutes
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of minutes in the sleep period of the "actionmgrd" process daemon between the dispatching of Subscription events. Low values can be used when a large number of events are expected, or to ensure events are processed close to their scheduled time. Large values can be used if few events are expected and their execution time is of lower importance. Valid Values: Positive integer up to 1440 (the number of minutes in a 24-hour day).

preference.name: AWB_default_secondary_page
preference.preference_description: Defines the default page shown in the secondary Work Area. The preference value will be of type:page format, which define a default page for a particular type. If the type value is BusinessObject, then the page will be for any type which does not have a specific preference value. If a type is not defined, the system will look for the first defined super type in the preference. The page can be the title key of the page or the enablement feature key for a contributed page.

Valid values are: * true: The edits are committed as soon as a user navigates away from the table cell. This is the default value. * false: The user must explicitly save any edits using the Save Edits command or discard any edits using the Cancel Edits command.

preference.name: AWC_defaultViewerConfig.VIEWERCONFIG
preference.preference_description: Defines the default viewer configuration for Active Workspace. The format of SEARCHORDER entry should be as follows: SEARCHORDER.<Business_Object_Type>=<GRM1>,<GRM2>,<GRM3>... The format of Dataset-Viewer mappings should be as follows: <Dataset_Type>.<Viewer_Name>=<reference_Name>

preference.name: AWC_default_image_resolution
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default resolution to use to render images across Active Workspace client. Valid values are name of the derived image type as defined in the preference TC__image_compression_types. * Low: Indicates low resolution translated version of the source image. * Medium: Indicates Medium resolution translated version of the source image. * High: Indicates High resolution translated version of the source image.

preference.name: AWC_display_configured_revs_for_pwa
preference.preference_description: Specifies if Items business objects in primary work area should be displayed as configured revision.

preference.name: AWC_followMultiEventConfig_max
preference.preference_description: Maximum number of events to be configured for batch subscription creation in Active Workspace. Valid value is number greater than 1. Default value is 5.

preference.name: AWC_followMultiEventConfiguredEventTypes
preference.preference_description: Default configured event types for multi event follow in Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_followMultiObject_max
preference.preference_description: Maximum number of objects for batch subscription creation in Active Workspace. Valid value is number greater than 1. Default value is 5.

preference.name: AWC_req_do_html_conversion
preference.preference_description: Performs the html conversion of Word document during Import Specification in Systems Engineering. The default value is true (perform html conversion).

preference.name: AWC_show_audit_logs
preference.preference_description: Activates the visibility of the "Audit Log" tab in Active Workspace. By default, this is "true" for members of the "dba" group.

preference.name: AWC_use_item_not_configured_rev
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of business object types for which system should use their Item object and not the configured revision. Business object types defined in this preference would be excluded to switch to the configured revision while dealing with the favorites and the tiles. Valid values are: Internal names of the business object of type Item or its subtype.

preference.name: AWS_Inbox_Polling_Interval
preference.preference_description: Defines the frequency of polling (in minutes) to set a site level client polling mechanism for Inbox badge. If the value is set to 0 (or a negative number), the inbox badge command is hidden.

preference.name: AWS_Notifications_Polling_Interval
preference.preference_description: Defines the frequency of polling (in minutes) to set a site level client polling mechanism. If the value is set to 0 (or a negative number), the notification alert command is hidden.

preference.name: AWS_SearchPreFilter_Property2
preference.preference_description: Contains the required information needed to display the second pre-filter in the Search panel of the Active Workspace client (AWC). Valid values are in the format: * The first value is the type and property internal names in the format "type.property" (e.g. "WorkspaceObject.object_type"). * The second value onwards is the internal values for the property [For example, "ItemRevision"].

preference.name: AWS_allowedTypesForDelete
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Business Object types for which the "Delete" command is visible. Making the "Delete" command visible does not enable deleting the Business Object type. Currently only limited types support an intelligent delete that breaks relations and then deletes the object, e.g. folders and datasets.

preference.name: ChangeSummaryTableColumns
preference.preference_description: Defines column names which needs to be displayed in Change Summary Table on summary page of Change Notice Revision. The preference contains three type of values. 1. Type:TYPE_NAME,Property:PROPERTY_NAME,Width:PIXEL_WIDTH : For this entry system will read source property name for the column from PROPERTY_NAME and will get diplay name for the column from owning type TYPE_NAME. Example : Type:WorkspaceObject,Property:object_name,Width:200 2. Type:Key,Property:KEYNAME,Width:PIXEL_WIDTH : For this entry system will search for preference ChangeSummaryTableColumns_KEYNAME to retrieve source property names for the column. For example for ID column source property can be item_id for ItemRevision type and cpd0design_element_id for DesignElement type. Example : Type:Key,Property:ID,Width:250 3. Type:NoType,Property:action,Width:PIXEL_WIDTH : This entry is to display "ACTION" column in Change Summary Table. Example : Type:NoType,Property:action,Width:150

preference.name: Dma1CreateDocOnDrop
preference.preference_description: Defines the drag-and-drop behaviour when dragging the files from desktop and dropping them into a folder in Active Workspace. Valid values are: * Object name: If set to a Business Object name, e.g. Item, Requirement, Document, it will create a new business object and attach it to the target folder. Then create a new Dataset for each dropped file and attach it to the newly created Business object. * ShowCreatePanel: If set to the string "ShowCreatePanel", the Add panel for Document will be shown. Optionally a different Business object may be configured to be created by the Add panel using a colon followed by a Business Object name. For example with the string "ShowCreatePanel:Drawing", the Add panel would create an Drawing. Additional Business Objects names may be added to the string using an ampersand which would allow user to select from a list which object they want create. For example with "ShowCreatePanel:Document&Drawing", the Add panel would allow the user to create a Document or a Drawing. Note: If no value is provided, new Dataset for each dropped file will get created and newly created Dataset will be attached to the target folder. This is the default behaviour. Note: When using the ShowCreatePanel option, the Business Object's create stylesheet needs to include a file attachments section in order for dropped files to be included.

preference.name: EWI_InstructionRelationsInfo
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties/relations data to be shown in the Instruction view in the Electronic Work Instructions (EWI) solution in the Active Workspace Client (AWC). The valid format for the values is "<property/relation name>[:<type names>]" where: * <property/relation name> is the property or the relation name of the step object (sub-type of BOMLine). * <type names> is a comma separated list of internal type names of the secondary objects to show for the given property/relation. This argument is optional. In case the type names are not provided, all of the secondary objects information will be shown. Note: If the instructions are simple string property values, only specify the <property/relation name> parameter. In this case, if the <type names> parameter is specified then it will be ignored.

preference.name: SM_Gantt_Filter_Properties
preference.preference_description: Defines the Schedule Task properties to be displayed in the filter panel in Gantt sub location. The property must be an attribute of Schedule Task or its sub types. The order of the preference values defines the display order of properties in the filter panel. Valid values are: * Internal names of any single valued persistent attribute on Schedule Task except reference attributes. (Array, runtime, reference, relation and compound properties are not supported.) * 'ResourceAssignment' and 'schedule_deliverable_list'. These are special filter properties to display resources and schedule deliverables assigned to Schedule Tasks respectively.

(Array, runtime, reference, relation and compound properties are not supported.)

preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of view names for "Workflow" tab in the client. The view names are defined in Workflow UI configuration file, which is stored in the dataset named by the value of preference "WRKFLW_graph_legend_configuration_file_name". This is a site preference.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_resourcepool_assignments
preference.preference_description: Activates the visibility of the "Resource Pool" tab in the "User Search" panel in Active Workspace. The default value is true.

preference.name: WRKFLW_graph_legend_configuration_file_name
preference.preference_description: Registers the name of dataset which stores an XML file containing the Workflow Graph UI configuration. This is a site preference.

preference.name: WRKFLW_graph_presentation_rules_file_name
preference.preference_description: Registers the name of dataset which stores an XML file containing the Presentation Rules of the shapes. This is a site preference.

preference.name: WRKFLW_graph_presentation_styles_file_name
preference.preference_description: Registers the name of dataset which stores an XML file containing the Presentation Styles of the shapes. This is a site preference.

preference.name: WRKFLW_hide_subsequent_task_errors
preference.preference_description: Deactivates the visibility of error/notification message on UI when the subsequent task in the workflow has failed. Valid values are: * true: the message is not visible for the above-mentioned Workflow types. This is the default value. * false: the message is visible for the above-mentioned Workflow types.

preference.name: WRKFLW_preferred_diagram_layout
preference.preference_description: Controls the preferred layout for Workflow Designer UI. Valid values are: * GcLeftToRightLayout: Left-to-Right layout. This is the default value. * GcRightToLeftLayout: Right-to-Left layout * GcTopToBottomLayout: Top-to-Bottom layout * FixedLayout: Manual layout

preference.name: WRKFLW_preselect_first_task
preference.preference_description: Determines whether in Active Workspace client the first task is pre-selected when user goes to Inbox. Valid values are: * true: First task in inbox will be pre-selected. This is the default value. * false: First task in inbox will not be pre-selected.

preference.name: WRKFLW_save_node_positions
preference.preference_description: Activates the save positions command on Workflow Designer UI. Valid values are: * false: the save positions command should not be displayed. * true: the save positions command should be displayed. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_use_fixed_position
preference.preference_description: Activates the fixed and automatic layout commands on Workflow Designer UI. Valid values are: * false: the fixed and automatic layout commands should not be displayed. * true: the fixed and automatic layout commands should be displayed. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_user_panel_content_display
preference.preference_description: Controls the display of users and groupmember lists in Active Workspace user selection panels. Valid values are: * 0 - Users without checkbox: Display users and hide the checkbox that allows switching to users with group/role. * 1 - Users with checkbox: Display users and show the checkbox that allows switching to users with group/role. * 2 - Group members without checkbox: Display users with group/role and hide the checkbox that allows switching to users. * 3 - Group members with checkbox: Display users with group/role and show the checkbox that allows switching to users.

preference.preference_description: Registers the summary stylesheet for objects of type Awp0SearchFolder (Active Folder objects).

preference.name: AWC_Category_Filter_Show_Count
preference.preference_description:
Defines the maximum number of pre-expanded filter values displayed for a filter category. Default is 50, which is configurable. This preference value can be defined with 3 values 'ALL' OR Positive Number OR 'Hidden'. Description of these values are given below. ALL: all filters will be fetched Hidden: the category will be hidden. Positive value N: normal case. the N number of filters will be fetched. Any other values: the default number of filters will be fetched.
To specify a value different from the default for a filter category, add an entry with the format of "Internal name of the property=Maximum number of expanded filter values", e.g. POM_application_object.owning_user=20.

preference.name: AWC_DefaultPageSize
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default number of objects shown per page.

preference.name: AWC_Global_Search_Suppress_Types_From_Results
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of internal names of types which need to be suppressed from global search results. For example, consider the dataset type with display name as MS WordX, the user should provide the internal type name i.e., MSWordX. Valid values are internal type names as defined in BMIDE. If the preference AWS_FullTextSearch_Index_Dataset_File_Content is set to true and dataset types are set as a value to this preference, the dataset types are still suppressed from the global search results. Out of the box, no values will be there in this multivalued preference.

preference.name: AWC_Hide_Unassigned_FacetCategories
preference.preference_description: Hides the display of unassigned value facet categories from the filter panel. This applies to non classification categories. Valid values are: * true : All single facet categories with unassigned values are hidden. This is the default value. * false : All unassigned value single facet categories are displayed.

preference.name: AWC_Limited_Filter_Categories_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the categories defined in AWC_Limited_Filter_Categories_Expanded are the only ones returned as expanded after a search. Out of the box, this feature will be turned off.

preference.name: AWC_Limited_Filter_Categories_Expanded
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of internal names of categories which need to be expanded by default after execution of a search. Only comes into picture if AWC_Limited_Filter_Categories_Enabled preference is set to true Out of the box, no values will be there in this multivalued preference. Categorization.Category and WorkspaceObject.object_type will be always expanded as they are required out of the box.

preference.name: AWC_Master_List_Limited_Filter_Categories_Expanded
preference.preference_description: Specifies the master list of internal names of categories which need to be expanded with default/custom sublist. If the preference, AWC_Limited_Filter_Categories_Expanded are set with default/custom categories, the categories in default/custom list are Selected in the master list.

preference.name: AWC_Rev_Rule_List
preference.preference_description: Specifies the revision rules visible to the user in Active Workspace Search and Profile. These are the default revision rules for the user/session and do not apply to the revision rules in content. This preference overrides the list of all revision rules supported for a given user. Only revision rules accessible by the logged in user will be visible. The default value is empty, meaning that all the revision rules accessible by the user are displayed. Valid values are all the revision rules in the database. Example: "Latest Working". Make sure the preference "AWC_Rev_Rule_Selected" is deleted if the first value of this preference has to be selected in AWC Client. Add a valid value to preference "AWC_Rev_Rule_Selected" if a specific revision rule in the list has to be selected. If the "AWC_Rev_Rule_List" preference is modified to remove the value matching the AWC_Rev_Rule_Selected value, delete the AWC_Rev_Rule_Selected preference."

preference.name: AWC_Rev_Rule_Selected
preference.preference_description: Specifies the revision rule selected by the user in Active Workspace. Make sure this preference is deleted if the first value of "AWC_Rev_Rule_List" preference has to be selected in AWC Client. Add a valid value to this preference if a specific revision rule in the list has to be selected. If the "AWC_Rev_Rule_List" preference is modified to remove the value matching the AWC_Rev_Rule_Selected value, delete this preference."

preference.name: AWC_SavedSearch.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary stylesheet for objects of type SavedSearch (Saved Search objects).

preference.name: AWC_Search_DisplayODSContent
preference.preference_description: Activates displaying published objects for search results in the Search application of the Active Workspace. The default value is false (display local objects only in search results).

preference.name: AWC_Search_Enable_Snippets
preference.preference_description: A logical preference when set to true will return snippets in Search location Primary work area( object tile ). Before this, need to set global constant "Awp0StoreDatasetContent" in BMIDE to true and re-index all the datasets.

preference.name: AWC_Search_Enable_UserExit_Datasets
preference.preference_description: Specifies if indexer user exit is enabled for dataset objects. Set this preference to true to enable UID filtering user exit for datasets.

preference.name: AWC_Search_Enable_UserExit_NonDatasets
preference.preference_description: Specifies if indexer user exit is enabled for non dataset objects. Set this preference to true to enable UID filtering user exit for non datasets. Indexer performance might be negatively impacted.

preference.name: AWC_Search_Filter_Values_Sort_Order
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the search filters are to be sorted by count or in a lexicographical order. If the value is TRUE, the filters are sorted by count. If the value is FALSE, the filters are sorted in a lexicographical order. Out of the box, the value is TRUE which implies the filters are sorted by count.

preference.name: AWC_Search_Results_Recency_WeightAge
preference.preference_description: Defines the priority attribute for date in listing search results in the Active Workspace client. Value should be an integer between 0 and 6. The value 0 will turn off the date boost and the value 6 will maximize the date boost. Date boost is a boost given by solr to documents based off the age of the document. The higher the value for this preference will result in a more recent document being boosted higher than an older doucment. The lower the value the less older documents are pentalized in the boost. Default value is set to 1.

preference.name: AWC_Search_Results_Word_Proximity
preference.preference_description: Defines the proximity distance between two terms in a search. This boosts results where the terms searched for fall within the specified proximity distance of eachother. The value can be set between 5 and 500. Default value is set to 10.

preference.name: AWC_Search_Threshold_Value
preference.preference_description: This Preference contains the threshold value for the total results found for a search, If the total results found is greater than the unsigned integer value in this preference, then we return only Categorization.Category and WorkspaceObject.object_type along with Classification.type and Lbr0LibraryElement.lbr0Ancestors categories in the search response. Default out of the box value for this preference is 0. Setting this value to 0 will disable the preference.

preference.name: AWC_Search_Trim_Snippets_Size
preference.preference_description: This preference comes into picture if the snippet returned by the index engine is greater than 400 characters( excluding extra spaces ). In which case, we want to trim the snippet size .This number signifies how many words will be shown to the left and right of the matched search criteria. for e.g. if the original snippet size is 450 characters, then this preference will be honored. It will take the integer value specified and those many words will be taken which are to the left and right of the matched search criteria and will be returned as the final snippet for that object. Default value is 10.

preference.name: AWC_UidsForQuickSearch
preference.preference_description: This is an internal preference. In order to show the quick searches in correct form regardless of locales, this preferences is used. For the quick searches stored in Quick_Access_Queries preference, this is a corresponding preference which contains the quick search UIDs.

preference.name: AWC_WSOM_find_list_separator
preference.preference_description: Defines the characters used to separate multiple entries for Advanced Search queries in Active Workspace. Default values are SEMICOLON, NEWLINE and TAB. Supported values are SEMICOLON, NEWLINE, TAB and COMMA. The search criteria can consist of any of the supported values in between multiple entries to obtain the appropriate results. Please note SEMICOLON, NEWLINE, TAB and COMMA are keywords and must be specified exactly as values for the preference.

preference.name: AWC_dynamicPriority_hideUnassignedValueFacetCategories
preference.preference_description: Hides the display of unassigned value facet categories from the filter panel. Valid values are: * true : All single facet categories with unassigned values are hidden. This is the default value. * false : All unassigned value single facet categories are displayed.

preference.name: AWC_dynamicPriority_preferredNumberOfFacets
preference.preference_description: Specifies the preferred number of facets that can be used in dynamic prioritization of facet categories algorithm to decide on facet priorities. The default value is "4".

preference.name: AWC_dynamicPriority_threshold
preference.preference_description: Specifies the percentage to be used as threshold object count returned by search to trigger facet category re-prioritization. Valid values should be between 1 and 100 (inclusive). The default value is "50".

preference.name: AWC_indexing_unitSystem
preference.preference_description: Specifies the unit system to be used for indexing the numeric properties. Valid values are: * 0 : metric. This is the default value. * 1 : non-metric.

preference.name: AWC_search_automatic_wildcard
preference.preference_description: Controls the automatic addition of wildcard to user search criteria. Valid values are: - 0: the user search criteria are not altered. - 1: the search engine will suffix * to user values (e.g. "part" will be "part*"). This is the default value. - 2: the search engine will prefix * to user values (e.g. "part" will be "*part"). - 3: the search engine will prefix and suffix * to user values (e.g. "part" would become "*part*"). - any other value is considered 0. If a user adds a wildcard as part of the search criteria, no additional wildcard will be added in that place. This is the same for both prefix and suffix. (e.g. "part*" will be "part*").

preference.name: AWC_search_filter_wildcard
preference.preference_description: Specifies how wild card will be applied for facet filter. Valid values are: * 0 : No wild card will be applied to search string. * 1 : Trailing wild card will be applied to search string. * 2 : Leading wild card will be applied to search string. * 3 : Both leading and trailing wild cards will be applied to search string. This is the default value. If the preference is either not set or has a value other than in the list above, the following preference will be used instead: AWC_search_automatic_wildcard.

preference.name: AWC_search_show_all_filters
preference.preference_description: Show all the classification filter categories and filter values through pagination. Filter by value search will show all matching results. The default value is true. Valid values are true or false. * true : Show all the classification filter categories and filter values. * false : Do not show classification filter categories.

preference.name: AWC_select_firstobject_inSearchLocation
preference.preference_description: Makes Search sublocation select the first object in the primary workarea. Valid values are: * TRUE : Enables this preference * FALSE : Disables this preference Default value is set to True.

preference.name: AWC_select_firstobject_onSearch
preference.preference_description: Makes search based sublocations select the first object in the primary workarea. This only applies when in "List with Summary" view mode. Valid values are: * TRUE : Enables this preference * Anything but TRUE: Disables this preference

preference.name: AWS_Default_Query_Operator
preference.preference_description: Contains the default operator for query expressions in the Active Workspace client. Possible values are "AND" or "OR".

preference.name: AWS_FullTextSearch_FacetFilters
preference.preference_description: Contains the list of facet filters to be used during full text search.

preference.name: AWS_FullTextSearch_Index_Dataset_File_Content
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to process or skip dataSet file content indexing. Valid values are true or false. Default value is false.

preference.name: AWS_FullTextSearch_Solr_Index_ObjectData
preference.preference_description: Contains the collection name that holds the logical index of object data.

preference.name: AWS_FullTextSearch_Solr_MaxBooleanClauses
preference.preference_description: Represents "maxBooleanClauses" value of solrconfig.xml. If this preference value is modified,"maxBooleanClauses" value of solrconfig.xml has to be modified with the same value of this preference.

preference.name: AWS_FullTextSearch_Solr_SiteID
preference.preference_description: Contains the Site ID of the site used for indexing data in Solr for full text search functionality.

preference.name: AWS_FullTextSearch_Solr_URL
preference.preference_description: Contains the list of URLs to the Solr installation for the Active Workspace full text search functionality.

preference.name: AWS_Preferred_Attributes
preference.preference_description: Defines the high-priority attributes for listing search results in the Active Workspace client. Values should be the type name and internal property name in the format "type.property" (e.g. "POM_application_object.owning_user"). Followed by the desired boost value and if applicable attribute name in the format "BOOST:Attribute" (e.g. "HIGH:$ME") The accepted boost values are LOW, MEDIUM and HIGH. The accepted attributes for owning_user, project_list and owning_group are $ME, $MY_PROJECT, $MY_GROUP or user input. If no input is put for Attribute the boost field is ignored. Acceptable examples: WorkspaceObject.project_list:LOW:$MY_PROJECT; POM_application_object.owning_user:MEDIUM:$ME; POM_application_object.owning_group:HIGH:Engineering Unacceptable examples: WorkspaceObject.project_list:LOW, POM_application_object.owning_user:MEDIUM, POM_application_object.owning_group:HIGH All other scenarios only need to be in the format of "type.property:BOOST". e.g.(ItemRevision.awp0Item_item_id:MEDIUM). In the scenario where errors are found in the boosting value, the default value of MEDIUM will be used. The default values for this preference are: ItemRevision.awp0Item_item_id:MEDIUM, WorkspaceObject.project_list:MEDIUM:$MY_PROJECT, and POM_application_object.owning_group:LOW:$MY_GROUP

preference.name: AWS_SearchPreFilter_Property1
preference.preference_description: Contains the required information needed to display the first PreFilter in the AWS client. The first value should be the type name and property name in the format: type.property e.g. POM_application_object.owning_user The second value onwards will be the internal values for the property e.g. infodba

preference.name: AWS_Search_disable_exclude_prefilter
preference.preference_description: A logical preference control whether exclude prefilter for facet. true The prefilter will not be excluded for facet false The prefilter will be excluded for facet, this is the default behavior

preference.name: AW_Advanced_Search_Reference_Sort_property
preference.preference_description: Specifies the attribute used to sort search results for typed reference properties. For example, consider the "owning_user" typed reference property of Item, its "user_name" attribute can be used to sort all Items. Valid values are in the format "typedReferenceProperty.attribute". Search results show objects of the same business object type. If a preference value refers to a property that does not exist for the type, the preference value is not used for sorting.

preference.name: AW_Advanced_Search_Visibility
preference.preference_description: Disables and hides the Advanced Search tab and corresponding link to Advanced Search. The default value is true which will enable Advanced Search tab and link.

preference.name: AW_DisableTypeAheadFacetSearch
preference.preference_description: Turns off the type-ahead facet search in the filter panel in the Active Workspace. When this value is true, the facet search box is rendered with a search icon which requires a click or ENTER key to perform the facet search. When this value is false, the facet search box does not have a search icon, and each key-pressing will perform a facet search. The default value is false (type-ahead is on).

preference.name: AW_FTSIndexer_skip_modifications_via_relations
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the modification through relation queries can be done or not during the "TcFTSIndexer" sync process. This preference should be set to false if alternate id on Item is being indexed in Active Workspace. The default value is true.

preference.name: AW_FacetValue_Separator
preference.preference_description: Defines a string value that can be used as facet value separator for processing multiple facets values within a facet. Default value is set to ^.

preference.name: AW_Highlighting
preference.preference_description: Activates the highlighting feature for search results in the Search application of the Active Workspace. The default value is true (Highlighting activated).

preference.name: AW_Indexable_File_Extensions
preference.preference_description: Lists file extensions only allowed for text content extraction during search indexing. Valid values are file extension names (e.g. ".txt", ".doc"). If no value is specified, the extensions listed under the BMIDE global constant "Awp0IndexableFileTypes" will be used.

preference.name: AW_IndexedProperties_for_Phrased_Search
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of attributes which will be used to create search phrase suggestions. Values should be the type name and internal property name in the format "type.property" (e.g. "POM_application_object.owning_user").

preference.name: AW_Search_Results_Export_Max_Rows
preference.preference_description: Specifies default number of rows from search result to be exported.

preference.name: AW_Search_check_read_access_for_RevRule
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of Revision Rules for which more precise evaluation is done while returning search results. This is helpful in scenarios where certain working revisions are prematurely filtered out from the final search results.

preference.name: AW_TypeAheadFacetSearch_Delay
preference.preference_description: Defines the delay in type-ahead facet search (in millseconds). The type-ahead facet search will be delayed by the specified milliseconds. This is to reduce the performance issue caused by otherwise frequent search and rendering of the facets. Any invalid values (including zero or negative), will cause the value set to 500 milliseconds. The default value is 500 millseconds.

preference.name: AW_search_indexer_query_hint
preference.preference_description: Specifies the best SQL execution plan needed for TcFtsIndexer query based on start and end date. This is to avoid long running SQLs for query calls since the DB chooses the wrong hint in some cases. When indexing the entire DB, watch the process through DBA tool, if there is any performance problem, follow below steps to figure out the best execution plan, set the preference value appropriately for next run. * Analyze SQL generated by TcFTSIndexer, get the optimized SQL from DBA tool * Consult with DBA to set what hint is best for the SQL

preference.name: AW_search_suggestion_handler
preference.preference_description: Specifies the request handler for displaying suggestions during a search in Active Workspace. Valid values are: * SpellCheck : Displays single word suggestions. This is the default value. * Phrase : Displays phrased suggestions. * NoSuggestions : Do not return any suggestion.

preference.name: Awp0FullTextSavedSearch.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of properties that are to be displayed under a cell for objects of type Awp0FullTextSavedSearch in the Active Workspace client.

preference.name: SavedSearch.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of properties that are to be displayed under a cell for objects of type SavedSearch in the Active Workspace client.

category.name: Active Workspace Viewer
category.category_description: Active Workspace Viewer-specific preferences.

preference.name: AWC_3DViewerDisplayUnit
preference.preference_description: Sets the display unit for the 3D viewer. The valid values for display unit will be: 1: Millimeters. 2: Centimeters. 3: Meters. 4: Inches. 5: Feet. 6: Yards. 7: Micrometers. 8: Decimeters. 9: Kilometers. 10: Mils.

preference.name: AWC_Adobe_IDSN_OpenItemRevisionOrder
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types that are to be opened with the Adobe application extension when selected in the Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_Adobe_ILST_OpenItemRevisionOrder
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types that are to be opened with the Adobe application extension when selected in the Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_Adobe_OpenSupportedTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types that are to be opened with the Adobe application extension when selected in the Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_Adobe_PHXS_OpenItemRevisionOrder
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types that are to be opened with the Adobe application extension when selected in the Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_DeclarativeMode
preference.preference_description: Activates the declarative mode in Active Workspace. The default value is "true": the declarative user interface is used.

preference.name: AWC_HARD_LOAD_COUNT
preference.preference_description: Frees up the memory to the OS by forcing a hard full reload of Active Workspace client. Based on a number of user operations such as navigating to a new location or selecting a new tab in the work area will increment an internally managed counter. When the counter reaches the value supplied by this preference then a hard full reload of AW is performed. The internal count will be reset to 0 and the whole process will be repeated. Note: This preference only applies to the MS Internet Explorer (IE) Browser. Valid values are: * Less than or equal to 0 : Results in no Hard Reloads. -1 is the default value. * Greater than 0 : Results in Hard Reloads. A value of 20 is recommended initially, and increased or decreased based on browser memory consumption for common use cases.

preference.name: AWC_OC_OpenSupportedTypes
preference.preference_description: Enables opening the specified object types in Teamcenter Client for Office when selected in the Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_PLMXML_export_supported_types
preference.preference_description: This preference contains the list of types which are supported for PLMXML export in the Active Workspace client. The type hierarchy is supported automatically. The type internal name instead of display name should be used.

preference.name: AWC_RAC_OpenSupportedTypes
preference.preference_description: Enables opening the specified object types in Teamcenter Rich Client when selected in the Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_SnapShotViewData.INFORENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of info stylesheet for SnapShotViewData objects.

preference.name: AWC_SnapShotViewData.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for SnapShotViewData objects.

preference.name: AWC_VIS_OpenSupportedTypes
preference.preference_description: Enables opening the specified object types in Teamcenter Visualization Client when selected in the Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_applyTrueShadingMaterial
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default "Apply true shading material" mode for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are: * true : applies true shading material. This is the default value. * false : true shading material is not applied.

preference.name: AWC_dynamicPriority_facetCategories
preference.preference_description: Specifies the facet categories that can be used to determine whether dynamic prioritization of facet categories is required. Valid values are the properties defined as facet-able in BMIDE. The default value is "Lbr0LibraryElement.lbr0Ancestors".

preference.name: AWC_dynamicPriority_hideSingleValueFacetCategories
preference.preference_description: Hides the display of single value facet categories from the filter panel. Valid values are: * true : All facet categories with single values are hidden. * false : All single value facet categories are displayed. This is the default value.

preference.name: AWC_vis3DNavigationMode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default 3D navigation mode for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are: * EXAMINE : Sets the 3D navigation mode to EXAMINE. This is the default value. * WALK : Sets the 3D navigation mode to WALK.

preference.name: AWC_visAllOn
preference.preference_description: Allows user to set All On behavior for opening 3D model in Active Workspace. When set to true, Active Workspace will show 3D model with All On visibility applied.

preference.name: AWC_visColorScheme
preference.preference_description: The preference will allow any site administrator or individual user to control the colors in the 3D view. The valid values are: classic: The colors as defined below 3D/background=gray 3D/partSelection=yellow siemens: The colors as defined below 3D/background=white 3D/partSelection=orange

preference.name: AWC_visExamineZoomIn
preference.preference_description: Determines the zoom behavior of the Examine mouse navigation. The valid values are: Push: It will ZoomIn when the mouse moved away or scrolled away from user. Pull: It will ZoomIn when the mouse moved towards or scrolled towards the user.

preference.name: AWC_visExposedBetaFeatures
preference.preference_description: Determines the list of viewer beta features to be enabled in Active Workspace. For example "SessionUI" value present in this list will enable viewer session features in Active Workspace.

preference.name: AWC_visFloorOffset
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default floor offset for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are integers. The default value is 0.

preference.name: AWC_visFloorOn
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default floor visibility for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are true or false. * true : specifies Floor is on. * false : specifies the Floor is off. This is the default value.

preference.name: AWC_visFloorPlaneOrientation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default floor plane orientation for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are: * 0 : XY : Reorients the floor plane to XY * 1 : XZ : Reorients the floor plane to XZ. This is the default value. * 2 : YZ : Reorients the floor plane to YZ * 3 : -XY : Reorients the floor plane to -XY * 4 : -XZ : Reorients the floor plane to -XZ * 5 : -YZ : Reorients the floor plane to -YZ

preference.name: AWC_visGridOn
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default grid visibility for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are true or false. * true : specifies that the grid is on when the floor is turned on. This is the default value. * false : specifies that the grid is off when the floor is turned on.

preference.name: AWC_visMaterial
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default object material for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are integers from 0 to 29. * 0 : SHINY METAL : Sets the object material to SHINY METAL * 1 : BRUSHED METAL : Sets the object material to BRUSHED METAL * 2 : SHINY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to SHINY PLASTIC * 3 : ANALYSIS : Sets the object material to ANALYSIS * 4 : FLAT : Sets the object material to FLAT. This is the default value. * 5 : RED GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to RED GLOSSY PLASTIC * 6 : BLUE GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to BLUE GLOSSY PLASTIC * 7 : GREEN GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to GREEN GLOSSY PLASTIC * 8 : GRAY GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to GRAY GLOSSY PLASTIC * 9 : BLACK GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to BLACK GLOSSY PLASTIC * 10 : BROWN GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to BROWN GLOSSY PLASTIC * 11 : YELLOW GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to YELLOW GLOSSY PLASTIC * 12 : TEAL GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to TEAL GLOSSY PLASTIC * 13 : WHITE GLOSSY PLASTIC : Sets the object material to WHITE GLOSSY PLASTIC * 14 : CLEAR PLASTIC : Sets the object material to CLEAR PLASTIC * 15 : CHROME : Sets the object material to CHROME * 16 : COPPER : Sets the object material to COPPER * 17 : GOLD : Sets the object material to GOLD * 18 : BRASS : Sets the object material to BRASS * 19 : STEEL : Sets the object material to STEEL * 20 : BRUSHED CHROME : Sets the object material to BRUSHED CHROME * 21 : BRUSHED ALUMINUM : Sets the object material to BRUSHED ALUMINUM * 22 : BRUSHED TITANIUM : Sets the object material to BRUSHED TITANIUM * 23 : GLASS : Sets the object material to GLASS * 24 : SMOKEY GLASS : Sets the object material to SMOKEY GLASS * 25 : RED PAINT : Sets the object material to RED PAINT * 26 : GRAY PAINT : Sets the object material to GRAY PAINT * 27 : BLACK PAINT : Sets the object material to BLACK PAINT * 28 : BLUE PAINT : Sets the object material to BLUE PAINT * 29 : RUBBER : Sets the object material to RUBBER

preference.name: AWC_visNavigationMode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default navigation mode for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are: * ROTATE : Sets the viewer navigation mode to ROTATE. This is the default value. * PAN : Sets the viewer navigation mode to PAN. * ZOOM : Sets the viewer navigation mode to ZOOM.

preference.name: AWC_visOverlayDisplayEffectivity
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default "Display effectivity" mode for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are: * true : show effectivity. * false : false effectivity is not shown. This is the default value.

preference.name: AWC_visProductViewOpenConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Defines the configuration setting used while loading product views (SnapshotViewDataset objects) in 3D mode. The valid values are: Static: The product structure is not reconfigured while loading the product view. Any modifications in the structure made after saving the product view are not visible. Dynamic: The product structure is reconfigured while loading the product view. The 3D viewer displays the current state of the product with this mode. This is default value.

preference.name: AWC_visReflectionOn
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default reflection visibility for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are true or false. * true : specifies that the reflection is on when the floor is turned on. * false : specifies that the reflection is off when the floor is turned on. This is the default value.

preference.name: AWC_visSelectionDisplay
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Use Transparency" selection behavior, where selected items are shown in solid color and unselected items as transparent. When deactivated, selected items are shown in the highlighted color and unselected items shown as solid in their original colors. The default value is true.

preference.name: AWC_visSelectionLimit
preference.preference_description: Area Select will not permit a user to select more than this number of items in a single selection action. Default value is 40. Maximum allowed is 500.

preference.name: AWC_visShading
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default Shading modefor the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are true or false. * true : specifies shaded with edges is on * false : specifies shaded with edges is off. This is the default value.

preference.name: AWC_visShadowOn
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default shadow visibility for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are true or false. * true : specifies that the shadow is on, when the floor is turned on. * false : specifies that the shadow is off when the floor is turned on. This is the default value.

preference.name: AWC_visStdViewOrientationFront
preference.preference_description: Specifies the camera orientation for the Front view for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Back's camera orientation value will be set opposite of Front. Valid values are: * +x : Sets the Front view orientation to +x * +y : Sets the Front view orientation to +y. This is the default value. * +z : Sets the Front view orientation to +z * -x : Sets the Front view orientation to -x * -y : Sets the Front view orientation to -y * -z : Sets the Front view orientation to -z

preference.name: AWC_visStdViewOrientationLeft
preference.preference_description: Specifies the camera orientation for the Left view for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Right's camera orientation value will be set opposite of Left. Valid values are: * +x : Sets the Left view orientation to +x. This is the default value. * +y : Sets the Left view orientation to +y * +z : Sets the Left view orientation to +z * -x : Sets the Left view orientation to -x * -y : Sets the Left view orientation to -y * -z : Sets the Left view orientation to -z

preference.name: AWC_visStdViewOrientationTop
preference.preference_description: Specifies the camera orientation for the Top view for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Bottom's camera orientation value will be set opposite of Top. Valid values are: * +x : Sets the Top view orientation to +x * +y : Sets the Top view orientation to +y * +z : Sets the Top view orientation to +z * -x : Sets the Top view orientation to -x * -y : Sets the Top view orientation to -y * -z : Sets the Top view orientation to -z. This is the default value.

preference.name: AWC_visTrihedronOn
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default Trihedron visibility mode for the Viewer in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are true or false. * true : specifies Trihedron is on. This is the default value. * false : specifies Trihedron is off.

preference.name: AWV02DViewerRenderOption
preference.preference_description: Determines which rendering technology should be used in Active Workspace 2D viewer. The valid values are: CSR: Client Side Rendering technology will be used while displaying 2D tab in Active Workspace. SSR: Server Side Rendering technology will be used while displaying 2D tab in Active Workspace. This is default value.

preference.name: AWV0AWVisReuseTCServer
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the Teamcenter server is to be shared between the user's Active Workspace and Visualization Server sessions. The valid values are: SharePartViewer: Teamcenter Server will be shared by the Part Viewer but will not be shared by the Assembly viewer. This is the default value. ShareAllViewers: Teamcenter Server will be shared by both the Part Viewer and the Assembly viewer. ShareNone: Teamcenter Server will not be shared by the Part Viewer or the Assembly viewer.

preference.name: AWV0HostAWInVisUponLaunch
preference.preference_description: Determines if Active Workspace page is to be hosted inside Teamcenter Visualization when user launches part or product from Active Workspace. When set to true, the Teamcenter Visualization starts showing Active Workspace page with part or product upon launch.

preference.name: AWV0LaunchAsSession
preference.preference_description: When sharing Session data between Active Workspace and Teamcenter Visualization by launching Fnd0AppSession objects from Active Workspace to Teamcenter Visualization, set this preference True. This passes the Fnd0AppSession object to Teamcenter Visualization. If the preference is set to False, only the Configured Assembly information is sent to TcVis.

preference.name: AWV0SectionCapsEdgesInitialState
preference.preference_description: Determines if Caps and Cut Lines option is on or off when a user first visits the Section panel during a session in the Active Workspace viewer. When set to false, the viewer will not generate Caps and Cut Lines.

preference.name: AWV0UseAWAppConnect
preference.preference_description: When launching from Active Workspace to Teamcenter Visualization, set this preference True if you want to use Active Workspace Application Connector. This requires Teamcenter Visualization 12.3 or later.

preference.name: AWV0ViewerRenderOption
preference.preference_description: Determines which rendering technology should be used in Active Workspace 3D tab. The valid values are: CSR: Client Side Rendering technology will be used while displaying the 3D tab in Active Workspace. SSR: Server Side Rendering technology will be used while displaying the 3D tab in Active Workspace. This is default value.

preference.name: AWV0VisReuseTCServer
preference.preference_description:
Indicates whether the Teamcenter server is to be shared between the user's Active Workspace and standalone Tc Visualization when a Open in Visualization operation is performed from Active Workspace. The valid values are:
true: Teamcenter Server will be shared. false: Teamcenter Server will not be shared. This is the default value.

preference.name: Awb0TcVisPreFetchAllowed
preference.preference_description: Determines if pre-loading is allowed in the Active Workspace viewer. When set to true, the viewer starts loading products as soon as opened in the Active Content Experience (ACE).

preference.name: SnapShotViewData.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties that are to be displayed under a cell for objects of type SnapShotViewData in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names.

category.name: Active Workspace.APS
category.category_description: Active Workspace APS preferences

preference.name: Aps1EffectivitySupportedTypes
preference.preference_description: Contains a list of Business Object types that are currently supported for Advanced PLM Services (APS) effectivity command visibility.

category.name: Active Workspace.Active Collaboration
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: Ac0AutoMessagesEnabled
preference.preference_description: Used to indicate if auto messages should be generated on the Active Collaboration discussion panel. A true value will create the messages. A false value will not create the messages. Default value is true.

preference.name: Ac0DeleteDiscussionGroupRole
preference.preference_description: Grants permission to delete Discussions. Valid values are in the format "group_id/role_id".

preference.name: Ac0EnableSnapshotPreviewInDiscussion
preference.preference_description: Used to determine the level of detail in the snapshots shared through Discussions. Valid entries are as follows: "No images" - will allow snapshots to be shared but no snapshot images will be displayed in the Discussions. "Allow Low Res Only" - will allow Participants to see only a low resolution thumbnail of the shared snapshot in the discussions. "Allow High Res" - will allow Discussion Participants to see both high resolution images and low resolution images of the shared snapshot.

preference.name: Ac0EnableTrackedDiscussions
preference.preference_description: Used to display/hide the Tracker feature for Active Collaboration. A true value will enable the feature. A false value will hide the feature. Default value is false.

preference.name: Ac0SnapshotDiscussionsEnabled
preference.preference_description: Used to display/hide the snapshot icon on the Active Collaboration create panel. A true value will display the icon. A false value will hide the icon. Default value is true.

category.name: Active Workspace.BOM
category.category_description: Active Workspace BOM specific preferences.

preference.name: AWBBackgroundContextAutoSaveFrequency
preference.preference_description: BackgroundContext object is saved in two ways - one way is via explicit actions like, configuration change and other way is to automatically save it in certain intervals. This preference specifies the frequency (in seconds) for a BackgroundContext object to be automatically saved. If a 0 or negative value is provided, the BackgroundContext will not be saved automatically and will only be saved on explicit actions, like, configuration change. However, BackgroundContext will always be created, irrespective of the value of this preference.

preference.name: AWBBackgroundContextCleanupDays
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum age (in days) for a BackgroundContext object, after which the BackgroundContext object is deleted. Valid days are 1 or more days.

preference.name: AWBBackgroundContextMaxCountPerUser
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of BackgroundContext objects that can be created by a given user.

preference.name: AWBIndexBomSubscribers
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of valid applications that can subscribe for product structure index (Index BOM). The preference values are the valid values that are allowed to be set on the Awb0BOMIndexAdminData::awb0Subscribers property. Applications, based on these valid values will then enable features for that particular product and configuration represented by the Awb0BOMIndexAdminData instance. For example if the "MMV" value is set as subscriber on Awb0BOMIndexAdminData instance which represents a product and configuration, the Visualization application would enable Massive Model Visualization for that particular product and configuration.

preference.name: AWBItemTypesToHideOccurrenceCreatePanel
preference.preference_description: In Active Workspace client when adding a child component to the parent the user will be presented with a dialog to add occurrence properties on create. All the Item types listed under this preference will not see this dialog.

preference.name: AWBPropertiesToCompare.BVR
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of BOM Line properties to be considered for BVR to BVR comparison.

preference.name: AWBSavedQueries
preference.preference_description: Defines the saved queries to be displayed in the context of Active Content Experience. Valid values are the internal name of queries as defined in the qry_text_locale.xml localization file.

preference.name: AWBShowFailedIndex
preference.preference_description: Define the availability of failed index structure if fault isolation is supported.

preference.name: AWBShowOverwriteForConcurrentSave
preference.preference_description: This preference is to control the presence of overwrite option during concurrent save of a Fnd0AppSession object. The default value is true.

preference.name: AWBUseDefaultRevisionRule
preference.preference_description: Indicates the default Revision Rule to be used when opening a structure in Active Workspace BOM. If this preference is set to "true" the Revision Rule defined in TC_config_rule_name will be used for opening the structure.

preference.name: AWBUseObjectQuotaUnload
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Unload" feature based on object quota is to be used.

preference.name: AWBUseOccurrenceLevelStructureClone
preference.preference_description: Defines if the structure clone operation should be executed at occurrence level. Occurrence level structure cloning is supported from platform TC12.3 onwards. If this is set to true and platform supports Occurrence level clone execution, structure clone operation is executed at Occurrence level. If this is set to true and platfrom does not support Occurrence level clone execution, clone operation is executed at Item Revision level. If this is set to false, structure clone operation is executed at Item Revision level.

preference.name: AWB_RelStatusEffSupportedList
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Business Object types for which the "Revision" command is visible.

preference.name: AWB_ShowMarkup
preference.preference_description: This preference is set to true if markup mode is selected. It is false by default.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0ConditionalElement.INFORENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of information stylesheet for Awb0ConditionalElement objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0ConditionalElement.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Awb0ConditionalElement objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0DesignElement.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Awb0DesignElement objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0Element.INFORENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of information stylesheet for Awb0Element objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0Element.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Awb0Element objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0MarkupElement.INFORENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of information stylesheet for Awb0MarkupElement objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0MarkupElement.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Awb0MarkupElement objects.
