preference.preference_description: Registration of information stylesheet for Part Element objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0PartElement.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Part Element objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0PositionedElement.INFORENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of information stylesheet for Awb0PositionedElement objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0PositionedElement.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Awb0PositionedElement objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0SavedBookmark.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of create stylesheet for Saved Bookmark object.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0SavedBookmark.INFORENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of information stylesheet for Awb0SavedBookmark objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0SavedBookmark.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Awb0SavedBookmark objects.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0SavedBookmark.showObjectLocation.OccurrenceManagementSubLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary stylesheet for Awb0SavedBookmark objects for ShowObject location and OccurrenceManagement SubLocation.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0SavedBookmark.showObjectLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary stylesheet for Awb0SavedBookmark objects for ShowObject location.

preference.name: AWC_Awb0SavedBookmark.showObjectLocation.objectNavigationSubLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary stylesheet for Awb0SavedBookmark objects for ShowObject Location and Navigate SubLocation.

preference.name: AWC_Design Revision.showObjectLocation.OccurrenceManagementSubLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Design Revision for ShowObject Location and OccurrenceManagement SubLocation.

preference.name: AWC_Design Revision.showObjectLocation.ProjectContentsSubLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Design Revision for ShowObject Location and ProjectContents SubLocation.

preference.name: AWC_Design Revision.showObjectLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Design Revision for ShowObject Location.

preference.name: AWC_Design Revision.showObjectLocation.objectNavigationSubLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Design Revision for ShowObject Location and Navigate SubLocation.

preference.name: AWC_Discovery_Delayed_Filter_Apply
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the application of filter on a discovery indexed product is delayed or instantaneous on filter selection. The default value is false.

preference.name: AWC_EnableInlineAuthoringFeature
preference.preference_description: Enables inline authoring feature.

preference.name: AWC_Fnd0AppSession.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of create stylesheet for Fnd0AppSession object.

preference.name: AWC_Fnd0AppSession.INFORENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of information stylesheet for Fnd0AppSession type of objects.

preference.name: AWC_Fnd0AppSession.SAVEASRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of save-as stylesheet for Fnd0AppSession object.

preference.name: AWC_Fnd0AppSession.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Fnd0AppSession type of objects.

preference.name: AWC_Fnd0AppSession.showObjectLocation.OccurrenceManagementSubLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary stylesheet for Fnd0AppSession type of objects for ShowObject location and OccurrenceManagement SubLocation.

preference.name: AWC_Fnd0AppSession.showObjectLocation.SUMMARYRENDERING

preference.name: MMP_PERCENTAGE_OF_DELTA_TO_PURGE
preference.preference_description: This preference controls the percentage of Massive Model Product (MMP) structure delta files to purge when MMV_delta_collection_accumulation_limit is reached. Minimum value for this preference can't be less than 10% and maximum value should not exceed 100%. In case of wrong value set to this preference then system to consider 100% as default purge limit.

preference.name: MMV_delta_collection_accumulation_limit
preference.preference_description: Controls the maximum number of accumulated Massive Model Product (MMP) structure delta files in a Awv0MMPDeltaCollection dataset. When the limit is reached, older delta files are deleted from the dataset.

preference.name: MMV_keep_generated_files
preference.preference_description: With this preference it is possible to preserve the generated files for further examination in case if any error observed during complete file generation on tcserver. This preference can have one of below 3 values 1. on_error - Keep the generated files if error is occurred. 2. always - Always keep the generated files. 3. never - Default value. Never keep generated files.

preference.name: MMV_staging_directory
preference.preference_description: This preference controls the working directory to be used for tcxml2mmp conversion process on tc server. If not set then default temporary directory will be used as staging directory.

preference.name: AM_enable_RIP_for_child_groups
preference.preference_description: Enables Role in Project of Object (RIP) accessor to evaluate the roles under the groups which are not directly added to the project team, but their parent or ancestor groups are. Valid values are: * true: RIP accessor for the roles under the sub-groups in projects are evaluated. (the RIP accessor has to exist) * false: (default) Only the roles under the top-level groups in projects are evaluated. When the preference is set to true, Login may slow down if the number of groups in the project team which the user is in, is very large

preference.name: TC_allow_group_hierarchy_traversal
preference.preference_description: Activates the group hierarchy lookup in Access Manager while determining access privilege for a sub-group user. The default value is "true": group hierarchy lookup is turned on.

preference.name: TC_object_type_delegation
preference.preference_description: Configures the Access Manager delegation for object types to a class. The format is typeName:className , which delegates access for named references of the type identified by typeName to the owning class identified by className . By default, the access for the following five object types are delegated to its owning dataset: ImanFile UGPartAttr UGPartAttributesForm UGPartBoundingBoxForm UGPartMassPropsForm You do not need to add entries for these types.

preference.name: TC_show_all_aces
preference.preference_description: Influences the Access Control Entries (ACEs) displayed in the Access Control List (ACL) dialog. Valid values are: * false: To display only the ACEs relevant to the session user and the object ACLs. This is the default value. * true: To display all ACEs relevant to the object.

category.name: Administration.eIntegrator
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: EINT_adapter_names
preference.preference_description: Defines valid adapters. Valid Values: Names of valid adapters.

preference.name: EINT_create_new_forms
preference.preference_description: Determines whether or not to create a new form when importing external data. If left unset, create a new form for the imported data. Valid Values: 0 - Updates the existing form with the imported data if found by the given name. If not found, create a new form for the imported data. 1 - Always creates a new form when importing external data.

preference.name: EINT_form_refresh_pref
preference.preference_description: Controls whether or not the refresh operation updates the form data from the external source. Valid Values: 0 - The form data is not updated when the refresh operation is run. 1 - A SQL query runs and fetches the external data every time the form is refreshed.

preference.name: EINT_item_rev_pref
preference.preference_description: Defines the behavior for attaching a form to an item revision when there is no item revision mapping and the latest version of the item revision is released. Valid Values: 0 - Indicates that no new item revision can be created. 1 - Creates a new item revision based on the released revision and creates and attaches a new form to this item revision. Existing forms, if any, are not copied from the released revision.

preference.name: EINT_max_num_rows
preference.preference_description: Determines the number of external data rows results after performing an SQL query before asking for user confirmation. Valid Values: Single, positive integer.

preference.name: EINT_sqlnet_adapter
preference.preference_description: Display name for the SQL Net adapter. Valid Values: Names of valid adapters.

preference.name: TC_audit_append_lov_display_value
preference.preference_description: Specifies if display value of LOV properties being audited be appended to its real value. Display value recorded on audit log will be in master locale. Valid values : true - Append display values of LOVs in master locale on audit log. false - Keeps original behavior of recording real value of LOV property being audited on audit log.

preference.name: TC_audit_avoid_delegation_for_audit_access
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of audit log types for which the default audit log access delegation mechanism is disabled. For these types, the access rights defined in the Access Manager application apply. Make certain the correct access rules are defined for users to be able to view the audit logs. Valid values are audit log types, for example, Fnd0OrganizationAudit and Fnd0GeneralAudit.

preference.name: TC_audit_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the number of audit records to be inserted into the database in a single batch call. The records are buffered and inserted at the end of SOA or thin client call. If the batch size is exceeded within the SOA or thin client call, then the limit number of records are written and the remaining ones are accumulated again. The default size is 5 (minimum is 1, maximum is 20).

preference.name: TC_audit_buffer_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of audit records in the buffer.

preference.name: TC_audit_delimiter
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delimiter for text file format. It is only used when TC_audit_file_format=0. Although it is not enforced, usually the delimiter is single character because some spreadsheet programs such as Excel do not allow multiple character delimiter. If the delimiter is changed to other than ^, the user also needs to manually modify the delimiter in the first line of TcAuditLog.txt.

preference.name: TC_audit_disabled_dataset_types
preference.preference_description: (Deprecated) This is deprecated in Teamcenter 12.2 and will be removed after Teamcenter 14. Use conditional auditing feature by configuring BMIDE condition on ImanFile audit definition to control auditing file events. Refer sample BMIDE condition Fnd0FileAuditCondition. Specifies the list of Dataset types that should not be audited for ImanFile::_Read_File event.

preference.name: TC_audit_display_gmt
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the logged dates in audit logs are shown in the GMT time zone. Valid Values: true - Logged dates are in the GMT time zone. false - Logged dates are in the local server time zone.

preference.name: TC_audit_file_format
preference.preference_description: Specifies the format of external audit files. Valid Values: 0 - Indicates text format(.txt). 1 - Indicates XML format(.xml).

preference.name: TC_audit_log_dir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the audit log directory. Valid Values: Single string as a value; must be a valid directory path.

preference.name: TC_audit_manager

* ON: The auditing mechanism is enabled. This is the default value. * OFF: The mechanism is turned off.

preference.name: TC_audit_manager_version
preference.preference_description: Activates a particular version of auditing. Valid Values: * 1 - Legacy auditing mechanism is enabled * 2 - Audit Manager is enabled * 3 - New Audit Manager is enabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_audit_number_of_logs_to_load

preference.name: TC_audit_track_changed_properties_only
preference.preference_description: Specifies if audit logs are written when there are no changes to any tracked attribute value. This preference applies to the Modify event type only. Valid Values: True - Audit logs are written only when a tracked attribute value changes. False - Audit logs are written irrespective of changes in tracked attribute values.

preference.name: TC_audit_use_DefaultDateFormat
preference.preference_description: Specifies if logged dates in audit logs are displayed in DefaultDateFormat configured in timelocal_locale file. Otherwise audit logs logged dates are displayed in audit date format dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss. Valid values : true - Logged dates are in DefaultDateFormat configured in timelocal_locale. false - Logged dates are in audit date format dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_authorization_mode
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to evaluate all the group memberships of a user and the user's role in those groups when authorizing access to an application or to evaluate the user's current group logon and role in that group.For information about configuring access to an application, see Application Administration.To access the Organization application, a user must have dba privileges (be a member of dba with the role of DBA). If the user is a member of both the dba and the Engineering groups and logs on under the Engineering group, the user may or may not have access to the Organization application depending on how TC_authorization_mode is set:If set to on (evaluate all group memberships and the roles in the groups), the user has administration privileges based on membership in the dba group, even though the user is not currently logged on under that group. The user can access the Organization application.If set to off (evaluate only the current logon group and the role in that group), the user does not have administration privileges through the Engineering group. Therefore, the user cannot access the Organization application. Valid values are on - Evaluates all the group memberships of a user and the user's roles in those groups to determine the user's access to an application. off - Evaluates only the user's current logon group and the user's role in that group to determine the user's access to an application.

preference.name: ADA_Custom_Security_Mapping
preference.preference_description:
Defines the information needed to administer security grouping. Security groups are defined for custom ADA license objects and include a specific workspaceobject classification property and a user object clearance property. Each grouping also contains the administrator and classifier privileges for that security grouping. Valid values are in the format "<Classification>:<Clearance>:<License>:<ADMIN_privilege>:<CLASSIFIER_privilege>", where * <Classification> is to be replaced by the custom classification property name * <Clearance> is to be replaced by the custom clearance property name * <License> is to be replaced by the custom license type name * <ADMIN_privilege> is the admin privilege name for this security grouping. With this privilege set, the user is granted the ability to: Set or modify custom classification on workspace object Create/Modify/Delete custom license Attach custom license to a workspace object Detach custom license from workspace object Delete custom license * <CLASSIFIER_privilege> is the classifier privilege name for this security grouping. With this privilege set, the user is granted the ability to: Set or modify custom classification on a WorkspaceObject object
An example would be: EAR_class:EAR_clear:EAR_license:EAR_ADMIN:EAR_Classifier

preference.name: ADA_admin_notifier_list
preference.preference_description: Lists the administrative users to receive Teamcenter notifications when users or groups specified on any ADA license are deleted, or when groups part of any ADA license are renamed. Valid values are the user identifiers. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ADA_enable_subgroups

preference.name: ADA_enabled

preference.name: ADA_license_administration_privilege

preference.name: ADA_saveas_propagated_license_types

preference.name: TC_multi_site_gov_classification_user_bypass

preference.name: TC_multi_site_ip_classification_user_bypass

preference.name: ASSIGNED_ITEM_ID_MODIFIABLE
preference.preference_description: Determines whether an automatically generated Item ID can be modified by users after it has been generated. Valid Values: 0 - When the Item ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated Item ID cannot be modified by the user. 1 - When the Item ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated Item ID can be modified by the user.

preference.name: ASSIGNED_ITEM_REV_MODIFIABLE
preference.preference_description: Determines whether an automatically generated Item Revision ID can be modified by users after it has been generated. Valid Values: 0 - When the Item Revision ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated Item Revision ID cannot be modified by the user. 1 - When the Item Revision ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated Item Revision ID can be modified by the user.

preference.name: AltIdentifier_require_on_create
preference.preference_description: Determines whether an alternate identifier is required when creating an identifiable of the type specified in this preference in a rich client session. Valid values are to a set of Item types. If an Item type is included in this preference, whenever the Item Revision associated with this type is created in the rich client, an alternate is required. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter Item type.

preference.name: BMF_CUSTOM_IMPLEMENTOR_PATH
preference.preference_description: Defines the full path to custom libraries where any custom methods for the Business Modeler IDE framework are maintained. Alternatively, you can add the custom libraries to a directory in your system PATH environment variable (for example, TC_BIN). Multiple path definitions are allowed in this preference, and you can define both Windows and UNIX/Linux paths at the same time. The application only loads those that match the current server platform. This preference needs to be set so that the application knows where to look for custom extensions. Once set, close the rich client and start it again to load the new site preference values. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as value. Must be a valid file location.

preference.name: BMF_SUPPRESS_ACTION_RULES_DISPLAY
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to display the Action Rules tab in the Business Modeler IDE application. Use this tab to configure canned methods. These methods were moved to the Extensions Rules tab during Teamcenter 2005. If your site created custom canned methods, however, these custom methods cannot be converted to extension rules without implementation details such as function name, library, and so on, for creating an extension. Thus action rules and the Action Rules tab are still supported. Valid Values: ON - Suppresses the Action Rules tab in the Business Modeler IDE application. OFF - Does not suppress the Action Rules tab in the Business Modeler IDE application.

preference.name: BMIDE_ALLOW_FULL_DEPLOY_FROM_CLIENT
preference.preference_description: Determines whether Business Modeler IDE clients can deploy templates to the server that contain the full data model, including schema definitions such as classes, attributes, business objects, properties, and so on.Set this preference to False so that the schema on a production server cannot be inadvertently updated from a Business Modeler IDE client. When you use this setting, you must schedule a server down time to update the schema using the Teamcenter Environment Manager install wizard. With this setting, you can still use the live update functionality in the Business Modeler IDE to update non-schema data on the production server.Set this preference to True to deploy all data model, including schema changes. This is typical when you are deploying to a test server where the number of users are few and updates occur more frequently. Valid Values: True - Allows any Business Modeler IDE client with administrative access to update the schema, business objects, business rules, and other Business Modeler IDE objects on the server. False - No Business Modeler IDE client can update the server directly. Templates must be updated using the Teamcenter Environment Manager install wizard.

preference.name: BMIDE_ALLOW_LIVE_UPDATES
preference.preference_description: Allows live update deployment from the Business Modeler IDE and Teamcenter Environment Manager (TEM). This preference is set to true when you select the Allow Live Updates check box on the Live Update preference. You cannot change this preference directly. Valid Values: true - Allows live updates from the Business Modeler IDE and TEM. false - Prevents live updates from the Business Modeler IDE and TEM.In this case, updates to a production server can be made only during system downtime by installing a template using the full deployment feature in TEM.

preference.name: Bypass_property_rules
preference.preference_description: Determines whether property rules defined in Business Modeler IDE are bypassed. Valid Values: 0 - Property rules are not bypassed. 1 - Property rules are bypassed.

preference.name: ITEM_autogenerate_id
preference.preference_description: Determines whether an initial ID is automatically created when creating an item of the type specified in this preference in a rich client session. This preference is deprecated. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter item type.

preference.name: IdentifierContextPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the separator between the ID or Revision ID and the context name in the object_str property of an identifier. Valid Values: Accepts a single character as a value.

preference.name: IdentifierLengthPref
preference.preference_description: Restricts the maximum length of the ID Context Name in the object_str property of an identifier. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a positive integer. The maximum value is 240. (The maximum length of the ID Context Name is 32 characters.)

preference.name: Live Update
preference.preference_description: Specifies the data model elements to enable for live update. Select the Allow Live Updates check box to set the BMIDE_ALLOW_LIVE_UPDATES preference and allow live update deployment from the Business Modeler IDE and Teamcenter Environment Manager (TEM). Valid Values: To select the elements to allow for live update, move them from the Available list on the left to the Selected for Live Updates list on the right: Alias ID RuleAlternate ID Rule Application Extension Point Application Extension Rule Business Context Business Object Constant Business Object Constant Value Override Change Condition Deep Copy Rule Dispatcher Service Config Display Rule EDA Derived Data Event TypeEvent Type Mapping Functionality GRM RuleGlobal Constant Global Constant Value Override Icon ID Context IRDC LOV LOV Attachment Localization Naming Rule Naming Rule Attachment Occurrence Type Print Configuration Property Constant Property Constant Value Override Property Renderer Revision Naming Rule Status Storage Media System Stamp Configuration Tool Unit of Measure Verification Rule View Type

preference.name: METHOD_CM_execute_before_custom
preference.preference_description: Determines whether all canned methods are executed at a site before site custom methods or after site custom methods. Valid Values: 0 - All canned methods are registered after site custom methods are registered. 1 - All canned methods are registered before site custom methods are registered.

preference.name: TC_dataset_deep_copy_rules
preference.preference_description: Defines which dataset business objects are deep copied when using either the Save As or Revise command on the primary dataset. A deep copy creates copies of not only the primary dataset, but also secondary datasets. Use this preference to define the deep copy of the primary dataset business object, the secondary dataset business object, and the relation with which the latter is attached to the former.This preference is deprecated. The recommended best practice is to replace this preference with deep copy rules in the Business Modeler IDE. Although a deep copy during the revise action continues to process this preference, the system ignores preferences with conflicting deep copy rule configurations. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each value must specify a valid primary dataset, secondary dataset, and relation in the following format: primary dataset type:relation type:secondary dataset type primary dataset type is the dataset attached to the item revision, secondary dataset type is the dataset business object associated with the primary dataset type, and relation type is the relation with which the secondary dataset is associated with the primary dataset. F or example: UGMASTER:IMAN_Rendering:DirectModel This value specifies that when the Save As or Revise command is performed on a UGMASTER dataset, any secondary IMAN_Rendering datasets attached with the DirectModel relation are also copied.This preference accepts the asterisk (*) character as a wildcard. Use the following setting to allow deep copy of all primary datasets with any attached secondary dataset using any relation:*:*:*

preference.name: TYPE_DISPLAY_RULES_list_of_primary_types
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of primary business objects on which display rules can be configured in Business Modeler IDE. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid primary type.

preference.name: TYPE_DISPLAY_RULES_list_types_of_subclasses
preference.preference_description: Shows business object display rules propagated from the sub-business objects defined in the list of business objects in the preference. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid primary type.

preference.name: CPD_execute_dataset_save_post_action
preference.preference_description: Activates dataset save post action that updates the Positioned Geometry for a Design Component object whenever a dataset of type UGMASTER, UGALTREP or DirectModel is attached to an Item Revision, which is referenced by that Design Component. The update action may modify one or more of the following depending on the information available from the dataset being attached on the Item Revision: * bounding box coordinates * Trueshape Data * Direct Model Data The default value is true, which enables the above action.

preference.name: CPD_execute_relation_save_post_action
preference.preference_description: Activates relation save post action that updates the Positioned Geometry for a Design Component object whenever a dataset of type UGMASTER, UGALTREP, DirectModel is attached (with either IMAN_specification or IMAN_rendering relation) to an Item Revision that is referenced by that Design Component. The update action may modify one or more of the following depending on the information available from the dataset being attached on the Item Revision: * bounding box coordinates * Trueshape Data * Direct Model Data The default value is true, which enables the above action. Note: This preference is needed even when the "CPD_execute_dataset_save_post_action" preference is set to true. This is because the Dataset attached to an Item Revision might be preexisting, and hence the Dataset save post-action will not update the Positioned Geometry in case of a "Cut and Paste" action.

preference.name: Update_CPD_bbox_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Defines the batch size to process bounding boxes in one iteration. This preference value is used by the "mdl0_update_bbox" utility. A valid value can be any integer greater than zero. The default value is 25000.

preference.name: CM_color_of_add

Each color level is represented by the range of decimal numbers from 0 to 255. The total number of available colors is 256 x 256 x 256, or 16,777,216 possible colors.
