Valid Values: Decimal numbers from 0 to 255.

preference.name: CM_derive_BOMEdits
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether derived BOM edits are created for children at all lower levels when a BOM edit is created for the parent. Derived BOM edits have the effect of rendering the children in same color as the parent in the BOM panel, regardless of whether the children have been changed. Valid Values: * true: Derived BOM edits are created for children at all lower levels, but at the expense of performance. * false: No derived BOM edits are created, producing better performance. This is the default value.

preference.name: CM_derive_thumbnail_from_relations
preference.preference_description: Enable derive thumbnail from relation to Change Item Revision. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CM_disp_bom_edits_dialog
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to create a BOM edit when BOM structures associated with change objects are modified directly in Structure Manager application in the rich client, instead of through either the Classic Change or the Change Manager applications. Valid Values: * ASK: a dialog to be displayed to ask the user to choose whether to create a BOM edit for the change. This is the default value. * NO: no dialog to be displayed and no BOM edit will created for the change. * YES: no dialog to be displayed and a BOM edit will be created for the change.

preference.name: CM_enable_global_change_context
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether UI element to set Global Change Context is displayed or not. Valid Values: * true: Change Context option is displayed in UI ( i.e. User Setting panel in RAC, Header in Active Workspace ). * false: Change Context option is not displayed in UI.

preference.name: CM_form_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation to use between change forms and change items. Valid Values: Any valid Teamcenter relation.

preference.name: CM_graph_legend_configuration_file_name
preference.preference_description: Registers the name of dataset which stores an XML file containing the Change Graph UI configuration. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CM_graph_presentation_rules_file_name
preference.preference_description: Registers the name of dataset which stores an XML file containing the Presentation Rules of the shapes. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CM_graph_presentation_styles_file_name
preference.preference_description: Registers the name of dataset which stores an XML file containing the Presentation Styles of the shapes. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CM_impacted_item_relation
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of relations that contain the target of a change process where workflow handlers attach the objects. Valid Values: Change Manager relations that contain the target object of a change process. It can be any of the following relations: CMHasImpactedItem CMHasSolutionItem CMImplements CMReferences CMHasProblemItem CMHasWorkBreakdown

preference.name: CM_initial_position_of_sliders
preference.preference_description: Specifies the initial position of all control sliders in the Graphical History dialog box. If set to 100, only the affected assembly is displayed. If set to 0, only the problem assembly appears. Any number in between initially displays both the added and cancelled parts. Valid Values: Decimal numbers from 0 to 100.

preference.name: CM_newOther_relation_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the relation type for the summary rendering stylesheet. The system will update this preference automatically when the "Add New..." action is seletected from the Reference Items table on the Summary view.

preference.name: CM_note_types_to_track
preference.preference_description: Specifies which product structure note types can be tracked for a particular change type. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values; each string must contain a valid Teamcenter change type, and one or more valid Teamcenter note types using the following syntax:CM_note_types_to_track= Change-Type1:Note-Type1,Note-Type2Change-Type2:Note-Type1,Note-Type4For example, a valid value is: ChangeNotice:UG Geometry,UG NAME

preference.name: CM_notehistory_extra_columns
preference.preference_description: Determines which fields of the BOM change form are included in the Note Change History dialog box. This dialog box is opened from the Structure Manager application and tracks note changes for a particular component of an assembly. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values; each string must contain a persistent property of the BOM change form, using the following syntax: CM_notehistory_extra_columns= Form-Field1 Form-Field2

preference.name: CM_progression_tree_relation
preference.preference_description:
Determines which of two possible relationships to use for the revisions in the Progression tree. Valid Values: TC_based_on - Displays the problem/solution relationship where the selected revision is the solution revision. The problem revision is shown as a parent revision. This relationship can only be displayed in the Progression tree if the selected revision is part of a change process. Use this setting if your site is not using change management for BOM tracking.
EC_affected_to_problem_relation - Displays the based on relationship where the revision upon which the selected revision was based is shown as the parent revision. This relationship is not dependent on the selected revision being part of a change process. Use this setting if your site is using change management for BOM tracking.

preference.name: CM_relation_creation_flag
preference.preference_description: Determines if a newly-created in-context change item is automatically related to the latest item revision or a user-selected revision. You can set different values for change items and non-change items. Valid Values: ChangeItems=1 - Automatically creates a relation between the new change item and the latest revision of the selected existing change item. ChangeItems=0 - Forces the user to select the existing change item revision to be related to the new change item. NonChangeItems=1 - Automatically creates a relation between the new change item and the latest revision of the selected existing non-change item. NonChangeItems=0 - Forces the user to select the existing non-change item revision to be related to the new change item.

preference.name: CM_revise_impacted_item_preferred_revision_type
preference.preference_description: Determines whether supplemental revision types are preferred or if the initial/secondary revision rules they supplement are preferred for the Solution Item when executing the Revise Impacted Item function in Change Manager. Revision Naming Rules must be defined in BMIDE and attached to the ItemRevision, or a given subtype, for this preference to apply. Valid Values: * "supplemental": Supplemental revision types are preferred and will be used over the initial/secondary revision types they supplement if available. This is the default rule. * "initial_or_secondary": Initial or secondary revision types are preferred and will be used over any corresponding supplemental revision type if available. * "none": No specific revision type is preferred. Uses revision type of Impacted Item for Solution Item.

preference.name: CM_show_common_parts
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether or not common parts display during the initial loading of graphical compare in the rich client interface. Valid Values: TRUE - Common parts are initially displayed when a graphical compare is loaded. FALSE - Common parts are not initially displayed when a graphical compare is loaded.

preference.name: CM_single_intent_per_changenotice_enabled
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Change Notice can be configured by single intent or multiple. Valid Values: * true: Change Notice can be configured by single intent only. This is the default value. * false: Change Notice can be configured by multiple intent.

preference.name: CM_solution_items_relation
preference.preference_description: CM_solution_items_relation has been deprecated and will be removed in a future version of Teamcenter. Keep the preference set to its default value until it is removed. Defines the relation containing the objects which are identified as solution objects by the change process. Valid Values: Change Manager relation that identifies the solution object. It can be any of the following relations: CMHasSolutionItem CMImplements CMHasImpactedItem CMReferences CMHasProblemItem CMHasWorkBreakdown

preference.name: CM_track_variant_condition_changes
preference.preference_description:
Defines the change types for which variant BOM changes can be tracked. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values; each string must contain a valid Teamcenter change type using the following syntax:
CM_note_types_to_track= Change-Type1:Note-Type1,Note-Type2 Change-Type2:Note-Type1,Note-Type4
For example, a valid value is: ChangeNotice:UG Geometry,UG NAME

preference.name: CM_validate_changeNotice_dependency
preference.preference_description: Value of true, activates Change Notice Revision dependency assertion when adding a release status to the Change Notice Revision. The addition of the release status will not be allowed if the Predecessor Change Notice revisions are not already released or in the target list of the current workflow adding the release status and if the Concurrent Change Notice Revisions are not also in the target list for the current workflow adding the status. Furthermore, if this site utilizes the release status progression path xml to define release status relative maturities then the release status being added must be the same or lesser maturity than that of the predecessor Change Notice Revisions release status. The default value is false (not activated).

preference.name: CM_varianthistory_extra_columns
preference.preference_description: Determines which fields of the BOM change form are included in the Variant Change History dialog box. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values; each string must contain a persistent property of the BOM change form, using the following syntax: CM_varianthistory_extra_columns= Form-Field1 Form-Field2

preference.name: CM_work_breakdown_relation
preference.preference_description: Defines the relation containing the work breakdown schedules of the change process. Valid Values: Change Manager relation that contains the work breakdown schedules of the change process. It can be any of the following relations: CMHasWorkBreakdown CMHasImpactedItem CMHasSolutionItem CMImplements CMReferences CMHasProblemItem

preference.name: CPD_CM_ProductContext_Relations
preference.preference_description: List the sub-types of CMRelation, used to query the related Item Revisions and Design Components when a Change Item Revision is sent to 4th Generation Design(4GD). The Design Components and any realized Design Components of Item Revisions in Change are then opened together in 4GD.

preference.name: ChangeEffectivityItem
preference.preference_description: Defines the item_id of the configurator Item which contains intent information.

preference.name: ChangeNoticeRevision_default_workflow_template
preference.preference_description: Defines the workflow that starts when a change notice revision is submitted. Valid Values: Any valid workflow type.

preference.name: ChangeRequestRevision_default_workflow_template
preference.preference_description: Defines the workflow that starts when a change notice revision is submitted. Valid Values: Any valid workflow type.

preference.name: Cm0ImpactedItemReleasedStatuses
preference.preference_description: This preference holds the list of possible release statuses to be considered for an item revision to be added as an impacted revision for the corresponding solutions added to a Change Notice.

preference.name: Cm0SimpleChangeRevision_default_workflow_template
preference.preference_description: Defines the workflow that starts when a simple change revision is submitted. Valid Values: Any valid workflow type.

preference.name: ECM_affected_item_relations
preference.preference_description: The list of relations that are considered to be affected items of an EC Used by workflow handlers to attach the objects under these relations as target of a EC process.

preference.name: ECM_bomchange_formtype
preference.preference_description: Formtype to use for Customized BomChange attributes

preference.name: ECM_change_name_is_mandatory
preference.preference_description: Importance of the Name field to Create an EngChange Item (through UI). Valid values are TRUE/FALSE.

preference.name: ECM_delivered_engine_status
preference.preference_description: BOM changes are considered delivered engine change, when the affected revision has the following release status. This is used in genealogy viewer to distinguish between a normal change and a delivered change.

preference.name: ECM_form_relation
preference.preference_description: The relation through which the EC forms are attached to the EC.

preference.name: ECM_genealogy_expansion_rule
preference.preference_description: Expansion rule for genealogy display Possible values are NEW - Supercedure already displayed are ignored ALL - All supercedures are displayed irrespective of whether it is already displayed or not.

preference.name: ECM_note_types_to_track
preference.preference_description: This site preference controls which PS Note types to be tracked for a specified change type. This preference is shipped as blank.

preference.name: ECM_notehistory_extra_columns
preference.preference_description: This site preference lists the field (s) of BomChange Form that should be displayed as extra columns in Note Change History Table. This preference is shipped as blank.

preference.name: ECM_prev_structure_relation
preference.preference_description: The relation which is supposed to contain the objects which are identified as problem objects by the EC and replaced by that EC

preference.name: ECM_prev_structure_relation_name
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ECM_property_access
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ECM_property_display_names
preference.preference_description: The list of property labels displayed by the viewer table for EC

preference.name: ECM_property_names
preference.preference_description: The list of properties displayed by the viewer table for EC

preference.name: ECM_set_genealogy
preference.preference_description: The genealogy tab is visible only when this preference is set to ON. Valid values are ON/OFF.

preference.name: ECM_track_variant_condition_changes
preference.preference_description: This site preference controls whether Variant condition changes to be tracked for a specified change type. This preference is shipped as blank.

preference.name: ECM_varianthistory_extra_columns
preference.preference_description: This site preference lists the field (s) of BomChange Form that should be displayed as extra columns in variant Change History Table. This preference is shipped as blank

preference.name: ProblemReportRevision_default_workflow_template
preference.preference_description: Defines the workflow that starts when a change notice revision is submitted. Valid Values: Any valid workflow type.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_RelationBrowserViews.Relations.ChangeItemRevision
preference.preference_description: default the display view of relation browser to "Change View" for object type ChangeItemRevision context.

preference.name: TC_CM_approvers_modifier_roles
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of roles that have the privilege of modifying the approver list in Change Management.

preference.name: TC_bomchange_export
preference.preference_description: Determines whether BOMChange objects are included in the export of engineering change objects. Valid Values: TRUE - BOMChange objects are included in the export of engineering change objects. FALSE - BOMChange objects are not included in the export of engineering change objects.

preference.name: TC_supercedure_export
preference.preference_description: Determines whether supersedure objects are included in the export of engineering change objects. Valid Values: TRUE - Supersedure objects are included in the export of engineering change objects. FALSE - Supersedure objects are not included in the export of engineering change objects.

preference.name: WEB_Enable_Create_Change
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the New->Change->Create, New->Change->Context Create, and New->Change->Derived Change menu commands are displayed in the thin client. Valid Values: true - Displays the menu commands. false - Hides the menu commands.

category.name: Change Management Active Workspace
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: AWC_ChangeNoticeRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for ChangeNoticeRevision objects.

preference.name: AWC_ChangeRequestRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for ChangeRequestRevision objects.

preference.name: AWC_Cm0DevRqstRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Cm0DevRqstRevision objects.

preference.name: AWC_Cm0SimpleChangeRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Cm0SimpleChangeRevision objects.

preference.name: AWC_DisplayableChangeTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of "ChangeItemRevision" types that are presented in the "Change Management" application in the Active Workspace Client (AWC). Valid values are types internal names.

preference.name: AWC_ProblemReportRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for ProblemReportRevision objects.

preference.name: CMEnableChangeDashboard
preference.preference_description: Enable Change Dashboard to be shown on Dashboard Sublocation.

preference.name: CMMyChangesSublocationQuery
preference.preference_description: Registers the saved queries for the contents of the tabs in "My Changes" Location. Valid values are in the format "tab_name,saved_query_name".

preference.name: CM_Cm0SimpleChangeRevision_AddToMyChange_Relations
preference.preference_description: Defines list of relations which needs to be presented when object of type "Cm0SimpleChangeRevision" is selected on "Add To My Changes" panel in Active Workspace Client (AWC). Valid values are internal of relation types.

preference.name: CM_GnChangeNoticeRevision_AddToMyChange_Relations
preference.preference_description: Defines list of relations which needs to be presented when object of type "ChangeNoticeRevision" is selected on "Add To My Changes" panel in Active Workspace Client (AWC). Valid values are internal of relation types.

preference.name: CM_GnChangeRequestRevision_AddToMyChange_Relations
preference.preference_description: Defines list of relations which needs to be presented when object of type "ChangeRequestRevision" or "DeviationRequestRevision" is selected on "Add To My Changes" panel in Active Workspace Client (AWC). Valid values are internal of relation types.

preference.name: CM_GnProblemReportRevision_AddToMyChange_Relations
preference.preference_description: Defines list of relations which needs to be presented when object of type "ProblemReportRevision" is selected on "Add To My Changes" panel in Active Workspace Client (AWC). Valid values are internal of relation types.

category.name: Change and Schedule Management Interface
category.category_description: Change and Schedule Management Interface Preferences

preference.name: ScheduleTask.CHGDETAILRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of the Change Details style sheet for schedule task objects. Valid values: ScheduleTaskChgDetails Specifies the xml filename that contains the Change Details style sheet.

category.name: Check-In/Out
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: Form_double_click
preference.preference_description: If the preference is set to Edit, Form objects will open in edit mode on double-click.

category.name: Classification
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: CLS_allow_deleting_default_objects
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to allow deleting the out-of-box default objects that are supplied in Classification foundation. Valid values are: * true: allow deletion of the out-of-box objects. * false: blocks deletion of the out-of-box objects. This is the default value.

preference.name: CLS_enforce_classification_on_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the types of classifiable workspace objects for which classification enforcement needs to be enabled.

preference.name: CLS_search_apply_read_access_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to include the 'read only' objects during a Classification object search. Valid values are: * true: only objects for which the user has read access, are returned by the Classification search. * false: all objects matching the search criteria are returned, without taking read access status into account. This is the default value.

preference.name: CLS_search_max_results
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of search objects returned by Teamcenter during a Classification object search.

preference.name: CLS_search_return_classified_objects
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Classification searches return Classified objects or simply Classification objects. Valid values are: * true: In case of non stand-alone Classification objects, classified TC objects are returned. And in case of stand-alone objects, the Classification objects themselves are returned. * false: Classification objects are extracted from returned result sets. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_FilterBy_Library_types
preference.preference_description: Identifies the library types to be used as filters by the dictionary dialog user interface. Valid Values: Any strings.

preference.name: ICS_GraphicsBuilder
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the preference that points to the graphics builder utility that is used by Classification to enable the graphic creation functionality in the Classification application. Valid Values: List of preferences that point to the associated graphics builder utility.

preference.name: ICS_Print_HeaderLabel_Style
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the headers in the Classification application should be displayed for the Print function. Valid Values: HEADER_UNCT, HEADER_NAME, HEADER_SHORTNAME or HEADER_ANNOTATION.

preference.name: ICS_SysCopy_HeaderLabel_Style
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the headers in the Classification application should be displayed for the SysCopy function. Valid Values: HEADER_UNCT, HEADER_NAME, HEADER_SHORTNAME or HEADER_ANNOTATION.

preference.name: ICS_Table_HeaderLabel_Style
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the headers in the Classification application should be displayed for the Table. Valid Values: HEADER_UNCT, HEADER_NAME, HEADER_SHORTNAME or HEADER_ANNOTATION.

preference.name: ICS_active_unit_search
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default search unit system that is initially used for a classification class that is defined to hold both metric and non-metric values. Valid Values: metric non-metric both

preference.name: ICS_admin_requires_dba
preference.preference_description: Give NON-DBA users access to the Classification Admin. Application. Valid Values: true/false. true - User requires dba privileges to access Classification Admin. false - User has access to Classification Admin. If you allow non-dba users to log into Classification Admin., please note that the users will have full read/write access! To protect the hierarchy, the dictionary, and the KeyLOVs from unauthorized access, they need to be protected using the AccessControl tab.

preference.name: ICS_allow_deprecated_lovs_on_copy
preference.preference_description: Determines whether users can copy classification objects (ICOs) that use deprecated LOV values for classification properties. This preference applies for users performing the following actions in Teamcenter: Performing a Revise or SaveAs operation on an Item or Item Revision from anywhere outside Classification. Revising product structure that contains the classified objects. Valid Values: True - Allows users to create copies of ICOs that use deprecated LOV values for classification properties. False - Prevents users from copying ICOs that use deprecated LOV values for classification properties.

preference.name: ICS_allow_deprecated_lovs_on_update
preference.preference_description: Determines whether users can update and save classification objects (ICOs) that use deprecated LOV values for their classification properties. Valid Values: True - Allows users to use deprecated LOV values for classification properties. False - Requires users to use nondeprecated LOV values for the classification properties.

preference.name: ICS_allow_min_max_range_override
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the system allows Classification Admin to specify values to the following: Class attribute minimum and/or maximum constraints outside the range of Dictionary attribute minimum and/or maximum constraints. View attribute minimum and/or maximum constraints outside the range of Class attribute minimum and/or maximum constraints. Valid Values: True - Allows Classification Admin to specify values. False - Does not allow Classification Admin to specify values.

preference.name: ICS_array_attribute_value_separator
preference.preference_description: Defines a separator used when listing the values of a variable length array attribute in the results table in Classification and Resource Manager. Valid Values: A single character value.

preference.name: ICS_attribute_displayable_properties
preference.preference_description: Displays the list of attribute properties on classification properties in the Classification application. The administrator provides valid dictionary attribute properties and user-defined properties, for example: AttributeID Name Valid Values: Any string.

preference.name: ICS_attribute_mapping_trim_zeros
preference.preference_description: Determines whether, during attribute mapping between NX and Classification, leading and/or trailing zeros are stripped from Classification attribute values when they are sent to NX. Valid Values: keep - Does not change the Classification attribute value. For example, 001.3400 is transferred as 001.3400 to NX. leading - Leading zeros are stripped from the Classification attribute value. For example, 001.3400 is transferred as 1.3400 to NX. both - Leading and trailing zeros are stripped from the Classification attribute value. For example, 001.3400 is transferred as 1.34 to NX.

preference.name: ICS_attribute_mapping_unit_support
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset and item types for which classification unit support, including optimization, is active when mapping attributes to NX. If you do not set this value, when you map an attribute whose value is 100,000 mm to an NX attribute, only the value 100,000 is transferred. If you set this preference for the object type that you map, and the value is optimized in Teamcenter, the value 0.1 m is transferred to NX. Valid Values: List of valid Teamcenter item types and dataset types. For example: EDAComAllegro (dataset type) EDAComPart (item type) UGMASTER (dataset type) Mfg0MEResource (item type)

preference.name: ICS_autocompute_validate
preference.preference_description: Enables the auto-compute data validation during the auto-compute engine initialization. If set to "true", all the input data that are provided in auto-compute custom logic are validated. If set to "false", no validation of such data happens.

preference.name: ICS_classifiable_types
preference.preference_description: Identifies whether the particular type can be classified or not .

preference.name: ICS_classify_immediately
preference.preference_description: Determines the default setting of the Classify Immediately option in the New Item, Save As, and Revise dialog boxes. This preference is valid only when the ICS_classify_new preference is set. Valid Values: 0 - The Classify Immediately option is not selected by default when the dialog box appears. 1 - The Classify Immediately option is selected by default when the dialog box appears.

preference.name: ICS_classify_immediately_NX
preference.preference_description: Specifies if new Items or ItemRevisions are classified when they are saved from NXManager Unigraphics. Valid values are 0/1. If a value 1 is specified and NXManager Unigraphics is started from Teamcenter Rich Client and save a newly created part in Unigraphics, the user will be asked in Rich Client to classify the new item / item revision. 0 - Do not classify from Unigraphics (default value). 1 - Classify from Unigraphics.

preference.name: ICS_classify_new
preference.preference_description: Enables the Classify Immediately option in the New Item, Save As, and Revise dialog boxes, and specifies whether it is the item or the item revision that is classified. The Classify Immediately option is displayed only if the item type that you create is listed in the ICS_classifiable_types preference. When you specify Item or ItemRevision, this is valid for all the item or revision types listed in the ICS_classifiable_types preference. Valid Values: Item - Immediately classifies the item. ItemRevision - Immediately classifies the item revision.

preference.name: ICS_classify_sendto
preference.preference_description: Controls which of the available applications are displayed when you use the Send To command in Classification and Resource Manager. Valid Values: List of strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter application ID or application name.

preference.name: ICS_datasettype_for_class
preference.preference_description: Specifies the type of dataset used when images are added to subclasses. Valid Values: A valid Teamcenter dataset.

preference.name: ICS_default_class_document
preference.preference_description: Determines which of the documents defined in the ICS_presented_class_documents preference display by default. Valid Values: One or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid named reference file type that has been defined in the ICS_presented_class_documents preference.

preference.name: ICS_default_instance_document
preference.preference_description: Determines which of the named reference file types defined in the ICS_presented_instance_documents preference displays in the instance viewer by default. Limiting the values defined in this preference can quicken viewing time. For example, by not specifying BOMAssembly object in this preference, BOM assemblies have to be expressly selected to appear. This saves users time when paging through classification objects of large assemblies. When none of the document types defined in this preference are associated with a classification object, the instance viewer displays no attachment by default. Valid Values: One or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid named reference file type that has been defined in the ICS_presented_instance_documents preference.

preference.name: ICS_disable_class_viewer_show_images
preference.preference_description: Disables the class image viewer in the Classification and Classification Admin applications. Valid Values: * true: class image viewer is disabled. * false: class image viewer is enabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_disable_default_classifiable_types
preference.preference_description: Deactivates the usage of the default classifiable types. The default classifiable types are: MEOP, MEOPRevision, MEProcess, MEProcessRevision, MEWorkarea, MEWorkareaRevision, MEActivity, MEActivityRevision. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: ICS_disable_instance_viewer_show_images
preference.preference_description: Disables the instance image viewer in the Classification application. Valid Values: * true: instance image viewer is disabled. * false: instance image viewer is enabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_display_unformatted_numbers
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Teamcenter shows leading zeros when displaying attribute values. Valid Values: True or a list of attributes IDs for which the leading zeros should be shown.

preference.name: ICS_enable_graphical_browser
preference.preference_description: Enables the Graphical Browser tab in Classification and the Classification Search Dialog. You can browse through the classification hierarchy by viewing thumbnail graphics representing each class. Valid Values: true - Makes the graphical browser tab visible in the hierarchy pane. false - Removes the Graphical Browser tab from the user interface.

preference.name: ICS_enforce_min_max_constraints_on_copy
preference.preference_description: Determines whether Classification allows copying existing classification objects (ICOs) whose property values do not conform to the minimum and/or maximum constraints. This preference applies for users performing the following actions in Teamcenter : Performing a Revise or SaveAs operation on a classified item or item revision from anywhere outside Classification. Revising a product structure that contains the classified objects. If you revise an item revision but the item is classified, the new item revision does not contain any classification information so the revise action does not honor the maximum and minimum constraints. Valid Values: True - Classification does not allow copying existing ICOs whose property values do not conform to the minimum and/or maximum constraints. False - Classification allows copying existing ICOs whose property values do not conform to the minimum and/or maximum constraints.

preference.name: ICS_enforce_min_max_constraints_on_update
preference.preference_description: Determines whether Classification enforces minimum and/or maximum constraints on all classification property values during updating and saving classification objects (ICOs). Valid Values: True - Enforces minimum and/or maximum constraints on all classification property values when updating and saving ICOs. False - Does not enforce minimum and/or maximum constraints on all classification property values when updating and saving ICOs.

preference.name: ICS_favorites_separator
preference.preference_description:
Defines the separator character to be used when storing the favorites in Classification application.
The default value of the separator is ",".

preference.name: ICS_force_mandatory_attribute_check
preference.preference_description: Activates a check that all mandatory attributes contain values during the creation of any Classification object (ICO). This preference is used for all situations that do not involved user interface interaction (both rich and thin client). For activities performed in the user interface, the preference is ignored. Valid Values: true - Classification checks that all mandatory attributes contain values when you save or create a Classification object using any method. false - Classification does not check that mandatory attributes contain values when you save or create a Classification object.

preference.name: ICS_hierarchy_sort_option
preference.preference_description: Determines how the classification hierarchy tree is sorted and displayed. The tree is sorted and displayed alphanumerically in ascending order based on the value assigned. Valid Values: -600 - Class ID/subclass ID. Groups are treated as classes. -607 - Name. -612 - User1 property -613 - User2 property

preference.name: ICS_ico_id_case_sensitive
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the classification object (ICO) ID is case sensitive. Set this preference to prevent the creation of IDs that have the same characters but different case, such as Abc and ABC. Valid Values: true - The classification object ID is case sensitive. false - The classification object ID is not case sensitive.

preference.name: ICS_import_attribute_find_free_dbindex
preference.preference_description: Specifies that Teamcenter should find the next free dbindex position in the database if the specified dbindex position is already in use when importing Classification Admin data using PLM XML or XML data. This preference is only evaluated if the ICS_import_attribute_use_dbindex preference is set. Valid Values: True - Teamcenter tries to find the next dbindex position when importing data. False - If the specified dbindex position is in use, Teamcenter displays an error.

preference.name: ICS_import_attribute_use_dbindex
preference.preference_description: Specifies the use of the dbindex position in the database when importing Classification Admin data. When you import PLM XML or XML data in Classification Admin, the dbindex position is used. To disable this, set this preference to False. Valid Values: True - Teamcenter uses the dbindex position when importing data. False - Teamcenter ignores dbindex position when importing data.

preference.name: ICS_instance_image_revision_rule
preference.preference_description:
Specifies the revision rule for displaying an image of the Classified Object in the Classification application. This preference is only applicable to the Rich client.
The default value is "Latest Working".

preference.name: ICS_itemrev_master_dataset_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relationship between the item revision and the dataset type that is defined in the ICS_master_datasettypes_for_itemrev preference. Valid Values: Valid Teamcenter datasets.

preference.name: ICS_localization_feature_enabled
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the Classification L10N template has been installed using the Teamcenter Environment Manager (TEM). Do not modify this preference manually. Valid Values: true or false (default value).

preference.name: ICS_mapping_target_type
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the mapping target item or item revision is classified. Siemens PLM Software recommends you set this preference to ItemRevision. You can map classification objects (ICOs) from one class of your class structure to another as needed, such as when converting catalog data to customer data. To make the target object a classified resource, the target ICO must classify a newly created object, usually an item revision or a similar classified object type. Use this preference to define the target objects type. Siemens PLM Software recommends you set the following preferences to the same value as this preference:MRMClassifyResourceICS_classify_newGCS_classify_type Valid Values: Single string as a value. Must be Item, ItemRevision, or a valid custom item or item revision type.

preference.name: ICS_master_datasettypes_for_itemrev
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset types that can be classified, when used in conjunction with the ICS_classifiable_types preference. For example, if Dataset is included as a classifiable type in the ICS_classifiable_types preference and UGMASTER is included as a value for the ICS_master_datasettypes_for_itemrev preference, item/item revision/UGMASTER are considered a set and the following configuration rules apply:If the item is classified, the item revisions and corresponding dataset cannot be classified, but they inherit the classification record from the item.If an item revision is classified, the corresponding dataset and item cannot be classified. Other revisions of the same item can, however, be classified. If the dataset is classified, the corresponding item revision and item cannot be classified. Other revisions and datasets, however, can be classified. Valid Values: Valid Teamcenter relation.

preference.name: ICS_max_number_of_components
preference.preference_description: Determines the maximum number of components an assembly can contain before a warning appears. When the selected assembly (typically a resource assembly) contains more than the defined number of components, the warning states the selected assembly is large and requires the user to confirm loading the assembly. The user can click Yes to display the assembly, or No to not display the assembly. If set to 0 or left undefined, assemblies are always displayed, regardless of size, without warning. Valid Values: 0 - All assemblies are always displayed, with no warning regarding assembly size. Single positive integer - If assembly has less components than the number defined, no warning appears when displaying the assembly. If assembly has more components than the number defined, a warning appears:The assembly contains more than components. Do you really want to show it?

preference.name: ICS_override_unit_definition_precision
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Teamcenter overrides the precision defined in the Decimal Places attribute in the unit definition ICO while displaying the attribute value of the attributes for which optimized display is turned on. Valid Values: true - Teamcenter overrides the number of decimal places specified in the unit definition. false - Teamcenter displays the number of decimal places specified in the unit definition.

preference.name: ICS_presented_class_documents
preference.preference_description: Determines which named references display in the class viewer. The system searches all datasets of the selected class for named references. Any named references corresponding to the values of this preference display as a tab in the class viewer. Valid Values: One or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid named reference.

preference.name: ICS_presented_instance_documents
preference.preference_description: Determines which named references display in the instance viewer. The system searches all datasets of the selected object for named references. Any named references corresponding to the values of this preference display as a tab in the instance viewer. Valid Values: One or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid named reference, or one of the following values: BOMAssembly JTAssembly

preference.name: ICS_reference_attribute_use_format_for_display
preference.preference_description: Specifies that the reference attribute format is used to determine the size of the text field when searching in the Classification application. Valid Values: * true: the format of the dictionary attribute is used to determine the size of the text field. * false: the size of the text field of a reference attributes is always 256 characters. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_root_selector_entries
preference.preference_description: Defines what classes are displayed in the Classification root selector. The root selector allows to display only a subset of the classification hierarchy. This preference contains value pairs: the first and second value are the first pair, third and fourth the second pair and so on. The first value in each pair is the class ID. The second value in each pair is the name that is displayed in the root selector in the Teamcenter rich client user interface.

preference.name: ICS_search_filter_by_read_access
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the classification search filters out the ICOs for which the user does not have read access on the classified object while performing the search. Privileges on the class definition are not honored when this preference is set. Setting this preference to true has a negative performance impact on the search mechanism. Valid Values: true - The classification search returns only those ICOs for which the user has read access. false - The classification search returns all ICOs. When paging through the results, the user receives a message each time an ICO is reached for which there is no read access.

preference.name: ICS_search_image_order
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ICS_search_use_revision_rule
preference.preference_description: Determines whether revision rules can be used for a classification search. Valid Values: true - Enables revision rules functionality for classification searches. false - Disables revision rules functionality for classification searches.

preference.name: ICS_share_related
preference.preference_description: Determines which related objects of a Classification class/view are shared when the class/view is shared. Use this preference with shared Classification functionality. Valid Values: classImage - Shares class images. viewImage - Shares view images. partFamilyTemplates - Shares part family templates.

preference.name: ICS_show_autofilter
preference.preference_description: Determines whether auto filter functionality is enabled in Classification. Valid Values: true - Auto filter functionality is enabled in Classification. The Auto filter button displays before the text fields of attributes. false - Auto filter functionality is not enabled in Classification.

preference.name: ICS_show_multiple_classification_tooltip
preference.preference_description: Specifies the attribute IDs displayed in the multiple classification tab tooltips. In addition to the common ICO attributes, the following internal attributes can be used: -570 WSO Type -572 WSO Name -599 ICO Object ID -600 Class ID -607 Class Name -630 Class Unit -732 ICO Type If an attribute is specified in this preference but is not available in the ICO, it is ignored in the tooltip. The values are displayed in the following format: Attribute Name: Attribute Value The default value is: -600

preference.name: ICS_synchronize_automatically
preference.preference_description: Enables automatic synchronization of Classification data to the sites specified in the ICS_synchronize_sites preference. Valid Values: True - Classification hierarchy data is automatically shared to the selected sites whenever the data is saved. False - Classification hierarchy data is not shared to the selected sites whenever the data is saved.

preference.name: ICS_synchronize_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the sites with which Classification data can be shared with Multi-Site Collaboration. The sites specified in this preference appear in the Shared Sites dialog box in the Class Details pane in Classification Admin. Valid Values: Multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter site name. Site names must be entered into the database in a Organization/Sites format.

preference.name: ICS_table_header_style
preference.preference_description: Controls the display of attribute names in the table page header. Valid Values: Short - Displays abbreviated attribute names. Long - Displays the full attribute name. ID - Display attribute IDs.

preference.name: ICS_table_pagesize
preference.preference_description: Determines the number of rows (instances) initially displayed in the Classification table page in the thin client. Valid Values: A positive integer.

preference.name: ICS_unit_active
preference.preference_description: Specifies the active system of measurement that is initially displayed when a classification class is defined to hold both metric and nonmetric values. Valid Values: 0 - Metric system of measurement. 1 - Nonmetric system of measurement.

preference.name: ICS_unit_default
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default system of measurement when creating a class in the Classification Admin application. Valid Values: 0 - Metric system of measurement. 1 - Nonmetric system of measurement. 2 - Both metric and nonmetric systems of measurement.

preference.name: ICS_use_access_control
preference.preference_description: Determines the availability of the Classification access control feature. Valid Values: 0 - Disables access control functionality. 1 - Enables access control functionality.

preference.name: ICS_user_defined_button_class
preference.preference_description: You can define the user-defined button settings in the attribute's user fields. If the preference is set to "USER1", the system tries to find the user-defined button class code in the attribute's User 1 field. If the preference is set to "USER2", the system searches for the code in the User 2 field. Valid values are "USER1" and "USER2". Please refer to the Teamcenter documentation "Creating a user-defined button" for more information.

preference.name: ICS_web_preferred_jt_image
preference.preference_description: Determines which JT image is displayed in the Classification thin client when users select TcVis from the View menu. Use this preference to determine which image (single JT or JTs of BOM lines) displays when the classification object's contains both a single JT image and is a BOM assembly with JTs in the BOM lines. When the classification object contains only one image, the JT displays as follows: When the classified object contains a single JT file (as a direct model dataset) the JT file appears. When the classified object is a BOM assembly, the JTs of the BOM lines display. Valid Values: BOM_Assembly - Displays BOM assembly JTs. Single_JT - Displays single JT.

preference.name: ICS_web_preferred_unit
preference.preference_description: Specifies the unit system in which to display a selected classification object (ICO) in the Classification thin client application. Valid Values: metric - Displays an ICO in the metric system. non-metric - Displays an ICO in a nonmetric system.

preference.name: ICS_web_search_in_unit_system
preference.preference_description: Specifies the unit system when searching for classification objects (ICOs) in the Classification thin client application. Valid Values: metric - Search in the metric system only. non-metric - Search in the nonmetric system only. both - Search in both the metric and nonmetric systems, with switching enabled in the Query tab.

category.name: Classification.Administration
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: AWC_classification_facets_threshold
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of classification facets to be shown in filter panel. Valid values should be between 1 and the maximum number of classification facets in the system. The default value is "200".

preference.name: AWS_cls_attribute_interchangeability_definition
preference.preference_description: Defines the interchangeability between classification attributes. For example consider attributes with attribute IDs 1000 and 1001 are to be defined as interchangeable. The values should be specified as below - 1000:1001 1001:1000 Multiple attributes to be defined as interchangeable need to provided in comma-separated format - 1010:1005,2005

preference.name: CLS_auto_sync_node_hierarchy
preference.preference_description: Allows the system to mirror operations performed on Classification storage class hierarchy onto the Node hierarchy. Valid values are: * true: The system will mirror Storage class hierarchy operations onto the Node hierarchy. * false: No mirroring will take place. This is the default value.

preference.name: CLS_is_presentation_hierarchy_active
preference.preference_description: Preference to enable user to work with presentation classification hierarchy in Active Workspace client. Valid values are: * true : Enables the user to work with presentation classification hierarchy. * false : Enables the user to work with traditional classification class hierarchy.

preference.name: CST_default_migration_status
preference.preference_description: Specifies the status assigned to an object when migrating it from a traditional classification hierarchy to a CST (Classification Standard Taxonomy) hierarchy. Valid values are: * Develop: objects are still under development and can be changed. This is the default value. * Released: objects can no longer be modified. User can classify in released classes only.

preference.name: CST_default_namespace
preference.preference_description: Specifies the namespace for traditional classification to CST (Classification Standard Taxonomy). A namespace is required when creating definition objects in CST. An administrator must specify the value for the namespace before the migration from traditional classification can start.

preference.name: CST_supported_eclass_releases
preference.preference_description: Allows the system to support multiple eClass releases into single Teamcenter environment. This is multi valued preference where odd index entry represents actual eclass release identifier and even index entry represents display name of the corresponding release. Valid values are: * 0173-1#11-ECLASS9#001 * eclass 9.0 * 0173-1#11-ECLASS91#001 * eclass 9.1 * 0173-1#11-ECLASS10.0.1#001 * eclass 10.0.1 * 0173-1#11-ECLASS10.1#001 * eclass 10.1 * 0173-1#11-ECLASS11#001 * eclass 11.0 * 0173-1#11-ECLASS11.1#001 * eclass 11.1

preference.name: Cls0HierarchyNode_dataset_search_order
preference.preference_description: Lists the dataset types (in order of preference) used to obtain the preview image for Classification Hierarchy nodes. Valid values are dataset named references, in order of priority, separated by a comma (,).

preference.name: Cls0HierarchyNode_relation_search_order
preference.preference_description: Lists the Relations and Properties (in order of preference) used to obtain the preview image source object for Classification Hierarchy nodes. Valid values are Relations and Properties of a Cls0HierarchyNode Business object, separated by a comma (,).

preference.name: ICS_allow_remote_parent
preference.preference_description: Determines whether classes and views can be added under classes that are not locally owned. Valid Values: true - Classes and views can be added under classes that are not locally owned. false - Classes and views cannot be added under classes that are not locally owned.

preference.name: ICS_allowed_chars_for_class_id
preference.preference_description: Specifies the special characters that are permissible in group or class IDs in the classification hierarchy. By default, you cannot use a space or any of the following special characters:|%*:(){}[] \ You can, however, specify a subset of these characters that are permissible using this preference. To assist you in converting legacy group or class IDs, you can use the smlutility utility to find IDs that contain invalid characters. Valid Values: Any of the special characters either within quotation marks (if you want to include the space character) or without quotation marks. For example, if you set the value of this preference to %*, group or class IDs can contain these two characters, but the others in the list are not permitted. If you set the value of this preference to "{ }", the two brackets and the space character between them are permissible in the IDs.

preference.name: ICS_class_abstract_default
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default class type when creating a class in the Classification Admin application. The default value is true.

preference.name: ICS_copy_classid_pattern
preference.preference_description:
Determines the pattern of a class ID when a class is copied. All classes in Classification have unique identifiers. When performing a copy of a class (hierarchy), users must enter a new class ID for all classes to be copied. These new class IDs can also be automatically generated for one class or for all classes of a hierarchy. Use this preference to determine the pattern of class IDs when the classes are copied. Valid Values: Any single string value, used alone or in conjunction with the following placeholders: ${P} - Represents the class ID of the parent class. ${NNN} - Represents a three digit numerical sequence. Any number of digits can be defined. ${CID} - Represents the original class ID when a class is copied.
For example, ${CID}${NNN} generates SourceID000, where SourceID is the original class ID and 000 is the next iterative number. Another example, ${NNNN} generates 0000, where 00000 is the next iterative number. Another example, ${P}_${NNN} generates Parent_000, where Parent is the name of the parent class and 000 is the next iterative number. Another example, ${CID}.new generates SourceID.new, where SourceID is the original class ID, suffixed by .new.

preference.name: ICS_import_view_drop_attributes_not_in_class
preference.preference_description: Enables the PLM XML import of views to continue when the operation encounters an attribute not contained in the parent class. Valid Values: True - The attribute is ignored and the import continues. False - Teamcenter aborts the import upon encountering an attribute that is not contained in the parent class.

preference.name: ICS_keylovs_allowing_undefined_values
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Key LOV IDs (negative integers) that allows the use of temporarily undefined Key LOV entries during the creation and edition of Classification objects. Caution: Adding a key LOV ID to this list can cause data integrity problems.

preference.name: ICS_migrate_classid_pattern
preference.preference_description:
Determines the pattern of a class ID when migrating legacy SML subclasses to abstract subclasses and storage classes. All classes in Classification have unique identifiers. When SML subclasses are migrated, a new abstract class is created for each SML class and a storage class is created directly below the new abstract class for each subclass belonging to the SML class being migrated. Use this preference to determine the pattern of the class IDs when subclasses are migrated. Valid Values: Any single string value, used alone or in conjunction with the following placeholders: ${P} - Represents the class ID of the parent class. ${NNN} - Represents a three digit numerical sequence. Any number of digits can be defined. ${CID} - Represents the original class ID when a class is migrated. ${SID} - Represents the original class ID of the SML subclass being migrated.
For example, ${CID}${SID}${NNN} generates SMLClassIDSubclassID000, where SMLClassID is the original class ID, SubclassID is the original class ID of the SML subclass being migrated and 000 is the next iterative number. Another example, ${NNNN} generates 0000, where 00000 is the next iterative number. Another example, ${SID}_${NNN} generates SubclassID_000, where SubclassID is the original class ID of the SML subclass being migrated and 000 is the next iterative number.

preference.name: ICS_new_classid_pattern
preference.preference_description:
Determines the pattern of the class ID when a new class is created. All classes in Classification have unique identifiers. Use this preference to determine the pattern of the class ID when a new class is created. Valid Values: Any single string value, used alone or in conjunction with the following placeholders: ${P} - Represents the class ID of the parent class. ${NNN} - Represents a three digit numerical sequence. Any number of digits can be defined.
For example, ${P}${NNN} generates Parent000, where Parent is the name of the parent class, and 000 is the next iterative number. Another example, ${NNNNNN} generates 000000, where 000000 is the next iterative number. Another example, ${P}.new generates Parent.new, where Parent is the name of the parent class, suffixed by .new.

preference.name: ICS_override_root_node_name
preference.preference_description: Specifies that the admistrator can override the default name of the Classification root node. The default value is false.

preference.name: ICS_perform_xmlschema_validation
preference.preference_description: Activates schema validation during a "Classification XML Import" operation. The default value of this site preference is true. Valid Values: True - Schema validation takes place during the XML import operation. False - Schema validation is ignored during XML import operation.

preference.name: ICS_searchindex_view_visible
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the "Search Index View" type is available in the list of Classification View types that users can create. The default value is "false": the view is not available.

preference.name: ICS_use_view_attributes_when_moving_icos
preference.preference_description: Determines which attribute values are set when an classification object (ICO) is moved to a different class. Use this site preference to set only the attribute values visible to the user, or to set all attribute values, during ICO moves. Moving classes in Classification is similar to copying classes, but is performed via drag-and-drop from the Classification hierarchy tree. A user can move classes when the class is not shared, he has read access to all children of the class, and the new parent class is locally owned. Valid Values: true - Only attribute values which the current user can see in his view are set when an ICO is moved to a different class. false - All attribute values are set when an ICO is moved to a different class.

preference.name: ICS_view_selection_order
preference.preference_description: Determines the order in which Classification views are searched, based on the current user ID. Valid Values: Any of following strings as values. The order of the values determines the order in which the views are searched. USER PROJECT ROLE GROUP

category.name: Column Preferences
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: AVColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default settings for the AV tree table in Assembly View Application.

preference.name: AVShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the columns (identified by AVColumnsShownPref) for the AV tree table in Assembly View Application.

preference.name: ActivityColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Preference that holds the list of column names that will be displayed in the Activity tree table in Manufacturing MSE application.

preference.name: ActivityShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Preference that holds the list of column widths (for column names identified by ActivityColumnsShownPref) that will be used in the Activity tree table in Manufacturing MSE application.

preference.name: Admin - Employee Information_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: Admin - Group/Role Membership_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: AllocationsNavigatorColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Preference that holds the list of column names that will be displayed in the Allocation tree table in CC Application

preference.name: AllocationsNavigatorShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Preference that holds the list of column widths (for column names identified by AllocationsNavigatorColumnsShownPref) that will be used in the Allocation tree table in CC Application.

preference.name: AnalysisEditorColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names that will be displayed in the Analysis/Composite tree table in CAESE application. Possible values are me_cl_display_string to display the "Line" column, me_cl_object_desc for "Description" and al_context for "Relation".

preference.name: AnalysisEditorShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the column names (identified by AnalysisEditorColumnsShownPref) that will be used by the Analysis/Composite tree table in CAESE application.

preference.name: AnalysisView_OpenByName_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be displayed on Open By Name dialog Table in the CAE Manager application Analysis View.

preference.name: AssignedProductsColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the column configuration for the assigned products table for the current user. When user change visibility or order of column from assigned products table, the updated information is store in this preference. This preference is populated internally and is not meant to be modified by users.

preference.name: AssignedToolsToActColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates the default columns of the resources on activity table in Edit Resource Dialog in MSE.

preference.name: AssignedToolsToOpColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates the default columns of the resources on operation table in Edit Resource Dialog in MSE.

preference.name: AttachmentColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names that will be displayed in the Attachment tree table in Manufacturing MSE application.

preference.name: AttachmentShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the column names (identified by AttachmentColumnsShownPref) that will be used by the Attachment tree table in Manufacturing MSE application.

preference.name: BOM_Properties_For_Column_Selection
preference.preference_description: Specifies the system names of the available property columns that will be displayed in Structure Manager when the user inserts a column. This preference can be set at each of the required levels, that is, Site, Group, Role, and User. System will use the intersection list of properties defined on all scope levels. Valid Values: Any valid BOM line property name, including any additional BOM line property names derived by using the Fnd0BOMLineItemConfigProps, Fnd0BOMLineRevConfigProps, BOMLineFormConfiguredProperties, and BOMLineRevConfiguredProperties global constants.

preference.name: CAECompositeViewAnalysisViewShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths (in characters) for the CAE Composite View shown columns (left-to-right order).

preference.name: CAECompositeViewModelViewShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths (in characters) for the CAE Composite View shown columns (left-to-right order).

preference.name: CAECompositeViewProductViewShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths (in characters) for the CAE Composite View shown columns (left-to-right order).

preference.name: CAEFileExplorerViewTcFileColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of ImanFile properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right in the File Explorer View in the CAE application. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the CAE File Explorer View code itself.

preference.name: CAEFileExplorerViewTcFileShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths (in characters) for the CAE File Explorer View shown columns (left-to-right order).

preference.name: CAEModelViewerShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the width (in characters) of the columns shown in the Model view of the CAE Manager application in the left-to-right order.

preference.name: CAEProductViewerShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the width (in characters) of the columns shown in the Product view of the CAE Manager application in the left-to-right order.

preference.name: CAETargetRefViewShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths (in characters) for the CAE Target References View shown columns (left-to-right order).

preference.name: CCObject_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be displayed for objects of type CCObject.

preference.name: CPDDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of names of the columns displayed in the Content Explorer tree table in the 4G Designer application. Valid Values: Any string which is a valid property name.

preference.name: CPDShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the columns (identified by CPDDisplayNameColumnsShownPref) for the Content Explorer tree table in 4G Designer(4GD) application.

preference.name: Cfg0ProductItem_OpenByName_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: The OOTB columns to be displayed for the Cfg0ProductItem open by name pop-up

preference.name: ChangeSummaryColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the column configuration for the change summary table for the current user. When user change visibility or order of column from change summary table, the updated information is store in this preference. This preference is populated internally and is not meant to be modified by users. To change the default column configuration for change summary table please update ChangeSummaryTableColumns preference.

preference.name: ChangeSummaryColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the widths of the columns for the column names as defined in ChangeSummaryColumnsShownPref preference. This preference is populated internally and is not meant to be modified by users. To change the default column configuration for change summary table please update ChangeSummaryTableColumns preference.

preference.name: CollaborationTreeColumnsShownPref

ScheduleTask.object_name - Displays object name in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.ResourceAssignment - Displays resource assignment in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. predecessors - Displays predecessors in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. successors - Displays successors in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened.
