preference.name: CATIA_V4_checkin_generate_vis_data_priority
preference.preference_description: The scheduling priority for Catia V4 to JT check-in and/or save translations. The valid values of this preference are 0,1,2, and 3 corresponding to OFF, low, medium, and high priority. If this preference is not specified, no visualization data will be generated for check-in and/or save.

preference.name: CATIA_V4_translation_service_name
preference.preference_description: The TSTK provider name and service name of translator to be used for Catia V4 to JT translation. This preference value is specified using the provider and service attribute values from the corresponding translator element in the TSTK Module configuration translator.xml file (e.g. EDS.catiav4tojt). WARNING: If this preference is not specified, requests for Catia V4 to JT translations will be ignored.

Example: If your parameter definition is as follows:Round all sharp corners to [Radius: 0.4, 0.5, 0.6] inches and heat treat to [Temperature: 200, 220, 230] degrees Fahrenheit. If the value of this preference is true, the Note Text box of the standard note displays the parameter name and parameter values as follows: Round all sharp corners to Radius 0.01 inches and heat treat to Temperature 100 degrees Fahrenheit. If the value of this preference is false, the Note Text box of the standard note displays only parameter values as follows: Round all sharp corners to 0.01 inches and heat treat to 100 degrees Fahrenheit. preference.name: ETS_released_status_type_names
preference.preference_description: Specifies which released status types are copied from an item revision to a visualization dataset. The status type names are used to filter the setting of the released date and released status for visualization datasets. When an item revision's released status type matches a status type defined in this preference, the released date and released status are copied to the visualization dataset. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid status type name.

preference.name: ETS_trans_rqst_referenced_dataset_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies which dataset type names may be referenced by translation requests as primary or secondary objects. A pre-delete action is registered for each of these dataset types to support deletion of CAD data while a translation is in process. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Must be a valid dataset type name.

preference.name: ETS_trans_rqst_user_exit_states
preference.preference_description: Specifies which translation request states activate the Dispatcher translation request state transition user exit. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Dispatcher state.

preference.name: ETS_update_state_delay
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delay time in seconds after which a dispatcher request object can be updated.When there are multiple dispatcher clients in a Dispatcher installation, multiple dispatcher clients can update the state of the same dispatcher request object. The delay time makes sure that only one dispatcher client updates the dispatcher request object.If you set a very high delay time, the performance of the dispatcher request may be affected. Siemens PLM Software recommends that the delay time should not be greater than 5 seconds. Valid Values: Must be a single positive integer.

preference.name: RDV_show_targets_on_results_dialog
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the target parts table is displayed in the results dialog box after a proximity search. Applies to spatial searches in the Structure Manager and Multi Structure Manager applications. This preference is also applicable to the Manufacturing Process Planner application but only honored when searching filtered in-process assemblies. It is not honored in the structure search. The target parts table is visible at all times on the Structure Search Results view. Valid Values: true - The target parts table is displayed. false - The target parts table is not displayed.

preference.name: RDV_show_targets_on_spatial_dialog
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the target parts table is displayed in the spatial search dialog box during a proximity search. It applies to spatial searches in the Structure Manager and Multi Structure Manager. This preference also applies to spatial searches in the Manufacturing Process Planner application, but it is honored only for the structure search. It is not honored when searching filtered in-process assemblies. The target parts table is visible at all times on the Spatial Filter dialog box. Valid Values: true - The target parts table is displayed. false - The target parts table is not displayed.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWordX_ets_dst_ds_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset type, which will be the result of the Siemens tozipfile translation of a Microsoft WordX dataset. If you do not specify a dataset type, the service configuration is invalid and an error occurs during translation. Valid Values: Must be a valid dataset name.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWordX_ets_dst_nr_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset named reference type, which is the result of the Siemens tozipfile translation of a Microsoft WordX dataset. If you do not specify a dataset type, the service configuration is invalid and an error occurs during translation. Valid Values: Must be a valid dataset reference type.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWordX_ets_dst_relation_to_src
preference.preference_description: Specifies if a relation must be created between the Microsoft WordX source dataset and destination dataset. Valid Values: true - Creates a relation between the source and destination dataset. false - Does not create a relation between the source and destination dataset.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWordX_ets_dst_relation_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation type of the relation to be created between the source dataset item revision and the destination dataset. If the source and destination dataset types are the same, this preference is ignored. You must specify this preference if the source and destination datasets are different; otherwise, the service configuration is invalid and an error occurs during translation. Valid Values: Must be a valid relation type.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWordX_ets_nr_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the source dataset named reference necessary for translation. One of the dataset named reference types specified by this preference must exist for the Microsoft WordX dataset to be valid for translation. If you do not specify named reference types, the service configuration is invalid and an error occurs during translation. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. It must be a valid dataset reference type.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWord_ets_dst_ds_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset type, which is the result of the Siemens tozipfile translation of a Microsoft Word dataset. If you do not specify a dataset type, the service configuration is invalid and an error occurs during translation. Valid Values: Must be a valid dataset name.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWord_ets_dst_nr_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset reference type, which is the result of the Siemens Provider tozipfile translation of a Microsoft Word dataset. If you do not specify a dataset type, the service configuration is invalid and an error occurs during translation. Valid Values: Must be a valid dataset reference type.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWord_ets_dst_relation_to_src
preference.preference_description: Specifies if a relation must be created between the Microsoft Word source dataset and destination dataset. Valid Values: true - Creates a relation between the source and destination dataset. false - Does not create a relation between the source and destination dataset.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWord_ets_dst_relation_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation type of the relation to be created between the source dataset item revision and the destination dataset. If the source and destination dataset types are the same, this preference is ignored. You must specify this preference if the source and destination datasets are different; otherwise the service configuration is invalid and an error occurs during translation. Valid Values: Must be a valid relation type.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWord_ets_nr_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the source dataset named reference necessary for translation. One of the dataset named reference types specified by this preference must exist for the Microsoft Word dataset to be valid for translation. If you do not specify named reference types, the service configuration is invalid and an error occurs during translation. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. preference.preference_description: Defines the properties/relations data to be shown in the Animation view in the Electronic Work Instructions (EWI) solution in the Active Workspace Client (AWC). The valid format for the values is "<property/relation name>[:<type names>]" where: * <property/relation name> is the property or the relation name of the step object (sub-type of BOMLine). * <type names> is a comma separated list of internal type names of the secondary objects to show for the given property/relation. preference.name: EWI_DocumentItemsInformationRule
preference.preference_description: Defines which document items should be shown in the Electronic Work Instructions (EWI) solution in the Active Workspace client. Valid values are: * Assigned: Shows the document items directly assigned to the current step. * Attached: Shows the document items attached to the current step. * Assigned,Attached: Shows the document items directly assigned and those attached to the current step. This is the default value.

preference.preference_description: Defines the relation between the document item attachment line and its parent. Documents attached to a process line with the specified relationship are displayed in the "Documents" and "References" views in the Electronic Work Instructions (EWI) solution in the Active Workspace Client (AWC).

preference.name: EWI_DocumentRelationsInfo
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties/relations data to be shown in the Document view in the Electronic Work Instructions (EWI) solution in the Active Workspace Client (AWC). The valid format for the values is "<property/relation name>[:<type names>]" where: * <property/relation name> is the property or the relation name of the step object (sub-type of BOMLine). * <type names> is a comma separated list of internal type names of the secondary objects to show for the given property/relation. This argument is optional. In case the type names are not provided, all of the secondary objects information will be shown.

preference.name: EWI_ExecutionEnabled
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the execution features are enabled in the Electronic Work Instructions (EWI) application.

preference.name: EWI_FORCE_SHOW_UNCONFIGURED_OFF
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the EWI application forces all MPP 'Show Unconfigured...' configurations toggles to off while loading the structures. If this preference is set to true (the default value), EWI will set these toggles to false and will display configured data only. In this mode, EWI does not respect the MPP settings and intentionally sets all show unconfigured data toggle values "off". If it is set to false, EWI will respect the MPP definitions as follows: 1) When EWI is launched using a CC, the toggle values defined within the CC are used for EWI BOM configuration. 2) When EWI is not launched with a CC, EWI will use the MPP view toggle preferences values. These preferences are: MEShowUnconfiguredAssignedOccurrencesDefaultState, MEShowUnconfiguredChangesDefaultState, MEShowUnconfiguredOccurrencesEffectivityDefaultState and MEShowUnconfiguredVariantsDefaultState.

category.name: FMS
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: DM_Write_Ticket_Expiration_Interval
preference.preference_description: Determine the time interval (in seconds) used by FMS (File Management System) in order to set the Download Manager write ticket expiration time. If this value is not set, the ticket expiration interval is set to 259200 seconds (72 hrs) by default.

preference.name: Default_Transient_Server
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default transient file server location. Environment variable settings override this FCC configuration file setting. Valid Values: Accepts a single value. Must be a valid transient file server location. For example: Default_Transient_Serrver = http://www.transientserver.com

preference.name: Default_Transient_Volume_Id
preference.preference_description: Defines the corporate server transient volume. This preference must be defined to enable transfer of multi-site export metadata from site to site when running in a two-tier environment. Valid Values: Accepts a single value. Must be a valid transient volume ID.

preference.name: FMS_SAF_Batch_Transfer_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables FMS Store and Forward in batch transfer mode.Store and forward functionality can be implemented by two different methods:Single file: moves and cleans up files from the local volume one file at a time.This method uses dispatcher functionality.Batch method: queries the Teamcenter database all of the user's files stored in local volumes and transfers them to their specified destination volumes. This method combines move_volume_files utility and dispatcher functionality. Store and forward functionality defines default local volumes to be temporary local volumes that allow files to be stored locally before they are automatically transferred to the final destination volume. This improves end-user file upload times from clients by uploading files to a temporary volume. Store and forward functionality requires installation of dispatcher scheduler, module, client and the store_and_forward translator. Valid Values: True - Enables store and forward functionality in batch mode.This requires installation of dispatcher scheduler, module, client and the store_and_forward translator. False - Disables store and forward functionality in batch mode.

preference.name: HSM_integration_enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables the Volume Management application to work with third-party hierarchical storage management (HSM) software. Valid Values: true - Enables the Volume Management application to work with third-party HSM software. false - Disables the Volume Management application from working with third-party HSM software.

preference.name: HSM_primary_tier_hosts
preference.preference_description: Defines the host names on which the primary tier volumes are managed by third-party HSM software.HSM migration is applied to the volume files residing on hosts defined by this preference. The hsm_capacity_alert utility estimates the capacities of the volumes and uses the values defined in this preference to send e-mail alerts when the primary tier capacity exceeds alert levels. Volumes residing on hosts not defined by this preference are ignored for HSM migration and the hsm_capacity_alert utility. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid host name on which primary tier volumes reside. If all primary tier volumes are managed by third-party HSM software, you can set this preference to ALL rather than listing the individual host names.

preference.name: HSM_read_thru_supported
preference.preference_description: Declares whether read access to secondary and tertiary volumes is supported. If your HSM system or hardware platform does not support read access from secondary and tertiary volumes, the migrated files are moved to a higher tier to be read. For example, the IBM Tivoli HSM product does not provide read-through capability, and the EMC DiskXtender HSM product only provides read-through capability on Windows. In such situations, use reverse migration to return files to the primary tier. If this preference is set to false, the system moves the migrated files to a higher tier during the read operation, then during the next migration, returns the files to the tiers from which they were retrieved.This preference requires that the HSM_integration_enabled preference be set to true. Valid Values: true - Migrated files are not moved to a higher tier during the read operation. false - Migrated files are moved to a higher tier during the read operation. The files are returned to the tiers from which they were stored in subsequent migrations.

preference.name: Multisite_Ticket_Expiration_Interval
preference.preference_description: Specifies how long, in seconds, the ticket is good for access. Add this value to the current time when the ticket is generated to calculate the ticket expiration time. Environment variable settings override this FCC configuration file setting. Valid Values: Single positive integer.

preference.name: TC_Cache_Allowed
preference.preference_description: Indicates if local file caching is enabled or not.

preference.name: TC_Cache_Protection
preference.preference_description: Indicates the operating system protection applied to the files stored in the file cache.

preference.name: TC_Store_and_Forward
preference.preference_description: Determines whether store and forward functionality is enabled, improving upload performance for remote users. This functionality improves end-user file upload times from clients by uploading files to a temporary volume. Users can continue to work on their files from the temporary location. The system moves the files to its final destination according to administer-defined criteria. Files are accessible to FMS at all times. Enable this functionality by defining a default local volume (an initial upload volume) for users or groups and setting this preference to true. When users upload files, the files are temporarily uploaded to the defined initial FMS volume, returning control to the user in the client. In the background, the files are transferred to the final destination volume. This allows you to place an FMS volume on the remote users LAN, ensuring quick uploads into the FMS of this temporary volume. All file transfers are transparent to end users.You can view the status of file transfers from the Dispatcher request administration console.By default, the store and forward functionality moves files from the local volume to their final destination volume one at a time (using the fmstranslator Dispatcher translator). If you set the FMS_SAF_Batch_Transfer_Enabled preference to true, you can use the store_and_forward Dispatcher translator to upload files in batch. Valid Values: true - Enables store and forward functionality. false - Disables store and forward functionality by instructing the system to ignore the default local volume setting, uploading files directly to the destination volume.This setting is useful to quickly disable store and forward functionality. For example, if the scheduler or initial volume at a site goes offline unexpectedly, you can use this setting to quickly disable store and forward. The alternative is to alter the initial volume settings of all impacted users, which is a lengthy task.

preference.name: TC_Store_and_Forward_Transfer_Delay
preference.preference_description: Determines (in minutes) how long file transfer is delayed between file upload to the initial volume and file upload to the final destination volume.Use this preference to improve performance if you have a large amount of revisions created, cached, and purged at your site. Because the transfer task does not transfer purged filed, if numerous file revisions are saved frequently at your site, a delay time long enough to allow revisions to be purged before the transfer to the final destination volume reduces network traffic. For example, consider a site where all user files are automatically saved every 15 minutes, and purged after every third revision. If store and forward functionality is enabled, and this preference is set to 46, the transfer task activates every 46 minutes, sees that the revisions have been purged, and does not attempt the transfer. Only files not purged are transferred to the destination volume, decreasing network traffic. Valid Values: Any positive integer.

preference.name: TC_VOLUME_MONITOR_CRITICAL_LEVEL
preference.preference_description: Specifies the percentage full a volume must reach to achieve critical level. When a volume's capacity reaches critical level, its volume data is colored red in the Volume Monitor view of the Volume Management perspective. Additionally, such volumes display when filtering the table tree to list only volumes with a severity of Critical. Valid Values: Accepts a single value between 1 and 99, inclusive. The value must be greater than the value set for the TC_VOLUME_MONITOR_WARNING_LEVEL preference.

preference.name: TC_VOLUME_MONITOR_WARNING_LEVEL
preference.preference_description: Specifies the percentage full a volume must reach to achieve warning level. When a volume's capacity reaches warning level, its volume data is colored yellow in the Volume Monitor view of the Volume Management perspective. Additionally, such volumes display when filtering the table tree to list only volumes with a severity of Warning. Valid Values: Accepts a single value between 1 and 99, inclusive. The value must be less than the value set for the TC_VOLUME_MONITOR_CRITICAL_LEVEL preference.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Failover_Trigger
preference.preference_description: Specifies the percentage full a volume must reach to trigger volume failover behavior for importing files. When volume capacity reaches the percentage full specified by this preference, importing files are directed to the failover volume specified by the TC_Volume_Failover_Volume_Name preference.This preference setting is used by the system only when the TC_Volume_Failover_Volume_Name preference is set. Valid values are Accepts a single float value, from 0-100.Siemens PLM Software recommends setting this preference between 80 and 95. Setting this value too low triggers failover behavior too often. Setting this value too high prevents failover behavior from initiating.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Failover_Volume_Map
preference.preference_description: Specifies a mapping of failover (alternate) volumes. This preference can be used when a volume is marked as read-only or is otherwise inaccessible for write operations. Specifying the alternate volume using this preference ensures that future write operations are done to the alternate volume. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. The string must include valid volume names. Each value should be of the form: source-volume:destination-volume The mappings can be cascaded such that an entry of the form VolA:VolB and VolB:VolC indicates that the system should use VolC when VolA is the current volume.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Failover_Volume_Name
preference.preference_description: Specifies the volume to use in failover situations during file import. Setting this preference with a volume name prompts the system to check the original target volume before import. If the target volume is filled beyond the capacity specified by the TC_Volume_Failover_Trigger preference, the imported file is directed to the failover volume specified by this preference. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value; the string must be a valid volume name.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Status_Resync_Interval
preference.preference_description: Indicates the minimum amount of time (in seconds) that must pass before the percentage full value of a volume is retrieved from the FSC. The percentage full values are cached to prevent excessive FSC requests. The system only checks for this cached value during file import, and only when volume failover during file import behavior is enabled by setting the TC_Volume_Failover_Volume_Name preference. Valid Values: Accepts a single positive integer as a value.Siemens PLM Software recommends keeping this setting similar to the default value. Setting this value too high causes the cached percentage full value to be out of date. Setting this value too low generates excessive FSC requests.

preference.name: TC_allow_inherited_group_volume_access
preference.preference_description: Allows a group to inherit access to a Teamcenter volume from its parent group. That is, if a group is explicitly granted volume access, and this preference is set to a nonzero number, that group's subgroups (and the subgroup's children) are implicitly granted access to that volume. Inherited access applies to all volumes including default local volumes, also known as store and forward volumes. Valid Values: 0 - Does not allow groups to inherit access to a volume from its parent group. Single positive integer - Allows groups to inherit access to a volume from its parent group.

preference.name: TC_enable_backup_modes
preference.preference_description: Determines whether backup functionality is enabled. The integrated backup and recovery feature facilitates third-party backup systems to perform online backup, allowing Teamcenter to operate continually. This functionality focuses on the area of backing up metadata and file, and recovering that data in different restoration scenarios. To accomplish this, the integrated backup feature places Teamcenter in different operation modes using the backup_modes utility. Valid Values: true - Enables backup functionality. false - Disables backup functionality.

preference.name: TC_sfr_process_life_time
preference.preference_description: Specifies (in minutes) how long the system continues to check for recovered files after a user-initiated single file recovery action is activated. Valid values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a positive integer.

preference.name: TC_sfr_recovery_interval
preference.preference_description: Specifies (in seconds) how often the system checks for recovered files after a user-initiated single file recovery action is activated. This preference is used for single file recovery. Valid values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a positive integer.

preference.name: Ticket_Expiration_Interval
preference.preference_description: Specifies how long, in seconds, the ticket is good for access. Add this value to the current time when the ticket is generated to calculate the ticket expiration time. Environment variable settings override this FCC configuration file setting. Valid Values: Single positive integer.

preference.name: Ticket_Expiration_Resolution
preference.preference_description: Indicates the resolution (minimum amount of time in seconds) before the FMS ticket expiration is changed. Setting this value advances the computed expiration time up to the value set, and limits the change in expiration time by the resolution. This value can be used to improve performance of browser client applications that render files stored in FMS such as thumbnails. This value should not be large and should not be larger than the normal ticket expiration intervals. If this value is not set, a default of 7200 seconds is used.

preference.name: Transient_Volume_Installation_Location
preference.preference_description: Specifies the node name of the transient volume. It is a location-based logical identifier, and is generally set to the host name of the local machine by the tc_profilevars script. When a four-tier transient volume is mounted on all Teamcenter server hosts at a given location, use this setting to configure the distributed transient volume. The environment variable of the same name overrides this preference setting. Valid Values: Accepts a single value. It must be a valid host name.

preference.name: Transient_Volume_RootDir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the transient volume's root directory. This preference accepts multiple values to support a UNIX/Windows heterogeneous site. FMS takes the first value which is valid for the platform, UNIX or Windows; the validity check is simply the presence or absence of a backslash (\) character. Environment variable settings override this FCC configuration file setting. Transient volumes are file locations to which TcServer processes have direct access. These locations are typically used for server side file generation operations such as PLM XML files. Files within transient volumes are typically generated by the TcServer, read by a client (usually) once, then deleted.This preference is set during the initial database population. Its value should not be changed, even if several other Teamcenter installations point to the same pre-populated database. Valid Values: Accepts multiple values, in order to support a UNIX/Windows heterogeneous site. For example: Transient_Volume_RootDir= C:\temp /tmp You cannot define the path as a UNC path, for example, \\server\shared-transient-folder. You must use a direct path location. This is partly due to the fact that some ZIP archive utilities do not accept UNC paths, resulting in failure of exports to Microsoft Excel or Word.

preference.name: blobbyVolume_NT
preference.preference_description: Specifies an alternate volume location on a Windows platform, allowing for constant Teamcenter availability during hot backup. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a valid volume location. Maximum character length of the string is 15 characters. For example: c:\temp

preference.name: blobbyVolume_UNX
preference.preference_description: Specifies an alternate volume location on a UNIX platform, allowing for constant Teamcenter availability during hot backup. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a valid volume location. Maximum character length of a string is 15 characters. For example:/tmp

preference.name: FMS_Enable_Selective_File_Caching
preference.preference_description: Enables the Teamcenter server selective file caching logic.

preference.name: FMS_Use_SHA256_Tickets
preference.preference_description: Configures Teamcenter to use FMS tickets that have SHA256 digests. Restart the Teamcenter Server after changing this value for it to take effect. The default FMS tickets use MD5 digests which are deprecated from Tc13.1. The FMS master configuration should also be updated to reflect the use of SHA256 tickets using the ticketdigest element.

preference.name: Fms_BootStrap_Urls
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of FMS Bootstrap (Entry point) servers for FMS client applications like the Thin Client, the Teamcenter server and Teamcenter utilities. Active Workspace has its own set of FMS Bootstrap URLs defined in its deployment. Desktop clients like the Teamcenter Rich Client and NX that use the File Cache Client (FCC) have their list of bootstrap FMS servers defined in the fcc.xml. The fcc.xml should typically have the same set of FMS servers defined as this Bootstrap URL list. Once FMS is initialized using the Bootstrap URLs, the client application typically gets one or more Assigned FSCs (File Server Cache) that serve the subsequent FMS file requests. Any FSC can act as the FMS Bootstrap URL. For failover purposes, you can include multiple FMS servers in this preference. This preference can be set using the preference name as an environment variable. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid server location. For example: Fms_BootStrap_Urls= http://abc.com http://def.com:4040 http://ghi.com

preference.name: TC_Volume_FilesPerDir_Check_Interval
preference.preference_description: Specifies the interval (in seconds) at which the volume subdirectory should be checked for its maximum file limit. This option is only valid when the preference TC_Volume_Max_Files_Per_Dir is set to a value greater than 0. Very low values can affect the performance of the system. High values can affect the accuracy of TC_Volume_Max_Files_Per_Dir, so new sub-directories could get created much later than when the file limit has been reached.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Max_Files_Per_Dir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of allowed files in a sub-directory in a volume. The system automatically creates new sub-directories for storing new files, once the current sub-directory has reached this limit. Setting this value to 0 effectively disables this feature, so all files being created go into the same (current) sub-directory in the volume. Very low values can affect the performance of the system. Values less than 10000 will be converted to a default minimum value of 10000. Suggested values are in the range 100000 - 500000 for most file systems.

preference.name: 4GD_Mode
preference.preference_description: Sets the default mode used during the 'Add to Current Change' action.The default mode sets the automation behavior by which additional Impacted Objects are added to a Change. Valid integer values to represent them are 1 (for Authoring Mode), 2 (for Discovery Mode) and 3 (for Authoring and Discovery Mode). Default Mode value is 1.

preference.name: 4GD_Sync_Queue_BatchSize
preference.preference_description: Defines the optimal batch size for automatic synchronization utility "4gd_process_sync_queue". The default batch size is 1000.

preference.name: 4GD_massupdaterealization_query_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Defines the batch size for querying realizations found by 'Mass Update Realization' in My Teamcenter and Change Manager application.It is advisable to set the batch size based on network parameters between Teamcenter client and server such as latency, bandwidth etc. A value of 0 or less than 0 indicates that there is no maximum batch size and that all the realizations will be queried in single batch. Any positive integer value indicates the maximum batch size and thus the realizations will be queried in multiple batches as per the batch size specified by this preference.

preference.name: 4G_populate_release_status_to_ignore
preference.preference_description: List of status names to ignore while release status propagation from source objects to 4G objects. 4G_populate will ignore propagation of release status from Source objects if it belongs to ignore list. Default value is empty list. User can add multiple status names to ignore list. e.g. TCM Released

preference.name: AIWS_SEND_TIMEOUT
preference.preference_description: Valid values are 0 - 32678.

preference.name: AMPatternMatchStyle
preference.preference_description: Indicates the pattern matching style to use while evaluating Access Manager rules. Valid Values: *1: Uses "%" for multi-char replacements and use "_" for single char replacements. *2: Uses "*" for multi-char replacements and use "." for single char replacements. *3: Uses "*" for multi-char replacements and use "?" for single char replacements. This is the default value.

preference.name: AM_PROJECT_MODE
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the system evaluates the roles in all the active projects of the logged in user, or just the role of the current project, when processing the Role in Project and Role in Projects of Object accessors.The Teamcenter servers must be restarted after setting this site preference, for the setting to become effective in Access Manager evaluation. Valid Values: true - System evaluates the roles in all active projects of the logged in user while processing the Role in Project and Role in Projects of Object accessors. false - System evaluates only the roles of the current project of the logged in user while processing the Role in Project and Role in Projects of Object accessors.

preference.name: AM_read_expression_mgr_svc_active
preference.preference_description: This is an internal preference.

preference.name: ARM_acquire_license
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's license acquisition performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the request to the FLEXlm sever to the return of the license key. Valid Values: * ON: Enables the performance monitoring of the license acquisition performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses the performance monitoring of the license acquisition performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_archive_operation
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of archive operations. Valid Values: * ON: Enables the performance monitoring of archive operations. * OFF: Disables the performance monitoring of archive operations.

preference.name: ARM_bom_compare
preference.preference_description: Activate the BOM compare performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time between the beginning of the operation and the completion of the comparison. Valid Values: * ON: Enables the performance monitoring of the BOM compare performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses the performance monitoring of the BOM compare performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_checkin_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's check-in objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to when all objects are checked-in. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the check in objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the check in objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_checkout_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's check-out objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to when all objects are checked-out. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the check out objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the check out objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_copy_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's copy objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all objects. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the copy objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the copy objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_create_changeitem
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Create Change Object" performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the insertion of the initial task into all target inboxes. This action occurs only when the "Start Process On Create" option is checked while creating a new change. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the "Create Change Object" performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the "Create Change Object" performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_create_dataset
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Create Dataset" performance transaction. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the "Create Dataset" performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the "Create Dataset" performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_create_item
preference.preference_description: Activates the create item performance transaction. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the "Create Item" performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the "Create Item" performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_create_itemrev
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Create Item Revision" performance transaction. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the "Create Item Revision" performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the "Create Item Revision" performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_create_supersedure
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Create Supersedure" performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of the supersedure. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the "Create Supersedure" performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the "Create Supersedure" performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_cut_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's cut objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of operation to the display of remaining objects. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the cut objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the cut objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_delete_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's delete objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of operation to when all objects are deleted. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the delete objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the delete objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_display_changeitem
preference.preference_description: Activates the Portal's display change object performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all change folders. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the display change performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the display change performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_display_form
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's display form performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all objects. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the display form performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the display form performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_display_genealogy
preference.preference_description: Activates the display genealogy performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the selection of the superseded item to when the genealogy is displayed. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the display genealogy performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the display genealogy performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_display_prop
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's display of object properties performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all objects. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the display object properties performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the display object properties performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_expand_bomview
preference.preference_description: Activates the BOM view expansion performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time between the beginning of the operation and the display of top-level components. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the BOM view expansion performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the BOM view expansion performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_expand_object
preference.preference_description: Activates the Expand Object performance transaction. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the expand folder performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the expand folder performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_export_dataset
preference.preference_description: Activates the export dataset performance transaction. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the export dataset performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the export dataset performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_idsm_import
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Teamcenter remote import function. For client processes, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform a remote import operation on the selected objects. For ODS processes, the transaction reports the time required to locate and transfer the selected remote objects and to report operation status back to the requesting client process. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Teamcenter remote import function. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Teamcenter remote import function.

preference.name: ARM_idsm_version_check
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration internal version check function. For the client process, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform a version request of the IDSM server at a remote node. For the IDSM process, the transaction reports the time required to respond to the version check request. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration internal version check function. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration internal version check function.

preference.name: ARM_import_dataset
preference.preference_description: Activates the import dataset performance transaction. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the import dataset performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the import dataset performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_initiate_process
preference.preference_description: Activates the process initiation performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the insertion of the initial task into all target inboxes. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the process initiation performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the process initiation performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_launch_mynavigator
preference.preference_description: Activates the rich client's launch My Teamcenter performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time for loading the "My Teamcenter" application. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the launch My Teamcenter performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the launch My Teamcenter performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_load_lov
preference.preference_description: Activates the Portal's load LOV performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from selecting an LOV to the display of all objects in the list. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the load LOV performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the load LOV performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_ods_publish
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration publish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. For client processes, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform a publish object operation on the selected objects. For ODS processes, the transaction reports the time required to create the publication records for the objects and to report operation status back to the requesting client process. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration publish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration publish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service.

preference.name: ARM_ods_remote_find
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring for the Multi-Site Collaboration remote find function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. For client processes, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform a remote find operation for the published objects that match the query parameters. For the ODS process, the time required to perform the remote find operation on the objects that match the query parameters is reported. Valid Values: * ON: Enables performance monitoring for the Multi-Site Collaboration remote find function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring for the Multi-Site Collaboration remote find function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service.

preference.name: ARM_ods_unpublish
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration unpublish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. For client processes, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform an unpublish object operation on the selected objects. For ODS processes, the transaction reports the time required to remove the publication records for the objects and to report operation status back to the requesting client process. Operation status or error code metrics can also be reported for both client and server processes. preference.name: AbsOccGrmSecondaryCopyRules
preference.preference_description:
Determines system behavior when revising a context BOM view revision (BVR) that is copying absolute occurrence General Relationship Management (GRM) relation overrides forward to the new item revision. Use this preference to specify a reverse lookup for absolute occurrence GRM relation overrides by identifying the class of the GRM relation, the class of the primary object, the relation type, and the action taken during the revision.An assembly with trace links to absolute occurrence objects is required to test this preference. When adding new values (copy rules) to this preference, verify the rule by revising an item revision object related to the trace link at least once. Then, check the syslog file to verify no errors are thrown while reading the preference. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Strings are case sensitive and trailing blanks are not allowed. Each string is a concatenation of class, relation, and action values that must be in the following format: class-name-1:class.AbsOccData:Relation:relation-type:action
class-name-1 - Specifies the class of the primary object, for example, class.ItemRevision. class.AbsOccData - Specifies the class of the secondary object. This class name must always be class.AbsOccData. Relation - The relation must always be Relation. All other types are ignored. relation-type - Specifies the relation type used when applying the action. It must be a valid relation type. action - Specifies the action that is performed on the primary object. It must be one of the following values: Ignore - The GRM relation is not copied to the new BOM view revision. Reference - Creates a new GRM relation that points to the same primary object that was defined on the original absolute occurrence GRM relation object. Note: The following rule example reflects the default COTS behavior for the carry forward of trace links on item revision objects to the latest revision. *:class.AbsOccData:Relation.FND_Tracelink:Reference

preference.name: Baseline_auto_remote_checkout_allowed
preference.preference_description: Determines whether automatic remote checkout of replicated objects is allowed during a baseline operation. If allowed, replica items, and BOM views of replica item revisions, will be (automatically) checked out during baseline operations. The resulting baseline object is owned by the original owning site once the item or BOM view is remotely checked back in (automatically) after the baseline operation successfully completes.Use this preference at sites using the remote check out/check in method, rather than the method of transferring ownership of objects. If your site often creates baselines of remote objects, enabling this preference improves system performance. Before setting this preference to True, ensure that the baseline business rules are the same at the owning site and remote site. Otherwise, revision IDs produced at the baseline will be of inconsistent values. The status type to be applied at the replica site must also exist at the owning site. Valid Values: True or On or 1(case insensitive) - Automatic remote checkout of replicated objects is allowed during baseline operations. False or Off or 0(case insensitive) - Automatic remote checkout of replicated objects is not allowed during baseline operations. Users can remote checkout replica objects manually, and proceed with a baseline operation.

preference.name: Baseline_restricted_item_types

When you baseline a structure and a restricted item type is found in the structure, Teamcenter displays an error message and none of the components in the structure is baselined. Valid Values: Any valid item type that is not listed below

preference.name: Briefcase_pkg_file_name
preference.preference_description: Defines the file name format for briefcase packages (named references attached to dataset objects). The format is based on the keywords representing attributes of the object being exported. The format is any combination of one or more of the attributes specified in the following valid values and any text string representing a constant in the file name. Valid Values: Any text string - The text forms a part of the package file name. Add SPLM as a prefix for the following format:SPLM_00001_A_Site1_31-Sep-2011_19-48-30.bcz ItemID - The item ID attribute forms a part of the package file name. Add ItemId as the attribute following the prefix for the following format:BCZ_00001_A_assembly1_31-Sep-2011_19-48-30.bcz RevID - The revision ID attribute forms part of the package file name. Add RevID as the second attribute for the following format:BCZ_00001_A_Site1_31-Sep-2011_19-48-30.bcz ItemName - The object's item name forms part of the package file name. Add ItemName as the third attribute for the following format:BCZ_00001_A_assembly1_31-Sep-2011_19-48-30.bcz TargetSite - The remote site name forms part of the package file name. Add TargetSite as the third attribute for the following format:BCZ_00001_A_Site1_31-Sep-2011_19-48-30.bcz TimeStamp - The time stamp forms part of the package file name. Add TimeStamp as the last attribute for the following format:BCZ_00001_A_assembly1_31-Sep-2011_19-48-30.bcz

The internal names can be found in file cc_locale.properties in portal.jar (look for entries [internal name].TABLABEL=[locale name]). Use a preceding *back slash* symbol for any empty space in the string value.

preference.name: CCObject.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the create stylesheet for CCObject objects.

preference.name: CFMEffConfigItemProperties
preference.preference_description: Determines the properties and values that define when an item is a configuration item. If this preference is not set, the system uses the default property of the is_configuration_item POM_attribute.You specify one or more properties and values that identify an item as an effectivity configuration item. A configuration item defines an effectivity boundary in a product structure, that is, a point at which the product context is modified. (This is point at which the revision rule end item changes.) Valid Values: Any item property with its value on the following line prefixed with == characters. To use a simple logical property to define configuration items, configure this preference in the following format: is_configuration_item == Y For example, to use items of the Product type as configuration items, configure this preference in the following format: object_type == Product

preference.name: CFM_ITEM_TYPE_RULE_INCLUDE_SUB_TYPE
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether or not sub types and its hierarchy can be used when we have base type in has item type rule. Valid values are true/false. true - Allow the user to configure structure of sub types based on the base type in revision rule entry. false - Allow the user to configure the structure only when the rule item type equals the type of the item.

preference.name: CM_AllowVendorPartContractAssignment
preference.preference_description: This preference is to enable auto propagation of Contract licenses from Commercial Part Revision to Vendor Part.

preference.name: CM_Cm0ActionItemRevision_Relations_To_Propagate
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of relations to be propagated when deriving from a Cm0ActionItem Revision.

preference.name: CM_Cm0DevRqstRevision_Relations_To_Propagate
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of relations to be propagated when deriving a change from a deviation request revision. Valid Values: One or more strings representing a valid Change Manager relation.

preference.name: CPD_4GPopulate_ChangeOwningUserGroupEnabled
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the owning user and owning group of realized 4GD objects are identical to the ones of their corresponding Item Revisions in the 4GD application. Valid Values: * true: the owning user and owning group of realized 4GD objects are identical to the ones of their corresponding Item Revisions. * false: the owning user and owning group of realized 4GD objects are identical to the ones of the logged-in user. This is the default value.

preference.name: CPD_4GPopulate_CreatePartitionMemForSubordinateDEs
preference.preference_description: In context of 4G Populate, specifies whether to create Partition Membership objects for Subordinate Design Components to Partition if Partition Membership object for its Reuse Design Component exist. Valid Values: * true: Create Partition Membership Objects for Subordinate Design Components. * false: Do not create Partition Membership Objects for Subordinate Design Components. This is the default value.

preference.name: CPD_4GPopulate_Non_Supported_CAD_Datasets
preference.preference_description: Defines the CAD dataset types that are not supported on the organization nodes for realizing an Item Assembly to 4G model using the "4G Populate" command.

preference.name: CPD_4GPopulate_PartitionName
preference.preference_description: This preference enables users to control object name of partitions created using 4g_populate utility. User can use source_item_id, source_item_name or source_item_revid attributes from preview file to specify value of this preference. Default value of the preference is source_item_name. Sample patterns are as follows, source_item_id+_+source_item_name+_+source_item_revid source_item_name+_+source_item_revid source_item_id+_+source_item_revid

preference.name: CPD_4GPopulate_ReleaseStatusPropagation
preference.preference_description: In context of 4G Populate, specifies whether to apply Release Statuses of source Item Revision on realized Reuse Design Component. Valid Values: * true: Apply Release Statuses of source Item Revision on realized Reuse Design Component. * false: Do not apply Release Statuses of source Item Revision on realized Reuse Design Component. This is the default value.

preference.name: CPD_4GPopulate_RevisionRule
preference.preference_description: This preference contains Revision Rule name which will be used to get all candidate revisions corresponding to an Installation Assembly. This preference will be used by preview creation step of initial populate (4g_populate) utility. Based on Revision Rule clauses configured in this Revision Rule, Release status type information will be fetched such as "Released Status", "Working".

preference.name: CPD_4GPopulate_StartingEffectivity
preference.preference_description: Defines the starting date or unit effectivity used to calculate the net effectivity in order to identify target Installation Assembly revisions. This preference is used by the preview creation step of the initial populate (4g_populate) utility. If this preference does not contain any effectivity value, only the latest Installation Assembly per Release Status will be realized. Examples: 1. For an expected starting unit effectivity of 3, the preference value is "UNIT|3" 2. For an expected starting date effectivity of 1st June 2016, the preference value is "DATE|01-Jun-2016 00:00:00"

preference.name: CPD_4GPopulate_effectivity_group
preference.preference_description: Defines the Effectivity Group ID set on the BOM Window before performing the "4G Initial Population Preview" operation to filter out the BOM Lines based on effectivity values specified in the Effectivity Group object.

preference.name: CPD_CLDB_Include_Recipe_In_DuplicateClearanceValidation
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the recipe definition should be included in create validation of clearance calculation object in a product design. Clearance Calculation object is validated for unique combination of Product Design, Revision Rule, Effectivity and Variant Rule during create operation. True value will include recipe definition in above validation criteria. False value will perform create validation without recipe definition. The default value is false.

preference.name: CPD_ItemRlzItemRevPropsToCarryOver
preference.preference_description: Lists the properties to carry-over from Item Revisions to their realized Reuse Design Components (and the Subordinate Design Components of these Reuse Design Components) during the realization process. Valid values are Item Revision property internal names.

preference.name: CPD_Open_Viewer_By_Default
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the 3D viewer is opened automatically whenever a 4GD object is opened in the 4GD application. Valid Values: * true: When a 4GD object is opened in Content explorer view in 4GD, related 3D Viewer is opened automatically. This is the default value. * false: When a 4GD object is opened in Content explorer view in 4GD, related 3D Viewer is not opened automatically.

preference.name: CPD_design_context_maximum_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of objects in all Design Contexts to be returned by SOA operation generateDesignContext. If the number of found objects is greater than the given value, the SOA operation genreateDesignContext in 4th Generation Design will fail.

preference.name: CPD_design_context_proximity_distance
preference.preference_description: Specifies the distance value (in meter) for proximity search. TThis is leveraged by the SOA operation "generateDesignContext" to perform proximity search of realized Design Components. The result of the proximity search will then be added to the product context. The default value is 0, which means that the proximity search will find Design Components which bounding boxes touch those of the input ones.

preference.name: CPMarketingBriefRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for CPMarketingBriefRevision objects.

preference.name: CPThemeBoardRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for CPThemeBoardRevision objects.

preference.name: Cfg0AvailabilityMatrixLoadCount
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of Families for which availability information can be loaded in one server call. A valid value can be any integer greater than zero. The default value is 30.

preference.name: Cfg0CompoundOptionValueMemberTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of member option values that a Compound Option Value can hold. Valid Values: Accepts values in the format CompoundOptionValue::OptionValue.

preference.name: Cfg0ConfigurationColumnPropertiesWidth
preference.preference_description: This is an internal preference.

preference.name: Cfg0ConfigurationRetentionPeriod
preference.preference_description: (Deprecated)Defines the time interval in seconds by which the Configurator data cache (e.g. for variant options and constraint rules) has to age before the system considers a refresh. This limits the frequency of updating the Configurator data cache to a maximum of once in this interval.

preference.name: Cfg0ConfigurationViewDisplayColumn
preference.preference_description: (Deprecated) Specifies if only the ID column, or only the Name column is to be displayed in the "Variant Configuration" view in the Product Configurator application. Valid values are "NameOnly" or "IDOnly" (default value). Values specified in this preference are case insensitive.

preference.name: Cfg0ConfiguratorServerHost
preference.preference_description: Defines the URL of the Centralized Configurator server host.

preference.name: Cfg0ConfiguratorServerPort
preference.preference_description: Defines the port for Centralized Configurator server.

preference.name: Cfg0CreateVariantRuleType
preference.preference_description: Specifies the type of Variant Rule object that will be created in Product Configurator based variant configuration. The specified value must be be a valid Variant Rule type or its sub-type. The Valid Values: - VariantRule: When user saves a variant configuration from Product Configurator Variant Configuration view or Saved Variant Rules view, an instance of Variant Rule will be created. This is the default value. - Cfg0VariantCriteria: When user saves a variant configuration from Product Configurator Variant Configuration view or Saved Variant Rules view, an instance of Variant Criteria (Cfg0VariantCriteria) will be created.

preference.name: Cfg0DefaultLoadCount
preference.preference_description: Defines the initial number of search results to be returned in one page. This number may increase for subsequent pages based on the value of the Cfg0DefaultLoadCountIncreaseRate preference.

preference.name: Cfg0DefaultLoadCountIncreaseRate
preference.preference_description: Defines the increase in the number of search results displayed in one page compared to the one in the previous page. The number of values for the first page is controlled by the "Cfg0DefaultLoadCount" preference. The value indicates a percentage: * less than 100: less results are displayed (in the given percentage) * 100: the number of displayed results is the same * more than 100: more results are displayed (in the given percentage).

preference.name: Cfg0DefaultRuleDateForContent
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default rule date mode value for the configurator views in Content applications like 4G Designer and Structure manager application. The Valid Values: -Latest= The variability/rules will be loaded as of the current system date and time for the configurator context. -System Default= The variability will be loaded as of the current date and default time (i.e. midnight + offset) for the configurator context. This is the default value -No Rule Date= No rule date will bring all the variability/rules data currently saved in the system for the configurator context. No rule date always considers the latest and the greatest from the system NOTE: If we set Cfg0DefaultRuleDateForContent value to No Rule Date, there are chances of performance degradation.

preference.name: Cfg0DefaultRuleDateForPCA
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default rule date mode value in the Product Configurator application. The Valid Values: -Latest = The variability/rules will be loaded as of the current system date and time for the configurator context.This is the default value -No Rule Date = No rule date will bring all the variability/rules data currently saved in the system for the configurator context. No rule date always considers the latest and the greatest from the system -System Default = The variability will be loaded as of the current date and default time (i.e. midnight + offset) for the configurator context.

preference.name: Cfg0DefaultValidationMode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default mode used to validate the configuration expression in the configuration view of the Product Configurator application. The Valid Values: - Overlay: allows users to select explicitly or to imply more than one feature of the family. This is the default value. - Order: forces users to explicitly select or to imply no more than a single feature of the family.

preference.name: Cfg0EnableFreeFormRuleSupport
preference.preference_description: Enables or disables authoring of new Free-form Rules and editing of Free-form Expression in the Product Configurator application. The Valid Values: -true: Enables creation of Free-form rule. -false:Disables creation of Free-form rule. This is the default value.

preference.name: Cfg0EnableSummarizedByForModelsInAW
preference.preference_description: Enable users to browse Summarized By section for Product Model. This is an internal preference and will be deprecated once Tc13.3 release becomes the minimum supported platform for Active Workspace. Do not modify this preference manually.

preference.name: Cfg0EnableValidateAndSaveConfigObj
preference.preference_description: Enables the validation of the configurator rules and variant expressions in the Product Configurator. If enabled then on the completion of the save operation Product Configurator would validate the configurator rules and expressions otherwise it would do nothing. The Valid Values: -true: Performs the validation after the save operation. This is the default value. -false: Performs only the save operation.

preference.name: Cfg0EnableVariabilityBrowsingInAW
preference.preference_description: Enable users to browse the Variability in Active Workspace. This is an internal preference and will be deprecated once Tc13.2 release becomes the minimum supported platform for Active Workspace. Do not modify this preference manually.

preference.name: Cfg0EnableVariantsInAW
preference.preference_description: Enable users to browse the Variant Rules in Active Workspace. This is an internal preference and will be deprecated once Tc13.3 release becomes the minimum supported platform for Active Workspace. Do not modify this preference manually.

preference.name: Cfg0LoadExpressionInfoForVR
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether only expressions should be loaded ignoring the configuration session information while loading the Variant Rule or Variant Criteria in the configuration view. The Valid Values: -true: While loading the variant rule in configuration view, do not load the configuration session information along with expressions.This is the default value. -false:While loading the variant rule in configuration view, load the configuration session information along with expressions.

preference.name: Cfg0MinimumCacheRetentionPeriod
preference.preference_description: (Deprecated)Defines the time interval in seconds by which the Configurator data cache (e.g. for variant options and constraint rules) has to age before the system considers a refresh. This limits the frequency of updating the Configurator data cache to a maximum of once in this interval. This preference has been deprecated, use Cfg0ConfigurationRetentionPeriod instead.

preference.preference_description: This is an internal preference.

preference.name: Cfg0ProductItem_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: This is an internal preference.

preference.name: Cfg0PublicKey
preference.preference_description: Defines the public key for encrypting the request. Configurator constraint solver expects the input requests to be encrypted with the value provided in this preference.

preference.name: Cfg0RuleDateOffset
preference.preference_description: By default the Configurator Perspective uses the Revision Rule specified with preference "Cfg0DefaultRevisionRule". The system automatically sets a Rule Date for this Revision Rule. This Preference "Cfg0RuleDateOffset" specifies the offset (in seconds) to add to last midnight when setting this Rule Date. If the offset is 0 (the default value for this preference) the Rule Date will be set to today 12:00 AM. If a preference value is 21600 then the Rule Date is set to today 06:00 AM (midnight + 21600 seconds).If the offset calculation returns a future time or a time that is more than 24 h in the past the system will subtract or add days until the calculated time is less than 24 h ago.

preference.name: DesignContextPreciseRevRule.Alpha Best_App.PRECISE

Please make sure that a stripped down version of Revision Rule exists and is used for creating an Appearance Set. Here in this example "Alpha Best_App" is a stripped down version of revision Rule "Alpha Best", which has all clauses of "Alpha Best" other than the "Precise" clause. Syntax: DesignContextPreciseRevRule.<RuleName>.Suffix. Supported suffix constants are: ".PRECISE"

preference.name: DesignContext_ItemID_Revision_Query_lookup_string

The default search used by DesignContext is "Item Revision...", which corresponds to the lookup string "k_find_itemrevision_name". The Saved Query corresponding to this string is looked up from TC_ROOT/lang/textserver/<language>/qry_text_locale.xml file. If the User desires to use a separate Query for this purpose, the user should ensure that the query corresponds to the String defined for the following Preference and that it contains entries for "ItemID" and "Revision".

preference.name: DesignContext_Type_Name_Query_lookup_string
preference.preference_description: This is used for defining the look-up string corresponding to the saved query to find - EngChange Revisions (if "PortalDesignContextECObject.TYPE" defines a type other than an ItemRevision type), - Variant rules referenced on QPL search indexes, and/or - Workflow processes by "Type" and "Name" entries. The default search used by DesignContext is "General...", which corresponds to the lookup string "k_find_general_name". The Saved Query corresponding to this string is looked up from TC_ROOT/lang/textserver/<language>/qry_text_locale.xml file. If the User desires to use a separate Query for this purpose, the user should ensure that the query corresponds to the String defined for the following Preference and that it contains entries for "Type" and "Name".

preference.preference_description:
By default, the "MyTeamcenter" application shows preview images (jpeg, png and bmp formats) in the Preview area of the Summary tab. Enabling the thumbnail functionality to view these preview images is not needed.
This preference enables the thumbnails functionality, which converts all images associated with Item Revisions to small thumbnail images that are displayed in the Preview area of the Summary tab, in the header of the Summary page, and in the search results. Administrators must perform multiple configurations to enable thumbnails functionality (c.f. the "Getting Started with Document Management" chapter in the technical documentation). preference.name: GDEOcc_display_instance_num_for_types
preference.preference_description: Determines which GDE types an instance number on the GDEOccurrence. (Some, but not all, GDEOccurrence objects related to interfaces require the display of the instance numbers.) The GDE types specified in this preference will display in a structure with an instance number included with the GDEOccurrence title and name. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each value must be a valid Teamcenter GDE type. KBL (KabelBaumListe - wire harness description list) is a standard for wiring models that enhances the STEP AP212 model. The KBL object model provides high-level components that represent wires, harnesses, and parts in a vehicle that hosts the harness. This model is a subset of AP212 model and models represent wire harness data in a similar way. If KBL functionality has been installed, the following KBL type names must be defined. HRN_Core HRN_Cavity HRN_Slot

This preference is added as part of GRDVA Phase 3 project. By default, this is activated. This is a Site preference.

preference.name: GMS_UID_mapping_dbname_index
preference.preference_description: Lists the databases for remote Teamcenter Enterprise sites involved in data exchange. The indices of the databases specified are used for generating unique object UIDs in PLM XML. Valid Values: Enter values as instance-name:dbname1, dbname2, for example, svli60:sum501a. To determine these values, search the Teamcenter Enterprise fmsmaster.xml file for the accesson id value, for example, accesson id = "rhgtpqksvli60sum501a-aaG ". Split this value as follows:Drop the last three characters (aaG). In the remaining string, record the last eight characters (ignore any hyphens) as the dbname value, for this example, sum501a.Record the next six characters as the instance name, for this example, svli60.

preference.name: GMS_UID_mapping_remote_site_index
