preference.name: ITEM_autopublish
preference.preference_description: Enables or suppresses the automatic publication of all newly created items and the automatic republication of items when the item ID is modified. Newly created items are published to the ODS site specified by the ITEM_autopublish_sites site preference.When an existing item ID is modified, it is republished only if it is already currently published and then only to the ODS sites to which it has already been published. The ITEM_autopublish_sites site preference does not determine which ODS site to use for republication. Valid Values: TRUE - Enables the automatic publication of all newly created items and the automatic republication of items when the item ID is modified. FALSE - Suppresses the automatic publication of all newly created items and the automatic republication of items when the item ID is modified.

preference.name: ITEM_autopublish_ignore_errors
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to ignore publication errors detected during automatic publication. When a publication error is detected, any item creations/modifications known to be successful at that point are retained; failed items can be published manually at your convenience. This preference requires the ITEM_autopublish site preference to be set.Errors caused by invalid ODS site preference settings are ignored by this preference.Errors due to item creation or modification are not covered by this preference; the preference applies only to publication errors. Valid Values: TRUE - When automatic publishing is enabled via the ITEM_autopublish site preference, ignores publication errors detected during automatic publication. FALSE - When automatic publishing is enabled via the ITEM_autopublish site preference, publication errors prompt the system to cancel the item creation or modification.

preference.name: ITEM_autopublish_sites
preference.preference_description: Defines the ODS site to which newly created items are published. This preference requires the ITEM_autopublish site preference to be set. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a valid ODS site.

preference.name: ITEM_do_not_export_relation_if_type_excluded
preference.preference_description: When a relation type is excluded during an export/import operation, the relation object itself is exported by default but the secondary object is not. During import, the relation type as stored in the relation object is checked to make sure it exists and if the relation type is missing, the import operation cannot proceed. To avoid the export of relation objects when the relation type is excluded, set this preference to the name of the relation types. Although this may include pre-defined relation types such as IMAN_reference, this preference would be normally used for custom relation types that are not defined at remote sites. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ITEM_relation_types_update_lmd
preference.preference_description: Determines which relation types cause the update of the last modification date of the parent object when the secondary object of a class dataset or form is modified, or if the relation is added/removed from the parent object. If the relation is added/removed, the last modification date of the parent object is updated regardless of the class of the secondary object. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter relation. Excepting the IMAN_RES_audit and IMAN_RES_checkout relations, which are not valid values for this preference.

preference.name: JT_File_Excluded_Refsets
preference.preference_description:
Specifies names of reference sets you do not want Structure Manager viewer to load. See preference JT_File_Priority_Refsets for example of valid values.
For Lifecycle Visualization and/or standalone viewer application involving Teamcenter 8 or later created DirectModel datasets, this preference is only applicable when just the dataset itself loaded into viewer (not applicable for structures/assemblies loaded in viewer).

preference.name: JT_File_OverrideChildren_Refsets
preference.preference_description:
Specify strings used to name monolithic DirectModel datasets attached to assembly nodes representing end items, like supplier built assemblies, that you do not want to expand. As you expand the levels of the structure, nodes containing datasets conforming to this naming convention do not expand. Instead, the viewer uses the monolithic JT files as the stand-in to display the assembly content.
Valid values: Strings used for reference set names such as monolithic or $monolithic. To match the ends of names, start the string with an ""*"". For example, ""*-mono"" matches all file names that end with ""-mono"".
Note, this preference can have a major impact on visualization performance. It should be leveraged when monolithic DirectModel datasets are available to represent subassemblies.

preference.name: JT_File_Priority_Refsets
preference.preference_description:
Determines the load order of NX reference sets contained within DirectModel files. NX reference sets enable you to display different geometry configurations within the context of a single assembly. For the Lifecycle Viewer and/or standalone viewer application to use the reference set loading order specified with this preference, select the Teamcenter Reference Set settings take precedence check box in the Lifecycle Viewer and/or standalone viewer application 3D Loader Preferences.
DirectModel support of NX reference sets can take two forms:
DirectModel datasets created prior to Teamcenter 8, which consist of multiple JT files named according to the available reference sets
DirectModel datasets created using Teamcenter 8 or later, which may consist of a single JT file that contains all of the information necessary to define the geometry configurations for each reference set
Valid Values: For DirectModel datasets created using Teamcenter 8 or later: * $EMPTY * $ENTIREPART * $LASTSAVED * $MODEL * [user-defined]
For DirectModel datasets created prior to Teamcenter 8: * EMPTY * ENTIREPART * LASTSAVED * MODEL * [user-defined]
For a mixture of DirectModel datasets created using different releases: * $EMPTY * EMPTY * $ENTIREPART * ENTIREPART * $LASTSAVED * LASTSAVED * $MODEL * MODEL * [user-defined]

preference.name: LHN_Applications_List
preference.preference_description: Defines the applications displayed in the Left Hand Navigation (LHN) pane. The format of values for this preference is "perspectiveId:DisplayMode". For example, for setting the "My Teamcenter" perspective as primary and the "Getting Started" perspective as secondary, the preference values would be: com.teamcenter.rac.ui.perspectives.navigatorPerspective:primary com.teamcenter.rac.gettingstarted.GettingStartedPerspective:secondary If any conflict is found in the preference values then that value will be skipped. The preference does not have any value by default, which means that all applications are loaded as default in Teamcenter. If the value is "EMPTY", no application is displayed in the LHN. After modifying the preference, the rich client needs to be restarted. Preference values are only to be configured by a system administrator.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckDynamicIDICProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of BOM Line properties used by accountability check dynamic equivalence criteria when searching for equivalent BOM Lines. By default the BOM Line property "bl_item_item_id" is always included in dynamic equivalence criteria, unless certain structure search friendly properties are provided: - internal BOM Line properties pointing to Occurrence Note - compound property on a Form - property on an Item type, description or name ( e.g. "bl_item_object_type" ) - property on an Item Revision type, description or name ( e.g. "bl_rev_object_name") If none of these is available, the property "bl_item_item_id" will be used in conjunction with any other specified properties. The first cacheless(structure) search property in the preference is used as an initial property to collect the BOM Lines on which the other properties are evaluated. Empty property values are not considered as equal during compare. An example for a value to search for absolute transformations, the entry "bl_plmxml_abs_xform" can be added.

The properties are listed for "Revised Lines" and "Changed Lines" in Excel in the "Additional Properties" column, and in "AdditionalProperties UserData" elements in the XML. Valid values are property internal names for a BOM Line.

preference.name: MECTRevEffectivityChildLineCompareProperties

The properties are compared for all children of "Revised Lines" and listed if they are different. They appear as new rows with "Modified Properties" of "Changed Lines" in the excel, and in "AdditionalProperties UserData" elements in the XML. Valid values are property internal names for a BOM Line.

preference.name: MECTRevEffectivityDetailsProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties to be compared on Revised Lines in addition to "bl_rev_item_revision_id" (Revision), "bl_rev_last_release_status" (Release Status), and "bl_revision_effectivity" (Revision Effectivity). If the values are different, the property is listed in the "Change Tracker Details" panel, in the "Change Tracker Revision Details Report", and in the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML. In the "Change Tracker Details" panel, properties of child lines are also compared. Valid values are property internal names for a BOM Line.

preference.name: MECTRevEffectivityLineIdentificationProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties in addition to "bl_indented_title" (BOM Line) to include for identifying every revised and changed line in the "Change Tracker Revision Details Report" and in the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML. The properties are listed in the "Revised Lines" and "Changed Lines" columns in the Excel file, and in "LineIdentificationProperties UserData" elements in the delta XML. Valid values are property internal names for a BOM Line.

preference.name: MEConfiguringStructuresMode
preference.preference_description: Defines what configuring structures mode is used when loading structures into Manufacturing Process Planner. By default, the loaded composition structures (for example, processes) are only configured by their related loaded BOM structures. Examples of related structures are: Associated product and plant of a process which were loaded together per the MSE_load_related_product_process_plant preference.Structures contained in a loaded collaboration context. Valid Values: AllToAll - All loaded BOM structures configure all loaded composition structures. RelatedStructuresOnly - Only the product or plant structures related to a specific process structure configure it. Examples of related structures are:Associated product and plant of a process that were loaded together per the MSE_load_related_product_process_plant preference.Structures contained in a loaded collaboration context configure processes from the same collaboration context.

preference.name: MEEffectivityAssignmentMode
preference.preference_description: Defines the assignment behavior from Engineering BOM (EBOM) to Manufacturing BOM (MBOM), for the BOMLine property "bl_occ_effectivity". Valid Values: * 0 (default value): if the source EBOM line has an occurrence effectivity defined, the occurrence effectivity of the source line is assigned to the target line; otherwise, an empty occurrence effectivity is assigned to the target. * 1: if the source EBOM line has an occurrence effectivity defined, the occurrence effectivity of the source line is assigned to the target line; otherwise, the system finds the source line's closest parent which has an occurrence effectivity and assigns that to the target line. Note that when this preference is set to true, the source line and target line may not have the same occurrence effectivity, and an alignment check or accountability check may detect differences between the two lines for property "bl_occ_effectivity". * 2: the net effectivity of the source EBOM line is computed and assigned to the target MBOM line. Note that when this preference is set to 1 or 2, the source line and target line may not have the same occurrence effectivity, and an alignment check or accountability check may detect differences between the two lines for property "bl_occ_effectivity".

preference.name: NX0MotionSim_saveas_pattern
preference.preference_description:
Defines the pattern string of the name of new NX0MotionSim dataset object during a "Save As" operation. The value may contain text and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the "${PropertyName}" format, where "PropertyName" is either "ItemID", "RevisionID" or "UserText". The existing dataset name is expected to match this pattern. If the existing dataset name does not match the pattern, the new dataset name will not follow this pattern. Once an original dataset name is matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the "${ItemID}" and "${RevisionID}" with the new revision and Item ID in the pattern, and all occurrences of "${UserData}" with whatever text they matched in the original name. As a result, the new name is used for saving the new dataset.
Let us consider the example of a value "${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID}" where: * "${UserText}" is intended to be the name of the dataset, and * the minus sign is literal text. Suppose a user is saving the Item Revision "001234/B" to the Item Revision "002345/A". Since "${UserText}" in the pattern matches any string, a dataset of name "fea-001234/B" or "NX0MotionSim-001234/B" would also match the pattern. However, a dataset of name "NX0MotionSim_001234/B" would not match the pattern because the minus sign is required. Likewise, a dataset of name "NX0MotionSim-001235/B" would not match the pattern because the Item ID is incorrect. Using the example above, the dataset would be saved as "NX0MotionSim-002345/A".

The pattern {3,1} specifies priority-3 for piece parts and priority-1 for assemblies where 3-High, 2-Medium, 1-Low.

preference.name: PIE_allow_import_with_different_sml
preference.preference_description: Controls the import behavior when the site master language of the exporting site does not match that of the importing site. By default, if the site master language in the .xml file does not match the importing site's site master language, the PLM XML import is allowed. To deny the import, set the preference value to false. Valid Values: True - Allows PLM XML import if the site master language in the .xml file does not match the importing site's site master language. False - Prohibits PLM XML import if the site master language in the .xml file does not match the importing site's site master language.

preference.name: PLMXML_IC_Delta_export_transfermodes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of transfer modes that can be used for incremental change (IC) based PLM XML exports and the mode of export (Delta or Full) to use with each transfer mode. When a user selects any of the listed transfer modes when performing a PLM XML export, instead of full assembly, only the objects that are directly/indirectly affected by IC objects along with the object's parental hierarchy and descendants are exported. Both the Delta and Full modes initiate the export of ICs, but the Delta mode filters out the lines that are not affected by ICs, whereas the Full mode does no filtering. Valid Values: Multiple strings containing a transfer mode name and the export mode separated by a colon, for example: ICDeltaExportDefault:Delta The name can be any transfer mode for IC-based delta export that includes the basic minimum closure rules required for IC-based delta export to work properly. The export mode valid values are Delta or Full.

preference.name: PLMXML_export_key_properties
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the multifield key properties defined for objects are included in the PLM XML export file. If your Teamcenter environment does not have objects that can have duplicate item_id attributes (multifield key properties), you may set this preference to FALSE. Valid Values: true - All the multifield key properties for exported objects are included in the PLM XML export file. false - Only a single key property (item_id) for exported object is included in the PLM XML export file.

preference.name: PLMXML_export_supported_types
preference.preference_description: This preference contains the list of types which are supported for PLM XML export. The purpose of this preference is to support async for vertical products. If some unsupported type is added, the behavior is undefined. This preference should not be modified by end user.

preference.name: PLMXML_import_default_password
preference.preference_description: Defines the encrypted password used while importing a new user using PLM XML. The password must be an encrypted value generated by utility "install -encryptpwf". For security reasons, PLM XML does not export passwords to XML files. By default, during import, new users are created with the user name and password the same. If strong password preferences are set at the target site, importing users may fail. If your site uses strong password rules, define the value of this preference with a password that satisfies your site's rules. The system imports all user objects with the password defined by this preference. Each new user should change their password upon initial logon. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a encrypted password that meets the importing site's password rules.

preference.name: PLMXML_log_file_content
preference.preference_description: Determines the amount of information added to the PLM XML translation log. During large PLM XML translations, full logging can consume significant resources and generates a large memory footprint. Optimize performance by tuning the log file behavior through this preference. The PLM XML translation log is always generated, enabling analysis of translation performance, and signaling you when the translation is complete. The minimum amount of information you can tune the system to provide is the translation header and a list of any errors generated. Valid Values: basic - Logs the translation header and a list of any errors generated. This setting generates the least overhead for translation reporting. summary - Logs the translation header, summary, warnings, and a list of any errors generated. detailed - Logs the translation header, summary, warning, errors, and a closure rule analysis report. This setting generates the most overhead for translation reporting.

preference.name: PLMXML_pre_expand_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Sets batch size for each single expansion of a structure prior to running the PLM XML expand operation. Structures that are a target for export can be fully expanded prior to their export step, which provides a performance improvement. However, there are memory concerns with large structures whereby a full expansion may take more than the available memory of the system. This preference sets a limit. Values must be greater than 0. The smaller the batch size, the more likely that the value set in the PLMXML_pre_expand_max_line_limit preference will not be exceeded but at the cost of less performance gain. Valid Values: Accepts any integer value greater than 0.

preference.name: PLMXML_pre_expand_bop
preference.preference_description: Determines if the pre-expand functionality is run prior to a PLMXML expand operation. If the value of the PLMXML_pre_expand_max_line_limit preference is 0 and this preference value is true, the pre-expansion will happen (the PLMXML_pre_expand_batch_size preference will be set to its maximum value and the value of the PLMXML_pre_expand_max_line_limit preference will be disregarded).

preference.name: PLMXML_pre_expand_max_line_limit
preference.preference_description: Sets the maximum number of lines in a structure that are to be expanded prior to running the PLM XML expand operation. Structures that are a target for export can be fully expanded prior to their export step, which provides a performance improvement. However, there are memory concerns with large structures whereby a full expansion may take more than the available memory of the system. This preference sets a limit. Valid Values: 0 - No lines are pre-expanded. -1 - There is no limit on the number of lines to pre-expand.

preference.name: RDV_default_variant_condition
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default variant condition for NULL Variant Projects. Valid values are under the format "ItemInfo:OptionName:OptionValue", where: * In a non-MFK (Multifield key) environment, "ItemInfo" is the ID of any item that exists in the database (e.g. "GMC00723:Color:Red"). * In an MFK environment, "ItemInfo" is the key of any item which uniquely identifies the item (e.g. "item_id=GMC00723,object_name=topitem,object_type=Item:Color:Red"). The key is a delimited string which contains name/value pairs of item attributes usually of the form attr1=value1,attr2=value2.... etc, where attr1, attr2 are property internal names (e.g. "item_id=GMC00723,object_name=topitem,object_type=Item"). To include a delimiter character (e.g. ',' or '=') in a key, it should be escaped by a backslash character ('\'). E.g.: * if the item ID contains an equals sign (123=456), the key string would be: "item_id=123\=456,object_type=Document". * if the item ID contains a backslash (123\456), the key string would be: "item_id=123\456,object_type=Document".

preference.name: RDV_show_lou_prop

The user can then add any of these columns by right-clicking and choosing Insert Column from the list. Teamcenter shows the properties of the configured part solutions of an architecture breakdown element (ABE), as a comma-separated string on the ABE itself. Valid Values: Any valid property name prefixed with bl_lou_.

preference.preference_description: Determines whether rule checks and variability are evaluated in the variants overlay only (VOO) analysis when using RDV. Valid Values: TRUE - Expands conditions into True Availability statements. May slow VOO analysis. FALSE - Conditions are not expanded.

preference.name: RDV_year_lov_name
preference.preference_description: For Global RDV Automation default is Usage Years

preference.name: REQUESTOBJECT_object_columns_shown

preference.name: REQ_CompareSpecificationHistory
preference.preference_description:
Controls if the user can compare the Requirement Specification history in Active Workspace client. The default value is true. To view the Requirement Specification history, "REQ_Microservice_Installed" also needs to be set to true.
Valid Values: * true: User will be able to see Requirement Specification history. * false: User will not be able to see Requirement Specification history.

preference.name: REQ_WordToHTMLTranslatorUsingLoggedInUser
preference.preference_description: Controls if the login user will be used to run the word to HTML conversion utility, the default is true. * true: the login user will be the user that runs the word to HTML conversion utility * false: the user designated during the installation will be the user that runs the word to HMTL conversion utility

preference.name: REQ_default_object_template
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the default object template. It drives the data to be exported per object during export to word operation.

preference.name: REQ_default_spec_template_for_export
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the default specification template. It drives the overall layout of the document generated during export to word operation.

preference.name: REQ_default_spec_template_for_view
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the default specification template. It drives the overall layout of the document generated during view/edit operation.

preference.name: REQ_exporttoword_skip_childspecification
preference.preference_description: Controls the behavior of nested Specifications during "Export to MSWord" operations. Valid Values: * true: Nested Specifications and their sub-trees are exported to the MSWord document. * false: Nested Specifications and their sub-trees are not exported to the MSWord document. This is the default value.

preference.name: REQ_import_keywords

preference.name: RICH_CLIENT_MARKER_ID

The URL created for rich client should be of the format http://web_server:port/cgi-bin/portal?-s=TCSession&-o=ObjectUID&-sid=serverMarker. The "serverMarker" in the example is read from RICH_CLIENT_MARKER_ID preference.

preference.name: TCAutomateAndLinkErrorInsteadOfWarning
preference.preference_description: Currently, automateAndLink does not return any error ( gives a warning) when there is an issue. This by design behavior causing issue in bulk object creation context. When preference value is set to true, automateAndLink extension returns error if there is an error from this extension, othewise no error is returned( existing behavior). In bulk object creation context, when error is returned (preference value set to true) from this extension, object creation will be rolled back. Let's take an example of 10 objects bulk creation process. If 1 object creation fails due to automateAndLink when this preference is set to true and rest has no issue, 9 objects will be created. When this prefrence is set to "false", 10 objects will be created.

preference.name: TCCheckoutReserveOnly
preference.preference_description: Specifies for which business objects a restore copy is not created during checkout.If the business object supports sequences, a new sequence is not created during checkout. In this case, if the checkout is canceled, the business object's contents are not restored to their original values. Sequences are subrevisions of a business object that document the content of a revision during its evolution. Checking out a business object increments the sequence ID. You cannot delete the Item value from the object list for this preference. If any type of item revision is specified with this preference, sequences are disabled for that item revision type. The Undo Checkout action does not discard changes made after the item revision is checked out. You can display a warning message for object version changes without user input.For information, see the TCCheckoutReserveOnlyWarningNeeded preference. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a business object that can be checked in and out.

preference.name: TCCheckoutReserveOnlyWarningNeeded
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to display a warning message for Business Objects that does not support Cancel Checkout. Valid Values: * false: Does not display a warning message. This is the default value. * true: Displays a warning message.

preference.name: TCDefaultKeepLimit
preference.preference_description: Determines the number of sequences the system maintains as an Item revision is checked in and out of the database. Sequences are subrevisions of item revisions that document the content of a revision during its evolution. Checking out an Item revision increments the sequence ID. At logon, the system automatically removes the oldest sequence when the limit specified with this preference is reached. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a single, positive integer.

preference.name: TCDefaultKeepLimitByType
preference.preference_description: Determines the number of sequences the system maintains for the specified business object as it is checked in and out of the database. Sequences are subrevisions of a business object that document the content of a revision during its evolution. Checking out a business object increments the sequence ID. At checkin, the system automatically removes the oldest sequence when the limit specified with this preference is reached. When an item revision is checked out, a new sequence is created. Therefore, when the number of item revisions sequences is defined as 1, the system keeps two versions during checkout. When the object is checked in, the system purges sequences to comply with the keep limit. Valid Values: Accepts multiple string pairs as values. Each string must be a space-delineated pair consisting of a valid business object and a positive integer more than zero. For example: ItemRevision 3

preference.name: TC_CFG_PRODUCTS_USE_VARIABILITY
preference.preference_description:
Manually enforces or disables the evaluation of variability allocation statements if they exist for a given item revision. Variability allocation statements allow Teamcenter to import only some of the values of a variant option family in a product. If you leave this preference unset, Teamcenter dynamically determines this configuration setting. The performance of this dynamic configuration is impacted by the value set for the PortalDesignContextProductItemQuery preference. You can view and manage variability allocation statements with the Product Configurator or Platform Designer applications. Technically, variability allocation statements are specialized VariantExpression objects using the corresponding operator code, for example, PS_variant_operator_assy_uses+BOM_variant_op_rhs_is_string = 1002. For more information about these objects, see the $TC_INCLUDE/bom/bom_tokens.h file. If an item revision has variability allocation statements and their evaluation is not disabled, the Teamcenter variant configurators recognize only explicitly allocated variant option values. Otherwise, they recognize all variant option values that exist on the declared variant option family revision.Setting this preference is recommended but not required. If you are unsure, set this preference to TRUE. Valid Values:
Effect on classic variant Effect on item Effect on item revisions configurator initialization revisions with variability without variability allocations Preference value allocation statements statements
TRUE No database query is executed Teamcenetr configurators Teamcenter configurators when initializing a Teamcenter recognize only allocated recognize all variant or effectivity variant or effectivity variant or effectivity option values of all declared option configurator configuration option families values
FALSE No database query is executed Teamcenter configurators recognize Teamcenter configurators recognize when initializing a classic all variant or effectivity configuration all variant or effectivity option variant configurator. option values of declared option values of all declared option families. families
UNSET A database query is executed Teamcenter configurators recognize Teamcenter configurators recognize once when initializing a only allocated variant or effectivity all variant or effectivity option Teamcenter configurator(variant configuration option values. values of all declared option or effectivity). If at least one families. product item exists with variability allocation statements,the system behaves as if set to TRUE,otherwise it behaves as if set to FALSE

preference.name: TC_NX_UGALTREP_create_pattern
preference.preference_description:
Defines the pattern string of the names of new UGALTREP dataset objects during a "create" operation. Values may contain text, incremental numbering format and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID or RevisionID. The incremental numbering format will consist of two values separated by a colon: * The first value is the start number (typically '1'). * The second value is the number of digits to show. If the number of digits specified is more than the number of digits in the start value, the value will be padded with zeros on the left.
Example: Let us consider the preference value "alt${1:3}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID}". Suppose a user is creating item revision 001234/A. new altrep dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern. The new altrep dataset would be created as "alt001-001234/A".

preference.name: TC_NX_UGPART_create_pam_pattern
preference.preference_description:
Defines the pattern string of the names of new UGPART dataset objects during a "create" operation. When user selects physical architecture modeler(pam)tab and creates a pam part, this pattern string will be used to create the dataset name. Values may contain text, incremental numbering format and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID or RevisionID. The incremental numbering format will consist of two values separated by a colon: * The first value is the start number (typically '1'). * The second value is the number of digits to show. If the number of digits specified is more than the number of digits in the start value, then the value will be padded with zeros on the left.
Example: Let us consider the preference value "pam${1:3}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID}",pam stands for physical architecture modeler. Suppose a user is creating item revision 001234/A. new UGPART dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern. The new UGPART dataset would be created as "pam001-001234/A".

preference.name: TC_NX_UGPART_create_pattern
preference.preference_description:
Defines the pattern string of the names of new UGPART dataset objects during a "create" operation. Values may contain text, incremental numbering format and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID or RevisionID. The incremental numbering format will consist of two values separated by a colon: * The first value is the start number (typically '1'). * The second value is the number of digits to show. If the number of digits specified is more than the number of digits in the start value, then the value will be padded with zeros on the left.
Example: Let us consider the preference value "dwg${1:3}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID}". Suppose a user is creating item revision 001234/A. new UGPART dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern. The new UGPART dataset would be created as "dwg001-001234/A".

preference.name: TC_NX_UGPART_create_pattern_man
preference.preference_description:
Defines the pattern string of the names of new UGPART manifestation dataset objects during a "create" operation. Values may contain text, incremental numbering format and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID or RevisionID. The incremental numbering format will consist of two values separated by a colon: * The first value is the start number (typically '1'). * The second value is the number of digits to show. If the number of digits specified is more than the number of digits in the start value, then the value will be padded with zeros on the left.
Example: Let us consider the preference value "man${1:3}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID}". Suppose a user is creating item revision 001234/A. The new manifestation dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern. The new manifestation dataset would be created as "man001-001234/A".

preference.name: TC_ReviseTogether

When user revises an Item Revision side object with intention to revise together its related Drawing Revision (as defined through BMIDE setting of the Deep Copy rule), the value of TC_ReviseTogether indicates if performing revise together on the dataset level is necessary (true) or not (false). When selecting a Drawing Revision and revising it, both TC_DrawingOf and TC_DrawingUsing relations are propagated regardless if TC_ReviseTogether is set to true or false. It is necessary to create a Deep Copy Rule through BMIDE to revise together an Item Revision and its Drawing Revision. Here is an example of the parameters for such a Deep Copy Rule as defined in BMIDE: Operation Type : Revise Target Type : ItemRevision Relation Type : TC_DrawingOf Object Type : Drawing Revision Condition : isTrue Action : ReviseAndRelateToLatest Is Target Primary : false Copy Properties on Relation : true Required : true Secured : false

preference.name: TC_aqa_date_range
preference.preference_description: Several tuning parameters used when auditing the querying of appearances and checking appearances based on the audit statistics. The statistics take the form of histograms along the lines of "N queries have been performed (on a given AppearanceRoot) for a date between D1 and D2 and/or a unit-no between U1 and U2". The width of each histogram block (D2-D1) and (U2-U1) is specified by TC_aqa_date_range and TC_aqa_unit_no_range.

preference.name: TC_aqa_default_validation_worthiness_threshold

preference.name: TC_aqa_freshness_factor
preference.preference_description: After checking appearances, the validationWorthiness (adjusted for staleness) is increased by the freshness factor.

preference.name: TC_aqa_initial_validation_worthiness
preference.preference_description: Finding out which haven't been checked recently is done by using the ApprQueryAudit's lastWorthinessUpdateDate and validationWorthiness. When such an object is created, its lastWorthinessUpdateDate is set to its creation-date and its validationWorthiness is given an initial value.

preference.name: TC_aqa_minimum_validation_worthiness_threshold
preference.preference_description: Minimum validation worthiness threshold.

preference.name: TC_aqa_staleness_factor
preference.preference_description: Deciding which appearances to check is along the lines of "check those which have been queried most, and most recently, and which haven't been checked recently". Finding out which have been queried most is a simple matter of looking for the largest values of N, adjustment for "most recently" is done by dividing the stored value of N by the staleness decay factor once for every day since N was last incremented (so that the older the audit, the less interesting it is).

preference.name: TC_aqa_unit_no_range
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_aqa_validation_worthiness_threshold_adjustment
preference.preference_description: if it finds none, then it adjusts the threshold down by multiplying by the threshold adjustment and repeats the search.

preference.name: TC_cms_relation_optset_map
preference.preference_description: Controls mapping of Teamcenter relation names to the TC XML transfer option sets. Set this preference only when you want to control the relations that are included or excluded when an object is replicated.Multi-Site Collaboration allows you to include or exclude relations during transfers. During TC XML transfers, Multi-Site maps the user supplied relations to the corresponding TC XML transfer option set entry using the name-value pairs set by this preference.Use this preference to include or exclude relation objects during data_share or data_sync utility transactions that use the -low_level argument (TC XML transfers). Valid Values: One or more name-value pair strings, for example:IMAN_rendering,opt_rel_renderingThe name must be a valid Teamcenter relation, and the value must be a valid TC XML transfer options set entry.

preference.name: TC_config_condition_max_normalization_effort
preference.preference_description: Selects the strategy for normalizing configuration expressions such as variant conditions. This nornalization process is executed as part of saving the expression and automatically transforms the configuration expression into one or more Normal Forms (Conjunctive Normal Form - CNF or Disjunctive Normal Form - DNF). A CNF based normalization strategy is used if the estimated number of DNF terms (without removing redundancy) is less than the value defined by this preference. If the estimated number of DNF terms exceeds the preference value a DNF based strategy is selected, which is expected to result in a (usually significantly) smaller normalization result, but which is less optimal when evaluating configuration criteria. Since the estimate cannot take the effect of redundancy removal into account (a welcome by-product of the normalization process), the preference value significally overshoots the actual result. However, how much overshoot is acceptable depends on the nature and complexity of the configuration expression. Empirical analysis suggests that a good value is 30000 to reach a reasonable balance between save performance and configuration criteria evaluation performance. Valid values are all positive integer numbers greater or equal to 2. However, values less than the value for the preference "TC_max_cnf_count_for_condition_normalization" are not practical.

preference.name: TC_convert_text_file
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the system has to convert the EOF marker while transferring a file of a dataset. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not convert but transfer the file as is. 1 - Convert text file when transferring a file from/to client to/from server.

preference.name: TC_current_role

Valid Values: true - A member of the role has access to an object only when the role is that user's current role. false - A member of the role has access to an object even when the role is not the user's current role.

This role-based preference applies even when running command-line utilities such as the item_export or the data_share utility. Valid Values: Accepts the value FALSE. If set to any other value, the system ignores the preference setting.

preference.name: TC_default_export_sites

This preference is used only if the TC_USE_DEFAULT_EXPORT_SITES environment variable is defined and set to any value.This preference is not used with interactive Teamcenter and is intended only for compatibility with ITK programs. Valid Values: Any valid site IDs.

preference.name: TC_default_part_type
preference.preference_description: Determines the default part type created. Valid Values: One or more strings as values; each string must be a valid Teamcenter type.

preference.name: TC_deliverable_class_list

Use the ScheduleDeliverableWSOTypes preference instead.When adding a type, subtypes are not considered. For example, adding the Dataset type allows you to use Microsoft Word, Microsoft WordX, and Microsoft Excel.However, adding the Item type does not allow you to use the Document subtype of Item. Valid Values: The type of internal storage class names for any subtype of (and including) WorkspaceObject business object.

preference.name: TC_disallow_release_status_on_replica

If you are using Global Change Management, you must set this preference value to false to allow application of release status to replicas that are not remotely checked out during a remote workflow activity. Valid Values: true - Prevents replicas from being released. false - Allows replicas to be released (have a release status).

preference.name: TC_do_not_insert_imported_objects_into_folder
preference.preference_description: Determines whether imported objects are added to the user's home folder. This preference affects imported objects pushed to a specific user at a remote site and objects imported by the user using the item_import utility.In situations where the home folder contains thousands of objects, set this preference to TRUE to improve performance. Valid values are TRUE - Imported objects are not inserted into the specific user's home folder. Objects are stored in the database with no reference to any folder. To locate the imported objects, users must search the database. FALSE - Imported objects are inserted into the specific user's home folder.

preference.name: TC_encapsulation_application_key

preference.name: TC_export_child_groups

Set this preference to OFF to improve performance if groups at your site contain a large number of child groups. Valid Values: ON - Enables export of child groups when exporting groups using PLM XML. OFF - Disables export of child groups when exporting groups using PLM XML.

preference.name: TC_export_parent_groups

Set this preference to OFF to improve performance when groups at your site have a large number of parent groups. Valid Values: ON - Enables export of parent groups when exporting groups using PLM XML. OFF - Disables export of parent groups when exporting groups using PLM XML.

preference.name: TC_gms_export_default_transfermode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the PLM XML transfer mode used when exporting from Briefcase. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a valid PLM XML import transfer mode.

preference.name: TC_max_cnf_count_for_condition_normalization
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of sub-expressions that are accepted as a result from normalizing a configuration expression such as a variant condition. This normalization process is executed as part of saving the expression and automatically transforms the configuration expression into one or more Conjunctive Normal Forms (CNF) that are optimized for evaluating configurtion criteria. The number of sub-expressions that result from this normalization depends on the nature and complexity of the configuration expression. If the normalization process produces more sub-expressions than defined by this preference, a different strategy is applied which (usually significantly) reduces the number of sub-expressions, but which is less optimal when evaluating configurtion criteria. Empirical analysis suggests that a good value is 500 to reach a reasonable balance between scalability (by setting this upper bound for the sub-expression count) and performance (during configuration criteria evaluation). Valid values are all positive integer numbers greater or equal to 2. However, values less than 10 or greater than 10000 are not practical.

preference.name: TC_modified_only_export
preference.preference_description: Prevents a user from turning off the Include Modified Objects Only button in the Import/Export Options dialog box. This option usually results in better overall import/export efficiency. This preference does not apply when running command-line utilities such as the item_export or the data_share utility. Valid Values: Accepts the value TRUE. If set to any other value, the system ignores the preference setting.

preference.name: TC_ods_client_extra_attributes
preference.preference_description: Specifies and describes extra attributes of an object being published that you want stored in the publication record. Only string attributes can be specified. The attribute must have an initial value.When adding custom attributes to the publication record, you may want to populate these extra attributes when an object is published. For example, a new security level attribute is added to the publication record and you want to specify where the publication code retrieves the security information associated with the object being published.Use this preference for attributes that are part of the object's extended attributes (or any attributes from the Master form, if the object is an item or item revision).In multifield key (MFK) environments, this preference must be defined on the ODS client side and must contain the required publication record key attributes.When the custom attribute is not part of the object or its master form, you must implement a user exit to populate the custom publication record attributes. Valid Values: class-name - Specifies the name of the class that defines the po_pom_attr_name attribute. This is required only if po_pom_attr_name is used in multiple classes, in which case you must qualify the attribute name. This entry is optional and is normally not used. object-POM-attribute - Specifies the POM name of the extra non-array string attribute of the object being published. This should either be part of the class definition of the object or part of its master form (for items and item revisions). This entry is required. pub-record-POM-attribute - Specifies the POM name of the extra non-array string attribute of the publication record class where the value of po_pom_attr_name is stored. This should be part of the publication record class definition at both client and server sides. This entry is required.This attribute name cannot start with pubr, which is reserved for internal use. option - Indicates whether an extra attribute is mandatory or not. To indicate that an extra attribute is mandatory, set the option value to MANDATORY. This is an optional entry; if given, the attribute is assumed to be optional. This value may also be set to EXTERNAL to indicate that the attribute is not published from this site but should be returned by a search operation. In this case, the po_pom_attr_name should be same as pr_pom_attr_name.

preference.name: TC_overwrite_protection
preference.preference_description: This preference is used to indicate that the same property of the object has been modified concurrently by another user. A message will be displayed that will inform the user to discard their edits and update the property with latest value. When the preference is FALSE, the property value will be saved without any indication about concurrent modification. This will overwrite the property values modified by another user. Default value of this preference is FALSE. Applicable to Properties dialog, Form dialog, Viewer view, Summary view, Properties view and Details View inside My Teamcenter, BOM Window view within System Engineering, Office Live and Requirements applications.

preference.name: TC_reference_update_lmd
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the last modified date of a locally owned item revision is updated when an object with an associated reference relation is modified.The last modified date of the parent item is automatically updated as a consequence of the associated item revision update. Valid Values: TRUE - The last modified date of the item revision is modified when an object with an associated reference relation is modified. FALSE - The last modified date of the item revision is not modified when an object with an associated reference relation is modified.

preference.name: TC_relation_excluded_on_export
preference.preference_description: Prevents the given relation types from being exported to another site during the import/export operation. Valid Values: A list of valid relation type names, one name per line. The database name, not the display name, of a relation type must be given. Invalid values in the list are ignored.

preference.name: TC_relation_export_hidden
preference.preference_description: Prevents users in certain roles from seeing all available relation types in the Import/Export Options dialog box. This prevents users from including the hidden relation types for import/export operations. All hidden relation types are automatically excluded from the import/export operations. The OBJIO-send-target-objects action handler does not support use of the TC_relation_export_hidden preference. The action handler fails when it runs the preference. As a workaround, use the -exclude_relation argument in the OBJIO-send-target-objects action handler. Valid Values: A list of valid relation type names, one name per line. The database name, not the display name, of a relation type must be given. Invalid values in the list are ignored.

preference.name: TC_relation_export_on_transfer
preference.preference_description: Determines which interpart relation types are included when an object is exported/imported regardless of whether the export is a replica or with transfer of ownership. If the exporting site and the importing site have conflicting rules, the rule at the exporting site prevails. For example, if the importing site does not require the manifestation relation but the exporting site does, manifestations are included. Relations that are in this preference override relations that are also included in the TC_relation_required_on_transfer preference.To avoid having replicated participants missing in the Assign Participants dialog box, do not include the HasParticipant relation in this preference value. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter relation. An exception is the IMAN_RES_checkout relation, which is not a valid value for this preference.

preference.name: TC_remote_checkin_assy_option
preference.preference_description: Determines how the system manages newly added components when a remotely checked out BOM view revision (BVR) or item revision is remotely checked in. The typical use case is for a remote user to remotely check out a BVR to add new components owned by the local site (the site adding the component). When the BVR is remotely checked in, this preference determines how these locally owned components are handled.This preference is deprecated as of Teamcenter 10.1.1; it will be removed in a future release, and should not be used. This functionality has been replaced by options in the standard Teamcenter import and export options dialog boxes. Teamcenter ignores the preference setting when any import or export option is selected in the dialog box. Valid Values: 0 - The components are stubbed upon remote check in. A copy is not sent to the site that owns the BVR. Instead, at the owning site, the component is replaced by a POM stub. When the assembly containing the BVR is opened at the owning site via Structure Manager, the application prompts the user to remotely import the component. 1 - The components are sent to the owning site as replicas. Site ownership of the components remains with the site performing the remote checkin. 2 - Site ownership of the components is transferred to the site that owns the BVR. The components at the site performing the remote check in become replicas.

preference.name: TC_remote_checkin_exclude_relations
preference.preference_description: Determines which relations prompt the system not to transfer attachments as part of the replica when a parent object is remotely checked in.How the system checks in locally attached objects is determined both by this preference and the relations added to the Include Reference list. The Include Reference list defines the types of related objects to be imported and exported. The list displays in the Advanced tab of the Multi-Site Collaboration, Import Remote section of the Options dialog box, accessed from the Edit menu. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid Teamcenter relation.

preference.name: TC_remote_checkin_preserve_replica_owning_user_and_group
preference.preference_description: Determines how ownership is assigned to replica revisions upon checkin. This preference must be set at both sites to take effect.If this preference is set at only the owning site (and not also at the remote site), the preference acts as if it was not set.Do not set this preference to TRUE at the remote site and FALSE at the owning site. In this situation, the system displays an error. Valid Values: TRUE - The ownership assigned to the replica revision is preserved, regardless of which user checks in the replica.For example, consider an item created at Site A by User 1. A remote export is performed on the item with transfer of ownership to Site B User 1.User 1 at Site A then checks out the item, revises Rev1 of the item, and checks it back in. User 1 at Site A then checks out Rev2 of the item, changes ownership of the item to User 2 at Site B, and checks it back in. Both Site A and Site B see the ownership of Rev2 is User 2.In this example, User 1 must be a valid user at both sites and User 2 must be a valid user at both sites. FALSE - The user checking in the replica is assigned ownership, regardless of any ownership assignments made by the user. This preserves the concept of unified ownership.For example, consider an item created at Site A by User 1. A remote export is performed on the item with transfer of ownership to Site B by User 1.User 1 at Site A then checks out the item, revises Rev1 of the item, and checks it back in. User 1 at Site A then checks out Rev2 of the item, changes ownership of the item to User 2 at Site B, and checks it back in. Site A sees the ownership of Rev2 as User 2, but Site B sees the ownership of Rev2 as User 1.

preference.name: TC_remote_checkin_relation_send_as_replica
preference.preference_description: Determines which relations prompt the system to transfer attachments as part of the replica when a parent object is remotely checked in.How the system checks in locally attached objects is determined both by this preference and the relations added to the Include Reference list. The Include Reference list defines the types of related objects to be imported and exported. The list displays in the Advanced tab of the Multi-Site Collaboration, Import Remote section of the Options dialog box, accessed from the Edit menu. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid Teamcenter relation.

preference.name: TC_rendering_update_lmd

Valid Values: TRUE - The last modified date of the item revision is modified when an object with an associated rendering relation is modified. FALSE - The last modified date of the item revision is not modified when an object with an associated rendering relation is modified.

preference.name: TC_retain_saveas_replica_dataset_name

preference.name: TC_split_shared_status_on_replication
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to split the release status when replicating a object that has a shared release status that references the item revision and its related dataset objects. For exports with ownership transfer, the shared release status is always split. Valid Values: TRUE - Replicated objects have shared release status split from the related objects. The release status references only the item revision at both the remote and owning site. FALSE - Replicated objects do not have the shared release status object split from the related objects. The release status references the item revision and all related objects at both the remote and owning site.Setting this preference value to TRUE increases the chance of an instance in use error occurring during Multi-Site operations, especially when objects with release statuses are replicated at the same time by different users.

preference.name: TC_subscribable_replica_classes

When users subscribe to the Replica Updated event for a replica object at a replica site, they are notified when the replica is updated due to re-import or synchronization. The notification is sent only for the objects of classes defined by this preference. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid workspace object implementation class, such as ItemImpl, ItemRevisionImpl, DatasetImpl, DocumentImpl, DocumentRevisonImpl.In the case of the item and item revision classes, Teamcenter accepts the object class (Item, ItemRevision) in addition to the object implementation class.

preference.name: TC_subscriptionmgrd_sleep_minutes

preference.name: TC_sync_auto_synchronize
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether Teamcenter automatically synchronizes replicas at remote sites when the master object is modified. For Teamcenter 9.1 and later releases, the Synchronize automatically checkbox in the Remote Export Options and Remote Import Options dialog boxes is not user selectable. Automatic synchronization is controlled only by this preference. The checkbox value is read-only and provided for informational purposes.This preference is not created by the Teamcenter installation process. If you require this functionality, you must create the preference.For information about creating and using preferences, see Teamcenter Basics.Siemens PLM Software recommends that you use the following values when creating this preference:Protection Scope: RoleCategory: Data Sharing.Multi-Site CollaborationEnvironment: DisabledYou must select Logical from the Type list and Single from the Multiple box. Valid Values: TRUE - The Synchronize automatically checkbox is selected in the Remote Export Options dialog box. Teamcenter performs automatic synchronization of remote objects. FALSE - The Synchronize automatically checkbox is cleared in the Remote Export Options dialog box. Teamcenter does not perform automatic synchronization of remote objects.

preference.name: TC_sync_projects_with_owning_site
preference.preference_description: Controls the synchronization of the project list of replicas with the project list of the master object when projects are removed at the owning site. By default, when a project is removed from the master object, the project for the replica object is not removed. This allows the replica to maintain a project list that is independent of the master object. By default, removing all projects from the master object removes all projects from the replica object. Use this preference to enable the importing site to override the default behavior. It must be defined at the importing site and has no impact on the exporting site. Define this preference at the importing site. Valid Values: ALL: Indicates that for all owning sites, when a project is removed from the master object, that project is also removed from the replica object; and when all projects are removed from the master object, all projects are removed from the replica object. ALL must be the only entry for the preference. FALSE: When a project is removed from the master object, the project is not removed from the replica object. This is the same as the default behavior. However, if all projects are removed from the master object, unlike the default behavior, projects are not removed from the replica object, allowing the replica to maintain a project list independent of the master object. FALSE must be the only entry for the preference. site-name: Indicates the ALL value behavior applies to the specified site. You can enter a list of sites, one site name per line. Invalid site names are ignored. The default behavior applies to all sites not specified.

preference.name: UGALTREP_saveas_pattern
preference.preference_description: Defines the pattern string of the names of new UGALTREP dataset objects during a "Save As" operation. Value may contain text and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID, RevisionID or UserText. Existing dataset names are expected to match this pattern. If the existing dataset names do not match the pattern, then the new dataset names will not follow this pattern. Example: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, and the minus sign is literal text. Suppose a user is saving item revision 001234/B to item revision 002345/A. If a dataset's existing name is "altrep-001234/B" then the name is said to 'match' against the pattern. Since the ${UserText} at the start of this pattern matches any string, dataset name "fea-001234/B" would also match against the pattern. However, "altrep_001234/B" would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and "altrep-001235/B" would not match since the ItemID is incorrect. Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the two datasets would be saved as "altrep-002345/A" and "fea-002345/A". This is a site preference.

preference.name: UNLOAD_MINIMUM_LIFE
preference.preference_description: Determines which unused objects are qualified for memory cleanup, based on when objects were last accessed. Valid Values: Accepts any positive integer. The value specifies (in seconds) when an object must have been last accessed to be qualified for memory cleanup. Objects accessed more recently than the specified value are not removed from server memory.

preference.name: UNLOAD_OBJECTS
preference.preference_description: Offers the capability to disable the automatic unloading of objects. Valid Values: true: object unloading happens. This is the default behavior. false: object unloading is disabled.

preference.name: UNLOAD_TRIGGER_CEILING
preference.preference_description: Initiates the automatic cleanup of unused objects from the server memory. Specifies (in kilobytes) what memory size must be reached to initiate the unloading of unused objects from server memory.Automatic cleanup is performed during the operation occurring after the specified ceiling is reached. Thus, the specified memory size might be exceeded if the final loading action uploads a large amount of data.For example, if this preference is set to 12000 and memory consumption is at 11900 KB, at least one more load operation is required before the ceiling is reached. If the next load operation adds a large amount of data, such as 20000 KB, total memory consumption is 31900 KB when the automatic cleanup begins.Automatic cleanup of unused objects is enabled by default. This cleanup alleviates increased memory issues.Setting the value very low reduces the memory server footprint, but decreases performance. Valid Values: Accepts any positive integer. The number must be higher than the value set for the UNLOAD_TRIGGER_FLOOR preference. If an invalid value is set, the default value is used. InValid Values: A negative number. A number lower than the value set for the UNLOAD_TRIGGER_FLOOR preference Non-numerical characters Setting the value very low reduces the memory server footprint but decreases performance because most loaded objects are quickly unloaded, and when reloaded, must be unloaded again.

preference.name: UNLOAD_TRIGGER_FLOOR
preference.preference_description: Stops the automatic cleanup of unused objects from the server memory. Specifies (in kilobytes) what memory size must be reached to stop the unloading of unused objects from server memory after memory cleanup has begun.Automatic cleanup continues until the memory size specified by this preference is achieved. However, if the total size of unmovable object exceeds the floor amount, the specified memory size is not reached.For example, if objects cannot be removed because their life span does not meet the requirements specified by the UNLOAD_MINIMUM_LIFE preference, and the memory space consumed by these objects exceed the specified floor size, the specified memory size is not reached.Automatic cleanup of unused objects is enabled by default. This cleanup alleviates increased memory issues.Determining the optimum value for this preference requires investigation, and possibly experimentation in a working environment. Valid Values: Accepts any positive integer. The number must be higher than the value set for the UNLOAD_TRIGGER_CEILING preference. If an invalid value is set, the default value is used. InValid Values: A negative number A number lower than the value set for the UNLOAD_TRIGGER_CEILING preference Non-numerical characters

preference.name: VIS_expand_below_batch_size

A value of -1 indicates that there is no maximum batch size and that all lines in a single level will be processed in one batch. The default value is 50. preference.name: VIS_mmv_use_lwb

Valid Values: *true: the Light-weight BOM is used which provides higher performance but currently has some feature limitations (no effectivity support). *false: the regular BOM is used, which provides full BOM feature support but has reduced performance. This is the default value.

preference.name: VIS_mmvindexgen_admin_group
preference.preference_description: Lists the name of user group that is authorized to run the mmvindexgen translator from the Translation menu in the Rich client.

preference.name: VIS_mmvindexgen_admin_role
preference.preference_description: Lists the name of user roles that is authorized to run the mmvindexgen translator from the Translation menu in the Rich client.

preference.name: VIS_multi_file_datasettypes
preference.preference_description: Lists the Datasettypes that can contain more than one visualizable named references. This allows users to view the selected named reference in the My Navigator Viewer tab.

preference.name: VMS_Maintain_Vendor_History
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the system moves or copies data during change vendor operations. Valid Values: TRUE - If the preference is set to TRUE, the system copies the vendor data. FALSE - If the preference is set to FALSE, the system moves the vendor data.

preference.name: VMS_vendor_part_selection_rule
preference.preference_description: Stores the active condition name corresponding to current vendor part selection rule. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid condition.

preference.name: VM_auto_approve_vendor_registration
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Vendor should be bypassed from approval process.

preference.name: ValReqResult.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the summary stylesheet for ValReqResult objects.

preference.name: ValidationResult.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the summary stylesheet for ValidationResult objects.

preference.name: VendorManagement_feature_installed
preference.preference_description: Indicates that VendorManagement feature is installed

preference.name: VendorRevision_PseudoFolder
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of properties that can be displayed as a pseudo folder under a node for VendorRevision objects. This preference can be set using the preference name as an environment variable. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a property of VendorRevision.

preference.name: Vendor_Part_BOMLine_Properties
preference.preference_description: Defines the Vendor Part string properties, displayed (along with Vendor Part ID and location) in the "Vendor Parts" column in the Product Structure Manager. Valid values are property internal names. The default value is "vendor_id". The preference can be empty.

preference.name: Vendor_default_workflow_template
preference.preference_description: Defines the default workflow template to be used when Vendor object is submitted to workflow.

preference.name: Vis_DE_NoGeom_Property
preference.preference_description: Indicates which 4GD Design Element Teamcenter property (Design Element attribute key/name) is used to identify a Design Element as a No Geometry component. If the preference identified Design Element Property key exists on a given Design Element and has a value of "No", that Design Element is treated as as a No Geometry component.

preference.name: Vis_Doc_OpenOption
preference.preference_description: Specifies the behavior for opening the document by the embedded or standalone Lifecycle Visualization, in case the same document is already opened by that viewer. Valid Values: * "CreateNewDocument": to create a new document/view pair. * "ActivateExistingDocument": to activate the existing document/view pair. This is a default value.

preference.name: Vis_InteropWith3DSnapshots
preference.preference_description: Indicates if 3D Snapshot dataset should be sent to TcVis with ItemRev/BVR in InterOpt. Valid Values: TRUE/FALSE.

preference.name: Vis_InteropWithMotion
preference.preference_description: Indicates if motion data should be sent to TcVis with 3D Snapshot Dataset in InterOpt. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE.

preference.name: Vis_SendViewToSMTempFolder
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the Teamcenter folder where the transient Product View dataset is stored while sending a 3D view from Teamcenter Visualization to Rich Client Structure Manager viewer. The temporary Product View dataset is removed after it is applied in the Structure Manager viewer.

preference.name: VisualReportDefinition_OpenByName_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the columns to be displayed for the column names as defined in the "VisualReportDefinition_OpenByName_ColumnPreferences" preference.

preference.name: VisualReport_Use_Classification
preference.preference_description: Activates the usage of the Classification search for loading visual reports. Valid Values: * true: The Classification search is used to load reports. * false: The reports are searched based on names. This is the default value.

preference.name: Vm0ExchangeLine.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary Stylesheet for Exchange Line objects.

preference.name: Vm0PrtnrContractRevision_default_workflow_template
preference.preference_description: Defines the default workflow template to be used when Partner Contract Revision object is submitted to workflow.

preference.name: Vm0SupplierResponseObject.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary Stylesheet for Supplier Response objects.

preference.name: WEB_msoffice_integration
preference.preference_description: MS Office Integration true - enable it false - disable it.

preference.name: WRKFLW_PKI_user_validation_fieldname
preference.preference_description: Defines the fieldname from the client certificate to be used for user authentication. Accepts a single string as a value. The string must be a valid field name from the client certificate. For example, the valid values in the Siemens PKI certificate are SERIALNUMBER, CN(Common name), SN(Surname), G(Given name) and O(Orgnaization name) Default value is "NONE". By default, the authentication is performed using client certificate.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_checked_out_targets
preference.preference_description: Enables the workflow handler to attach checked-out objects as targets. This is currently supported for the "EPM-attach-related-objects" handler. Valid Values: * true: Enables adding checked-out targets as attachments. * false: Disables adding checked-out targets as attachments.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_signoff_assignment_to_OOO_user
preference.preference_description: Controls the task assignment of a signoff when the delegate is already a member of the signoff team. Valid Values: * true: Assigns the signoff to the out-of-office user because the delegate is already a member of signoff team. * false: Assigns the signoff to the resource pool belonging to the out-of-office user. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_skipped_task_restart
preference.preference_description: Controls the restart behavior of a skipped task. Valid Values: * 1: Restart the skipped task. This is the default value. * 2: Restart the skipped task only if the task has multiple successors. * 3: Do not restart the skipped task.

preference.name: WRKFLW_auto_subscribe_to_resource_pools
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the inbox content of all the Resource pools which Group and/or Role match the Group and/or Role of the logged-in user. Valid Values: * true: Show the inbox content of Resource pools. This is the default value. * false: Show the inbox content of manually subcribed Resource pools.

preference.name: WRKFLW_multitask_reassign_consolidated_email
preference.preference_description: Controls if a consolidated email notification to the new assignee should be sent in case of multiple task reassignments. Valid Values: * true: A single consolidated email is sent to the new assignee. * false: A separate email is sent for each task to the new assignee, if a notify handler is configured on the task's start action. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_skip_TasksToTrack_update
preference.preference_description: Set this preference to true to disable Workflow Inbox Task-To-Track folder updates.

preference.name: WRKFLW_skip_abort_on_sub_process
preference.preference_description: Controls the abort operation on sub-processes when the parent process is aborted. The preference is honored only for independent sub-processes. If there is a dependency from a parent process to its sub-processes, aborting the parent will also abort the dependent sub-processes, irrespective of the value of the preference. The default value is false which will abort the sub-processes along with parent process.

preference.name: WRKFLW_skip_root_task_from_acl_evaluation
preference.preference_description: Enables the ACL (Access Control List) accessor evaluation on Workflow root task. Valid Values: * true: Skip root task for ACL evaluation. * false: Consider root task for ACL evaluation. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_update_PSL_on_root_action
preference.preference_description: Update the Process Stage List (PSL) of the Target objects of a workflow only when the root task start, completes or aborts. Valid Values: * true: Update PSL when root task starts, completes or aborts. This is the default value. * false: Update PSL for all tasks.

preference.name: WSOM_find_bomLoadLimit
preference.preference_description: Indicates the number of objects to load out of a BOM for limiting a query in each pass. The larger the number the quicker the load time, but less control the user has to abort.

preference.name: WSOM_find_pffdtd

preference.name: WSOM_find_qry_filerunner_dtd

preference.name: WSOM_find_qrydtd

preference.name: WSOM_report_add_duplicate_rows
preference.preference_description: Add duplicate rows to report VLA attributes. Valid values are ON/OFF. ON - Display in multiple rows. OFF - Display in a single row.

preference.name: Weld_Item_ReleaseStatus
preference.preference_description: Specifies the status type that will be assigned to the weld items when released automatically. An empty value indicates that weld items should NOT be automatically released.

This preference only applies to the following cases: Exporting Teamcenter requirement structures to live Word using the Export for structure editing and work offline option.Opening and loading Teamcenter requirement structures from the Teamcenter ribbon in Microsoft Word. Valid Values: true - The name of the requirement object is displayed as the DisplayName property configured in the Business Modeler IDE. false - The name of the requirement object is displayed as a combination of the object ID and name.
