preference.name: TC_gms_server_ca_file
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the file that stores the trusted certificates of the Certificate Authorities (CAs) for servers including Global Services server. This file should be in PEM format. This preference is applicable only when the Global Services is deployed in HTTPS mode. The value of this preference can be left blank if server certificate validation is not required.

preference.name: TC_gms_server_ca_path
preference.preference_description: Specifies the path to the directory with trusted certificates of the Certificate Authorities (CAs) for servers including Global Services server. This preference is applicable only when the Global Services is deployed in HTTPS mode. The value of this preference is optional and can be left blank if server certificate validation is not required.

preference.name: TC_gms_server_web_UI
preference.preference_description: Defines the Teamcenter Integration Framework web-based UI URL location. In cases involving Teamcenter Global Services, use the value defined under Tc_gms_server preferences.

preference.name: TC_gms_sso_enabled
preference.preference_description: Determines whether Global Services uses Security Services to provide single sign-on (SSO) capability. If this preference is not set to true, the following preferences must be set to provide user credentials for Global Services: GS_USER_NAME GS_USER_PASSWORD Valid Values: true - SSO is enabled for Global Services. false - SSO is not enabled for Global Services. User ID and password preferences must be defined so that users can log onto Global Services.

This list is used by image translation service to translate the original high resolution image to specified lower resolutions. The width of the image would be assigned by the image translation service based on the aspect ratio of the original image.

preference.preference_description: Specifies if a site has AIE Encapsulation Manager installed or not. Valid values are YES/NO.

preference.preference_description: Indicates if the system has to export files from read-only datasets as read-only files on the client. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: AIE_file_types_to_ignore
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of file extensions that will be ignored if found in the client connection directories.

preference.name: AIE_import_master
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the user has permissions to modify import information in the xml files when importing them back to Teamcenter. Valid values are Application/both. Application - User is not allowed to change the import information from Teamcenter. both - User is allowed to modify import information from Teamcenter.

preference.name: AIE_installed
preference.preference_description: Indicates if a site has AIE (Application Integration Environment) installed or not. Valid values are YES/NO.

preference.preference_description: Lists all the AIE (Application Integration Environment) families. For e.x. NX, etc.

preference.name: AIE_named_refs_to_export
preference.preference_description: Preference that allows a user to specify the named references to export to a connection. Valid values are all/select/primary. all - All the named references in the dataset will be exported. select - A dialog will be displayed that will provide an option to the user to select the named references. primary - Primary named reference for the dataset will be exported.

preference.name: AIE_no_BVR_edit
preference.preference_description: Determines whether a particular BOM view revision is changed during an NX Remote Manager import operation from defined CAD system. If any dataset types defined in this preference appears together with a dataset type registered with NX Remote Manager (for example, with ACADDWG specifying AutoCAD Manager, or SE Part specifying Specification Manager), then the BOM view revision is not changed during the NX Remote Manager import. Valid Values: Accepts any or all of the dataset types defined by default by the system. This preference is defined during NX Remote Manager installation.

preference.name: AIE_overwrite_default_import_item_types
preference.preference_description: Determines whether users importing non-NX files from a directory can choose from among all the item types available to the data model service (DMS) or is restricted to default item type defined by the system administrator. Valid Values: ON - The user can choose from all item types listed in the DMS, whether selecting new files to be imported or previously exported files. OFF - The user cannot chose from any item type; the first item type defined in the data model service is used as the default item type. Previously exported files revert to their existing item type and new files are imported using the default item type only.

preference.name: AIE_save_transaction_log
preference.preference_description: Preference that indicates if we need to save the transaction log after the connection has been deleted. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: CAEShowConfigurationHeader
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of configuration headers in the Product and Model views of the CAE Manager application. Examples of configuration header information are: "Revision Rule", "Variant Rule", "Effectivity", "Incremental Change Context". The default value is true (information is displayed).

preference.name: CAE_Inspector_summary_dataset_name
preference.preference_description: This is an optional preference. Specifies the name of the dataset in which the Inspector Summary value will be saved as a named reference. Valid Values: A non-empty multi-character string not greater in 128 characters in length.

preference.name: CAE_KPI_Table_AttributeSupport_for_AW_stylesheet
preference.preference_description: This is an internal preference to enable the appropriate KPI page for the CAE 3D Analysis Revision and CAE 3D Analysis Template Revision in Active Workspace as per the Teamcenter release. In order to show the appropriate properties for CAE KPI table in minor release and enable the newly added properties on KPI page for the current release, the preference value ("NodeIDElementID") is used in the Active Workspace stylesheet (Cae1CAE0AnaTemplateRevSummary.xml, Cae1CAEAnalysisRevSummary.xml). If any new properties are added in the CAE KPI table (cae0KPITable) in the future releases then the value will be changed and the stylesheet condition needs to be updated accordingly. If the user changes the default value, then the KPI page for CAE 3D Analysis Revision and CAE 3D Analysis Template Revision in Active Workspace will also need to be updated.

The valid values for Criteria "Model With Different Product Revision Target" are "Do Nothing", "Use New Model", "Use Model Related to Product Item", "Use Model Related to Product Revision", "Use Revised Model", "Replace Relationship" and "Add Relationship". The valid values for Criteria "Model With No Product" are "Do Nothing", "Add Relationship" and "Remove Model". The valid values for Criteria "Extra Model Components" are "Do Nothing" and "Remove Model". The default value for all the Criteria is "Do Nothing".

preference.name: TC_ODBC_release_status
preference.preference_description: This file can be found in the /vobs/src/tc/data/teamcenter_env_wnt.default directory.This is a file that the tc_preferences.xml preference file links to for a Windows-only application. Before starting the application, set the option to ALL or LATEST to retrieve either all the release statuses or the latest release status in the list, respectively.There is a new preference file in the \vobs\src\tc\data_odbc_exclude_tcbomlist directory. Before starting the application, move the columns you do not want to see in the BOM table in this file. The format of the file is as follows: EXCLUDED_LIST_START bl_formatted_title bl_indended_title #bl_line_name #bl_config_string #bl_variant_state Each line contains the name of a column (a BOM property). Remove the comment symbol (#) to add the name. Add the query criteria Parent_Item_Rev_Id like xxx after specifying the Parent_Item_Id criteria, using the standard query interface in the application.The WhereUsed table in the table list, has six column attributes for a user to report. The columns are: Child_Item_Id Child_Item_Rev_Id level_of_search item_id item_rev_id object_name Add Child_Item_Id criteria and after that, add Child_Item_Rev_Id criteria, using the standard query interface in the application. Valid Values: ALL - Outputs all in the release status list. LATEST - Outputs the latest one in the release status list.

preference.name: LDAP_attribute_mapping
preference.preference_description:
Maps LDAP attributes to Teamcenter attributes. The mappings control what information the synchronization tool sets in the Teamcenter user and person objects. For example:LDAP_attribute_mapping= LDAPPersonName cn %REPLACE_ME% LDAPEngUserId uid %REPLACE_ME% LDAPLastUpdate modifyTimestamp %REPLACE_ME% LDAPOsUser uid %REPLACE_ME% LDAPUserGroup %REPLACE_ME% Engineering LDAPUserRole %REPLACE_ME% %REPLACE_ME%
Valid values: Accepts multiple strings, in pairs, as values. Each pair must contain valid LDAP and Teamcenter attributes.

preference.name: LDAP_base_dn
preference.preference_description: Defines the distinguished name (DN) of the top-level entry under which all user entries to be checked are defined. Use this preference to limit which part of the LDAP directory the synchronization tool examines when searching for Teamcenter users. This functionality can also be used to partition users within a single LDAP database across several Teamcenter installations.If a site does not have this degree of organization in its LDAP directory, this value should be set to the lowest level in the directory that would encompass all of the Engineering users. Following is an example of how a high-level value might appear:dc=ugs,dc=com A more specific entry would look as follows:ou=Engineering Users,ou=special users,dc=ugs,dc=com Valid values: Accepts one or more strings as a value. Must be a valid LDAP directory name.

preference.name: LDAP_cert_db_path
preference.preference_description: Defines the path to the certificate used for the Security Services connection. The system only checks this preference if the LDAP_use_ssl preference is set to TRUE. Ensure this preference points to a correctly configured certificate database. Otherwise, errors are encountered when configuring the LDAP synchronization tool to use the SSL. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be the full path to the certificate database used for the Security Services connection.

preference.name: LDAP_group_attr_mapping
preference.preference_description:
Maps LDAP object attributes to Teamcenter group attributes. The mappings control what information the synchronization tool (the ldapsync utility) sets in the Teamcenter group object. LDAPGroupName cn %REPLACE_ME% LDAPGroupDesc description %REPLACE_ME% LDAPLastUpdate modifyTimestamp %REPLACE_ME% LDAPGroupDBA %REPLACE_ME% 0 LDAPGroupRole %REPLACE_ME% %REPLACE_ME%
Valid Values: Accepts triples of strings.Each attribute mapping consists of three strings: the attribute identifier, the mapped LDAP attribute name, and the default value (to be used if there is no LDAP mapped attribute or if the LDAP mapped attribute value is null).

preference.name: LDAP_group_base_dn
preference.preference_description: Defines the distinguished name (DN) of one or more nodes in the external directory where the group synchronization process begins searching. This preference limits which part of the LDAP external directory the sync tool views when searching for groups to synchronize with Teamcenter.Use this attribute to improve performance and to partition groups within a single LDAP database across several Teamcenter installations. If your site's LDAP directory does not have a high degree of organization, set this value to the lowest level DNs that encompass all of the Teamcenter groups. For example, a high-level DN is:dc=net,dc=plm,dc=ugs,dc=com An example of a specific DN is:ou=Engineering Groups,ou=groups,dc=net,dc=plm,dc=ugs,dc=com Valid Values: A set of one or more strings.

preference.name: LDAP_group_object_class
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP object class that the customer uses to model groups to be synchronized with Teamcenter. If you use multiple classes that all represent groups, use this preference to specify the common base class of those classes. This optional preference allows you to define specific subclasses in LDAP to differentiate groups and roles. If groups and roles both have the same object class, they must be differentiated by values of the attribute specified using the LDAP_object_type_attr preference. Valid values: Accepts a single string, which is the name of an LDAP object class.

preference.name: LDAP_group_query_filter
preference.preference_description: Defines a set of conditions that an LDAP object must satisfy to be matched as a group object for synchronizing with Teamcenter. If you are familiar with LDAP query filter syntax, use this optional preference, which is a more sophisticated object matching mechanism. Valid value: Accepts a single string in LDAP query filter syntax.

preference.name: LDAP_ignore_users
preference.preference_description: Defines a set user IDs that should not be processed by the ldapsync utility. This list normally contains Teamcenter user IDs that are used for administrative purposes and do not have corresponding entries in the LDAP repository. Valid values: Accepts one or more strings.

preference.name: LDAP_member_list_attr
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP group object attribute that contains the list of member distinguished names (DN) for the object. This preference applies to objects representing either groups or roles defined in LDAP. Use this preference only if the LDAP_member_type_attr preference is set. Valid values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: LDAP_member_type_attr
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP group object attribute that contains the membership type (direct or indirect) for this object. Valid values: TRUE - Specifies indirect group membership. If this setting is used, the LDAP_member_list_attr preference must also be set. FALSE - Specifies direct group membership.

preference.name: LDAP_object_type_attr
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP group object attribute that contains the object type (group or role) for this object. Valid values: group - The object represents a group defined in LDAP. role - The object represents a role defined in LDAP.

preference.name: LDAP_person_attr_mapping
preference.preference_description:
Maps LDAP user attributes to Teamcenter person attributes. The mappings control what information the synchronization tool sets in the Teamcenter person objects.LDAP_attribute_mapping= LDAPPersonName cn %REPLACE_ME% LDAPLastUpdate modifyTimestamp %REPLACE_ME% PA1 postaladdress %REPLACE_ME% PA2 localityName %REPLACE_ME% PA3 st %REPLACE_ME% PA4 postalCode %REPLACE_ME% PA5 co %REPLACE_ME% PA6 o %REPLACE_ME% PA7 employeeNumber %REPLACE_ME% PA8 physicalDeliveryOfficeName %REPLACE_ME% PA9 mail %REPLACE_ME% PA10 telephoneNumber %REPLACE_ME%
Valid values: Accepts triples of strings.

preference.name: LDAP_port_number
preference.preference_description: Defines the port number used when connecting to the hosts defined in the LDAP_service_hosts preference. This preference works with the LDAP_use_ssl preference. If this preference is set to the SSL port on the directory server, but the LDAP_use_ssl preference is set to FALSE, the directory server ignores the connection request from the synchronization tool, making it appear that the tool has hung. When configuring the LDAP synchronization tool to use the SSL, make certain the LDAP_use_ssl preference is set to TRUE. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a single positive integer. Define the Security Services server port to enable synchronization.

preference.name: LDAP_role_attr_mapping
preference.preference_description:
Maps LDAP attributes to Teamcenter role attributes. The mappings control what information the synchronization tool sets in the Teamcenter role object.LDAP_role_attr_mapping= LDAPRoleName cn %REPLACE_ME% LDAPRoleDesc description %REPLACE_ME% LDAPLastUpdate modifyTimestamp %REPLACE_ME%
Valid values: Accepts triples of strings.Each attribute mapping consists of three strings: the Teamcenter attribute name, the mapped LDAP attribute name, and the default value (to be used if there is no LDAP mapped attribute or if the LDAP mapped attribute value is null).

preference.name: LDAP_role_object_class
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP object class used to model roles to be synchronized with Teamcenter. If you use multiple classes that all represent roles, use this preference to specify the common base class of those classes. This optional preference allows you to define specific subclasses in LDAP to differentiate groups and roles. If groups and roles both have the same object class, they must be differentiated by values of the attribute specified using the LDAP_object_type_attr preference. Valid values: Accepts a single string. Must be the name of an LDAP object class.

preference.name: LDAP_role_query_filter
preference.preference_description: Defines a set of conditions that an LDAP object must satisfy to become matched as a role object for synchronizing with Teamcenter. This optional preference allows administrators familiar with LDAP query filter syntax to use a more sophisticated object matching mechanism. Valid values: Accepts a string in LDAP query filter syntax.

preference.name: LDAP_service_hosts
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of hosts providing LDAP directory service for the synchronization installation. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid host name. Define hosts running the LDAP directory that you want to use for synchronization.

preference.name: LDAP_sync_member_flags
preference.preference_description: Defines the group member synchronization setting flags in a chmod-style character string format.Group member synchronization requires both user synchronization and group synchronization to be enabled. If group member synchronization is enabled but either user or group synchronization is not, then group member synchronization is skipped. Valid Values: s (synchronize) - If set, enables group member synchronization. c (create) - If set, allows new externally managed group member objects to be created in Teamcenter during group member synchronization. d (deactivate) - If set, allows externally managed group member objects to be deactivated in Teamcenter during user synchronization. e (externalize) - If set, any internally managed group objects found in Teamcenter to have the same user ID, group name, and role name as a group member relationship in LDAP is converted to externally managed during group member synchronization.

preference.name: LDAP_sync_role_flags
preference.preference_description: Defines the role synchronization setting flags in a chmod-style character string format. Role synchronization requires group synchronization to be enabled. If role synchronization is enabled but group synchronization is not, then role synchronization is skipped. Valid Values: s (synchronize) - If set, enables role synchronization. c (create) - If set, allows new externally managed role objects to be created in Teamcenter during role synchronization. u (update) - If set, allows externally managed role objects to be updated in Teamcenter during role synchronization. e (externalize) - If set, any internally managed role objects found in Teamcenter to have the same role name as a role object in LDAP is converted to externally managed during role synchronization.

preference.name: LDAP_sync_user_flags
preference.preference_description: Defines the user synchronization setting flags in a chmod-style character string format. Valid Values: s (synchronize) - If set, enables user synchronization. c (create) - If set, allows new externally managed user and person objects to be created in Teamcenter during user synchronization. d (deactivate) - If set, allows externally managed user and person objects to be deactivated in Teamcenter during user synchronization. u (update) - If set, allows externally managed user and person objects to be updated in Teamcenter during user synchronization. e (externalize) - If set, any internally managed user and person objects found in Teamcenter to have the same user ID and person name as a user object in LDAP is converted to externally managed during user synchronization.

preference.name: LDAP_use_ssl
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the connection to the LDAP server uses Security Services. If the LDAP_port_number preference is set to the SSL port on the directory server, but this preference is set to FALSE, the directory server ignores the connection request from the synchronization tool, making it appear that the tool has hung. When configuring the LDAP synchronization tool to use the SSL, make certain this preference is set to TRUE. Valid Values: TRUE - The LDAP server connection uses Security Services. If this setting is used, the LDAP_cert_db_path preference must also be set. FALSE - The LDAP server connection does not use Security Services.

preference.name: LDAP_user_object_class
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP object class that the customer uses to model users to be synchronized with Teamcenter. If you use multiple classes that all represent users, then this preference should specify the common base class of those classes. Valid values: Accepts a single string. Must be the name of an LDAP object class.

preference.name: LDAP_user_query_filter
preference.preference_description: Defines a set of conditions that an LDAP object must satisfy to be matched as a user object for synchronizing with Teamcenter. This optional preference allows administrators familiar with LDAP query filter syntax to use a more sophisticated object matching mechanism. Valid values: Accepts a single string. Must be in LDAP query filter syntax.

category.name: LDAP.Synchronization
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: LDAP_sync_group_flags
preference.preference_description: Defines the group synchronization setting flags in a chmod-style character string format. Valid Values: s (synchronize) - If set, enables group synchronization. c (create) - If set, allows new externally managed group objects to be created in Teamcenter during group synchronization. u (update) - If set, allows externally managed group objects to be updated in Teamcenter during group synchronization. e (externalize) - If set, any internally managed group objects found in Teamcenter to have the same group name as a group object in LDAP is converted to externally managed during group synchronization.

category.name: Language
category.category_description: Defines parameters for the session langage.

preference.name: TC_language_force_thin_client_locale
preference.preference_description: Forces the thin client to start up with the default language as defined by the TC_language_default environment variable. The TC_language_force_thin_client_locale_no_warning preference can be used to suppress a warning message about the default locale being used when the TC_language_force_thin_client_locale preference is set to true. Valid Values: true - The thin client always starts with the default locale. false - The thin client starts with the language specified by the ?lang= URL parameter and the browser preferences.

preference.name: TC_language_force_thin_client_locale_no_warning
preference.preference_description: Suppresses the error message that warns the user that the default language is being used. The TC_language_force_thin_client_locale_no_warning preference can be used only when the TC_language_force_thin_client_locale preference is set to true. Valid Values: true - Suppresses the default language warning message. false - Allows the default language warning message to display each time the thin client is launched.

preference.name: TC_language_no_encoding_discrepancy_warning_message
preference.preference_description: Prevents the display of the warning message regarding discrepancy between the Teamcenter server encoding and the database encoding. Valid Values: True - The warning message is never displayed. False - The warning message is always displayed.

preference.name: TC_language_search
preference.preference_description: Specifies the locale used in doing search operations. The search criteria specified by the user is assumed to be in this locale. If the value is not set, the search locale defaults to the client locale. If localization for Classification is enabled, selecting the search language in the attribute dictionary in the Classification Admin application changes the value of the TC_language_search preference interactively for all Teamcenter applications. Valid Values: cs_CZ - Czech de_DE - German en_US - English es_ES - Spanish fr_FR - French it_IT - Italian ja_JP - Japanese ko_KR - Korean ru_RU - Russian zh_CN - Chinese (as spoken in China) zh_TW - Chinese (as spoken in Taiwan)

preference.name: TC_no_obsolete_message
preference.preference_description: Suppresses the obsolete or deprecated messages coming from the Teamcenter server process which are printed on its console window. The default value is false (messages are printed) and out-of-the-box it can be set through an environment variable of the same name.

category.name: Licensing
category.category_description: Configuration for Teamcenter feature licensing.

preference.name: LICENSE_consumer_enforcement_enabled
preference.preference_description: Activates the consumer license enforcement feature. The default value is false (disabled).

preference.name: LicenseUsage_admin_notifier_list
preference.preference_description: Specifies the identifiers of the administrative users who will receive Teamcenter notifications when the Occasional Author exceeds the allotted usage and/or grace period limits specified for the Occasional Author license level.

preference.name: LicenseUsage_days_warning_level
preference.preference_description: Specifies the remaining duration in days in the allotted usage when occasional logged-in users start receiving warning messages as a notification that they are approaching their alloted usage days.

preference.name: LicenseUsage_hours_warning_level
preference.preference_description: Specifies the remaining duration in hours in the allotted usage when occasional logged-in users start receiving warning messages as a notification that they are approaching their alloted usage hours.

preference.name: LicenseUsage_module_usage_warning_level
preference.preference_description: Specifies the remaining usage in terms of new unique logins in current month when the configured administrators start receiving warning messages as notification that the module usage is approaching the allowed limit.

preference.name: LicenseUsage_show_userId_in_report
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the actual user ID in the license usage report. The default value is true (activated).

preference.name: License_allow_dba_to_change
preference.preference_description: Allows the Default Local License Server to be changed by a DBA when they log in. Value of 'true' means anyone in the DBA group/role will create a new Default Local License Server if their value of SPLM_LICENSE_SERVER is different than that found in the database. Value of 'false' means that a DBA cannot change the Default Local License Server. Note - the user 'infodba' will always be allowed to change the Default Local License Server.

preference.name: license_warning_level
preference.preference_description: Specifies a threshold number of remaining licenses. When an administrator assigns license levels or license bundles, the system displays a warning when the number of remaining licenses is equal to, or lower than, the value of this preference. License levels and license bundles are assigned using either the Organization application or the make_user utility. When assigning a license to a user, the following message appears when a threshold set to 5 is reached: The number of available licenses is running low: 5 licenses are left. When assigning a license bundle to a user, the following message appears when a threshold set to 5 is crossed: The number of available licenses is running low: 5 licenses of bundle bundle-name are left. Valid Values: Any single string. Must be a single, positive integer more than zero.

category.name: Localization
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: TC_language_data_entry
preference.preference_description: Defines which locales users may use for data entry. Limit the values of this preference to locales supported by your database encoding. When this preference is set, the system displays the following message after a user enters the appropriate credentials: You must limit data input using locales L10N_a and L10N_b.L10N_a and L10N_b are values set for this preference. The system implements this preference as follows:If the requested locale does not exist on the Teamcenter server, the connection is served in English. If the requested locale does not belong to the database encoding, and the Teamcenter server is running on a UTF-8 system (for example, Linux), the connection is served with this locale. If the requested locale does not belong to the database encoding, and the Teamcenter server is running on a non-UTF-8 system, the connection is served in English. If none of these situations apply, the requested locale is served. Valid Values: cs_CZ - Czech de_DE - German en_US - English es_ES - Spanish fr_FR - French it_IT - Italian ja_JP - Japanese ko_KR - Korean ru_RU - Russian zh_CN - Chinese (as spoken in China) zh_TW - Chinese (as spoken in Taiwan)

preference.name: TC_language_localization_display
preference.preference_description: Displays translation information as read-only for properties that are localizable. Valid Values: true - Displays translation information. false - Hides translation information.

preference.name: TC_language_localized_property_value_display
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of languages for displaying localized property values. Valid Values: cs_CZ - Czech de_DE - German en_US - English es_ES - Spanish fr_FR - French it_IT - Italian ja_JP - Japanese ko_KR - Korean ru_RU - Russian zh_CN - Chinese (as spoken in China) zh_TW - Chinese (as spoken in Taiwan)

preference.name: TC_language_localized_property_value_entry
preference.preference_description: Specifies the data entry locale (master locale) of the logged-on user. The master locale is the one used by the user to create/edit data in a localized property. Valid Values: cs_CZ - Czech de_DE - German en_US - English es_ES - Spanish fr_FR - French it_IT - Italian ja_JP - Japanese ko_KR - Korean ru_RU - Russian zh_CN - Chinese (as spoken in China) zh_TW - Chinese (as spoken in Taiwan)

category.name: Logging
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: UNLOAD_LOGGING_LEVEL
preference.preference_description: Determines the level of detail logged in the in-session and end-session reports sent to the .unloadlog log file. Valid Values: 0 - No log file is created. 1 - In-session report includes number of cache objects and unload time. End session report includes total number of objects unloaded and the average unload time. 2 - In-session report includes all information from a level 1 report, as well as memory usage before and after loading. End-session report includes all information from a level 1 report. 3 - In-session report includes all information from a level 2 report, as well as callback information. End-session report includes all information from a level 2 report, as well summary unload reports by type. 4 - In-session report includes all information from a level 3 report, as well object types loaded and unloaded from the cache. End-session report includes all information from a level 3 report. Setting this preference to 1 through 4 does not produce a log file unless the FCC is restarted on the client, for example: FMS_HOME\bin\fccstat -restart

category.name: Mail
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_admin_email_address
preference.preference_description: Whom to send emails regarding failure to process an appearance update package in background mode. Special values are: - $USER meaning the Teamcenter user that the appearance updater is logged in as - $OSUSER meaning the OS user running the appearance updater As shipped, the value is $OSUSER, to ensure that at least someone is notified.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_email_interval_for_different_package
preference.preference_description: The minimum interval (in minutes) to allow the sending of emails regarding the failure of the appearance updater to process any package in background mode.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_email_interval_for_same_package
preference.preference_description: The minimum interval (in minutes) to allow the sending of emails regarding the failure of the appearance updater to process a particular package in background mode.

preference.name: Briefcase_tcmail_notification
preference.preference_description: Determines if an email notification should be sent when the Briefcase creation is complete. The default value is false if the Vendor Management extension is installed.

preference.name: EMLPOLLING_default_polling_config_id
preference.preference_description: Defines the identifier for email polling configuration to be used in the email polling operation. Valid Values: Any identifier for email polling configuration.

preference.name: EMLPOLLING_keep_review_mail_attachments
preference.preference_description: Activates the creation of a Gate Keeper workflow during email polling. The default value is true.

preference.name: Email_polling_download_dir
preference.preference_description: Defines the existing directory where mail attachments are downloaded for the email polling functionality. Valid Values: Accepts single string as a value; each string must be the full operating system path of the directory.When a Windows path is used, a double slash is required after the drive designation, for example:Email_polling_download_dir=c:\\temp

preference.name: Fnd0EMLPollingRevFrm.FORMJAVARENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the Java class to render the property panel of a form with type Review Email Polling Revision Form.

preference.name: Fnd0EMLPollingRevFrm.JAVARENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the Java class to render the property panel of a form with type Review Email Polling Revision Form. Valid Values: Java class to render the property panel of a form.

preference.name: Fnd0_review_email_attachments_workflow
preference.preference_description: Defines the create workflow for email polling functionality. Valid Values: A Teamcenter Workflow process, although Review Mail Attachments is the Teamcenter provided default.

preference.name: Folder_mail_properties
preference.preference_description: Lists all properties of an object folder that can be sent via Teamcenter mail. Valid Values: One or more strings as values; each string must be a valid object folder property name.

preference.name: IDSM_dsa_notification_email_address
preference.preference_description: Determines which administrators are notified by e-mail when system administration data (such as organization data, relation types, revision rules) is received from a remote site with the dsa_util utility. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter e-mail address, separated by a semicolon.

preference.name: Mail_OS_from_address
preference.preference_description: Defines a "From" e-mail address for OS notification e-mails. Valid vallues are: * a valid email address: this value appears in the e-mail header "From" line. * an empty value: the "From" email address is taken from the sender's Person definition. This is the default value.

preference.name: Mail_internal_mail_activated
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the Teamcenter internal mail functionality is available when using the notify workflow handler. Default value is false. Valid Values: * true: The Teamcenter internal mail functionality is available. * false: The Teamcenter internal mail functionality is not available.

preference.name: Mail_send_file_attachments_activated
preference.preference_description: Activates sending dataset attachments as email file attachments. This takes effect when the envelope functionality sends messages directly to an email address instead of a Teamcenter user. When the mail is sent to a Teamcenter user, this preference has no impact, and the user always receives links to the envelope object. Valid Values: * true: Activates sending dataset attachments as email file attachments. The external recipient can open the attached files without requiring a Teamcenter logon or privileges. Consider site security guidelines before setting this preference to true. * false: Deactivates sending dataset attachments as email file attachments. External recipients of emails receive only Teamcenter client links to the attached datasets and not the actual files.

preference.name: Mail_server_authentication_activated
preference.preference_description: Defines if the Mail sent from Teamcenter needs to be Authenticated. Valid Values: * true: The authentication will be performed while sending an email. An admin will need to update Mail_server_authentication_id, Mail_server_connection_security, Mail_server_authentication_passwd_location and Mail_server_ssl_protocol if authentication is true. * false: The email will be sent without authentication. An admin may need to update the Mail_server_port if authentication is false. This is the default value.

preference.name: Mail_server_authentication_id
preference.preference_description: Defines the email id or user id for Email Authentication. Make sure you specify the password location and email id/user id if Mail_server_authentication_activated is true.

preference.name: Mail_server_authentication_passwd_location
preference.preference_description: Defines the password location of email id used for authentication. Make sure you specify the password location and email id/user id if Mail_server_authentication_activated is true. Note: You need to use "install encryptpwf" utility to generate the password file.

preference.name: Mail_server_charset
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Teamcenter mail server character set that is used to send mail.

preference.name: Mail_server_connection_security
preference.preference_description: Defines the connection security between SMTP Mail Utility (Teamcenter) and Mail Server. Valid Values: * None * SSL/TLS * STARTTLS This value depends on the Mail server configuration for SMTP.

preference.name: Mail_server_name
preference.preference_description: Sets the name of the mail gateway server. The mail server name should be a machine running a sendmail daemon. Leaving it as "your mail server machine" while the "Mail_OSMail_activated" preference is true may give you errors telling you to set this preference if you try to use the "Send" command. Valid Values: Text server name or an numeric IP address.

preference.name: Mail_server_port
preference.preference_description: Specifies the port number used by the SMTP mail server to send OS mail. This preference must be used in conjunction with the Mail_server_name preference. Default value is 25. Valid Values: Must be a valid SMTP port number.

preference.name: Mail_server_ssl_protocol
preference.preference_description: Defines the connection security protocol between SMTP Mail Utility (Teamcenter) and Mail Server. This value depends on the Mail server configuration for SMTP. Valid Values: TLSv1_3, TLSv1_2, TLSv1_1, TLSv1, SSLv23. These are the only supported ssl/tls protocol.

preference.name: Mail_subscription_notify_sub_groups_too
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to include subgroups in subscription notification. Valid Values: TRUE - Subgroups are included in subscription notification. FALSE - Subgroups are not included in subscription notification.

preference.name: OCS_company_email_domain
preference.preference_description: For the Teamcenter integration with Microsoft Office Communicator, specifies the company domain name for messages, but only when the OCS_use_email_property preference value is false. Valid Values: Any valid e-mail domain.

preference.name: OCS_use_email_property
preference.preference_description: For the Teamcenter integration with Microsoft Office Communicator, specifies whether to use the e-mail ID from the e-mail ID field of the user Person object. Valid Values: true - The e-mail ID is taken from the user Person object e-mail data. false - The e-mail ID consists of the user ID and the value of the OCS_company_email_domain preference.

preference.name: Siemens_PL_email_id
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Siemens PL email id which will be receiving notificatins when any module usage limit exceeds its allowed usage.

preference.name: TC_Person_PA9_Email_Validation
preference.preference_description: Specifies if a value for the person attribute PA9 should be validated against email format. Valid values are true/false. If email addresses support non-ascii characters, keep the value to false.

preference.name: TC_mail_interval
preference.preference_description: Determines how often Teamcenter checks for new system mail. This can also be set in the rich client interface by choosing Edit->Options->Mail. Valid Values: A single positive integer. This is polling interval in Minutes

preference.name: TC_use_tc_alias_in_pa8
preference.preference_description: Allows the use of e-mail addresses longer than 32 characters. If set to ON, the user's e-mail attribute is assumed to be an address list. The name of this address list must be less than 32 characters, but the e-mail addresses of list members may exceed 32 characters. Valid Values: * ON: Allows e-mail addresses of address list members to exceed 32 characters. * OFF: Does not allow e-mail addresses to exceed 32 characters.

preference.name: WRKFLW_mail_surrogates

preference.name: AccountabilityCheckReportStylesheetName
preference.preference_description: Determines which XSL style sheet of the report definition should be used to generate the accountability check report.A user can add more than one XSL style sheet to the report definition. If this preference is defined and a style sheet with this name is found, the accountability check report is generated by using the style sheet that is found. Otherwise, the default style sheet is used.An accountability check compares a bill of materials (BOM) with a bill of process (BOP) to ensure all lines in the source BOM are consumed in the target BOP. This allows you to ensure that all occurrences of product components and features are used in the process structure as consumed items. You can compare the entire assembly or only a subassembly to the selected process. Valid Values: Accepts strings as value. Each string must be a valid style sheet name from the accountability check report definition.

preference.name: AccountabilityCheckUseRollUpQuantity
preference.preference_description: Activates Accountability Check to count equivalent lines based on the number of lines, their Quantity property value, and their parent's Quantities, in order to determine if they are full or multiple matches. When set to false, the count is based on the number of BOMLines, including packed lines but otherwise not taking the Quantity property into account.

preference.name: Activity_Default_Duration_Time

preference.name: AdditionalAccountabilityCheckProperties
preference.preference_description: Determines the additional properties the system checks when performing an accountability check.An accountability check compares a bill of materials (BOM) with a bill of process (BOP) to ensure all lines in the source BOM are consumed in the target BOP. This allows you to ensure that all occurrences of product components and features are used in the process structure as consumed items. You can compare the entire assembly or only a subassembly to the selected process.The system checks this preference when the Compare additional properties option in the Accountability Checkbox dialog box is selected. Any properties defined by this preference are included in the accountability check. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid property of the selected BOM line.

preference.name: AppInterface_TCPublishingTechnicalPortfolio_shown_relations

Defines the relations available when pasting a TCPublishingTechnicalPortfolio dataset under an intermediate data capture (IDC) while creating technical portfolios. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter relation and it must include the value set for the AppInterface_TCPublishingTechnicalPortfolio_default_relation preference.

preference.name: ArcWeld.CREATERENDERING

BOM lines containing occurrence notes defined in this preference are omitted.Manufacturing baselines are a convenient method of releasing composition/process structures whose contents do not change over time. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values; each string must be a valid occurrence type.

preference.name: CCObject_ColumnWidthPreferences

Valid Values: KeyEntry - Specifies the string that appears as the title attribute in the PLM XML code for the UserValue element. PropEntry - Specifies the string that appears as the value attribute in the PLM XML code for the UserValue element.

preference.name: ConfigureOutParentProcess
preference.preference_description: This preference is obsolete and replaced by the preference "typeAndRuleForProcessConfiguration". Configures Parent processes depending on their child occurrences. Accepted values are: * true: The parent process will be configured out if all of its children operations or subprocesses are configured out. This is the default value. * false: The parent process will not be configured out.

preference.name: CopyPasteTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when pasting processes, operations, and partitions within enterprise bill of process (EBOP) structures or study structures. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter cloning rule.

preference.name: DatumPoint.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for DatumPoint objects.

preference.name: DefaultAccountabilityCheckProperties
preference.preference_description: Determines which properties the system checks by default when performing an accountability check.An accountability check compares a bill of materials (BOM) with a bill of process (BOP) to ensure all lines in the source BOM are consumed in the target BOP. This allows you to ensure that all occurrences of product components and features are used in the process structure as consumed items. You can compare an entire assembly or only a subassembly to the selected process.If the Compare additional properties option in the Accountability Checkbox dialog box is not selected, the values defined in this preference are the only properties upon which the accountability check is performed. preference.name: Default_Collaboration_Context_Type

preference.name: Default_StructureContext_Type
preference.preference_description: Determines which type of structure context is created when saving a loaded object as a context. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid type and be of the following format: item_type:structure_context_type

preference.name: EP_TimeAnalysisMode
preference.preference_description: This preference defines what view should be displayed while working with time detailing of an operation. Valid values are as follows. OPERATOR_ACTIONS : If time detailing is to be done using operator actions. ACTIVITIES : If time detailing is to be done using teamcenter activities. TICON : If time detailing is to be done with ticon application using MTM datacard. The default value is ACTIVITIES.

preference.name: EndItemState
preference.preference_description: Controls the End Item state in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) and Product Structure Engineering (PSE) applications. Valid values are : * true: the "End Item" dialog is displayed in the Edit menu, and the End Item icon appears when an End Item is set on a line's occurrence. This is the default value. * false: the "End Item" functionality is totally hidden.

preference.name: FindCheckedOutColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width of the columns displayed in the dialog of the Find Checked Out Objects command, as defined by the FindCheckedOutColumnsShownPref preference. Valid Values: Accepts positive integers. The number of values should be the same as the number of values in the FindCheckedOutColumnsShownPref preference.

preference.name: GCS_classify_type
preference.preference_description: Determines whether items/item revisions are created and classified for components with connection points. Siemens PLM Software recommends you set this preference to ItemRevision. When assigning connection points to nonclassifying classification objects (ICOs), a new classified object is created to receive the connection points. To make the target object a classified resource, the target ICO must classify a newly-created object, usually an item revision or a similar classified object type. Use this preference to define the target object's type. Siemens PLM Software recommends you set the following preferences to the same value as this preference: MRMClassifyResource, ICS_classify_new, ICS_mapping_target_type. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be Item, ItemRevision, or a valid custom item or item revision type.

preference.name: GDT_formtypes
preference.preference_description: Activates geometric dimensioning and tolerance (GDT) symbols for Teamcenter objects of any sub-type of Form (e.g. "Master Form"). Once a value is given for this preference, the properties that may contain GDT symbols are defined through the "GDT_properties" preference. Valid values are the internal names of any sub-type of Form.

preference.name: GDT_properties
preference.preference_description: Indicates the properties that may contain geometric dimensioning and tolerance (GDT) symbols. The icons associated to GDT symbols addition will be displayed next to the properties fields, provided the property is not a list of values (LOV). Valid values are the properties internal names for the sub-types of Form specified in the preference "GDT_formtypes".

preference.name: GenericBOPAllowedTemplates
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules available when using a generic BOP as a template for the creation of a product BOP. The rules in this preference are displayed in the Cloning Rule menu of the Configuration pane of the Enter Template Information step in the New Product BOP wizard. Valid Values: Accepts a list of names of cloning rules.

preference.name: GenericBOPTemplate

Generic BOP templates are available in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter naming rule. preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances of classified object in a Product Bill of Material (BOM) starting from a Classification. Valid values are in the format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be * for any class, class.<class name> for specific class or type.<type name> for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary * the attribute_key must be one of the following: Attribute, OccType, Relation. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference or Ignore.

preference.name: ItemRevision.MEOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances of classified object in a Operation starting from a Classification. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference or Ignore.

If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference or Ignore.

preference.name: MBMAssignmentDomainMBOMTypes
preference.preference_description: This preference is to specify item types from the MBOM structure which can be used to define the assignment domain relation.

preference.name: MBMChangeManagementWithCSP
preference.preference_description: This preference decides whether to show the change summary panel when a work package is opened in the context of a change notice.

preference.name: MBMCheckoutCheckForFocus
preference.preference_description: If this preference is set to true, user will have to check out the node before focusing on it. If the selected node is not checked out by the same user, user will not be able to focus on it.

preference.name: MBMEnableBOMFiltering
preference.preference_description: This preference allows to perform alignment between sub-sections of EBOM and MBOM by showing only relevant nodes based on a relation.

preference.name: MBMEnableEffectivityValidation
preference.preference_description: Allows user to compare the net effectivity of a part in EBOM and MBOM. If a part does not have effectivity definition on it, net effectivity is effectivity defined on the nearest parent. This effectivity validation is only for Unit effectivity

preference.name: MBMEnableModularMBOM
preference.preference_description: This preference allows to search and add existing manufacturing representations (mini-MBOM) in higher level product context.

preference.name: MBMPasteAsReferenceType
preference.preference_description: When user performs copy-paste action in MBOM, the value mentioned in this preference will be used as a default occurrence type on pasted occurrence. If the preference is empty, no occurrence type value will be assigned.

preference.name: MBMPropertiesForDashRollEquivalence
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of bomline properties that should be considered for finding the equivalent occurrences of parts after a dash roll in EBOM.

preference.name: MBMPropertyForDashRollIdentification
preference.preference_description: Property to identify the dash roll assemblies.

preference.name: MBMRegExForDashRollIdentification
preference.preference_description:
This preference defines the regular expression for the value of the property defined by MBM_PropertyForDashRollIdentification. The part of the property that should be compared to find dashRoll should be enclosed in ().
Default expression is "([^-]+) - \d+" that will match all strings having any sequence of characters except '-' followed by ' - ' followed by digits. The string matching the expression enclosed in parenthesis "[^-]+" will be compared to identify dash roll assemblies.
Example - Given assembly names Engg_Assembly - 001, Engg Assembly - 002, Engg Install - 003 and Engg Assembly001. The names that match the default regular expression are Engg_Assembly - 001, Engg Assembly - 002, Engg Install - 003. The part matching the expression "[^-]+" would be Engg_Assembly, Engg_Assembly and Engg Install. As this value is same for the assemblies Engg_Assembly - 001 and Engg Assembly - 002, they will be considered the dash roll of each other.

preference.name: ME3DPDFAllowedImageDatasetTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of 2D product views and dataset types that are available to choose from when creating new 2D PDF reports. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings which are valid dataset types.

preference.name: ME3DPDFAllowedReportTemplates
preference.preference_description: List of PDF templates, which are available to choose from, for Generate 3D PDF Report command. According to their order, the default template is defined.

preference.name: ME3DPDFEncodingTypes
preference.preference_description: Provides a list of encoding types required by the 3DPDF mechanism when generating reports containing Process Simulate data. The XML files that are used to create the report must be set with an encoding type that supports the specific language in which the report is being generated.The 3DPDF report is generated using the first value in the list. Valid Values: Accepts a list of encoding types supporting the following languages.Windows-1252: French, German, Italian, Spanish, Swedish, Scottish, Portuguese, Irish, Dutch, Albanian, Finnish, Danish, NorwegianWindows-1251: Russian, Bulgarian, Serbian, Ukranian, UzbekGB-2312: Simplified ChineseISO-8859-8: HebrewWindows-1250: Croatian, Czech, Hungarian, Polish, Romanian, Transliterated Serbian, SlovakShift_JIS: JapaneseEUC-KR: KoreanBig5: Traditional Chinese

preference.name: ME3DPDFReportDatasetType
preference.preference_description: Specifies the type of dataset that is created for new PDF reports. Valid Values: A single string which is a valid dataset type derived from Mes0PDFReport.

preference.name: ME3DPDFReportDebugMode
preference.preference_description: This preference will be used to allow debugging environment when set to true. In this case, the translator will run on the client machine and not using dispatcher, and will write more logging information.

preference.name: MEACCOUNTABILITY_MBOM_ASSM_IDIC
preference.preference_description:
Determines whether the accountability check optimization for closure rules like AccountabilityLinkedAssmOrLeaves between 2 BOM structures is enabled. These closure rules consider prior assignment to target structure to traverse the source structure. Valid values: 0 - no optimization for closure rules like AccountabilityLinkedAssmOrLeaves. 1 - optimization for closure rules like AccountabilityLinkedAssmOrLeaves. 2 - in addition to optimization just as value 1, provides support for lines with IDIC (ID In Context) which are in lower level contexts as long as those assemblies are linked to the source structure.
The default value is 1.

preference.name: MEAPCEnableTrueShapeFiltering
preference.preference_description: Enables true shape filtering for "Auto Feature Part Connector" command. The default value is "true".

preference.name: MEAPCSearchType
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of the parts that are searched by the Auto Weld Part Connector dialog box. Valid Values: Accepts a strings as value. The string must be a valid Teamcenter type.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckAllowableReturnedLines
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of lines that can be returned by the accountability check. This includes all the source and target lines to be colored, as well as their parent lines. Valid Values: Accepts a positive integer less than or equal to 10,000.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckEnableDatasetInContextForBOE
preference.preference_description: Determines wheather accountability check considers the In-Context datasets of referenced lines for comparison between Bill of Equipment structures. Valid values: true - The accountability check compares the In-Context datasets of referenced lines and their children. false - The accountability check does not compare the In-Context datasets of referenced lines and their children. The default value is 'true'.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckEnableFilteringRules
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the Expand Below by Filter Rule menu command for the filtering rule verification is enabled. Valid Values: true - The Expand Below by Filter Rule menu command is available. false - The Expand Below by Filter Rule menu command is hidden.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckEnableNetEffectivity
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the net effectivities are compared when the accountability check tests for a partial match. Valid Values: true - Net effectivities are checked. false - Net effectivities are not checked.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckIncludedActivityProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the default list of properties to be included when comparing equivalent activities for partial match when using the accountability check. Valid Values: Accepts an array of strings representing the activity property names.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckIncludedAttachmentRelations
preference.preference_description: Defines the default list of relations to be included when comparing attachment for equivalent process and operation for partial match. The valid values are internal name of a Relation Type.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckParentDelimiterInHierarchy
preference.preference_description: Lists the BOM Line properties to be added as columns to the accountability check Excel report for each source line in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Cells in the column contain the value of the property for each BOM Line. Valid Values: Accepts a list of valid Teamcenter internal property names.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckPropertiesInHierarchy
preference.preference_description: Lists the BOMLine properties to be concatenated for each parent in the value of the property "Hierarchy From Root" (mfg0BlHierarchyFromRoot), which is a concatenation of all parents of a BOMLine. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid property of the parent BOMLine.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckPropertyDelimiterInHierarchy
preference.preference_description: Defines the delimiter to separate the parents of a BOMLine in the hierarchy from root in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid Values: Accepts a list of valid Teamcenter internal property names.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckQuickFavorite.PBOP.PlantBOP
preference.preference_description: Defines which Accountability Check Favorite is to be used to run easy update commands for the direction Product BOP to Plant BOP. Value can be of any of the below two forms : a) <uid>:<Favorite name> b) <uid> where uid is the UID of the dataset and Favorite name is the name of the favorite.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckReportCombineLines
preference.preference_description: Activates the combination of lines in the Accountability Check excel report. When generating report, many lines can show the same information. For example, all packed lines can have the same item ID and property values. In this case, it does make sense to combine them. If the value is "false", the report is generated in the classic manner. The default value is "true".

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckReportProperties
preference.preference_description: Lists the BOM line properties to be added as columns to the accountability check Excel report for each source line in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Cells in the column contain the value of the property for each BOM Line. Valid Values: Accepts a list of valid Teamcenter internal property names.If a team leader or manager needs an accountability check report to verify which BOM lines in a Process view are missing in the source MBOM view, the administrator could add the properties bl_indented_title and bl_sequence_no to the preference. The sections Source Properties and Target Properties would then allow them to compare MBOM source lines and Process view target lines. To get the parent chain of each line in the report, the administrator could then add the property fnd0bl_parent_chain. When the team leader or manager generates the accountability check report, an extra Parent Chain column is displayed in the Source Properties and Target Properties sections . The Parent Chain value is a concatenation of all the parents of the target, starting from the top line parent on the left all the way down to the immediate parent line on the right.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckSourceStructureExpansionFilterRules
preference.preference_description: Provides a list of closure rule names to be used for source structure traversal for accountability check.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckTargetStructureExpansionFilterRules
preference.preference_description: Provides a list of closure rule names to be used for target structure traversal for accountability check.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityKeepNonDynIdicCriteria
preference.preference_description: Defines whether Accountability Check should remove all other criteria when dynamic equivalence mode is choosen. Under the hood, if there is no equivalence set found for a line by one criteria, other criteria can be used. Sometimes this could lead to problem if both IDIC (ID In Context) and dynamic equivalence are used. To avoid such problem, the Accountability check removes all other criteria if dynamic equivalence is used. If the value is "true", the criteria are kept. The default value is false.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityMarkBrokenLinksClosureRule
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the closure rule used by the Mark Broken Links command in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. This command is used to find broken links in process structures. Valid Values: Accepts a valid Teamcenter closure rule.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityMarkBrokenLinksColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the background color used by the Mark Broken Links command in the Manufacturing Process Planner application to mark broken link lines. Valid Values: Accepts a valid RGB (red green blue) code representing a color. This code represents any color as a combination of three digits, each of which is between 0 and 255. The three digits are separated by commas.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityMarkBrokenLinksCountTrigger
preference.preference_description: Specifies the minimum number of broken links that causes an information pane to be displayed by the Mark Broken Links command in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. The pane shows the total number of broken links found by the command. Valid Values: Accepts a positive integer.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityMarkInBaseViewColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the background color used by the Mark In Base View command in the Manufacturing Process Planner application to mark lines in the base view. Valid Values: Accepts a valid RGB (red green blue) code representing a color. This code represents any color as a combination of three digits, each of which is between 0 and 255. The three digits are separated by commas.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityUseCacheless
preference.preference_description: Accelerates the accountability check when part of a BOM source is compared to an entire bill of process (BOP) target and the Missing in Source option is not selected. This functionality relies on the cacheless search in a bill of process. In some cases, such as when using generic design elements (GDEs), this is not supported. If the data has such lines, set the preference value to false. Valid Values: true - The accountability check uses the cacheless search to accelerate the check. false - The accountability does not use the cacheless search to accelerate the check.

preference.name: MEActiveParentColorPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color to be used as highlighting when displaying an active parent for the Paste Here command in the structure view. Valid Values: Accepts a standard supported string, an octal number, or a hexadecimal number. The standard supported strings are: black white lightGray gray darkGray red pink orange yellow green magenta cyan blue The default color is sea green (#50b080).

preference.name: MEActivityCustomTimeProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of customer-defined properties of the CfgActivityLine class that are treated as times in the activity tree of Activities and Time views. The values of these properties are displayed in the time units selected in the Manufacturing section of the Options dialog box. Valid Values: One or more strings in a list. Each string must be a valid customer-defined property.

preference.name: MEActivityTypeColors
preference.preference_description: Specifies the colors associated with the types of activities, as defined in the time_system_category property of the MEActivity class. A color is represented by a string composed of the red, green, and blue values of the color, separated by a decimal point. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as a value. Each string must have the following format: type;color type is a value of the time_system_category property and color is the red, green, and blue values of the corresponding color, separated by decimal point.

preference.name: MEAdditionalPropagatableProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of read-only properties that are displayed in the Propagation Settings dialog box. A property is displayed and selectable for propagation only if it is selected in the Partial Match tab of the Accountability Check dialog box. Valid Values: Accepts a list of valid Teamcenter properties.

preference.name: MEAdvancedSearchResultsViewColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the width of the columns displayed in the Search Result pane in the Structure Search Results view when performing a manufacturing structure search. This setting affects each column defined in the MEAdvancedSearchResultsViewColumnsShownPref preference. Valid Values: Integers that define the number of characters permitted in each column. There should be one value for each column defined in the MEAdvancedSearchResultsViewColumnsShownPref preference, and the values are applied in the same order (that is, the first value in this preference is applied to the first column in the MEAdvancedSearchResultsViewColumnsShownPref and so on).

preference.name: MEAlignedPropertiesList
preference.preference_description: Specifies the supported BOM line properties for alignment initialization, out-of-sync detection and synchronization. This is site preference.

preference.name: MEAlignedPropertiesToExcludeFromDetection
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM line properties to be excluded from out-of-sync alignment detection. The entries are part of a subset of the "MEAlignedPropertiesList" preference. This is site preference.

preference.name: MEAlignedPropertiesToExcludeFromInitialization
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM line properties to be excluded from alignment initialization. The entries are part of a subset of the "MEAlignedPropertiesList" preference. This is site preference.

preference.name: MEAlignedPropertiesToExcludeFromSync
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM line properties to be excluded from alignment synchronization. The entries are part of a subset of the "MEAlignedPropertiesList" preference. This is site preference.

preference.name: MEAlignmentCheckReportDefinition
preference.preference_description: Contains the name of the report definition that controls the creation of the EBOM-MBOM alignment check report. A default report definition is provided but you can supply a custom report definition if necessary. Valid Values: A single character string that contains the name of an existing report definition object.

preference.name: MEAlignmentCheckReportLocation
preference.preference_description: Defines if a persisted EBOM-MBOM alignment report is stored in a dataset in the My Teamcenter Newstuff folder or if it is attached to the item revision of the top line of the target window. Valid Values: 0 - The alignment check report is stored in the Newstuff folder. 1 - The alignment check report is stored on the item revision of the top line of the target window.

preference.name: MEAlignmentCheckReportStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Contains the name of the Microsoft Excel style sheet on which the EBOM-MBOM alignment check report is based. A default style sheet is provided, but you can supply a custom style sheet if necessary. Valid Values: A single character string that contains the name of an existing Microsoft Excel style sheet.

preference.name: MEAllocatedTimeReportDefinitionID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID for the Allocated Time report. Valid Values: Accepts a valid report ID string.

preference.name: MEAllocatedTimeReportStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the XSL style sheet used for the Allocated Time report. Valid Values: Accepts a valid style sheet name.

preference.name: MEAllocationLevel
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of process area that can have an operation or process allocation. If no type is defined, there is no limitation on the operation allocation. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a persistent item subclass, for example: Mfg0MEProcLine The subclass types are not inherited. You must add each new subclass to the preference individually.

preference.name: MEAllowDragDropInBetweenBomlines
preference.preference_description: Activates drag-and-drop of BOM Lines in between any target BOM Lines for BOP structures in the Manufacturing applications. Splitters are displayed when BOM Lines are dragged and placed in between the target BOM Line. Valid Values: *false: the drag-and-drop in between the BOM Lines is not allowed. Splitters are not displayed. This is the default value. *true: the drag-and-drop in between the BOM Lines is allowed. Splitters are displayed.

preference.name: MEAllowDragDropWithinContext
preference.preference_description: Defines the behavior of the drag-and-drop of BOM Lines within context for BOP stuctures in the Manufacturing applications. Valid Values: *0: the drag-and-drop of BOM Lines within context is allowed. This is the default value. *1: the drag-and-drop of BOM Lines within context is blocked.

preference.name: MEAllowedShopFloorCCTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of CCObject types used by Shop Floor Worker. The values are internal names of CCObject types.

preference.name: MEAlternativeDefaultPrefix
preference.preference_description: Specifies the prefix for the new Alternative name.

preference.name: MEAlternativeDefaultReleaseStatus
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default release status to be assigned to cloned objects that do not have any release status. If several values are provided, only the first value is taken into consideration. Valid values are internal names of release statuses.

preference.name: MEAssemblyItemTypesForDatasets
preference.preference_description: Value format: Item_type_internal_name ( one internal item type per line) This should contain the type of the Installable Assembly. If this preference is empty it uses immediate parent to collect the datasets. MEAssemblyItemTypesForDatasets preference defines for which item types there is a need to reflect the datasets on the BOP lines.

preference.name: MEAssignAttachmentAndRelationToUseInCopyRule
preference.preference_description: Defines the attachment and relation types that are referenced or copied when assigning from an EBOM to an MBOM. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values, each string must have the following format: AttachmentType:RelationType:CopyRule AttachmentType and RelationType are the internal names of the attachment and relation types, and CopyRule is either the Copy or Reference rule. Currently, only Reference is supported.For example, if you create a custom form and attach it to an object, the Attachments view is displayed as follows:The attachment type is Customform, and the relation type is Specifications. To define the attachment and relation type for this example, the preference has the following value:Customform:IMAN_specification:ReferenceThe internal name of the relation is IMAN_specification. The internal and display name of the custom form are the same.

preference.name: MEAssignAttachmentContext
preference.preference_description: Indicates the context of the in-context attachments after assignment. Valid Values: TopLine - All in-context attachments are copied or referenced (depending on the value of MEAssignAttachmentAndRelationToUseInCopyRule) to the target structure in the context of the top line of the target structure. DirectParent - All in-context attachments are copied or referenced (depending on the value of MEAssignAttachmentAndRelationToUseInCopyRule) to the target structure in the context of the direct parent of the line being assigned. This is the default value if the preference is not set.

preference.name: MEAssignCustomizedOccurrenceType
preference.preference_description: Determines the Occurrence Type used by default for Paste, Assign and Drag-and-Drop operations. The syntax is "[targetType].[sourceType]:[occurrenceType]" The targetType (to) and sourceType (from) fields can be set to "All" to determine the default for all types that are not specifically listed in the values of this preference. The occurrenceType field can be set to "Empty" to enforce that by default no occurrence type is used.

preference.name: MEAssignProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies BOM line properties that are copied over when assigning from an engineering bill of materials (EBOM) to a manufacturing bill of materials (MBOM) and from a product to a process. Valid Values: Accepts valid internal property names.

preference.name: MEAssignPropertiesInContext
preference.preference_description:
Defines the internal BOMLine property names which will be copied from Engineering Bill of Material(EBOM) to Manufacturing Bill of Material(MBOM), if the property is defined in-context in EBOM. Currently, the only allowed value is: bl_plmxml_abs_xform.
Teamcenter needs to be restarted for any value change to take effect.

preference.name: MEAssign_support_incontext_below_consumed
