preference.preference_description:
Enables the children of consumed Manufacturing Lines in Bill of Process structure to show in-context data. This has a performance impact if turned on. The default value is false.
Teamcenter needs to be restarted for any value change to take effect.

preference.name: MEAssignmentIndicationDefault
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default Accountability Check favorite to be used internally for the Visual Assignment Check feature. Valid Values: Format: AssignmentIndication_Source typeTarget type:Default AC favorite name.

preference.name: MEAssignmentIndicationGraphicsMode
preference.preference_description: Holds the last selected graphics mode in the Visual Assignment Check view. Valid Values: This is an internal preference. Do not modify this value.

preference.name: MEAssignmentIndicationIgnoreObjectType
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types which are excluded for Assignment Indication. Valid values are internal name of object type.

preference.name: MEAssignmentIndicationTransparencyValue
preference.preference_description: Defines the transparency value to be used in the Visual Assignment Check. Valid Values: 0.1 - 0.9

preference.name: MEAssignmentStatesForTarget
preference.preference_description: Specifies the assignment states that are considered to reference the consumed parts in the target structure when cloning or allocating a process structure. When cloning or allocating a process or operation, only the parts that have the assigned states specified in this preference are carried over and consumed by the cloned process or operation.If no value is specified, all the consumed parts are referenced in the target structure. Valid Values: Accepts any of the following values: No State Pending Accepted Rejected

preference.name: MEAssignmentsViewColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the width of the columns displayed in the Assignments view. This setting affects each column defined in the MEAssignmentsViewColumnsShownPref preference. Valid Values: Integers that define the number of characters permitted in each column. There should be one value for each column defined in the MEAssignmentsViewColumnsShownPref preference, and the values are applied in the same order (that is, the first value in this preference is applied to the first column in the MEAssignmentsViewColumnsShownPref and so on).

preference.name: MEAttachmentOpen
preference.preference_description: List of object types that support open functionality in the attachment view.

preference.name: MEAutoReviseWhilePropagation
preference.preference_description: Enables automatic revise of an object while propagating changes if the object is not modifiable due to it's release status(es). However, the object is revised only if the user has write access on it. Currently this functionality is only supported for Alternative use-cases.

preference.name: MEAvailableTimeUnits
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of customized (additional) available time units. Each value contains a unique unit ID in English and a multiplier to convert from this unit to seconds (default unit). Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values, each string must be formatted as follows: unitID:multiplierToSeconds For example: myTimeUnitID:112.25

preference.name: MEBOEStationTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the types to be designated as Bill of Equipment (BOE) Station types. The values only need to change if new subclasses have been derived from MEWorkArea to represent BOE station types. Valid values are type internal names. Note:Teamcenter needs to be restarted for any change to take effect.

preference.name: MEBOPToBOEObjectTypeMap
preference.preference_description: Specifies the XML dataset name which has the object type mappings and their attribute mappings. These details are used while creating a Bill of Equipment (BOE) structure from a Plant Bill of Process (BOP) structure or vice versa.

preference.name: MEBlankDisplayTypes
preference.preference_description: Stores commonly used types (item, plant, and occurrence) that you want to display or blank using the Display by Type or Blank by Type commands in Manufacturing Process Planner, Part Planner, or Plant Designer. The values you list in this preference appear in the list of available types in the menu command. You can also set this preference in the rich client interface by choosing Edit->Options->Manufacturing and clicking the Graphics tab. Valid Values: Accepts a list of string values. Each entry in the list must be of the following format: structure-type:type-name For example: Product:Item Product:WeldPoint Plant:MEWorkArea Occurrence:MEConsumed

preference.name: MECTRevisionChangeAddAdditional
preference.preference_description: Controls whether additional objects are output by the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML for removed and replaced change elements, as controlled by the closure rule specified by the "MECTRevisionChangeClosureRule" preference. Valid values are true or false.

preference.name: MECTRevisionChangeClosureRule
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the closure rule to be used for outputting additional objects in the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML for removed and replaced change elements as controlled by the "MECTRevisionChangeAddAdditional" preference. If not specified, the closure rule "AccountabilityAll" is used. Valid value is the name of a closure rule.

preference.name: MECTRevisionReportStyleSheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the Dataset that contains the XSL stylesheet to be used for the change tracker revision detail report in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MECheckResultItemDisplayColumnPreferenceNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties displayed in the columns of "Check Result View Violation Tables" panel in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MECheckResultItemDisplayColumnPreferenceWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the width (in pixels) of the column in the "Check Result View Objects Table" panel as defined by the preference MECheckResultItemDisplayColumnPreferenceNames.

preference.name: MECheckResultViewViolationTableWidths
preference.preference_description: Defines the width (in pixels) of the violation and the description columns in the "Check Results View Violation Table".

preference.name: MEClosureRuleEditorDefaultClosureRules
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of closure rules which will be available in Closure Rule Editor view of Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP). Valid values are the closure rule names used for Briefcase export. The default value is "TIEExportDefaultCR".

preference.name: MEClosureRuleNameForIsolatedStudySyncPublish
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the closure rule to be used for sync and publish operations of Isolated Study.

preference.name: MECollectionTypeProcesses
preference.preference_description: Defines the Process types for which the allocated time calculation will ignore flows and will interpret the sub-processes or operations in sequence defined by the find number. For these types, the allocated time will be computed identically to the work time. The line balancing chart will only show children of processes of this type. Valid values are the internal name of the type Process (MEProcess) and any of its sub-types.

preference.name: MECompositionMismatchPropertyName
preference.preference_description: This preference indicate whether the current revision of the underlying component is different than the revision during assignment. Valid Values: "fnd0CompositionRevMismatch": an indication icon will be shown All other values: no indication icon will be shown. The default value is empty.

preference.name: MEConfigureStructuresDisplayNameColumnShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns displayed in "Configure Structures" dialog in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. The valid column names are: revision_rule, variant_rules, Mfg0VisibilityUncnfVar, Mfg0VisibilitySuppOcc, Mfg0VisibilityUncnfChanges, Mfg0VisibilityUncnfOccEff, Mfg0VisibilityUncnfAssgnOcc, Fnd0EffectvtyGrpList, Fnd0Effectvty. The column names are the internal names of the properties.

preference.name: MEConsiderFlowsOnReSequence
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default state of the Consider flows check box in the Re-sequence dialog box in Manufacturing Process Planner and Part Planner. After the first time you open the dialog box, the check box state is stored in a cookie. see Manufacturing Process Planner or the Part Planner. Valid Values: true - The Consider flows check box is selected. false - The Consider flows check box is cleared.

preference.name: MEConstraintsViewAutomaticLayoutOffAppendPositionPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the position of nodes newly added to the Line Balancing Constraints view.If the automatic layout mode is turned off, Teamcenter places new nodes into the Line Balancing Constraints view in the position defined by this preference. When calculating where to put the node, Teamcenter draws an imaginary box around all existing nodes, and then places the new node in one of three positions-bottom left, bottom right, or top right of the existing nodes. Valid Values: LOWER_LEFT - Places a new node at the bottom left of existing nodes. LOWER_RIGHT - Places a new node at the bottom right of existing nodes. UPPER_RIGHT - Places a new node at the top right of existing nodes.

preference.name: MEConstraintsViewDefaultAutomaticLayoutModePref
preference.preference_description: Defines the initial state of the Automatic Layout button when opening a new Line Balancing Constraints view. When on, Teamcenter automatically organizes the placement of nodes after each operation that you perform in the view, such as adding or deleting nodes, or adding or deleting constraints. Valid Values: true - The automatic layout mode is turned on by default.

preference.name: MECopyAssemblyInContextTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when copying a subassembly within BOM structures. Valid Values: You can define different rules for different types of items. For example, you can create a custom business object (item type) called x and then create a preference called x.x.CopyAssemblyInContext that defines rules for objects of type x that are different from the rules for items of type Item. If you then add x.x.CopyAssemblyInContext to MECopyAssemblyInContextTemplates, Teamcenter follows those rules.

preference.name: MECopyIdInContextLowerLevels
preference.preference_description: Determines if the in-context ID is copied to the assigned line for the subprocesses and suboperations during an assignment operation.See also the MECopyIdInContextToAssignedLine preference. Valid Values: True - The in-context ID is copied only for the items that are assigned to the subprocesses and suboperations during an assignment operation. The in-context ID of the subprocess or suboperation is not copied. False - The in-context ID is not copied to the assigned line for the subprocesses and suboperations during an assignment operation.

preference.name: MECopyIdInContextToAssignedLine
preference.preference_description: Determines if the in-context ID is copied to the assigned line during an assignment operation. When this preference is set to True, you do not have to expand a target structure before performing an accountability check or when using the Find in Other Panel menu command. Valid Values: True - The in-context ID is copied to the assigned line during an assignment operation. If no in-context ID is present, Teamcenter creates one and then copies it. False - The in-context ID is not copied (even if one is present) to the assigned line during an assignment operation.

preference.name: MECreateFipaStructure
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of "Filtered In Process Assembly" structure to be created in a Process structure. Valid values are "Nested" (default) and "Flat".

preference.name: MECurrentTimeUnit
preference.preference_description: Defines the ID of the time unit (as defined in the MEAvailableTimeUnits preference) in which all new time data is displayed. Set this value using the Time pane in the ME section of the preferences interface for the change to take effect without restarting the application. Valid Values: Accepts a string as value that must be one of the out of the box time unit IDs listed below or one of the IDs from the MEAvailableTimeUnits preference. This value must be in English. second minute 10th_min 100th_min 1000th_min hour day TMU MOD FAC

preference.name: MECustomViewArcWeldColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the width of each column defined in the preference "MECustomViewArcWeldColumnsShownPref".

preference.name: MECustomViewAttachmentsCommandNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the commands to be displayed above the attachments table in the right hand side section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are the IDs of each command in the order they are to appear: value_1, value_2. Each command is executed on the selection in the table. Optionally specify 'parent' after the command ID, separated by semicolon, to indicate that the command should be executed on the parent operation instead. Example: 'com.teamcenter.rac.checkoutProperties;parent'.

preference.name: MECustomViewAttachmentsIncluded
preference.preference_description: Defines which attachment lines should be included in the attachments table in the right hand side section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. The lines are filtered by object type and relation type. The asterisk character '*' can be used for either type to specify that all types are valid. Each value specifies an inclusion condition. All lines that meet the condition of at least one value are included. Valid values are the internal object and relation type names, separated by the semicolon character ';': "object_type;relation_type". Examples: "MSWord;IMAN_MEWorkInstruction": all MS Word documents that are attached as Work Instruction "Text;*": all Text attachments "*;IMAN_specification": all attachments that are attached as Specification

preference.name: MECustomViewChildHeaderCommandNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the commands to be displayed at the top of the child header section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are the IDs of each command in the order they are to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: MECustomViewChildLinesColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns defined in the preference "MECustomViewChildLinesColumnsShownPref".

preference.name: MECustomViewChildLinesCommandNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the commands to be displayed above the table in the left side of the Custom Process View in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts the IDs of each command in the order they should appear. command-1 command-2

preference.name: MECustomViewChildLinesCommandNames.PBOP
preference.preference_description: Defines the commands to be displayed above the table in the left hand side section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application if the scope of the Custom view is a line from a Product BOP structure. Valid values are the IDs of each command in the order they are to appear: value_1, value_2. Each command is executed on the selection in the table. Optionally specify 'parent' after the command ID, separated by semicolon, to indicate that the command should be executed on the parent process instead. Example: 'com.teamcenter.rac.checkoutProperties;parent'.

preference.name: MECustomViewChildLinesCommandNames.PlantBOP
preference.preference_description: Defines the commands to be displayed above the table in the left hand side section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application if the scope of the Custom view is a line from a Plant BOP structure. Valid values are the IDs of each command in the order they are to appear: value_1, value_2. Each command is executed on the selection in the table. Optionally specify 'parent' after the command ID, separated by semicolon, to indicate that the command should be executed on the parent process instead. Example: 'com.teamcenter.rac.checkoutProperties;parent'.

preference.name: MECustomViewConsumedItemsColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns defined in the preference "MECustomViewConsumedItemsColumnsShownPref".

preference.name: MECustomViewConsumedItemsCommandNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the commands to be displayed above each table on the right side of the Custom Process View in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts the IDs of each command in the order they should appear. command-1 command-2...

preference.name: MECustomViewConsumedItemsOccTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the occurrence types for each table that is displayed on the right side on the Custom Process View in Manufacturing Process Planner. Each entry in this preference creates a new table on the right side of the view. see Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts valid Manufacturing Process Planner occurrence types in the order the tables should appear.

preference.name: MECustomViewDatumPointsColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the width of each column defined in the preference "MECustomViewDatumPointsColumnsShownPref".

preference.name: MECustomViewMainHeaderCommandNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the commands to be displayed at the top of the main header section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are the IDs of each command in the order they are to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: MECustomViewPropertiesToEdit
preference.preference_description: Defines the BOM line properties that can be edited in the main and child header sections in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are the internal name of the BOM line property. Only string type properties are supported. Examples: "bl_rev_object_desc", "bl_item_object_desc", "bl_sequence_no".

preference.name: MECustomViewShowMfgFeatures
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of consumed Manufacturing Features in the Custom Process view. The default value is false.

preference.name: MECustomViewWeldPointsColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the width of each column defined in the preference "MECustomViewWeldPointsColumnsShownPref".

preference.name: MEDataPanelPosition
preference.preference_description: Specifies where to open the data pane of a structure, either to the right of the structure or below the structure. Valid Values: right - Displays the data pane to the right of the structure. bottom - Displays the data pane below the structure.

preference.name: MEDataSetsToBeCheckoutForProcessSimulate
preference.preference_description: Indicates which datasets to check out when running any of the scenarios that include datasets. It stores pairs of dataset types and relations. Valid Values: Accepts string values with the following format: Dataset type:Relation

preference.name: MEDatasetsToBeReflectedOnBOP
preference.preference_description: Value format: Dataset_internal_name:relation_internal_name (one dataset-relation pair per line) This is a main preference that controls the feature and should be non-empty, otherwise feature is disabled. It defines which dataset type and relation pairs should be reflected on BOP lines.

preference.name: MEDefaultActivityType
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default type of a new activity created in the Activity section in the operation Times pane in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts a string as a value. The value must be MEActivity or the name of a derived class.

preference.name: MEDelegatedOccurrenceProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of internal BOM Line properties to be delegated for lines assigned from the Product structure to the Bill Of Process (BOP) structure. Only the following properties are supported: bl_occ_effectivity (Occurrence Effectivity), bl_formula (Variant Formula), bl_quantity (Quantity), bl_plmxml_abs_xform (Absolute Transformation Matrix), bl_occurrence_name (Occurrence Name), bl_abs_occ_all_ids (ID In Context All Levels), bl_variant_condition (Variant Conditions), bl_all_notes (All Notes).

preference.name: MEDepartment.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for MEDepartment objects.

preference.name: MEDesignToBomAlignmentProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM Line properties to be included during alignment between Design and Part assemblies. The "bl_abs_occ_id" property is synchronized implicitly and should not be listed in this preference. Valid values are BOM Line property internal names.

preference.name: MEDesignToBomChildAlignmentProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM Line properties to be included during alignment between Design and child BOM Line representing that Design under Part assembly. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself. Valid values are BOM Line property internal names.

preference.name: MEDesignToBomFindDesignsSearchCriteriaProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of BOM Line properties used by search for design candidates when no candidates are found by IDIC or absolute transform. The default list is empty.

preference.name: MEDesign_default_non_bom_align_mode
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to create a light or heavy alignment when pasting a design revision to the "RepresentedBy" Pseudo folder of "PartRevision" in MyTeamcenter application. Valid Values: light - Represents light alignment. heavy - Represents heavy alignment. Values are not case sensitive. Teamcenter needs to be restarted for any value change to take effect.

preference.name: MEDisplayOccurrenceType
preference.preference_description: Defines the conditions to display occurrence types while pasting objects in the Manufacturing Process Planner rich client. This preference is used, for example, in the Paste As, Paste Special, and Assign Resource commands and in the Occurrence Type column visible in Bill of Materials (BOM) views. Valid Values: List of:*:target-type:source-type:comma-separated-preference-names Example: MEProcess:Item:MERelationTypePartsAssembled,MERelationTypePartsAssigned The wildcard (*) is only supported for target and source. Example: *:Item:MERelationTypePartsAssembled The occurrence types specified in these preferences are displayed to the user. The order in which preferences are specified is important because the occurrence type from the first preference is displayed first, followed by the occurrence type from other preferences.The order of entries in this preference is important. For a given target and source type, the list is evaluated from top to bottom and the first matching entry is considered for the evaluation of occurrence type. To get a correct match, the target and source object type should be same or a sub class of respective types specified in the entry.If the value of this preference is blank or the conditions are not satisfied, all occurrence types available in the system are displayed to the user. For multiple target (or source) objects of different types, the common occurrence types are shown. If one of the source and target pairs has no occurrence types defined, the system will assume all occurrence types are valid for that pair, and will perform an intersection to find common occurrence types for the other pairs. If no common occurrence types are found, an indication of that will be shown to the user.This preference can be edited to add new entries with custom-defined preference types and custom-defined objects to change an existing condition and to change the order of existing conditions. Following the edit, client/server relaunch is not required.If the default occurrence type for a given source and target, as specified in the MEAssignCustomizedOccurrenceType preference, is not mentioned in the below preference list for that source and target, the system automatically appends it to the list.

preference.name: MEDisplayOnAssign
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of assigned parts in the corresponding graphics in the Paste command of the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid Values: true false

preference.name: MEDoNotUseSCTypeForColumns
preference.preference_description: Specifies item revision business object types that have their own preferences to define columns in the primary view of a structure context. Other business object types displayed in the primary view of a structure context use structure context column preferences.In other words, when a structure context is opened in a BOM primary view in Manufacturing Process Planner or Part Planner, a tree table displays the data. The columns in this tree table are controlled by preferences. The preference names can be prefixed by the structure context business object type or by the top line item revision business object type. The default preference is the structure context type, unless the type of the item revision appears in this preference, in which case, the item revision preferences are used.For example, if there is a structure context that is a MySC business object type and the top line item revision is a MyItemRev business object type, the following occurs:If the MyItemRev type appears in the MEDoNotUseSCTypeForColumns preference, the preferences that are used for the columns in the BOM tree table are: MyItemRevColumnsShownPrefMyItemRevDisplayNameColumnsShownPrefMyItemRevShownColumnWidthsPrefIf the MyItemRev type does not appear in the MEDoNotUseSCTypeForColumns preference, the preferences that are used for the columns in the BOM tree table are: MySCColumnsShownPref MySCDisplayNameColumnsShownPref MySCShownColumnWidthsPref Valid Values:: Subtypes of the ItemRevision business object.

preference.name: MEDuplicateAssemblyInContextTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when duplicating a subassembly within BOM structures. Valid Values: You can define different rules for different types of items. For example, you can create a custom business object (item type) called x and then create a preference called x.x.DuplicateAssemblyInContext that defines rules for objects of type x that are different from the rules for items of type Item. If you then add x.x.DuplicateAssemblyInContext to MEDuplicateAssemblyInContextTemplates, Teamcenter follows those rules.

preference.name: MEDynamicIPADisableRepopulateForPS
preference.preference_description: Disables automatic repopulation for Dynamic In-Process Assembly (DIPA) objects for process simulate. The default value is "false".

preference.name: MEDynamicIPADisplayName
preference.preference_description: Determines the property of the predecessor in the given Process Structure to be considered when generating the name of the In-Process Assembly. A valid value is one of the following Plant BOP Line properties: "bl_item_object_name", "bl_rev_object_name".

preference.name: MEDynamicIPAOccurrenceTypes
preference.preference_description: Determines which Occurrence types to aggregate from predecessors in the given Process Structure to generate the In-Process Assembly (IPA). The default value is the Occurrence type "MEConsumed".

preference.name: MEDynamicIPARecursiveCreateProcessTypes
preference.preference_description: Determines Bill Of Process(BOP) object types to recursively generate the In-Process Assembly (IPA) in Sub-Hierarchies. The default values are "Mfg0MEProcStatnRevision" and "MEProcessRevision".

preference.name: MEDynamicIPARemoveOccTypes
preference.preference_description: Determines which occurrence types to consider for removal from aggregated parts of the predecessors in the given process structure to generate the dynamic in-process assembly (DIPA). Valid Values: Accepts the name of a valid Teamcenter occurrence type.

preference.name: MEDynamicIPARootItemTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the types of root Item allowed for Product Structures that are part of a Dynamic In-Process Assembly (DIPA). The default value is "Item".

preference.name: MEDynamicIPATraversalClosureRule
preference.preference_description: Determines the closure rule to be used for traversal of the Process Structure, to calculate dynamic In-Process Assembly. The default value is "DynamicIPAProcessOnlyWithPA".

preference.name: MEEnableItemAsResourceInBOE
preference.preference_description: Enables comaparision of the Item or Part which do not have occurence type in Bill of Equipment(BOE) in the Manufacturing applications. Valid Values: *false: Accountability check will not compare the Item or Part as a resource assignment. *true: Accountability check will compare the Item or Part as a resource assignment.

preference.name: MEEnableScopeFlowsForConfiguredRevision
preference.preference_description: This preference enables the scope flows only for configured revision of the least common parent.

preference.name: MEExpandFirstLevelOnLoad
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the root node of a structure (product, process or plant) is expanded to the first level when it is opened in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: true - The root node is expanded when opened in Manufacturing Process Planner. false - The root node is not expanded when opened in Manufacturing Process Planner.

preference.name: MEExpandToBaseTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types to be displayed in Manufacturing "Expand To Type" dialog when the selected line is of type "Process". For a given value, its associated subtypes will also to be considered. By default, the base types are MEOP and MEProcess.

preference.name: MEExpandToSelection
preference.preference_description: Specifies the behavior of the selection synchronization in manufacturing applications. Depending on the value of this preference, when using commands such as Find in other structure, Teamcenter expands the other hierarchy and highlights the selection. Valid Values: true - The synchronizing view partially expands to the selected line and highlights it. false - The synchronizing view highlights the selected line only if it is currently expanded. If a hierarchy was previously expanded and then collapsed, Teamcenter considers it collapsed. If the structure is collapsed, nothing is highlighted.

preference.name: MEFIPAErrorLinesColumnsWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the columns (identified by MEFIPAErrorLinesColumnsShownPref) displayed in the Filter Assembly Tree error dialogs.

preference.name: MEFilterIPARefObjColumnsShown
preference.preference_description: Indicates the default columns of the Reference Objects Table displayed during Assembly Tree Filtering in MSE.

preference.name: MEFilterIPARefObjColumnsWidth
preference.preference_description: Indicates the width of default columns (identified by preference MEFilterIPARefObjColumnsShown) of the Reference Objects Table displayed during Assembly Tree Filtering in MSE.

preference.name: MEFilteredChildTypes_MEOP_Mfg0MECompOP
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types that can be created under the Compound Operation.

preference.name: MEFormsToBeCheckoutForProcessSimulate
preference.preference_description: Indicates which forms to check out. It stores pairs of form types and the relation. Valid Values: Accepts string values with the following format: Type:Relation

preference.name: MEGANTTColumnPreferenceWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the width (in pixels) of the column in the Gantt tree as defined by the preference MEGANTTColumnPreferenceNames.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultDisplayMode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default display mode is used on startup of a Gantt chart viewer. Valid Values: show_calculated_duration_time - Displays the calculated startup time of a Gantt chart viewer using the calculated duration bar that appears on top of the duration bar of each level that has descendants. hide_calculated_duration_time - Hides the calculated startup time of a Gantt chart viewer. The calculated duration bar does not appear.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultDurationTimeColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default color the duration time bar has in the representation area of the Gantt chart viewer. For example, 0;0;0 represents the color black and 0;255;255 represents the color aqua. Valid Values: String of the format int;int;int with int:=0|1|2|..|255.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultEditMode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default edit mode used on startup of a Gantt chart viewer. Valid Values: full_edit_mode - Specifies the full edit mode to be used on startup of a Gantt chart viewer. In the full edit mode, you can use the toolbar buttons to edit the elements in the Gantt chart viewer. restricted_edit_mode - Specifies the restricted edit mode to be used on startup of a Gantt chart viewer. In the restricted edit mode, you can still change the duration of an element using the context menu of the element.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultFlowColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default color a flow has in the representation area of the Gantt chart viewer. For example, 0;0;0 represents the color black and 0;255;255 represents the color aqua. Valid Values: String of the format int;int;int with int:=0|1|2|..|255.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultMarkedColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default color a marked element has in the representation area of the Gantt chart viewer. For example, 0;0;0 represents the color black and 0;255;255 represents the color aqua. Valid Values: String of the format int;int;int with int:=0|1|2|..|255.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultSelectionColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) code for the color of selected objects in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. A valid value is a triplet of integers from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTDisplayNameColumnPreferenceNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the TCComponents properties displayed in the columns of Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Each entry is the internal name of a TCComponent property.

preference.name: MEGANTTElementHeight
preference.preference_description: Specifies the height of one element of the Gantt chart in the navigation and the representation area (the amount of pixels that are used for one element). There is no space between the elements (10 elements use 10 times the space of one element). Valid Values: Positive integers.

preference.name: MEGANTTElementRGBfillColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default fill color of the elements in red, green blue (RGB) code. For example, 0;0;0 represents the color black and 0;255;255 represents the color aqua. Valid Values: String of the format int;int;int with int:=0|1|2|..|255.

preference.name: MEGANTTImplicitFlowColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) code for the color of implicit flows in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTMarkedFlowColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default color a marked flow has in the representation of the Gantt chart viewer. For example, 0;0;0 represents the color black and 0;255;255 represents the color aqua. Valid Values: String of the format int;int;int with int:=0|1|2|..|255.

preference.name: MEGANTTName
preference.preference_description: Defines the property of the component that will be used to be displayed as its name in the Gantt charts of the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevel
preference.preference_description: Specifies the level up to which the duration propagation is executed in the Gantt chart when running the Propagate Calculated Duration command. The number of levels is counted from the top level object downwards.This value is only used if the MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevelEnabled preference is set to True, otherwise, Teamcenter propagates to level 0. Valid Values: A positive integer number (including 0). Setting this value to 0 indicates that all levels are propagated up.

preference.name: MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevelEnabled
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the Propagate up to level option is enabled in the Duration Propagation dialog box in the Gantt view and whether the value of the MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevel preference is used. In other words, if this preference is set to False, and the value of MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevel is set to 3, Teamcenter propagates up to level 0, as it ignores the value set in MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevel. Valid Values: True - The Propagate up to level option is enabled in the Duration Propagation dialog box. False - The Propagate up to level option is not enabled in the Duration Propagation dialog box.

preference.name: MEGenerateAssemblyTreeOccurrenceTypes
preference.preference_description: >Lists the Process types presented in Generate Assembly Tree command of the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application.

preference.name: MEGenerateAssemblyTreeProcessTypes
preference.preference_description: Lists the Occurrence types presented in Generate Assembly Tree command of the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for MEGenericBOP objects.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.MEGenericBOP.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste" operation is used to create new instances in a Generic Bill of Processes (BOP) starting from a Generic BOP.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.MEGenericBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the default cloning rule used when the Paste Duplicate command is executed between one generic BOP context and another generic BOP context. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter naming rule. Naming rules are created in Business Modeler IDE. see Business Modeler IDE.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.MEProductBOP.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste" operation is used to create new instances in a Product Bill of Processes (BOP) starting from a Generic BOP.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.MEProductBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the default cloning rule used when the Paste Duplicate command is executed between a generic BOP context and a product BOP context. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter naming rule. Naming rules are created in Business Modeler IDE. see Business Modeler IDE.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.Mfg0MEPlantBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the default cloning rule used when the Paste Duplicate command is executed between a generic BOP context and a plant BOP context. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter cloning rule.

preference.name: MEHideChangesIconsForAttributes
preference.preference_description: Controls the display of the incremental change and the in-context edit symbols on the BOM structure. By default, symbols appear for all attribute changes in a structure. Adding an attribute to this list eliminates the display of the change symbols for this attribute. The changes are still recorded (either in the incremental change or the context) but the symbols are not displayed. Valid Values: Valid property names for structure data overrides, for example, bl_sequence_no.

preference.name: MEIgnoreICForReleaseStatus
preference.preference_description: Specifies the release statuses for which incremental changes are not tracked in an incremental change (IC) context even if the IC is turned on. Valid Values: Accepts the internal name of a release status.

preference.name: MEImportMFGsManufacturingFeatureIdAttributeName
preference.preference_description: Specifies which BOM line property is used as the manufacturing feature ID when importing weld points, weld arcs, and datums from an external system. Valid Values: Any valid occurrence note.

preference.name: MEImportMFGsPartIdAttributeName
preference.preference_description: Specifies which BOM line property is used as the part ID when importing manufacturing weld points, weld arcs, and datums from an external system. Valid Values: Any valid occurrence note.

preference.name: MEImportMFGsUseAbsoluteLocation
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the Import Manufacturing Features command applies the transformation to manufacturing features, as written in the PLM XML. Valid Values: true - The transformation is applied as absolute location. false - The transformation is applied as relative location.

preference.name: MEIncrementalChangeMode
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether incremental change is applied per application or per structure in Manufacturing Process Planner, Part Planner, and Plant Designer. Valid Values: application - Incremental change works per application. If you set an incremental change, it is set for all the loaded structures. structure - Incremental change works per structure. If you set an incremental change, it is relevant only for the selected structure and for the secondary views connected to the selected structure. In this mode, each structure can use its own incremental change.

preference.name: MELBBalancingOverviewReportID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID of the report definition used for the Line Balancing Overview report. Valid Values: Accepts the ID of an existing Line Balancing Overview report.

preference.name: MELBBalancingOverviewStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the XSL stylesheet to be used for the line balancing overview report in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MELBChartColors
preference.preference_description: Specifies the colors used in the line balancing chart. Valid Values: Type - Specifies the object to be colored in the defined fashion. This is a mandatory keyword. Valid values are NormalSpecifies the color scheme for normal objects.SelectionSpecifies the color scheme for selected objects.HighlightSpecifies the color scheme for highlighted objects, the negative values of the TimesPerBar class, and the tooltip entries marking a subgroup.LimitViolationSpecifies the color scheme for objects above the capacity line.EmphasizedSpecifies the color scheme for operations with probability strictly lower than 100%.EmphasizedLimitViolationSpecifies the color scheme for operations with probability strictly lower than 100% and above the capacity line.DimmedSpecifies the color scheme for separation lines for subgroup entries.GridSpecifies the color scheme for grid lines.LimitLineSpecifies the color scheme for the capacity line. Class - Specifies the class type that is colored for color types. This keyword is mandatory. Valid values are OperationSpecifies boxes displayed in the bar area representing processes and operations.StationSpecifies boxes displayed in the axis area representing stations.CycleTimeLinesSpecifies the horizontal lines representing the multiple of the cycle time.CapacityLineSpecifies the line that shows the capacity of each station.AverageLineSpecifies the horizontal line that shows the height of the average work content over the different product variants.TimesPerBarSpecifies the time values shown on the top of each bar.OverlaySpecifies the box showing the maximum and minimum work contents of all product variants.TooltipSpecifies the tooltip area, including the fill colors and color of text.TooltipSeparatorSpecifies the lines between tooltip entries.Teamcenter uses the Operation value as default. Foreground and Background - Specifies the fill colors of boxes representing operations and stations. Valid values consist of red, green, and blue color values separated by a comma. This field is ignored for the Grid and LimitLine color types and can be left blank. LineColor - Specifies the color of lines for Grid and LimitLine color types. For all others, this value specifies the border color. Valid values consist of red, green, and blue color values separated by a comma. TextColor - Specifies the color of text. Valid values consist of red, green, and blue color values separated by a comma.

preference.name: MELBChartDnDSourceTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether you can drag and drop processes or operations in the line balancing chart. Valid Values: Internal names of MEOP or any of its subtypes.Internal names of MEProcess or any of its subtypes.MEProcess enables drag and drop for all process types.

preference.name: MELBChartDnDTargetParentTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the types of parent objects to which processes or operations can be dropped in the line balancing chart.This can include processes as well as process area types. Valid Values: Internal names of MEProcess or any of its subtypes.Internal names of Mfg0MEProcArea or any of its subtypes.

preference.name: MELBChartProcessOperationTypeDefaultValues
preference.preference_description: Specifies which types of objects have view options (View Menu->View Options) in the line balancing chart.This preference lets users quickly change the MELBChartProcessOperationType preference from the line balancing chart interface. Valid Values: ValueDescriptionMEOPOperation.MEProcessProcess.custom-object-nameIf an assembly line uses multiple types of operations, an administrator can define custom values for each. For example, if an assembly line planner wants to limit processes and operations in the line balancing chart view so that only riveting and welding operations are visible, the administrator can define these custom views and give them custom names such as MERivetOP, MERivetProcess, MEWeldOP, and MEWeldProcess. The planner can then quickly switch between them in the line balancing chart view options.

preference.name: MELBChartProcessOperationTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the types of objects used as processes or operations, and whether processes with no operations, or operations with processes, are shown in the line balancing chart.Substructures are ignored even if they contain objects of the types included in this preference.Users can quickly change this preference in the line balancing chart by choosing View Menu->View Options->MEProcess or MEOP. View options can also include custom names defined in MELBChartProcessOperationTypeDefaultValues. Valid Values: Internal names of MEProcess or any of its subtypes.Internal names of MEOP or any of its subtypes.MEProcess enables drag and drop for all process types.

preference.name: MELBChartStationNameDisplayPattern
preference.preference_description: Defines the display pattern of the station line names in the Line Balancing Chart view in Manufacturing Process Planner.The Line Balancing Chart view uses regular expressions as patterns to display only particular portions of the station line names. The parts to be displayed are marked by groups. The corresponding part strings of the names are displayed.For example, when applying the pattern .*([sS]t)ation([ .0-9]*).* to station line name 000140/A;1-station 1.1 for the assembling front axle, the string st matches the regular expression group ([sS]t), and the string 1.1 matches the regular expression group ([ .0-9]*).The result is that the display string is st 1.1 for this pattern. Valid Values: Accepts a valid regular expression that matches the station line names. The regular expression must contain at least one group.If the pattern is not defined correctly or if no group is defined, Teamcenter displays the original line name text.The following examples shows some patterns and corresponding results for the line name 000140/A;1-station 1.1 for assembling front axle.PatternResult[ 0]*([0-9]*)/.*140.*(station.*)station 1.1 for assembling front axle.*([sS]t)ation([ .0-9]*).*st 1.1

preference.name: MELBChartStationTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the types of process areas used as stations on the X axis of the line balancing chart.If this preference is empty, Teamcenter uses the MEAllocationLevel preference value. If MEAllocationLevel is empty, the line balancing chart uses objects of the type Mfg0MEProcArea. Valid Values: Internal names of Mfg0MEProcArea or any of its subtypes.

preference.name: MELBConstraintsConsistencyReportID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID of the report definition used for the constraints consistency report. Valid Values: Accepts an existing ID of a Constraints Consistency Check report.

preference.name: MELBConstraintsConsistencyStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the XSL style sheet used for the Constraints Consistency Check report. Valid Values: Accepts an XSL file name, for example, myConsistencyReport.xsl.

preference.name: MELBConstraintsViolationReportID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID of the report definition used for the Constraints Violation Check report. Valid Values: Accepts the ID of an existing Constraints Violation Check report.

preference.name: MELBConstraintsViolationStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the XSL style sheet used for the Constraints Violation Check report. Valid Values: Accepts an XSL file name, for example, MyConstraintsViolationReport.xsl.

preference.name: MELBLineDetailReportID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID of the report definition used for the Balancing Line Detail report. Valid Values: Accepts the ID of an existing Balancing Line Detail report.

preference.name: MELBLineDetailStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the XSL style sheet used for the Balancing Line Detail report. Valid Values: Accepts an XSL file name, for example, MyLBLineDetailReport.xsl.

preference.name: MELeadPlantBOPDefaultPrefix
preference.preference_description: Specifies the prefix for the derived Collaboration Context.

preference.name: MELeadPlantBOPDefaultReleaseStatus
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default release status to be assigned to the objects in cloned structures of Lead Plant BOP Collaboration Context in case these objects do not have any release status. Valid values are the release statuses internal names.

preference.name: MELine.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for MELine objects.

preference.name: MELoadAllLinkedStructures
preference.preference_description: Enables auto-loading of all the linked product structures and plant structures to a Bill of Process or Plant Bill of Process. Valid Values: true : it auto-loads all the linked product structures and plant structures to a Bill of Process or Plant Bill of Process. false: behavior will be based on preference "MSE_load_related_product_process_plant". Note: It would work, if the preference "MSE_load_related_product_process_plant" is set to "true"

preference.name: MELogicalDesignatorDelimiter
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delimiter in the displayed name of the logical designator form. The format is:value_1this_preference_value....value_nthis_preference_value Valid Values: Any character.

preference.name: MELogicalDesignatorFormNameSuffix
preference.preference_description: Specifies the suffix to the logical designator form. The form name for operations or processes is:item_id-this_preference_valueThe form name for partitions is:partition_name-this_preference_value Valid Values: Any string.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairAbsXformAngularTolerance
preference.preference_description: Defines the proximity value (in degrees) under which variations in the rotation section of a transform are seen as equal. The default value is 0.1 degree.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairAbsXformTranslationTolerance
preference.preference_description: Defines the proximity value (in millimeters) under which variations in the translation section of a transform are seen as equal. The default value is 0.001 millimeters.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairClosureRule
preference.preference_description: The name of the Closure Rule that will be used by the MBOM Assessment Search when "Missing in Target" in Accountability Check was not specified.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairDefaultSearchCriteria
preference.preference_description: List of criteria values that will be used by searching repair candidates in the MBOM Assessment Repair View. Each criteria value describes a BOMLine property which will be taken into account by the search. It is a comma separated string. For one criteria value string, the format is defined as follows: Part 1: either Mandatory or Optional Part 2: internal BOMLine property name Part 3: operator, currently only "=" is supported. Part 4: value type, currently only "string" type is supported.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairMissingInSourceQuickAction
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the default repair action that can be automatically set for "Missing in Source" lines with a single candidate in the MBOM Assessment Repair view. If no action is specified, the checkbox for "Missing in Source" lines will not appear in the view. The default value is "Replace". Valid names are the values of the Fnd0BOMRepairAction LOV.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairPartialMatchQuickAction
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the default repair action that can be automatically set for "Partial Match" lines with a single candidate in the MBOM Assessment Repair view. If no action is specified, the checkbox for "Partial Match" lines will not appear in the view. The default value is "Propagate". Valid names are the values of the Fnd0BOMRepairAction LOV.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairSearchCriteriaList
preference.preference_description: A List of criteria that can be used for searching repair candidates in MBOM Assessment Repair View.

preference.name: MEMCI0PMIViewDisplayNameColumnShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties columns displayed in Product Manufacturing Information (PMI) Management view in the Part Planner and Manufacturing Process Planner applications. Valid Values: in the format "ObjectTypeInternalName.PropertyInternalName", e.g. "BOMLine.bl_indented_title". The value for ObjectTypeInternalName can only be BOMLine or one of its derived types.

preference.name: MEMCI0PMIViewShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width of the properties columns determined by the preference MEMCI0PMIViewDisplayNameColumnShownPref in Product Manufacturing Information (PMI) Management view in the Part Planner and Manufacturing Process Planner applications.

preference.name: MEMCN_change_notice_mandatory_types
preference.preference_description:
Defines the list of BOMWindow's topline Item types for which a ChangeNoticeRevision is allowed to track changes. Optionally, the topline Item types can be qualified with a Release Status name. Changing the preference value requires a server restart in order to be taken into consideration.
Valid values are in the format "<Item_type><separator><Release_Status>", where the separator must be the value specified by the preference "TcServices_field_separator". For example: * "Mfg0MEPlantBOP" tracks changes in Plant Bill of Processes (Plant BOPs) by forcing a Change Notice to be applied. * "MEProcess;Pending" tracks changes in Bill of Process (BOP) Windows if the configured root revision has "Pending" Release Status by forcing a Change Notice to be applied. * If the entries are "MEProcess" and "MEProcess;Pending", the MEProcess is considered mandatory (the entry without any Release Status always wins). * To specify multiple Release Statuses on one Item type, the 2 entries would be "MEProcess;Pending" and "MEProcess;TCM Released". There is no default value.

preference.name: MEMCN_management_enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables the Change Notice Revision related commands to be shown in "Manufacturing Process Planner" application. The default value is false.

preference.name: MEMCN_previous_effectivity_is_mandatory
preference.preference_description: Activates the mandatory presence of the previous effectivity on a ChangeNoticeRevision object. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEMCN_release_bvr_with_rev
preference.preference_description: Enables the release of a BOMViewRevision when an ItemRevision is released, only when changes in the BOMWindow are being tracked with ChangeNoticeRevisions. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEMCN_release_revision_mode
preference.preference_description: Controls how statuses are created on ItemRevisions being tracked by a Change Notice Revision. The "preferred" ReleaseStatus will be one of statuses in preference "MEMCN_release_statuses" that is found on the ChangeNoticeRevision. Valid values are (case sensitive): * Share: The ItemRevisions share the "preferred" status with the ChangeNoticeRevision. * None: The ItemRevisions will not get a status. * ShareEffectivityOnly: The ItemRevisions will each have a new ReleaseStatus, all of which will share Effectivity with the Change Notice Revision "preferred" ReleaseStatus. * Clone: The ItemRevisions will get new ReleaseStatuses and Effectivities that are clones of the "preferred" ReleaseStatus. The default value is Share.

preference.name: MEMCN_release_statuses
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of mutually exclusive Release Statuses internal names that must be associated to a ChangeNoticeRevision associated to a Bill of Material (BOM) Window. There must be only one of these statuses on the ChangeNoticeRevision at any stage. The default values are "Pending" and "TCM Released". These could be replaced with appropriate values as per business needs: e.g.if using the cmtmes template, these could be replaced with "Mei0PendingRelease", "Mei0Released", "Mei0WorkInProgress".

preference.name: MEMCN_solution_object_collection_rule
preference.preference_description: Defines the closure rule for collecting the children of a newly created/pasted BOM Line for use with ChangeNoticeRevision.

preference.name: MEMFGDisplayName
preference.preference_description: Defines the customized display name in the tree structure for weld points, arc welds, and datum points. Valid Values: Accepts the five following Teamcenter properties. bl_item_item_id bl_item_object_name bl_rev_item_revision_id bl_rev_object_name bl_occurrence_name You can use multiple properties, for example: bl_item_item_id bl_item_object_name The weld point display name is then 000171;WP1

preference.name: MEMFGViewDisplayNameColumnShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns displayed in the MFG View pane. Valid Values: The System name of each column in the order you want them to appear, that is, value_1, value_2 and so on.

preference.name: MEMFGViewSubPanelColumnShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the columns displayed in the Connected Parts section of the Manufacturing Features view. Valid Values: Accepts any valid column name.

preference.name: MEMFGView_AssignmentFilterDefaultValue
preference.preference_description: Defines the filter type to be used when opening an assignment filter in the MFG View. The value of the filter type previously selected by the user in the MFG View is stored in the preference for the next session. Valid Values: ASSIGNED - The MFG View opens in assigned mode. UNASSIGNED - The MFG View opens in unassigned mode.

preference.name: MENEWMFG_DefaultDatumJTDatasetName
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the JT dataset that is attached by default to every newly created datum at import. Valid Values: The Teamcenter business object type, followed by the control direction and dataset name, in the following format: type:control_direction:datasetname

preference.name: MENEWMFG_DefaultJTDatasetNameForSpecificWeldType
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the JT dataset that is attached by default to each newly created weld point. The JT file used is dependent on the number of parts connected. Valid Values: Accepts a string of the following format: weld-type:number-of-connected-parts:dataset-name weld-type - Specifies the type of weld. The possible values are: Geo Process Respot number-of-connected-parts - Specifies the number of parts connected to each weld point. The possible values are: 2 2 3 4 4 dataset-name - Specifies the name of the JT file containing the weld point representation.

preference.name: MENEWMFG_DefaultWeldPointJTDatasetName
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the JT dataset that is attached by default to every newly created manufacturing feature. Valid Values: A single character string that represents the name of a dataset that contains a JT file of the same name.

preference.name: MENEWMFG_LastJTFilePathBrowsed
preference.preference_description: Specifies the path to which a user previously browsed to find the custom JT file to associate with a manufacturing feature. Valid Values: An operating system path.

preference.name: MEOP.MEGenericBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules to be used when pasting from a regular Operation structure to a Generic Bill Of Process (Generic BOP). Valid values are in the following format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be "*" for any class, "class.<class name>" for specific class or "type.<type name>" for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary. * the attribute_key must be one of the following: "Attribute", "OccType", "Relation". If the value is "Attribute", the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is "OccType", the attribute_value must be "Null" (no Occurrence Type) or "*" (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is "Relation", the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: "Clone", "Reference", "Ignore".

preference.name: MEOP.MEProcess.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when cloning an operation from a process using the Paste Duplicate menu command. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter cloning rule.

preference.name: MEOP.MEProductBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules to be used when pasting from a regular Operation structure to a Product Bill Of Process (Product BOP). Valid values are in the following format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be "*" for any class, "class.<class name>" for specific class or "type.<type name>" for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary. * the attribute_key must be one of the following: "Attribute", "OccType", "Relation". If the value is "Attribute", the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is "OccType", the attribute_value must be "Null" (no Occurrence Type) or "*" (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is "Relation", the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: "Clone", "Reference", "Ignore".

If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. preference.name: MEParentAssemblyItemTypesForDatasets

preference.name: MEPasteDuplicateResourceFromClassification

If the copied resource is an assembly, then default cloning rules will be applied, regardless of the preference value. Valid Values: * true: the copied resources are referenced in the MPP structure. * false: the copied resources are duplicated in the MPP structure. This is the default value.

preference.name: MEPerspectiveMode
preference.preference_description:
Defines the behavior of how views open in manufacturing perspectives. You can specify a mode for each manufacturing perspective in the user interface using the Window->Perspective Mode menu command. You can set the default mode for each perspective using this preference. Valid Values: Accepts a list of strings separated by a colon as follows: perspective-id:mode
perspective-id: Specifies the unique name of the manufacturing perspective. The following default perspectives are available by default: The Manufacturing Process Planner default perspective: com.teamcenter.rac.cme.mpp.MSEPerspectiveThe Manufacturing - Process Sequencing perspective: com.teamcenter.rac.cme.mpp.ProcessSequencing The Manufacturing - BOM Reconciliation perspective: com.teamcenter.rac.cme.mpp.BOMReconciliation If you create a new perspective by using the Save Perspective As menu command, you must select the mode using the Window->Perspective Mode menu command.
mode: Specifies how the views open in the perspective. There are two options:
OpenExplicitOnly : Opens structures in existing views where available. Any other open but not yet loaded structures are only opened in a view when explicitly opened (for example, by right-clicking the structure in the Open Items list and choosing Activate). For example, if you send a product with an associated process and plant to the Manufacturing - Process Sequencing perspective, the following occurs: The process view is filled because the Manufacturing - Process Sequencing perspective contains an empty process view. The product opens in a new view because you opened it explicitly (sent the product to the perspective). The plant is loaded, but no view opens for it because it was implicitly opened and there was no empty plant view available for it in the perspective. Prior to Teamcenter 10.0, manufacturing perspectives open structures using the OpenExplicitOnly mode.
OpenAllStrategy : Teamcenter opens a new view for each structure being opened. When objects are opened in another perspective,Teamcenter opens a new view for them in this perspective as well.
