Valid Values: true - Teamcenter does not remove the existing resolved part when resolving again. false - Teamcenter removes the existing resolved part when it resolves again.

preference.name: MERuleForBriefcaseExport
preference.preference_description:
Defines the rule to govern creation of Appearence Path Node (APN) for the lines during briefcase export of Collaboration Context. This will help the recepient of exported data to perform certain operations such as consumption of product to Bill of Processes (BOP).
Valid values are in the format "Type:StructureType; ClosureRule:ClosureRuleName; Lines:LinesValue;", where - StructureType: Specifies the type of structure from which BOMLines are identified. Valid Values: * Item : Product structure. * MEWorkarea : Workarea structure. * Mfg0MEPlantBOP: Plant Bill of Processes (BOP). * MEProcess: BOP. * Mfg0MEStudy: Study Structure.
- ClosureRuleName: Specifies the name of closure rule to be run on structure defined in Type. The closure rule can be blank. User defined closure rule is also accepted.
- LinesValue: Specifies the candidate lines for which APN is to be created. This option is ignored if valid closure rule is provided. This can be blank. Valid Values: * For "Item" and "MEWorkarea" Type : + AllLines : All lines in structures. + HierarchyOfConsumedLinesOnly : All lines in the hierarachy of Product/Plant lines consumed in a Process/Plant BOP structure. + HierarchyOfConsumedLinesAndSiblingsOnly : All lines which are in the hierarachy and are the siblings of Product/Plant lines consumed in a Process/Plant BOP structure. + HierarchyOfConsumedLinesAndHierarchyOfSiblings : All lines which are in the hierarachy and are the siblings and are in the hierarachy of siblings of Product/Plant lines consumed in a Process/Plant BOP structure. * For "BOP" and "Study" Type: + AllLines : For all lines in the BOP and Study structures. + Process : For all processes. + Operation : For all operations.
Some examples of the usage of this preference are: -"Type:Item; Lines:HierarchyOfConsumedLinesOnly;" Appearence Path Node (APN) will be created for all the lines in the hierarchy of product lines consumed in BOP or Study structure.
- "Type:MEWorkarea; Lines:HierarchyOfConsumedLinesAndSiblingsOnly;" Appearence Path Node (APN) will be created for all the lines which are in the hierarchy and which are the siblings of plant lines consumed in BOP or Study structure.
- "Type:Mfg0MEStudy; ClosureRule:MFGEBOPExportDefault; Lines:Process;" The value provided in the Lines option will be ignored and closure rule will be used.
- "Type:Mfg0MEPlantBOP; ClosureRule:; Lines:HierarchyOfConsumedLinesOnly;" Notice the invalid value for Lines. This will be ignored and Appearence Path Node (APN) will not be created for any line under the Plant BOP structure.
- "Type:MEProcess; ClosureRule:; Lines:;" Neither Closure Rule nor the Lines option value is specified. Thus, Appearence Path Node (APN) will not be created for any line under the Process structure.
One type can be specified only once in the preference value. If specified multiple times, the first value will be considered and the others will be ignored. For example, if the values are "Type:Item; ClosureRule:; Lines:HierarchyOfConsumedLinesOnly;" and "Type:Item; ClosureRule:MFGEBOPExportDefault; Lines:;", the first value will be considered and the second one will be ignored.
The default values for the preference is "Type:Item; ClosureRule:; Lines:AllLines;" "Type:MEWorkarea; ClosureRule:; Lines:AllLines;" Type:Mfg0MEPlantBOP; ClosureRule:; Lines:AllLines;.

preference.name: MES_3DPDF_UPDATE_WORKFLOW_BATCH_INTERVAL
preference.preference_description: Specifies the time interval in seconds after which the MES-Update3DPDFReports action handler checks for the request status when updating 3D PDF documents before sending them to a manufacturing execution system. Valid Values: Accepts a positive integer value.

preference.name: MES_3DPDF_UPDATE_WORKFLOW_CONTINUE_ON_ERROR
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the MES-Update3DPDFReports action handler should continue if any of the requests fail or return with an error when updating 3D PDF documents before sending them to an manufacturing execution system. Valid Values: True - The action handler continues to process requests if it encounters a problem. False - If the action handler encounters a problem, it stops processing requests and returns an error message.

preference.name: MES_3DPDF_UPDATE_WORKFLOW_LOG_FOLDER
preference.preference_description: Specifies the folder name where all log file datasets are created when updating 3D PDF documents. If any 3D PDF request fails during the workflow, a new dataset is created in this folder with the generated log file. Valid Values: Accepts an existing Teamcenter folder name.

preference.name: MES_3DPDF_UPDATE_WORKFLOW_WAIT_TIME
preference.preference_description: Specifies the total time in seconds for completing all requests when updating 3D PDF reports in preparation for transferring them to an external manufacturing execution system. If all requests do not complete in this time frame, the MES-Update3DPDFReports action handler returns an error message. Valid Values: Accepts a positive integer value.

preference.name: MESaveAsSC_PasteType
preference.preference_description: Specifies which object in a selected BOM line is pasted as a root when creating a structure context in Manufacturing Process Planner. see Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts one of the following values:ItemItemRevisionBOMViewBOMViewRevisionIf no BOMViewRevision object exists in the selection and that value is defined in this preference, Teamcenter uses the ItemRevision object instead. This occurs with product root BOM lines without children as they do not contain any BOMViewRevision object. If no BOMView object exists in the selection and that value is defined, Teamcenter uses the Item object instead.

preference.name: MESecondStructurePosition
preference.preference_description: Specifies which alignment of the second structure position to use, either to the right or on the bottom. Valid Values: right - Displays the second structure on the right. bottom - Displays the second structure on the bottom.

preference.name: MEShopFloorReleaseStatuses
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of release statuses of Process structure which Shop Floor Worker can add to CCObject. Valid values are internal names of release statuses.

preference.name: MEShowConfigurationHeader
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to show the configuration header in manufacturing views in Manufacturing Process Planner, Part Planner, and Plant Designer. The header shows configuration information such as revision rule, variant rule, effectivity, and incremental change context. Valid Values: true - The configuration header is shown in primary views. false - The configuration header is not shown in primary views.

preference.name: MEShowConnectedRetainSelection
preference.preference_description: Allows to keep original line selected on "Show Connected Manufacturing Features" or "Show Connected Lines". The default value of the preference is false. Valid Values: true - Keep the original line selected. false - Does not keep the original line selected.

preference.name: MEShowHideUnconfiguredAll
preference.preference_description: Determines the visibility and content of a rich client selector for show or hide all unconfigured actions when the Manufacturing application is opened or a new BOM window is created. Valid Values: Individual - The selector is not visible. Both - The selector is visible. All - The selector is visible, but the show unconfigured toggle actions are not visible on the toolbar.

preference.name: MEShowSuppressedOccsDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default state of the Show Suppressed Occurrences button or menu command when an application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The Show Suppressed Occurrences button is available in the Manufacturing Process Planner and Part Planner applications. The Show Suppressed Occurrences menu command is available in Multi-Structure Manager and Structure Manager. Valid Values: true - The Show Suppressed Occurrences button is on when the application is opened. false - The Show Suppressed Occurrences button is off when the application is opened.

preference.name: MEShowUnconfiguredAssignedOccurrencesDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default state of the Show Unconfigured Assigned Occurrences button or menu command when an application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The Show Unconfigured Assigned Occurrences button is available in the Manufacturing Process Planner and Part Planner applications. The menu command is available in Multi-Structure Manager. Valid Values: true - The Show Unconfigured Assigned Occurrences button is on when the application is opened. false - The Show Unconfigured Assigned Occurrences button is off when the application is opened.

preference.name: MEShowUnconfiguredChangesDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default state of the Show Unconfigured Changes button or menu command when an application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The Show Unconfigured Changes button is available in the Manufacturing Process Planner and Part Planner applications. The menu command is available in Multi-Structure Manager and Structure Manager. Valid Values: true - The Show Unconfigured Changes button is on when the application is opened. false - The Show Unconfigured Changes button is off when the application is opened.

preference.name: MEShowUnconfiguredOccurrencesEffectivityDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default state of the Show Unconfigured Occurrence Effectivity button or menu option when an application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The Show Unconfigured Occurrence Effectivity button is available in the Manufacturing Process Planner and Part Planner applications. The menu option is available in Multi-Structure Manager and Structure Manager. Valid Values: true - The Show Unconfigured Occurrence Effectivity button is on. false - The Show Unconfigured Occurrence Effectivity button is off.

preference.name: MEShowUnconfiguredVariantsDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default state of the Show Unconfigured Variants button or menu command when an application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The Show Unconfigured Variants button is available in the Manufacturing Process Planner and Part Planner applications. The menu command is available in Multi-Structure Manager and Structure Manager. Valid Values: true - The Show Unconfigured Variants button is on when the application is opened. false - The Show Unconfigured Variants button is off when the application is opened.

preference.name: MEShowWeldPointsConnectedToConfiguredOutParts
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of weld points when connected parts are configured out, in the manufacturing applications. Valid Values: True - Teamcenter displays weld points even if their connected parts are configured out. False - Teamcenter hides weld points if at least one of the connected parts is configured out.

preference.name: MESite.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for MESite objects.

preference.name: MESkipEditPermissionOnTimePopulate
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the Populate Allocated Time command should skip read-only lines in the structure. Valid values: true - When the object is read-only, there will be no drill down, and the time will be taken from the object. false - There will be drill down to the levels specified in the parameters of the Populate command. If an object is read-only, its time will not be updated. The default value of the preference is false.

preference.name: MEStation.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for MEStation objects.

preference.name: MEStockAbleBomLinePropertyName
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the property that is used to determine whether a BOM line is stockable. Setting this preference is required when working with product and manufacturing information and effectivity in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts the name of a valid Teamcenter property.

preference.name: MESupportMultipleRootsInStructureContext
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of multiple roots drop down on BOM primary views. The default value is false (display deactivated).

preference.name: MESyncOccGroupConfig
preference.preference_description:
Controls the synchronization of the configurations between the Occurrence Group window and the base view.
Valid Values:: - true: when the user changes the configuration of an Occurrence Group tab, the system will immediately apply the same configuration to the base view. - false: the configuration will only be copied from the Occurrence Group tab to the base view the next time the base view becomes visible. This will improve the performance when working with large structures in the base view, but has the side effect that other structures linked to the base view (like a process structure associated with a product) will only be updated when switching to the base view tab.
The default is true.

preference.name: METIMEAllocatedTimePopulationMode
preference.preference_description: Specifies which mode is used in the Populate allocated time command in the Time pane. Valid Values: 0 - Estimated time 1 - Simulated time 2 - Time analysis duration 3 - Customized

preference.name: METIMEPopulateAllocatedTimeUpToLevel
preference.preference_description: Specifies the level to which the Populate Allocated Time command should be executed. Valid Values: An integer value greater than or equal to 0. Setting this preference to 0 indicates that all levels are populated.

preference.name: METIMEPopulateAllocatedTimeUpToLevelEnabled
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the option to update the allocated time to a certain level (Populate up to level) is active in the Populate Allocated Time dialog box in the Time pane. Valid Values: True - The Populate up to level option is available. False - The Populate up to level option is not available.

preference.name: METIMEPopulateAllocatedTimeUsedSources
preference.preference_description: Specifies which time sources are used in which order when using the custom allocated time population mode in the Time pane. The order of sources in this preference defines the precedence in which they are used. Valid Values: 0 - Allocated time 1 - Simulated time 2 - Time analysis duration 3 - Estimated time

preference.name: METIMEPopulateAllocatedTimeZeroValuesEnabled
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether zero values are populated while executing the Populate Allocated Time command in the Time pane. Valid Values: True - Zero values are populated. False - Zero values are not populated.

preference.name: METWICreateTextControlsOnSave
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether content controls are created automatically for free text in work instructions documents. Valid Values: true - Content controls are created automatically. false - Content controls are not created automatically.

preference.name: METWIShowPreviewFile
preference.preference_description: Defines the default display mode of the Textual Work Instruction view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. The display is done according to the format specified by the preference "MEWiPreviewFormat". Valid Values: * true: to activate the view mode. This is the default value. * false: to activate the edit mode.

preference.name: METimeAnalysisReportDefinitionID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID for the Time Analysis report. Valid Values: Accepts a valid report ID string.

preference.name: METimeAnalysisReportStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the XSL style sheet used for the Time Analysis report. Valid Values: Accepts a valid style sheet name.

preference.name: METimeDataCardConversionFactor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the factor to convert from data card time units to seconds. It is applied to time values from a data card. The standard MTM data cards hold times in TMU. Valid Values: A character string.

preference.name: METimeDataCardPath
preference.preference_description: Specifies the location of the data card as URI. Use the goto protocol to navigate to an MTM data card, and the file protocol to navigate to a custom HTMLdata card. Valid Values: A character string.

preference.name: METimeDecimalPlaces
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of decimal places displayed for time properties. Valid values are -1, 0, ..., 6, where -1 represents all significant places. This preference should be set using the Manufacturing Options Time panel to take effect without restarting Teamcenter. The default value for this preference is 2.

preference.name: METimeSystemFieldMappingDataset
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset containing the XML mapping file between time system fields and activity properties. The value of each field in the mapping file is applied to the corresponding property whenever data is copied from the time system to Teamcenter. A valid value must have the format "name:type:reference", where "name" specifies the name of the dataset, "type" the dataset type, and "reference" the reference of the file.

preference.name: METimeSystemSearchCriterionFields
preference.preference_description: Specifies the time system fields that can be searched for. The fields can be grouped in different configurations. Each value (or configuration) must have the format "configuration:field_1,field_2,...,field_n", where "configuration" is the configuration name and "field_i" is the time system field. The fields appear in the default configuration if the "configuration" section of the preference value is empty.

preference.name: METimeSystemSearchResultFields
preference.preference_description: Specifies the time system fields that are displayed in the search result when performing a TiCon search in Manufacturing Process Planner. You can group the fields in different configurations. Valid Values: One or more strings. Each string must have the following format: configuration:field_1;width_1,field_2;width_2,...field_n;width_n field_x represents the time system field and width_x specifies the initial width of the field_x column in the search result table. If you leave the configuration value empty, the field appears in the default configuration.

preference.name: METimeSystemUpdateIncludeStructure
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the time element structure is included in assign and update actions when working in the TiCon integration in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: true - The structure is included. false - The structure is not included.

preference.name: METimeSystemUpdateStructureLevel
preference.preference_description: Specifies the level up to which the time element structure is included in assign and update actions when working in the TiCon integration in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: An integer value representing the level, or -1 for unlimited.

preference.name: METimeSystemWebServiceLocation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the location of the WSDL description for the time system web service. Valid Values: Accepts a string as value. The string must be a valid WSDL location. For example:http://localhost:4848/TiConService/?wsdlhttp://your-company.com:52000/TiConService/?wsdl

preference.name: METimeTabFilteredComponents
preference.preference_description: Defines which objects are filtered out in the Activities section on the Time pane. Valid Values: Accepts any general object type, such as Form or Dataset, or a specific type such as AllocationMap Master. You cannot filter out an activity. If an activity is listed in this preference, it is ignored.

preference.name: METimesActivityShownColumnWidths
preference.preference_description: Lists the widths of columns that appear in the Activity section of the operation Times pane in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: One or more positive integers.

preference.name: METimesActivityShownColumns
preference.preference_description: Lists the column names of the attributes that are shown in the Activity table in the operation Times pane in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid property of CfgActivityLine.

preference.name: MEValidStockAbleValues
preference.preference_description: Defines the value of the MEStockAbleBomLinePropertyName property that is used to determine whether a BOM line is stockable. Setting this preference is required when working with product and manufacturing information and effectivity in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts the name of a valid Teamcenter property.

preference.name: MEWiDcdNotEditableProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of data collection properties (DCDs) that cannot be edited in the Properties dialog box of the Work Instructions view. Valid Values: Accepts strings of the following format:DCD_type:att1,att2... DCD_type is a descendant type of the DCD base form.

preference.name: MEWiEnableAddSymbolCommand
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the Add Symbol and Remove Symbol buttons are displayed in the Standard Text view or the Work Instruction view. Valid Values: STXView - The Add Symbol and Remove Symbol buttons are displayed in the Standard Text view. TWIView - The Add Symbol and Remove Symbol buttons are displayed in the Work Instruction view.

preference.name: MEWiEnable_SynchronizePreviewFileCommand
preference.preference_description: Enables the "Synchronize preview file" command in the Teamcenter rich client. Valid values are true or false (default value).

preference.name: MEWiPifEditableProperties
preference.preference_description: This is deprecated starting at release Teamcenter 9.0.0. Specifies the list of PIF properties that can be edited via the properties dialog of the Work Instructions view. Each string will be in the following format: PIF_type:att1,att2,...

preference.name: MEWiPreviewFormat
preference.preference_description: Specifies the available file types for the format of the preview files created in the standard text editor and in the work instruction editor. Teamcenter creates a document of the file type specified by the first string. Valid Values: Accepts one of the following file formats supported by the Word Save As command: pdf mht docx rtf

preference.name: MEWiStandardTextTemplate
preference.preference_description: Specifies a name of a specification template that contains a Microsoft Word document used as a standard text template. The template is used as a starting point for standard text documents. Valid Values: Accepts a valid Teamcenter specification template name.

preference.name: MEWiWorkInstructionTemplate
preference.preference_description: Specifies a name of a specification template that contains a Microsoft Word document used as a work instruction template. The template is used as a starting point for work instruction documents. Valid Values: Accepts a valid Teamcenter specification template name.

preference.name: MEWorkarea.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for MEWorkarea objects.

preference.name: MEWorkarea.MEWorkarea.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when cloning a plant structure from a plant structure using the Paste Duplicate menu command. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter cloning rule.

preference.name: ME_EnableMixVariantModelCheck
preference.preference_description: Performs a check to determine whether the mixed model of legacy and Product Configurator variants is being used while loading contexts. Using a mixture of legacy and Product Configurator variants can cause data corruption. Set the value of the preference to false when only one model is used, or no workflow can create mix model situation. The default value is true.

preference.name: ME_Proximity_FilteredIPA_root_name
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the flat list collection that holds all the proximity search result groups. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as value. The string must be a valid occurrence group type.

preference.name: ME_Proximity_FilteredIPA_suffix
preference.preference_description: Defines the suffix of the filtered IPA names when the occurrence group holds proximity search result. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as value.

preference.name: ME_Proximity_search_result_occ_group_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the occurrence group type that represents a proximity search result collection in the process structure. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as value. The string must be a valid occurrence group type.

preference.name: ME_Proximity_search_result_occ_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the occurrence type that represents a proximity search result collection in the process structure. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as value. The string must be a valid occurrence type.

preference.name: ME_check_lines_below_consumed
preference.preference_description: Activates the Product BOM traversal while processing the children of consumed lines in Bill Of Process (BOP). This would be needed if a line below a consumed line is suppressed in BOM and is not expected to be visible in BOP. A noticeable performance impact exists if the value is set to true. The default value is false.

preference.name: ME_defer_commit_in_clone
preference.preference_description: Enables defer commit for Oracle Database during cloning of a structure in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. If the value is 'true', Oracle transaction parameters are set to commit redo logs in BATCH and NOWAIT. For Oracle Database version lower than 11, the parameter value is as follows - COMMIT_WRITE='BATCH,NOWAIT'. For Oracle Database version equal to or higher than 11, the parameters values are as follows - COMMIT_WAIT='NOWAIT' COMMIT_LOGGING='BATCH'. The default value of the preference is false.

preference.name: ME_defer_save_in_clone
preference.preference_description: Activates defer save option for Dataset, Form and Relation objects during cloning of a structure in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. The default value is true.

preference.name: ME_impacted_parts_report_background_impacted_items
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of tuples for finding impacted items associated with a background part. The tuple takes the form: 'SourceObjectType:PropertyToGetImpacted:PropertyToGetTarget' The property values are internal property names.

preference.name: ME_impacted_parts_report_parent_types
preference.preference_description: A ';' delimited string of parent object Item types to consider during impacted parts report generation.

preference.name: MPPTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of rules to be used when cloning an Activity in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MPP_BrokenLinkSearchCriteriaList
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of preferences that define candidate search criteria. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values, each string must be a valid preference name.

preference.name: MPP_DefaultCandidateSearchCriteria
preference.preference_description: Specifies a default list of properties used to determine candidates containing broken links that need to be repaired. Candidates are those for which the values of the specified properties match the values of the broken link's properties. Valid Values: logical - Specifies whether the match is mandatory or optional, meaning that at least one of the optional property values must match. Valid values are Mandatory or Optional. property - Specifies any BOM line property.

preference.name: MPP_ToolActivity_CustomUserData
preference.preference_description:
Define user customizable attributes that can be synchronized between NX-CAM and Teamcenter. Up to 15 custom properties can be defined that are stored with the MENCToolActivity of a CAM setup.
Valid values are in the format "pm0UserData[Custom Property Number]:[MOM Variable]:[Display Name]", where: - "[Custom Property Number]" is a two digit number in the range of 01 .. 15. - "[MOM Variable]" is the Manufacturing Output Manager (MOM) variable that is set in the NX-CAM TCL post processor (no spaces allowed). - "[Display Name]" is the display name that will be used as a label for the user defined attribute in the activities table.
Example definition of two user defined tool activity attributes: pm0UserData01:mom_tool_name:Tool Description pm0UserData02:mom_magazine:Magazine Position
Note: The support of user defined attributes must be activated using the preference MPP_ToolActivity_EnableUserData.

preference.name: MPP_ToolActivity_EnableUserData
preference.preference_description: Synchronize customizable attributes between NX-CAM and Teamcenter. Up to 15 custom properties can be defined that are stored with the MENCToolActivity of a CAM setup. These custom attributes are defined using the preference MPP_ToolActivity_CustomUserData.

preference.name: MPP_ToolActivity_NXCamTime
preference.preference_description: With the NX-CAM integration, the machining time is passed to the Activity. Using this preference the user can configure what NX time should be passed as the default time. It is possible to specify one of the following numbers. Ex. 3 for "Material Cutting Time". If set to "0", the legacy "Postprocessor Calculated Time" (old functionality) is used. Default value is: 0. 0 - Postprocessor Calculated Time 1 - Total Time 2 - Cutting Time 3 - Material Cutting Time 4 - Air Cutting Time 5 - Secondary Time 6 - Positioning Time 7 - Positioning Linear Time 8 - Positioning Rotary Time 9 - Positioning Mixed Time 10 - Dragging Time 11 - Delay Time 12 - Wait Time 13 - Tool Change Time

preference.name: MRMAutoPSPClassIDs
preference.preference_description: Contains class IDs for which the Propagation Start Point (PSP) will be set automatically. In Active Workspace there is a functionality that sets the PSP automatically to the right component, when a new component is added to an assembly. Only if the component - that should get the PSP - is classified in one class that is present in this preference or in one of their child classes, the PSP will be set automatically.

preference.name: MRMClassifyResource
preference.preference_description: Determines whether new items and item revisions are classified at the time they are created using the File->New->Resource menu command. Regardless of this preference's settings, existing objects can still be classified using the Classify Item and Classify Item Revision menu commands. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. The string must be either Item or ItemRevision. Siemens PLM Software recommends classifying item revisions during creation, otherwise some functionality (revisioning, propagated attributes, statuses) is limited.

preference.name: MRMCreateDefaultResourceTypes
preference.preference_description:
List all item types available in the "Create Resource" dialog in Active Workspace.
Notes: - Specify valid (exists in the database) internal item type names (not the display names). - These item types and related revision must also be listed in the "ICS_classifiable_types" preference.

preference.name: MRMCreateToolAssemblyAndComponent
preference.preference_description: Activates advanced functionality to create tool assemblies and components. In the menubar and toolbar two new commands will be available. An additional class selection dialog is displayed and a class specific Item ID (incl. counter) will be generated automatically (see also the MRMToolAssemblyAndComponentIDCounterFormat and MRMToolAssemblyAndComponentIDAutoGenerate preferences). Default value is: true

preference.name: MRMDefaultItemType
preference.preference_description: Defines the Item type selected as default in the "New Resource" dialog in the Resource Manager application, in case no resource is opened and the preference "MRMItemTypes" is not defined. Values must be a valid Item type. The default value is "Mfg0MENCTool".

preference.name: MRMExpandUptoLevelOnLoad
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of levels an assembly is expanded when it is opened in Resource Manager. Valid Values: Accepts an integer.

preference.name: MRMGCSItemType
preference.preference_description: Determines the Item type used when the Guided Component Search (GCS) functionality creates new Items. This is the case, for example, in the Classification application when a new classification object (ICO) is created in a class that has defined GCS connection point definitions (CPDs) defined or if a GCS CPD is added to a class that has ICOs without Items. A valid value is any valid Item types. The default value is "Item".

preference.name: MRMGCSShowCount
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the number of matching components for each class in the Classification search dialog after a Guided Component Search operation. This is a user preference.

preference.name: MRMGTC3DModelAttributeID
preference.preference_description: Defines the ID of the Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) class attribute that holds the filename of the 3D step model for a catalog component. The default value is -159003. If a future tool catalog uses a different attribute ID for this purpose, it can be reconfigured here.

preference.name: MRMGTC3DModelAttributeIDs
preference.preference_description: Defines the IDs of the Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) class attribute that holds the filename of the 3D step model for a catalog component. The default values are -159003 for detailed and -159016 for basic 3D model. The sequence of the IDs in list defines the sequence how the Resource Manager imports a 3D step model. At first the filename from the first specified attribute is used. If that attribute is empty and there is a second attribute specified in this preference, the filename from the second attribute is used.

preference.name: MRMGTCAdapterConnectionCodeAttributeIDs
preference.preference_description: Defines the IDs of the Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) class attributes that hold ISO adapter connection codes for a catalog component. The default values are -150046, -150048, -151011, -151012, -151021, -151022, -151031, -151032, -151041, -151042, -151051 and -151052. Those connection codes will be converted from ISO to DIN, when the ICO is mapped into another class.

preference.name: MRMGTCCloudAccess
preference.preference_description: Activates the availability of ToolsUnited Cloud Access functionality in the Resource Manager application. Valid Values: True,False

preference.name: MRMGTCConnectionCodeWildCards
preference.preference_description: Defines the wild characters that are used in vendor Generic Tool Catalogs (GTCs). Those wild characters will be converted to Teamcenter supported wild cards, when the ICO is mapped into Manufacturing Resource Library (MRL) classes. The default values are *, ? and $.

preference.name: MRMGTCInsertConnectionCodeAttributeIDs
preference.preference_description: Defines the IDs of the Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) class attributes that hold ISO insert connection codes for a catalog component. The default values are -150165, -151241, -151242, -151243 and -151244. Those connection codes will be converted from ISO to DIN, when the ICO is mapped into another class.

preference.name: MRMGTCPackageClientDir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the directory on the Teamcenter client where Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) packages are saved by the user and where Teamcenter looks for Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) packages to upload them to the Teamcenter server.

preference.name: MRMGTCPackageServerDir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relative directory where the Teamcenter server stores Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) packages that are uploaded form the Teamcenter client to the Teamcenter server. The ZIP file will be extracted to a directory below the $TC_DATA directory: $TC_DATA/relative-directory-from-this-preference In that directory, a new directory with the ZIP file name is created. If this directory already exists, a new directory with the ZIP file name and an appended timestamp is created.

preference.name: MRMGTCProductIDVendorAcronymSeparator
preference.preference_description: Defines the character(s) used to separate GTC product id and vendor acronym. Default value is: #

preference.name: MRMGTCVendorCatalogRootDir
preference.preference_description: Defines the root directories on the Teamcenter server where the generic vendor tool catalogs are stored. Valid Values: Accepts a valid operating system path. You can specify multiple entries.

preference.name: MRMHolderData
preference.preference_description: Activates the functionality to extract the holder data of resources from the Classification table panel and from the Resource Manager application. The default value is "true".

preference.name: MRMHolderDataAccuracy
preference.preference_description: Defines the default behaviour for the "Simplify" option when extracting holder geometry. By default all holder elements are extracted and stored in Teamcenter. Setting this preference to "Simplified" extracts a smaller set of parameters.

preference.name: MRMItemTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies what item type is selected as default based on the currently selected class in the New Resource dialog box in the Resource Manager application. This item type is used for the specified class and all its child classes. You can overwrite the item type in child classes. Valid Values: Accepts one or more pairs of strings as values. In each string pair, the first value must be a valid Classification class ID, and the second value must be a valid business object (type). The most common item types used with Resource Manager are: Display name Internal name Resource Mfg0MEResource NC Tool Mfg0MENCTool NC Machine Mfg0MENCMachine Equipment Mfg0MEEquipment

preference.name: MRMMappingSourceICOAttributeID
preference.preference_description: Defines the attribute ID of the source instance classified object (ICO) that is used to name the target instance. This algorithm is used when multiple ICOs are mapping in the Classification table. The default value is -40219.

preference.name: MRMMultiTool
preference.preference_description: Activates the functionality to add multi tool cutter to an assembly from the Resource Manager application. By default, the functionality is enabled (true).

preference.name: MRMNeutralCSYSPrefixes
preference.preference_description: Customizes the prefixes of the neutral coordinate system names that are used for Resource Manager automatic positioning. Teamcenter checks coordinate system names in the precedence that is defined in this preference. Valid Values: Accepts a list of strings representing the custom prefixes for names of coordinate systems.

preference.name: MRMPlugCSYSPrefixes
preference.preference_description: Customizes the prefixes of the machine-sided (plug) coordinate system names that are used for Resource Manager automatic positioning. Teamcenter checks coordinate system names in the precedence that is defined in this preference. Valid Values: Accepts a list of strings representing the custom prefixes for names of coordinate systems.

preference.name: MRMPropagationAlternateAttributes
preference.preference_description: Determines what alternate attributes are used for attribute value propagation. Normally the component attribute value with ID X will be propagated into the assembly attribute with ID X. This preference allows that additional attributes will be checked, if no value was found in any component in an attribute with ID X. Valid values are in the format "Class ID::Assembly Attribute ID::Component Attribute IDs", where: - "Class ID" defines for what class (incl. subclasses) this rule is valid. - "Assembly Attribute ID" is the attribute ID in the assembly class. - "Component Attribute IDs" contains the alternate component attributes that will be checked additionally. - "Component Attribute IDs" can contain multiple IDs seperated by commas.

preference.name: MRMPropagationReverseAttributes
preference.preference_description: Defines what attributes should be propagated in the opposite order. By default, assembly attributes are propagated bottom-up: Starting from the Propagation-Start-Point the components are checked up to the root component to find specific attribute values. The first component closest to the Propagation-Start-Point provides the value. All attributes listed in the preference behave in the opposite order: For these attributes, the system checks from the root component down the structure to the component with the Propagation-Start-Point. In this case, the value of the component closest to the root will be propagated to the assembly. Valid values are all Classification attribute IDs.

preference.name: MRMPropagationRevisionRule
preference.preference_description: Determines the revision rule used during the propagation of attributes. For example, when the user saves a resource assembly and there is a propagation start point (PSP) defined in the assembly, the system propagates the attribute values to the assembly level. The specified revision rule configures the component revisions that are used during this propagation. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as value. The string must be a valid revision rule defined in the database, such as Latest Working or Latest by Alpha Rev Order.

preference.name: MRMSetupSheetFixUnit
preference.preference_description: Specifies which unit system's setup sheet templates are used to generate setup sheets for resources. Valid values for this preference are "off", "metric", and "inch". The default value is "off". The different values lead to the following behavior: off: Based on the resource's ICO unit, the preference "MRMSetupSheetTemplatesMetric" or "MRMSetupSheetTemplatesInch" is used to determine the setup sheet template. metric: Only metric templates specified in the "MRMSetupSheetTemplatesMetric" preference are used. Inch ICO values are converted to metric when used in the setup sheet. inch: Only the inch templates specified in the "MRMSetupSheetTemplatesInch" preference are used. Metric ICO values are converted to inch when used in the setup sheet.

preference.name: MRMSetupSheetTemplatesInch
preference.preference_description: Specifies what inch drawing parts are used as templates to generate setup sheets for resources. Each valid value is defined as a pair of preference entries: the first entry must be a valid Classification class ID; the second entry must be an existing item revision (for example, "MRM_DRW_resources_general_inch/A", where "/A" is the revision ID) which contains the desired setup sheet template part file as a UGPart dataset. There can be any number of pairs. It is possible to specify a parent class for the Classification class ID, in which case the template is inherited to all child classes. It can, however, be overwritten for specific subclasses. Note: This preference defines only the inch template parts. Metric template parts need to be defined using the "MRMSetupSheetTemplatesMetric" preference.

preference.name: MRMSetupSheetTemplatesMetric
preference.preference_description: Specifies what metric drawing parts are used as templates to generate setup sheets for resources. Each valid value is defined as a pair of preference entries: the first entry must be a valid Classification class ID; the second entry must be an existing item revision (for example, "MRM_DRW_resources_general_metric/A", where "/A" is the revision ID) which contains the desired setup sheet template part file as a UGPart dataset. There can be any number of pairs. It is possible to specify a parent class for the Classification class ID, in which case the template is inherited to all child classes. It can, however, be overwritten for specific subclasses. Note: This preference defines only the metric template parts. Inch template parts need to be defined using the "MRMSetupSheetTemplatesInch" preference.

preference.name: MRMSetupSheets
preference.preference_description: Activates the functionality to generate setup sheets for resources from the Classification table panel and from the Resource Manager application. The default value is "true".

preference.name: MRMSiteData
preference.preference_description: Defines the classes that can be used to store the site specific data for resources. If there are multiple classes defined, multiple tabs are displayed in the Resource Site Data dialog. There must be one default view for each class. The class name and attributes define the title of the tab and the attributes that are displayed in the tab. Default value is: MRM_SITE_DATA_01

preference.name: MRMSiteDataEnabled
preference.preference_description: Activates the functionality to create or update site specific data for resources from the Resource Manager application. The default value is "false".

preference.name: MRMSocketCSYSPrefixes
preference.preference_description: Customizes the prefixes of the the workpiece-sided ( socket ) coordinate system names that are used for Resource Manager automatic positioning. Teamcenter checks coordinate system names in the precedence that is defined in this preference. Valid Values: Accepts a list of strings representing the custom prefixes for names of coordinate systems.

preference.name: MRMTUURL
preference.preference_description: Stores the URL to the ToolsUnited web page that is used to retrieve vendor tool component data from an external tool catalog in Resource Manager. ToolsUnited search is located in the classification search dialog box, show ToolsUnited view toolbar and menu command. Valid Values: Accepts the ToolsUnited URL.

preference.name: MRMToolAssemblyAndComponentIDAutoGenerated
preference.preference_description: Defines whether "new Item ID" auto generation is used for the advanced tool assembly and component creation functionality. * true : The Item ID is automatically generated using a prefix (from the class alias name) and a counter. * false : The Item ID can be assigned with the existing "Assign" functionality. This is the default value.

preference.name: MRMToolAssemblyAndComponentIDCounterFormat
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of digits used in the counters for the tool assemblies and components when item IDs are generated. Default value is: 8

preference.name: MRMToolCheckLevel
preference.preference_description: Defines what level of tool parameter checking is performed during Manufacturing Resource Manager save operations. Valid Values: "none": Suppresses all tool parameter checking during the save operation. "errors": Only checks for tool parameters that are mandatory but missing. "all": Also reports optional tool parameters that are not set, in addition to the errors.

preference.name: MRMToolCheckType
preference.preference_description: Defines the tool attribute categories that are checked during Manufacturing Resource Manager save operations. Valid Values: "NX CAM TOOL PARAMETERS": Checks the set of tool assembly attribute values that are sent to NX CAM based on its NX CAM tool type. "NX CAM TOOL RETRIEVE": Performs a dry run of the NX tool retrieve to ensure that the correct attribute values are used.

preference.name: MRM_MTL_macro_att_ids
preference.preference_description: Specifies the attribute IDs in which the Manufacturing Tooling Library (MTL) macro name and model name (that are needed for create graphic) is stored. Valid values are two integers. Each integer must be a valid Classification attribute ID. The first integer is the attribute ID for the MTL macro name. The second integer is the attribute ID for the MTL model name.

preference.name: MbmAlignmentPage3DViewerLayout
preference.preference_description: This preference lets the user configure the 3D layout of eBOM and mBOM on the alignment page. Allowed values are: 0 (Hide 3D viewer for eBOM and mBOM), 1 (Show 3D viewer for eBOM only), 2(Show 3D viewer for mBOM only) and 3 (Show 3D viewer for eBOM and mBOM).

preference.name: MbmReleaseStatusForModularBom
preference.preference_description: This preference governs the display of 'Has Manufacturing Representation' indication on EBOM nodes based on the release status associated with the BOMViewRevision of Mfg representation node. If the preference is empty, the non-released BOMViewRevision will be shown.

preference.name: Mci0ConfigureForRelativePMIValues
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the PMI has absolute or relative values for upper and lower specifications. This preference is read only while importing PMIs from IPXML file.

preference.name: Mci0ExtractPMISurfaceProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Product Manufacturing Information (PMI) surface properties should be extracted from JT. Valid Values: true false

preference.name: Mci0ExtractPatternPMI
preference.preference_description: Specifies if all of the Product Manufacturing Information (PMI) in a pattern should be imported. Valid Values: * "true": all the PMIs mentioned in the pattern are imported. * "false": only one PMI of the pattern is imported. This is the default value.

preference.name: Mci0GetDCDsClosureRule
preference.preference_description: Defines the closure rule used to retrieve all Data Collection Definitions (DCD) objects associated with an object.

preference.name: Mci0PMIBop_Details_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Defines the primary object for the Mci0PMIBop_Details relation.

preference.name: Mci0PMIDCDOverrideFormPropertiesList
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of runtime properties on PMI/DCD, which would be copy pasted to newly created BOP form through code.

preference.name: Mci0PMIImportNxToTcPMIIDPropertyMap
preference.preference_description: Maps the NX product manufacturing information (PMI) ID property to the Teamcenter PMI ID property. Changing the value of this preference can lead to a loss of data created in either NX or Teamcenter when synchronizing between the two. Valid Values: Accepts two property names separated by a colon, as follows: NX-property-name:Teamcenter-property-name

preference.name: Mci0PMIImportNxToTcPropertiesMap
preference.preference_description: Maps the NX product manufacturing information (PMI) properties to the Teamcenter PMI properties. Valid Values: Accepts two property names separated by a colon, as follows: NX-property-name:Teamcenter-property-name

preference.name: Mci0PMIPropagatePropertiesList
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties that can be updated as per the NX update in the "Import PMI" command.

preference.name: Mci0PMIXmlRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Defines the primary object for the Mci0PMIXmlRel relation. Valid Values: Accepts a valid Teamcenter object.

preference.name: Mci0PMI_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the default relations for product manufacturing information (PMI). Valid Values: Accepts a list of valid Teamcenter relations.

preference.name: Mci0PMI_Details_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Defines the primary object for the Mci0PMI_Details relation. Valid Values: Accepts a valid Teamcenter object.

preference.name: Mci0PMI_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations to be shown in the rich client when the product manufacturing information (PMI) object is expanded. Valid Values: Accepts a list of valid Teamcenter relations.

preference.name: Mci0PatternPMICountFormat
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of formats used to specify the count in a pattern of PMIs (e.g. 5X, 5Plcs, 5nos, where "5" is the pattern count and "X", "Plcs", "nos" is the format). The default value is "X".

preference.name: Mci0ProcessPartPMIJT
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the part JTs need to be attached as datasets to the automatic workflow after a CAD model is saved. By default, the assembly JTs are always attached as datasets to the automatic workflow. This preference gives option to attach part JTs as well. Valid Values: * "true": Part JTs get attached as dataset arguments to the automatic workflow after a CAD model is saved. * "false": Part JTs are skipped and not attached as dataset arguments to the automatic workflow after a CAD model is saved. This is the default value.

preference.name: Mci0ShowOrHideAssemblyPMI
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the configuration rules needs to be applied to the assembly Product Manufacturing Information (PMI). Assembly PMI lines are connected to its sub assembly parts with iman relation. So the PMI lines should configure according to configuration of the connected items. Valid Values: * "true": Assmebly PMIs should also be configured out if connected part is configued out. This is the default value. * "false": There should not be any impact of connected part configuration on the PMI line configuration. Assembly PMIs should always be showned.

preference.name: MciDCDFormTypeName
preference.preference_description: Defines the associated Product Manufacturing Information (PMI) form type to be used by the "Import PMI" command.

preference.name: MciImportPMIWorkflowName
preference.preference_description: Defines the workflow name that is executed after a CAD model is saved. A valid value is an existing Teamcenter workflow name.

preference.name: MciPMIFormTypeName
preference.preference_description: Defines the associated Product Manufacturing Information (PMI) form type to be used by the "Import PMI" command.

preference.name: MciPMIJTDataset_Details
preference.preference_description: Defines the relation of the owning item with the Direct Model dataset, the dataset type and the named reference to be used. The format for Valid Values: "Relation:DatasetType:NamedReference", e.g. "IMAN_Rendering:DirectModel:JTPART".

preference.name: MciPMIXmlDataset_Details
preference.preference_description: Defines the relation of the owning item with the Product Manufacturing Information (PMI) XML dataset, the dataset type and the named reference to be used. The format for Valid Values: "Relation:DatasetType:NamedReference", e.g. "Mci0PMIXmlRel:Mci0PMIXml:Mci0ipxml".

preference.name: MciPMIXmlDataset_relation
preference.preference_description: Defines the relation of the owning item with the Product Manufacturing Information (PMI) XML dataset.

preference.name: Mei0WIMESRepresentationRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Mei0WIMESRepresentationRel.

preference.name: Mes0MEDCD_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type i.e. Mes0MEDCD. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: Mes0MEDCD_Details_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Mes0MEDCD_Details.

preference.name: Mes0MEDCD_Override_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Mes0MEDCD_Override.

preference.name: Mes0MEDCD_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations to show when expanding Mes0MEDCD.

preference.name: Mes0MEPF_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type i.e. Mes0MEPF. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: Mes0MEPF_Details_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Mes0MEPF_Details.

preference.name: Mes0MEPF_Override_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Mes0MEPF_Override.

preference.name: Mes0MEPF_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations to show when expanding Mes0MEPF.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXElement.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the create stylesheet for Mes0MESTXElement objects.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXElementCreate.CREATE_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the Mes0MESTXElementCreate stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXElementRevision_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type i.e. Mes0MESTXElementRevision. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXElementRevision_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations to show when expanding Mes0MESTXElementRevision.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXFolder.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the create stylesheet for Mes0MESTXFolder objects.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXFolderCreate.CREATE_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the Mes0MESTXFolderCreate stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXLibrary.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the create stylesheet for Mes0MESTXLibrary objects.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXLibraryCreate.CREATE_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the Mes0MESTXLibraryCreate stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXLibraryRevisionColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns that will be displayed for the Standard Text Library structure in CME applications.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXLibraryRevisionDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOP Line properties whose display names appear as columns from left-to-right for Standard Text library structures in CME applications. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: Mes0MESTXLibraryRevisionShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the columns (identified by Mes0MESTXContextColumnsShownPref) within the CME applications.

preference.name: Mes0MEWIAssetsRelation_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Mes0MEWIAssetsRelation.

preference.name: Mes0MEWIPreviewRelation_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Mes0MEWIPreviewRelation.

preference.name: Mes0ManageDCDViaTWIEditor
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Data Collection Definition objects (DCDs) under Process/Operation should be managed by Textual Work Instruction (TWI) editor. Valid Values: * true: DCDs under Process/Operation will be managed by Textual Work Instruction editor. This is the default value. * false: DCDs under Process/Operation will be managed by Product Manufacturing Information (PMI).

preference.name: Mes0TWIRefInfoRelation_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Mes0TWIRefInfoRelation.

preference.name: Mfg0BvrProcess_AffectedChildrenProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties on a process object that are affected if children are added or removed.This preference is used for internal purposes only. Do not change the value of this preference. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values, each string must be a valid Teamcenter property.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOP.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for Mfg0MEPlantBOP objects.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOP.Mfg0MEPlantBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the default cloning rule used when the Paste Duplicate command is executed between a plant BOP context and a plant BOP context. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter cloning rule. The EBOPReference action is applied only for origin links if the paste action is within the same plant BOP structure. All other cases use the Ignore action.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOP.Mfg0MESimStudy.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the Paste operation is used to create new instances in a study starting from a bill of process (BOP) structure. Valid values are Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter cloning rule.

preference.name: Mfg0MEProcLine.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for Mfg0MEProcLine objects.

preference.name: Mfg0MEProcStatn.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for Mfg0MEProcStatn objects.

preference.name: Mfg0MEProdPrgCol_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths(in pixel) of the columns for the columns defined by the Mfg0MEProdPrgCol_ColumnPreferences preference.

preference.name: Mfg0MEShdStudy.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for SharedStudy objects.

preference.name: Mfg0MESimStudy.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for IsolatedStudy objects.

preference.name: Mfg0MESimStudy.MEOP.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Publish" operation is used from Study to an Operation.

preference.name: Mfg0MESimStudy.MEProcess.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Publish" operation is used from Study to a Process.

preference.name: Mfg0MESimStudy.Mfg0MEPlantBOP.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Publish" operation is used from Study to a PlantBOP.

preference.name: Mfg0MEStudy.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for Study objects.

preference.name: Mfg0MEStudy_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns defined in the Mfg0MEStudy_ColumnPreferences preference.This is an internal preference and should be modified automatically by Teamcenter only. Valid Values: Accepts positive integers. The number of values should be the same as the number of values in the Mfg0MEStudy_ColumnPreferences preference.

preference.name: Mfg0ProcResource.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the creation stylesheet for Mfg0ProcResource objects.

preference.name: NX_supported_operation_types
preference.preference_description: Determines which defined operation types are supported by the NX CAM Integration.Manufacturing engineers use the Part Planner application to outline the fabrication process plans necessary to manufacture components. The individual process planning operations are part of the fabrication process of a component. By default, the Teamcenter manufacturing process management , NX CAM Integration uses the MENCMachining operation type to support the NX CAM integration. Use this preference to define additional operation types to be supported by the integration. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter operation type.

preference.name: PLMXML_Pre_Expand_BOP_Rule_Name
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of a closure used to pre-expand process structures prior to a PLM XML export operation in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Pre-expansion on large structures increases the performance of the command and reduces the load on the database server. If the preference is not set, no pre-expansion is done. Valid Values: Accepts a valid Teamcenter closure rule. Teamcenter supplies you with the PreExpandProcess closure rule to perform the pre-expansion.

preference.name: PMPApplication_open_collaboration_panel
preference.preference_description: Determines if the Collaboration panel is displayed when the Part Planner application opens.

preference.name: PasteDuplicateAllowedPlantBOPTemplates
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of cloning rules names to be used when pasting duplicate objects (clones) between different types of plant bills of process. Valid Values: Accepts the names of cloning rules in the format SourceContextType.TargetContextType.RuleName where: SourceContextTypeSpecifies the root object type of the source structure.TargetContextTypeSpecifies the root object type of the target structure.RuleNameSpecifies the name of the cloning rule used.

preference.name: PasteDuplicateTemplates
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of cloning rules that are considered by the Paste Duplicate command. Teamcenter chooses the appropriate rule by matching the type names that are used as the rule name prefixes with the type names of the contexts participating in the Paste Duplicate operation. Valid Values: Accepts the names of cloning rules in the format SourceContextType.TargetContextType.RuleName.

preference.name: PertChart.AutoSizeMode
preference.preference_description: Enables or disables auto-size in the PERT chart. When auto-size is off, the size of the all newly created PERT nodes is uniform. When auto-size is on, the size of the newly created PERT nodes is automatically fitted to the displayed text, including allowing for multiple lines. Valid Values: yes - Enables auto-size. no - Disables auto-size.

preference.name: PertChart.BoxAutoSizeMaxWidth
preference.preference_description: If PertChart.AutoSizeMode is on, configures the maximal width to be used when new PERT nodes are created. Valid Values: A positive integer.If the PERT node text is larger than 250 pixels, the application splits the text into multiple lines as needed.

preference.name: PertChart.BoxDefaultHeight
preference.preference_description: If PertChart.AutoSizeMode is off, configures the default height to be used when new PERT nodes are created. The value is common for all PERT chart types; for example, once it is defined in the Process PERT chart, the Activity Flow chart and Station Flow chart use this value to define the height of newly created PERT nodes. Valid Values: A positive integer indicating the number of pixels.

preference.name: PertChart.BoxDefaultWidth
preference.preference_description: If PertChart.AutoSizeMode is off, configures the default width to be used when new PERT nodes are created. The value is common for all PERT chart types; for example, once it is defined in the Process PERT chart, the Activity Flow chart and Station Flow chart use this value to define the width of newly created PERT nodes. Valid Values: A positive integer indicating the number of pixels.

preference.name: PertChart.MEActivity.Text
preference.preference_description: Defines the text to be displayed in the PERT node of type MEActivity. The format for a valid entry are several segments structured like this: <free-text>[property-name]. <free-text> is any text except square brackets ([ and ]). The text can be empty. Use the formula editor (Edit -> Options -> Manufacturing -> Pert tab) to edit the values of the preference. <property-name> is a valid property name for MEActivity object. It must be wrapped in square brackets, e.g. [object_name].

preference.name: PertChart.MEOP.Text
preference.preference_description: Defines the text to be displayed in the PERT node of type MEOP. The format for a valid entry are several segments structured like this: <free-text>[property-name]. <free-text> is any text except square brackets ([ and ]). The text can be empty. Use the formula editor (Edit -> Options -> Manufacturing -> Pert tab) to edit the values of the preference. <property-name> is a valid property name for MEOP object. It must be wrapped in square brackets, e.g. [object_name].

preference.name: PertChart.MEPlant.Text
preference.preference_description: Defines the text to be displayed in the PERT node of type MEPlant. The format for a valid entry are several segments structured like this: <free-text>[property-name]. <free-text> is any text except square brackets ([ and ]). The text can be empty. Use the formula editor (Edit -> Options -> Manufacturing -> Pert tab) to edit the values of the preference. <property-name> is a valid property name for MEPlant object. It must be wrapped in square brackets, e.g. [object_name].

preference.name: PertChart.MEProcess.Text
preference.preference_description: Defines the text to be displayed in the PERT node of type MEProcess. The format for a valid entry are several segments structured like this: <free-text>[property-name]. <free-text> is any text except square brackets ([ and ]). The text can be empty. Use the formula editor (Edit -> Options -> Manufacturing -> Pert tab) to edit the values of the preference. <property-name> is a valid property name for MEProcess object. It must be wrapped in square brackets, e.g. [object_name].

preference.name: PertChartCreationLayout
preference.preference_description: Defines where newly created nodes are placed in the PERT chart. If the value is Horizontal, all newly created nodes are put at the top right corner; otherwise, they are placed at the bottom left corner. Valid Values: Horizontal - All newly created nodes are placed at the top right corner of the PERT chart.

preference.name: Plant.Template

preference.name: ProcessSimulate_DataPrep_RelationsType

preference.name: ReportXMLGenerationRules
preference.preference_description: Defines the specific components of a BOM to be included or excluded in an XML report. Valid Values: The preference syntax contains the following four fields. The primary, secondary, and relation fields accept an asterisk (*) as a wildcard. primary: secondary: relation: action These fields must be set in the following format: class.name/type.name:class.name/type.name:relation.name/attribute.name:Ignore/PublishCurrent/PublishChildren/PublishBOM Latter fields are subservient to former fields, allowing specific primary rules to override general rules set using wildcards.The relation.name/attribute.name specification must be one of the following:Teamcenter relation type: either a wildcard or a Teamcenter relation type name. BOM structure occurrence type: either a wildcard, null entry (for no occurrence type), or the occurrence type name.Folder content: specified with the string contents.The action setting must be one of the following: Ignore: does not publish the specified component. PublishCurrent: publishes only the current BOM line or attachment. PublishChildren: publishes only the current BOM line or attachment and its respective children. PublishBOM: publishes the entire BOM structure defined by the default revision rule, with the current component as the top line. The following examples illustrate valid settings for this preference: Publish the entire BOM structure: *:*:OccType.*:PublishChildren: Publish the entire, current, BOM structure, except for any BOM lines containing the MEConsumed and MEResource occurrence types (The specific rules of the first two lines override the general rule of the third line.): *:*:OccType.MEConsumed:PublishCurrent *:*:OccType.MEResource:PublishCurrent *:*:OccType.*:PublishChildren Publish the entire attachment structure: *:*:Relation.*:PublishChildren Publish the entire attachment structure, except any attachment with a IMAN_METarget orIMAN_MEWorkArea relation. In the first case, publish the entire BOM structure with the defined attachment as the top line of the structure. In the second case, publish only the current attachment without its children. (The specific rules of the first two lines override the general rule of the third line): *:*:Relation.IMAN_METarget:PublishBOM *:*:Relation.IMAN_MEWorkArea:PublishCurrent *:*:Relation.*:PublishChildren Publish the entire attachment structure, and ignore the TC_NX_nonps_occurrence relation. *:*:Relation.TC_NX_nonps_occurrence:Ignore Using this avoids the problem where the PS - BOM Structure report fails to expand subassemblies. Add the *:*:Relation.TC_NX_nonps_occurrence:Ignore rule before the *:*:Relation.*:PublishChildren rule.

ConflictColor:RGB-code - Applicable to operations only, specifies the color when a conflict is detected, for example, overlapping operations, or operations starting at the same position. DuplicateColor:RGB-code - Applicable to operations only, specifies the color whenever an operation occurs in multiple execution positions. ExceedingColor:RGB-code - Applicable to operations only, specifies the color whenever an operation exceeds the cycle time of station. ForegroundColor:RGB-code - Applicable to process zone and line boundaries only (ProductionZoneLine), specifies the color for text.

preference.name: typeAndRuleForProcessConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Configures process or compositions in the bill of process. This preference specifies what parent types in the process should be configured out depending on child occurrences of controlling types as defined by the controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration preference.You can also use this preference to configure out processes based on child relationships. If you do this, the controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration preference is ignored. Valid Values: parent-item-subtype - Specifies the item, operation, or process subtype as defined in the Business Modeler IDE application. This value is case-sensitive and must exactly match the business object specified in Business Modeler IDE. The second string after the colon must be one of the following:OneThe parent is configured out if any one of its controlling occurrences is configured out.AllThe parent is configured out only if all its controlling occurrences are configured out.AllLoadedThe parent is configured out only if all its loaded controlling occurrences are configured out. Loaded occurrences are occurrences that are referenced from another top line that is defined as the configuring structure.This parameter is not relevant for defining child types.OneLoadedThe parent process is configured out if one of its loaded controlling occurrences are configured out.This parameter is not relevant for defining child types. OCCType:occurrence-type | CHILD:child-type - Specifies that the filtering is based on the designated occurrence types or the designated child types. You can enter multiple occurrence types or multiple child types separated by a comma. Specifying this optional group of values for the preference causes the configuration mechanism to ignore the value of the controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration preference.
