preference.preference_description: Affects the behavior of the Teamcenter Integration for NX SaveAs Non-Master Part File dialog box as determined by the implementation of the USER_copied_datasets_details and USER_copied_dataset_name user exits. This preference is only read by these two user exits. To access the Integration Toolkit Function Reference, install the Teamcenter developer references when you install Teamcenter online help, or go to the Global Technical Access Center (GTAC): https://support.industrysoftware.automation.siemens.com/docs/teamcenter/ Specifies whether, once a user has been allowed to modify an automatically generated dataset name, it must be validated. Valid Values: true - Requires nonmaster datasets created in Teamcenter Integration for NX to pass the validation check. false - Does not require nonmaster datasets created in Teamcenter Integration for NX to pass the validation check.

preference.name: DATASET_saveas_never_copy
preference.preference_description: Affects the behavior of the Teamcenter Integration for NX SaveAs Non-Master Part File dialog box as determined by the implementation of the USER_copied_datasets_details and USER_copied_dataset_name user exits. This preference is only read by these two user exits. To access the Integration Toolkit Function Reference, install the Teamcenter developer references when you install Teamcenter online help, or go to the Global Technical Access Center (GTAC): https://support.industrysoftware.automation.siemens.com/docs/teamcenter/ Specifies dataset types that cannot be copied when the SaveAs command is implemented against a master part in Teamcenter Integration for NX to create a new revision. Valid values are Valid Teamcenter dataset types.

preference.name: DATASET_saveas_owner
preference.preference_description: Affects the behavior of the Teamcenter Integration for NX SaveAs Non-Master Part File dialog box as determined by the implementation of the USER_copied_datasets_details and USER_copied_dataset_name user exits. This preference is only read by these two user exits. To access the Integration Toolkit Function Reference, install the Teamcenter developer references when you install Teamcenter online help, or go to the Global Technical Access Center (GTAC): https://support.industrysoftware.automation.siemens.com/docs/teamcenter/ Specifies whether the owner of the new nonmaster part being created using the SaveAs command in Teamcenter Integration for NX should be the user performing the command, or the owner of the nonmaster part being copied. Valid Values: Original - The owner of the nonmaster part being copied is the owner of the new nonmaster part being created. SavingUser - The owner of the nonmaster part being copied is the user performing the SaveAs command.

preference.name: DATASET_saveas_pattern
preference.preference_description: Affects the behavior of the Teamcenter SaveAs dialog box as determined by the implementation of the USER_copied_datasets_details and USER_copied_dataset_name user exits.Also affects the behavior of the Teamcenter Integration for NX SaveAs Non-Master Part File dialog box in the same manner.This preference is only read by these two user exits.To access the Integration Toolkit Function Reference, install the Teamcenter developer references when you install Teamcenter online help, or go to the Global Technical Access Center (GTAC): https://support.industrysoftware.automation.siemens.com/docs/teamcenter/ Specifies a pattern used to generate and return the output name of nonmaster items during SaveAs of their master item. The pattern consists of literal text and the following tokens: ${UserText}, ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID}. Existing dataset names are expected to match this pattern, where ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} match the item ID and revision ID of the owning item revision respectively, and ${UserText} matches any text in the original name. For example, a typical pattern is: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, for example: drawing, and the minus sign (-) is literal text. If you are saving item revision 001234/B to item revision 002345/A, and the dataset's existing name is drawing-001234/B then the name is said to'match against the pattern. Because the ${UserText} at the start of this pattern matches any string, the dataset name fea-001234/B would also match against the pattern. However, drawing_001234/B would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and drawing-001235/B would not match since the item ID is incorrect.Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and item ID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the two datasets are saved as drawing-002345/A and fea-002345/A.You can modify these generated names using the DATASET_saveas_allow_name_modification preference. However, if the DATASET_saveas_force_name_validation preferences is set to true, the user-edited name is still required to match the pattern. Valid Values: ${UserText} - Dataset names are copied forward to the new revision unchanged.

preference.name: NXGraphicsBuilder
preference.preference_description: Specifies the path to the NX graphics builder utility used by Classification to enable the graphic creation functionality in the Classification application. Valid Values: ActivationMethod - Specifies the activation method for the graphics builder executable. This is normally set to TCE_Activation.You must set this option. CommandLine - Specifies the path to the graphics builder executable script, start_nx_graphicsbuilder.bat, typically located in the Teamcenter_root\bin\nx_graph directory. The path to the graphics builder batch file included with the software by default is set by the installation procedure. You must set this option. ScriptEvaluationPath - Specifies the path to the directory containing the ics_graphicsbuilder.tcl file.This option is optional. evaluateScript - Specifies whether to perform script evaluation of newly created classes. Valid values are yes, no, and not set.This option is optional. evaluateScriptWhenNotSet - Permits graphics builder to evaluate TCL scripts even when TCL script evaluation is defined as not set for the Classification object's class.This option is optional.

preference.name: NX_Supports_VISSC
preference.preference_description: Activates NX support of configuration using the VisStructureContext object during a Send to NX operation. Valid Values: true - Activates NX support. false - Deactivates NX support. The value must be set to false if using a version prior to NX 8.5.1.

preference.name: TC_NX_ATTRIBUTES_FORM

You can use the TC_object_type_delegation to override the delegation behavior. Valid Values: A single string as a value; the string must be a valid Teamcenter form type.

Values are in the format "ObjectType=object_type;Reason=reason;Actions=commands", where: object_type is the internal type reason associated with the modification on the object commands is the comma-separated list of commands.

preference.name: TC_NX_Current_Environment
preference.preference_description: Current NX environment that is set from preference or selected from the User Settings dialog. NX application launched with the current environment can only modify those models created in the same environment.

preference.name: TC_NX_DataExchange_Dataset_Preferences
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of dataset properties used by NX translators to import/export non-NX files from/to Teamcenter. All the file extensions supported by the translator need to be mentioned separately along with workflow such as import or export.During export, based on the user options if the translation results in multiple files then these files are zipped together and zip file is uploaded to dataset.For example, exporting NX assembly with external references to STEP.

preference.name: TC_NX_Database_Attributes_For_Load
preference.preference_description: Specifies the set of customer-defined, non-standard database attributes that are retrieved for each item type/dataset type whenever a part is loaded.All database attributes are retrieved for the top-level assembly. This preference controls the non-standard attributes that are retrieved for the child components of the top-level assembly and can be used for NX parts, transient parts, and JT parts. These non-standard attributes are defined using the attribute mapping definitions in Teamcenter and are refreshed on demand in NX depending on the operation that requests them. However, this may not necessarily occur when loading a part. The refreshing of attributes does not impact performance at low latencies, but does impact performance at higher latencies. If you are working with a latency greater than 10 milliseconds, it is recommended that you utilize this preference to refresh the database attributes whenever a part is loaded.To get an idea of the attributes that are being queried during load operations, load a sample assembly and check the NX syslog for messages about inefficient attributes loading.The following standard database attributes are always loaded for all contexts and do not have to be specified by this preference: DB_PART_NAME DB_PART_DESC DB_PART_NO DB_PART_REV DB_PART_TYPE DB_UNITS Valid Values: The value format is three keywords and their values. The keywords are: ItemType DatasetType AttributeTitle The format informs NX which database attribute to load for a specific context (ItemType/DatasetType). Values are enclosed in quotation marks. An empty string ("") can be applied to either or both of ItemType and DatasetType.The wild card designation, "*", can be specified as the value of AttributeTitle to indicate that all database attributes for that context are loaded when opening a part in NX. A context without any entries in TC_NX_Database_Attributes_For_Load loads standard database attributes only.

preference.name: TC_NX_Environments
preference.preference_description: List of NX environments that can be selected to launch the NX application in a specific environment from Teamcenter Client. The NX application with the selected environment can only modify those models created in the same environment. For each environment defined, for example ENV1, an additional preference named TC_NX_Location_for_ENV1 should also be defined to specify where the NX installation of that environment is located.

preference.name: TC_NX_Foreign_Datasets
preference.preference_description: Specifies the non-NX dataset types available to NX when it lists the datasets in an item revision.Specifying dataset types in this preference only makes the dataset types available to NX, it does not enable the application to read the dataset type. Valid Values: The value format is four values with each value separated by a semicolon. The actual values are based on these keywords: DatasetType;NamedReference;NamedReferenceFormat;NamedReferenceTemplate DatasetType is the extension for files of that type. NamedReference is the extension for files of that type. NamedReferenceFormat is the extension for files of that type. Valid values are BINARY or TEXT. NamedReferenceTemplate is the extension for files of that type. For example: DirectModel;JTPART;BINARY;jt For example: SE PART;SE-Part;BINARY;par The values are case sensitive and all of the entry must be included on one line for each dataset type.

preference.name: TC_NX_Navigator_Override_NX_Load_Option
preference.preference_description: Determines which configuration to load when an assembly is opened in Teamcenter Integration for NX from rich client. Its defined values are referenced only when an assembly is opened from My Teamcenter; assemblies opened from Structure Manager obey the revision rules set in Structure Manager. Valid Values: As Saved - Loads the part file as it was saved in Teamcenter Integration for NX. Latest - Loads the part file with the latest revision rule. None - Ignores the As Saved command and loads the assembly as defined in the load_options.def file.

preference.name: TC_NX_Object_Icons

preference.name: TC_NX_QuickSearch_Query

Example: __NX_STD_SIMPLE_ITEM_QUERY __NX_STD_SIMPLE_DESC_QUERY Provide the name of the saved query as the value of the preference. This will be used by NX simple search when customer default 'Teamcenter Integration - General - Browse - Quick Search Algorithm' is set to "Custom Query". Note: The query added here must also be added to the 'TC_NX_SavedQueries' preference and it should have a single search criteria of string type.

preference.name: TC_NX_Reference_OccTypes

preference.name: TC_NX_Supports_NXTCXML_Interop
preference.preference_description: Activates NX support of the NX-TCXML interoperability file type when using the "Send to NX" command from a Teamcenter structure application. If using NX 10 or higher, setting this to true should provide some performance improvement. It is done by sharing the structure window in Teamcenter instead of creating a new window in NX. The amount of performance improvement will vary from case to case. The default value is false.

preference.name: TC_NX_UPDATE_ATTRIBUTES
preference.preference_description: Determines whether NX attributes are synchronized with Teamcenter attributes. If this preference is set, define the attributes by setting the API_ugpart_attr_titles preference.This preference is enabled only when the newer method of NX/Teamcenter attribute synchronization is disabled by setting the UGII_UGMGR_ATTR_SYNC NX environment variable to OLD. Valid Values: yes - Synchronizes NX attributes with Teamcenter attributes. no - Does not synchronize NX attributes with Teamcenter attributes.

preference.name: TC_NX_View_Type
preference.preference_description: Sets the BOM view type that Teamcenter Integration for NX uses to read and write product structure information. Valid Values: A single string as a value; the string must be a valid Teamcenter BOM view type.

preference.name: TC_NX_allow_attrsync_master_with_item
preference.preference_description: Use with attribute synchronization functionality. Determines whether Teamcenter allows synchronization of UGMASTER attributes mapped to item-level properties from Teamcenter Integration for NX to Teamcenter.By default, attributes mapped to the properties of the Item Master form attached to item objects (not item revisions) will synchronize from Teamcenter to Teamcenter Integration for NX; but not in the reverse direction. These attributes are read-only in Teamcenter Integration for NX after the first execution of the NX Save command from the Teamcenter Integration for NX application.Permitting mapping in the reverse direction (Teamcenter Integration for NX to Teamcenter) allows mapping attributes to the properties of the Item Master form stored at the item level. This must not be done. Mapping at the item level may result in loss of data and/or the appearance of incorrect data. Valid Values: YES - Attributes mapped to the properties of the Item Master form will synchronize bidirectionally between Teamcenter Integration for NX and Teamcenter.This mapping allows multiple item revision objects (Rev/A, Rev/B, Rev/C, and so on) to overwrite the values stored on the Item Master form at the item level. Mappings at the item level may result in loss of data and/or the appearance of incorrect data. NO - Attributes mapped to the properties of the Item Master form will synchronize only from Teamcenter to Teamcenter Integration for NX.

preference.name: TC_NX_default_visual_report_folder_path

For example, when the Save As command is invoked upon a precise assembly with a revision rule of Latest Working, the new assembly is precise or imprecise, depending on the setting of this preference. Valid Values: yes - Creates a precise assembly. no - Creates an imprecise assembly.

preference.name: TC_NX_visual_report_additional_design_element_types
preference.preference_description: Indicates the additional Design Component types that are shown in the Teamcenter Property Selector for NX Visual Reporting besides the base type Design Component.

preference.name: TC_NX_visual_report_additional_item_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the additional item types that appear in the Teamcenter property selection dialog box of the NX visual reporting client. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid item type.

preference.name: TC_NX_visual_report_additional_secondary_object_types

preference.name: TC_SPSD_FOLDER

After this preference is defined, users can create Simulation Process Studio processes in any folder in the Teamcenter database. To see these processes in the Teamcenter Integration for NX palette, export the item revisions containing Simulation Process Studio datasets to the folder specified by this preference.Consumers use this folder to access process templates from Teamcenter Integration for NX.During database installation or upgrade, a folder is created with the name specified by this preference, if the folder does not already exist. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Must be a valid Teamcenter folder name.

preference.name: TC_SPSD_FOLDER_PATH
preference.preference_description: Defines multiple folders in the Teamcenter database where authors can create processes for testing and verification. All processes can be accessed via Teamcenter Integration for NX, allowing authors to test, validate, and finalize the processes. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values; each string must be a valid Teamcenter folder name.

ItemId ItemNameRevId TargetSite TimeStamp Valid Values: PDX-string - PDX-string is a string constant prefixed to the package file name of each exported package. You can use this to identify the package as desired, such as by the originating site. ItemId - Includes the item ID of the exported object as part of the package file name. ItemName - Includes the item name of the exported object as part of the package file name. RevId - Includes the revision ID of the exported object as part of the package file name. preference.name: AbsOccGrmCopyRules
preference.preference_description: Determines what action to take when revising a context BVR (Bom View Revision) which copies the Absolute Occurrence GRMs forward to new Item Revision of the BVR. The format is "className1:className2:Relation:RelationType:Action" where: - className1 - Is always class.AbsOccData. - className2 - Is either a class.Form or class.Dataset or * for either one. This is used for secondary object. - Relation - Not changeable and should always be Relation for GRM types. All other types are ignored. - RelationType - Type of relation as defined in the database under Admin->Types. - Action - Action to take with the secondary object. - Clone - Create a new GRM that points to copied secondary (form or dataset). - Ignore - The GRM is not copied to the new BVR. The default action is Ignore. - Reference - Create a new GRM that points to the old form or dataset. This mechanism will be used only for Absolute Occurrence GRMs that has either Forms or Datasets as secondary objects. For all other objects, the system will apply the default action (i.e. Ignore). Duplicate entries will take action from the first match from top. Default Rules and their Meanings: class.AbsOccData:class.Form:Relation.TC_Feature_Form_Relation:Clone GRM Primary = class named AbsOccData Secondary = class named Form Relation = TC_Feature_Form_relation Action = Clone - Will copy to the new revision class.AbsOccData:class.Form:Relation.IMAN_master_form:Clone GRM Primary = class named AbsOccData Secondary = class named Form Relation = IMAN_master_form Action = Clone - Will copy to the new revision class.AbsOccData:*:Relation.IMAN_Rendering:Ignore GRM Primary = class named AbsOccData Secondary = Any class Relation = IMAN_rendering Action = Ignore - This GRM is ignored class.AbsOccData:*:Relation.DependentOn:CloneRelationsToAbsOcc Similar to above, except that GRM primary and secondary are absolute occurrence GRM anchor and absolute occurrence respectively CAUTION - The preference specification is case sensitive and trailing blanks are not allowed. CAUTION - If secondary object is something other than Form or Dataset the system may error when trying to Clone that object. It is recommended to only Clone a Form or Dataset. All other objects should be Reference or Ignore for its action. CAUTION - If you add new copy rules, please verify it by Revising an Item Revision at least once and check the syslog to make sure there are no errors thrown while reading these preferences. Note that you need an assembly with absolute occurrence attachments to test this.

preference.name: BOMCompareVisibleModes
preference.preference_description: Determines which compare modes display in the BOM Compare dialog box and are returned by the BOM_compare_ask_modes ITK function. If this preference is removed, the default setting is used. Valid Values: IMAN_bcm_single_level_seq IMAN_bcm_single_level IMAN_bcm_var_level_seq IMAN_bcm_var_level IMAN_bcm_ext_var_level_seq IMAN_bcm_ext_var_level IMAN_bcm_lowest_level_seq IMAN_bcm_lowest_level IMAN_bcm_every_level Use the following compare modes for item-based logical BOM (LBOM) compares: IMAN_lbcm_var_level IMAN_lbcm_single_level IMAN_lbcm_lowest_level Use the following compare modes for occurrence-based logical BOM (LBOM) compares: IMAN_lbcm_var_level_occ IMAN_lbcm_single_level_occ Any custom compare mode must also be listed as a value in order for the mode to display in the BOM Compare dialog box.

preference.name: BOM_Display_Attachments_Panel
preference.preference_description: Controls the display behavior of the Attachments tab in the data pane. Valid Values: True - Attachments tab is displayed in the data pane. False - Attachments tab is not displayed in the data pane.

preference.name: BOM_Display_Referencer_Panel
preference.preference_description: Controls the display behavior of the Referencers tab in the data pane. Valid Values: True - Referencers tab is displayed in the data pane. False - Referencers tab is not displayed in the data pane.

preference.name: BOM_Display_Variant_Super_Panel
preference.preference_description: Controls the display behavior of the Variant tab in the data pane. Valid Values: True - Variant tab is displayed in the data pane. False - Variant tab is not displayed in the data pane.

preference.name: BOM_Frozen_Column_Count
preference.preference_description: Controls the scrolling behavior of the structure tree and other columns. The first n number of columns indicated by this preference are frozen for horizontal scrolling. Valid Values: Positive integer.

preference.name: BOM_enable_mem_mgt_probability_percent
preference.preference_description: Teamcenter can determine whether a product structure should be fully or partially expanded, depending on the quantity of server memory used. This preference specifies a percentage of free server memory, which (if exceeded) causes Teamcenter to limit structure expansion to conserve memory. It is effective for structure expansions initiated by the bomwriter and plmxml_export utilities, but not for expansions initiated in Structure Manager. Valid Values: Accepts a single integer in the range 0 to 100 as its value. If set to 0, there no limit on the use of available system memory for expansion.The following examples show the effect of different settings: Example 1: Total system memory - 4 GB Total available system memory - 2.5 GB BOM_enable_mem_mgt_probability_percent= 50 Total system memory used for BOM expansion = 1.25 GB approximately Example 2: Total system memory - 4 GB Total available system memory - 2.5 GB BOM_enable_mem_mgt_probability_percent= 25 Total system memory used for BOM expansion = 0.625 GB (625 MB) approximately The formula it utilizes to calculate the total system memory used is: (BOM_enable_mem_mgt_probability_percent X Available System Memory)

preference.name: BOM_enable_mem_mgt_structure_size_percent
preference.preference_description: Defines percentage of current BOM structure size which is used to calculate memory size affected to BOM memory management. This preference is considered only if BOM_enable_mem_mgt_probability_percent has value greater than 0. This preference is used only in Structure Indexing. Valid Values: integer values from 0 (BOM memory management disabled) to 100. Recommended value is 15.

preference.name: ClosureRulesForBomExpansion
preference.preference_description: Structure Manager allows the user to limit expansion of the product structure if a full expansion is not required. For example, you may not want to expand a subassembly if it is not assigned to your current project. Use this preference to specify one or more existing closure rules containing expansion constraints from which the user can select when expanding the structure. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be the name of a valid closure rule of type export.

preference.name: Configuration_override_with_CBOS
preference.preference_description: While using Configure Based on Selection (CBOS) feature, this preference defines behavior whether to replace existing applied configuration with Configuration Based on Selection. Here Configure Based on Selection means configuring the structure with the criteria created from the selected BOM Line's Rollup Variant Condition. Valid Values: * true: existing configuration applied on structure will be overridden with Configuration Based on Selection. * false: existing configuration will be added to Configuration Based on Selection.

preference.name: ConfigureToLoadEnableDefaultVariantConfig
preference.preference_description: Enables or disables the Do not show this dialog automatically when opening BOM check box in the Variant Rule or Configure dialog box in Structure Manager. The selected BOM line must also have at least one child line and classic variants defined to enable the check box. This check box is displayed only if you have enabled the configure to load feature. Valid Values: True - Hides the Do not show this dialog automatically when opening BOM check box in Structure Manager. False - Shows the Do not show this dialog automatically when opening BOM check box in Structure Manager.

preference.name: DisableSaveSos
preference.preference_description: Controls the saving of saved option sets (SOSs). Use this preference to manage the transition of variant data from SOSs to variant rules. If you set this preference to true, you should update all external references (for example, briefcases and Multi-Site replications) to the corresponding variant rules. Valid Values: true - Users may create new SOSs or modify existing SOSs. false - Users cannot create new SOSs or modify existing SOSs.

preference.name: DuplicateAssignToProject
preference.preference_description: Controls the status of the Assign Projects to New Items check box in the Duplicate... dialog box for duplicating Systems Engineering requirement structures. If the preference is set to true, the Assign Projects to New Items check box is selected and the section under the Projects header is expanded in the Duplicate... dialog box. Valid Values: true false

preference.name: DuplicateValidApps
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of rich client applications that allow running Duplicate operations in the background. The valid value is "com.teamcenter.rac.se.ui.SystemsEngineeringApplication". This is an internal preference that should not be modified by end users.

preference.name: GeneralDesignElement_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations to show when expanding a GeneralDesignElement.

preference.name: IC_SendTo_TargetApplications
preference.preference_description: Lists the different application IDs that are target applications for the context menu "Send To" in the Incremental Changes tab of the View/Edit Change dialog. An application ID is defined in an application's plugin.xml under the extension point com.teamcenter.rac.aifrcp.perspectiveDefs. Look for the property value of legacyAppId under the perspective definition.

preference.name: Incremental_Change_Management
preference.preference_description: Enables incremental change functionality and reveals the relevant menu commands. By default, this functionality is disabled.Enabling incremental change using the site preference activates this functionality in all applications where it is available, including Structure Manager, Manufacturing Process Planner, Part Planner, and Multi-Structure Manager. Individual users can use the corresponding user preference to hide the incremental change menu commands.An incremental change groups multiple structure changes to a given component (such adding a component, removing a component, modifying attachments, and so on). You can then apply effectivity to this incremental change to configure the associated changes. This change control method allows several independent structure changes to be made concurrently, including the addition or removal of unrelated components. Those changes can be implemented in any sequence. This method is suitable for large, flat structures without nested subassemblies or components. Teamcenter's other change control method (revisioning) is not suitable for this type of structure, as a separate revision would be required for every permutation of change.For information about creating incremental changes, see Structure Manager. Valid Values: true - Enables incremental change functionality and reveals the menu commands. false - Disables incremental change functionality and hides the menu commands.

preference.name: Internal_VariantRuleConfiguration_MultipleOptionValueSupport
preference.preference_description: Holds the list of rich client applications that support multiple values for a variant option during variant rule configuration. Valid Values: rich client application IDs. An application ID can be found in an application's plugin.xml under the extension point com.teamcenter.rac.aifrcp.perspectiveDefs. Look for the property value of legacyAppId under the perspective definition. The values are set by Teamcenter development and should not be altered by customers.

preference.name: Internal_VariantRuleConfiguration_OverlaySupport
preference.preference_description: Holds the list of rich client applications that support overlay of variant rules during variant rule configuration. Valid Values: rich client application IDs. An application ID can be found in an application's plugin.xml under the extension point com.teamcenter.rac.aifrcp.perspectiveDefs. Look for the property value of legacyAppId under the perspective definition. The values are set by Teamcenter development and should not be altered by customers.

preference.name: PSEAdditionColorPref
preference.preference_description: Determines the highlight color of an occurrence that has been added when displaying BOM compare results. Valid Values: Single string as a value; must be a valid color defined by your system at the X-Window System level.

preference.name: PSEAutoPackPref
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to place all occurrences on a single line. Valid Values: 0 - Does not pack identical occurrences on a single line. 1 - Packs identical occurrences on a single line.

preference.name: PSEChangedColorPref
preference.preference_description: Determines the highlight color of an occurrence that has been changed when displaying BOM compare results. Valid Values: Single string as a value; must be a valid color defined by your system at the X-Window System level.

preference.name: PSECreateVISameType
preference.preference_description: Determines whether variant items are always created as the same type as the parent, using the SaveAs creation method. Triggers an alternative variant item creation process, useful if Business Modeler IDE rules prevent normal variant item creation. Valid Values: true - Automatically creates variant items as the same type as the parent, using the SaveAs creation method. false - Does not provide an alternative item creation process. Does not automatically create variant items as the same type as the parent, using the SaveAs creation method.

preference.name: PSEDisplayTypePref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Structure Manager graphical display format. Valid Values: 1 - Vertical tree. 2 - Horizontal tree. 3 - Indented BOM.

preference.name: PSEEnableBranchConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Enables or disables the availability of branches to configure revisions in the structure. Valid Values: True - Enables branch-based configurations. By default, no branches are provided and you must create the necessary branches after enabling this capability False - Disables branch-based configurations.

preference.name: PSEImpreciseColorPref
preference.preference_description: Determines the display color for imprecise BOM view revisions. Valid Values: Single string as a value; must be a valid color defined by your system at the X-Window System level.

preference.name: PSEIsNewVILinkedToModule
preference.preference_description: Determines if variant items are linked to the generic component. Valid Values: true (variant items are linked to the generic component by default). false (variant items are not linked to the generic component by default).

preference.name: PSEPreciseColorPref
preference.preference_description: Determines the display color for precise BOM view revisions. Valid Values: Single string as a value; must be a valid color defined by your system at the X-Window System level.

preference.name: PSEShowDataPanelDefaultPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the "Show/Hide Data" panel is shown by default in the Structure Manager application. The default value is false (i.e. the panel is hidden).

preference.name: PSEShowSubstitutesPref
preference.preference_description: Determines how Structure Manager displays substitutes. Valid Values: 0 - Structure Manager does not display substitutes as separate BOM lines. 1 - Structure Manager displays substitutes as separate BOM lines.

preference.name: PSESubstituteColorPref
preference.preference_description: Determines the display color for substitutes. Valid Values: Single string as a value; must be a valid color defined by your system at the X-Window System level.

preference.name: PSE_Display_Pending_Edits
preference.preference_description: Determines whether pending edit markup functionality is enabled for editing actions such as adding, deleting, or modifying property attributes. These pending edits can be saved to the database, cancelled, or reversed. This preference can be set using the preference name as an environment variable.This editing mode is not available when an absolute occurrence or incremental change context is set. BOM compares cannot be run on objects containing pending edits. Valid Values: true - Pending edit markup is enabled for editing actions. false - Pending edit markup is not enabled for editing actions.

preference.name: PSE_enable_related_substitutes
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the Related Substitutes menu command displays in Structure Manager. Substitute part relationships are used to manage dependencies between substitute part selections. When there are dependencies between substitute part selections, you can relate the substitute part of one occurrence with substitute parts of the other occurrence. You can define these relationships for any occurrence in any BOM view revision. Valid Values: True - The Related Substitutes menu command displays in Structure Manager. False - The Related Substitutes menu command does not display in Structure Manager.

preference.name: PSE_expand_on_open
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the root node of an assembly is expanded when opened in Structure Manager, Manufacturing Process Planner, and Multi-Structure Manager. Valid Values: 0 - The root node of an assembly is not expanded when opened in Structure Manager, Manufacturing Process Planner, and Multi-Structure Manager. 1 - The root node of an assembly is expanded when opened in Structure Manager, Manufacturing Process Planner, and Multi-Structure Manager.

preference.name: PSE_icon_placement
preference.preference_description: Determines the location of icons within Structure Manager. Valid Values: 1 - Above. 2 - Right. 3 - Below. 4 - Left.

preference.name: PSM_classic_variants_date_families
preference.preference_description:
Manually controls variant option value mode detection for select variant option families in configurators "Teamcenter Classic Variant" or "Teamcenter Classic Effectivity". By default, a classic option family is recognized as a date family if all values are formatted as a date (as specified by ISO-8601). A value is considered to be formatted as a date if it matches the following pattern: dddd [{-}] dd [{-}] dd T dd [{:}] dd [{:}] ddZ, where d stands for a digit (e.g. "1975-04-28T02:20:00Z").
This is a site preference.

preference.name: PSM_global_option_item_ids
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of item IDs for items that contain global option definitions. These definitions can be reused when authoring variant modules. In the rich client, you can drop these global options into the module for which they are required. Set this preference by listing the IDs of all items that contain global options. For example: 000400 000410 000420 To add items to the list of IDs from within Structure Manager, select an item and choose Tools->Variants->Set/Unset Global Option Item. When you use this method, the item's UID is added to the list, for example: 000400 000410 000420 wVJ9K8VxIZ0KDB Valid Values: Valid Teamcenter item IDs that contain global options.

preference.name: PSM_overridden_jt_filetypes_to_retrieve
preference.preference_description: Specifies if only certain named references types for JT overrides be included in SOA 'getProductStructureArrangements' response. By default, no values are set for this preference, and the SOA response includes all named reference types for JT overrides. But sites can configure this behavior to filter out all named refereces other than values specified, e.g. "JTPART". Multiple values of valid DirectModel named reference types can be specified if desired, example valid values: JTPART Trushape-Data

preference.name: PS_allow_plmxml_transforms_with_no_legacy_factor
preference.preference_description: Allows Teamcenter to use the PS_set_plmxml_transform ITK call to set PLM XML transform data without first having to define a legacy transform factor via the PS_set_legacy_transform_factor ITK call. Use this preference when you have a new set up of Teamcenter with no legacy data, and thus no need to convert to or from legacy transform data. Valid Values: Yes - Ignores the legacy factor. No - Requires the legacy factor.

preference.name: PS_assume_legacy_transform_units
preference.preference_description: Determines how Teamcenter interprets the unit of measure for legacy transform data. Teamcenter and NX currently use meters for transform units of measure; legacy measurements were in inches or millimeters. This preference affects all data using legacy transforms which have no database-resident indication of the unit measurement with which they were stored. This preference can be set using the preference name as an environment variable. Valid Values: Inches - Assumes transform data is measured in inches. Millimeters - Assumes transform data is measured in millimeters. Unknown - No assumption made. User has to set the valid value either Inches or Millimeters.

preference.name: PS_assume_old_transform_format
preference.preference_description: (Deprecated)Determines how Teamcenter interprets the format of legacy transform data.This preference can be set using the preference name as an environment variable.This preference has been deprecated, to be removed from Tc15. Valid Values: In_Legacy_Format - Assumes all legacy transforms are in the same format as legacy NX transforms. Written_By_UG - Assumes all old transforms are in the same format as legacy NX transforms. Assumes all old transforms were written by Teamcenter Integration for NX. The PS_convert_legacy_transform ITK routine attempts to obtain the parent's unit information when converting transforms to eXT format. Unknown - No assumptions made. Use this setting when the transform data was written by an application other than Teamcenter Integration for NX.

preference.name: PS_bvr_names_to_carryover
preference.preference_description: Determines whether a PSBOMViewRevision (BVR) object will carry its modified name over to a copy (whether done with revise or save-as or structure duplication, etc.) of that PSBOMViewRevision. If the list of values is empty or none match the altered name, then the new copy of the PSBOMViewRevision will generate a default name based on the newly associated Item ID and BOM View Type name. Valid Values: * - Wildcard, will match any BVR name. (any entire BVR name) - Will match only that exact BVR name.

preference.name: PS_check_empty_transform_on_copy
preference.preference_description: Influences the copy of an occurrence's position data, in the specific scenario where the occurrence to be copied has no position data (i.e. its relative transformation data field is empty) but position data does exist on one or more occurrences higher in the structure. Valid Values: - true: The system will check for position data on parent occurrences of the occurrence to be copied. If found, the occurrence will be treated as if it contained an identity matrix for its relative transformation field. - false: The system will not check any further for position data if the occurrence to be copied has no position data (i.e. empty relative transformation data field). This is the default value.

preference.name: PS_convert_legacy_transform_to_plmxml
preference.preference_description: Allows Teamcenter to display legacy transforms in a PLM XML format. This preference is only effective if a legacy transform exists and no PLM XML transform is assigned.This preference can be set using the preference name as an environment variable. Valid Values: true - Teamcenter tries to convert the legacy transform to PLM XML format for display purposes only. false - Teamcenter displays the legacy transform as is.

preference.name: PS_option_value_delimiter
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delimiter to separate individual option values in variant rules if the option has multiple option values set. For example, if the option has values Red OR Blue OR Green, it is represented as Red(OR)Blue(OR)Green when this preference is set to (OR). Valid Values: Any delimiter string.

preference.name: PS_wu_configd_imprecise_only
preference.preference_description:
Determines whether parent item revisions are included in Where Used search results, regardless of whether they are configured by the revision rule. Where Used search results are filtered to include only those revisions configured by the selected revision rule. The revision rule is applied at each level, up to and including the top level. The system displays any intermediate level non-configured revisions referenced by precise occurrences, if the top of the chain of precise links is configured. Valid Values: true - Search results omit parent item revision objects that are not configured by the revision rule. This may occur if the specified revision rule contains only non-precise entries.This setting is equivalent to the default behavior in Teamcenter Engineering 9.1 and earlier releases. false - Search results include all parent item revision objects, regardless of whether they are configured by the revision rule.For example, use this setting to make a where-used query on Part1-A to identify every occurrence where Part1 is used with A as its configured revision. You obtain the same results whether you query one level at a time or all levels simultaneously, including with mixed precise and imprecise structures. You do not find any imprecise parent assemblies that are not configured by the selected revision rule.
Notes: This preference is not used by the "Configure Parent And Child" option. The "Configure Parent And Child" option will always return the latest parent revision that is configued by the revision rule.

preference.name: PUBLISH_AlignableSourceTypes
preference.preference_description: Determines which types are PublishLink sources. A PublishLink copies information from a source occurrence to a target occurrence. For example, transform data is copied from a design occurrence to a part occurrence. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings values. Each string must be a valid item type. The string can also contain subtypes of the item. For example: Item,Design

preference.name: PUBLISH_AlignableTargetTypes
preference.preference_description: Determines which types are PublishLink targets. A PublishLink copies information from a source occurrence to a target occurrence. For example, transform data is copied from a design occurrence to a part occurrence. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings values. Each string must be a valid item type. The string can also contain subtypes of the item. For example: Item,Part

preference.name: RAC_expand_below_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Determines the batch size in which BOM lines are processed when users click View->Expand Below. The selected BOM lines are expanded in levels of batches, the maximum size of each batch is the size set by this preference. Valid Values: Accepts a single integer as a value. A positive integer defines the number of lines processed per batch. Use -1 to indicate no maximum size, in which case all lines in a single level are processed in a single batch.

preference.name: RemoteObject_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the columns for the column names as defined in RemoteObject_ColumnPreferences preference

preference.name: Rollup_Variant_Feature
preference.preference_description: Determines whether variants on the EBOM are rolled up to the MBOM. When selected, Teamcenter adds the variant conditions of all the parent BOM lines of the selected line to its own variant condition. The resulting variant condition is called the rollup variant condition of the target BOM line. Teamcenter performs a roll up of variant conditions when a user performs an Assign, Compare or Propagate action on a linked EBOM and MBOM. Valid Values: true false

preference.name: Rollup_Variant_Traverse_Level_Is_InstallationAssembly
preference.preference_description: Specifies the upward traverse scope up to which line roll up variant conditions needs to be calculated. This preference will be considered only when the preference "Rollup_Variant_Feature" is set to true. Valid Values: * true: The roll up variant conditions are calculated up to the Installation Assembly in the BOM structure, if it exists. Otherwise, the roll up variant conditions are calculated up to the top line of the loaded structure. * false: They are calculated up to top line of the loaded structure. This is the default value.

preference.name: ShowModuleIcons
preference.preference_description: Determines whether modular variants are indicated in item and item revision icons. If set to true, the icon of items and item revisions containing a module are displayed in gray scale.This preference can be set using the preference name as an environment variable.Setting this preference to true impacts performance. Siemens PLM Software recommends that if modular variants are not used at your site, the default setting is kept.For information about indicating if an item or item revision is a variant item in item and item revision icons, see the preference. Valid Values: true - Displays icons of items and item revision containing modular variants in gray scale. false - Does not display icons of items and item revision containing modular variants in gray scale.

preference.name: TCEnforceSingleType
preference.preference_description: Determines whether items in a structure are restricted to a single item or GDE type, thus determining whether structures must be homogeneous, or can be heterogeneous.GDEs are general design elements used to model electrical interfaces. Valid Values: true - Items in a structure are restricted to a single item or GDE type. Users can only create homogeneous structures; any children added must be the same type as the parent.When this preference is set to true, the values of the TCAllowedChildTypes_

preference.name: TC_ENABLE_REPOSITION_DIALOG
preference.preference_description: Indicates the visibility in graphics menu of the dialog for the "Reposition" command. Valid Values: * true: Only the "Reposition" dialog is visible in graphics menu. * false: Only the "Transformation" dialog is visible in graphics menu. This is the default value. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_Undefined_Variant_State_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Determines if the undefined variant occurrence state is enabled. This state is indicated by the ? symbol. Valid Values: true - If any of the variant options in the variant condition is not set in the variant rule, the corresponding variant occurrence assumes an undefined (?) state. false - If any of the variant options in the variant condition is not set in the variant rule, the corresponding variant occurrence assumes a defined (Y) state.

preference.name: TC_show_option_family_prefix
preference.preference_description: Controls the visibility of the option family information in the Variant Condition returned by the Variant Configurator in the Product Structure application. Valid Values: - false: Hides the option family for the option. - true: Displays the option family for the option. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_show_option_item_prefix
preference.preference_description: Controls the visibility of the owning Item information in the Variant Condition returned by the Variant Configurator in the Product Structure application. Valid Values: - false: Hides the owning Item object for the option. - true: Displays the owning Item object for the option. This is the default value.

preference.name: view_view_valid_occurrence_types
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid occurrence types.

category.name: Password
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: PASSWORD_minimum_alpha
preference.preference_description: Determines the minimum number of alphabetic characters required in a password. Valid Values: A positive integer whose value, combined with other minimum password length values, does not exceed the maximum storage space allocated to a password in the database. A value of 0 means no minimum is required.

preference.name: PASSWORD_minimum_characters
preference.preference_description: Defines the minimum length required for a new password. Valid Values: A positive integer whose value does not exceed the maximum storage space allocated to a password in the database. A value of 0 means no minimum is required.

preference.name: PASSWORD_minimum_digits
preference.preference_description: Determines the minimum number of digits required in a password. Valid Values: A positive integer whose value, combined with other minimum password length values, does not exceed the maximum storage space allocated to a password in the database. A value of 0 means no minimum is required.

preference.name: PASSWORD_minimum_special_chars
preference.preference_description: Determines the minimum number of special characters (defined in the PASSWORD_special_characters preference) required in a password. Valid Values: A positive integer whose value, combined with other minimum password length values, does not exceed the maximum storage space allocated to a password in the database. A value of 0 means no minimum is required.

preference.name: PASSWORD_mixed_case_required
preference.preference_description: Determines if mixed case is required in a password. Valid Values: true - Mixed case is required in a password. false - Mixed case is not required in a password.

category.name: Product Structure.Appearance Configuration
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: APPR_allow_separate_spatial_processing
preference.preference_description: When set to "true", specifies that spatial cache processing for Appearances will be done in a separate update package (in a separate appearance updater process). A value of "false" means that spatial cache processing will occur in the same updater process as the rest of the appearance processing.

preference.name: APPR_max_appearances_per_process
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of appearances that will be processed at a time by the appearance updater. A lower value will result in lower memory consumption at the cost of performance of appearance updates.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextSupportInstallationAssemblySelection
preference.preference_description: Determines whether installation assemblies can be selected from search results. Valid Values: TRUE - Installation assemblies can be selected from search results. FALSE - Installation assemblies cannot be selected from search results.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextUseUnconfigurableSearchResults
preference.preference_description: Determines whether unconfigurable search results display in search results. Unconfigurable search results always prompt an error message (such as No revision found for current revision rule). This preference determines whether, after the error message displays, the unconfigurable search results display in the search results list. Valid Values: TRUE - Unconfigurable search results display. FALSE - Unconfigurable search results do not display.

preference.name: TC_allow_appr_checking
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the appearances checking is to be enabled or not. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: TC_allow_appr_query_auditing
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the appearances querying is to be audited or not. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: TC_appr_allow_remote_query
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the querying for remote appearances (ones associated with a remote published appearance-root) is to be enabled or not. Valid values are true/false. NOTE: To publish an appearance-root, ensure that AppearanceRoot is in the list for TC_publishable_classes preference.

preference.name: TC_appr_checking_interval
preference.preference_description: Specifies the appearances checking interval in hours (how often do we check appearances).

preference.name: TC_appr_remote_query_timeout
preference.preference_description: Specifies the timeout period (in seconds) for remote appearance queries.

preference.name: TC_prevent_appr_query_on_corrupt_root
preference.preference_description: Appearances Logical: do we allow the querying of appearances associated with a corrupt appearance-root?

category.name: Product Structure.Appearance Configuration Background
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: APPR_allow_background_updates
preference.preference_description: Deprecated. Whether to allow the appearance_updater to perform background updates (using its "-background" flag).

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_auditing_enabled
preference.preference_description: Deprecated. Whether to create audit records when the appearance_updater performs background updates.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_gap_between_tries
preference.preference_description: Deprecated. How long (in seconds) a background updater should wait between attempts (successful or otherwise) to look for packages to process.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_interval
preference.preference_description: Deprecated. How often (in minutes) to expect a background appearance updater to be run (for example in a cron job or equivalent). When a new package is placed on the update queue, then if background updaters are expected to be running (as specified by the supervisor preference being 0) and such an updater has not recently enough, then an email is sent to the recipient specified by the Site Preference "APPR_background_updater_admin_email_address".

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_max_num_failures
preference.preference_description: Deprecated. How many background updater failures to allow for a particular package. Once the number of failures exceeds this value, background updates are disabled (by setting the Site Preference "APPR_allow_background_updates" to false).

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_max_num_heartbeats
preference.preference_description: Deprecated. How many heartbeat records to keep per machine. A heartbeat record is simply a note made by the background appearance updater to show that it has run; this serves as a way to find out from the database whether such updaters are running as intended.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_max_num_records
preference.preference_description: Deprecated. How many records to keep about the appearance updater's background activity.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_max_num_tries
preference.preference_description: Deprecated. How many times an individual background updater should look for packages to process before exiting.

category.name: Product Structure.CAD BOM Alignment
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: FND0_COPY_DESIGN_PROP_TO_PART
preference.preference_description: Enable the functionality to copy properties from Design BOM Line to Part BOM Line on Alignment. Values will have format of Design_Property_name : Part_Property_name where Design_Property_name value from DesignBOMLine will be copied to Part_Property_name value from PartBOMLine. In case of invalid value format properties will not get copied and the operation of Alignment will continue.

preference.name: FND0_COPY_PART_PROP_TO_DESIGN
preference.preference_description: Enable the functionality to copy properties from Part BOM Line to Design BOM Line on Alignment. Values will have format of Part_Property_name : Design_Property_name where Part_Property_name value from PartBOMLine will be copied to Design_Property_name value from DesignBOMLine. In case of invalid value format properties will not get copied and the operation of Alignment will continue.

preference.name: FND0_DESIGNREVISION_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of ItemRevision Types qualified as Design Types defined by BO constant Fnd0PartDesignQualifier. This is a system managed preference and should not be edited manually. Use bmide_modeltool utility for populating the values.

preference.name: FND0_DESIGN_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Item Types qualified as Design Types defined by BO constant Fnd0PartDesignQualifier. This is a system managed preference and should not be edited manually. Use bmide_modeltool utility for populating the values.

preference.name: FND0_ENABLE_CBA_EXPOSURE
preference.preference_description: Enables the exposure of Part-CAD alignment user interface in Active Workspace. If true, Active Workspace UI will show aligned design for parts and will allow user to align designs to part. If false, the aligned designs section will not be presented in the user interface.

preference.name: FND0_ENABLE_DESIGN_BOM_ENGINEERING_BOM_ALIGNMENT
preference.preference_description: Enables Design - Engineering BOM alignment in Teamcenter. By default this is disabled.

preference.name: FND0_ENABLE_MULTIPLE_ALIGNMENT_CRITERIA
preference.preference_description: Enables multiple alignment criteria based on BOM Line property name and its property value Value will have format of: 1. BOMLine_Property_name=BOMLine_Property_value where BOMLine_Property_name is BOM Line property and BOMLine_Property_value is the property value need to be evaluate to satisfy multiple alignment criteria. 2. True, always enables multiple alignment 3. False, always disables multiple alignment In case of invalid BOMLine_Property_name=BOMLine_Property_value format it disables multiple alignment

preference.name: FND0_PARTREVISION_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of ItemRevision Types qualified as Part Types defined by BO constant Fnd0PartDesignQualifier. This is a system managed preference and should not be edited manually. Use bmide_modeltool utility for populating the values.

preference.name: FND0_PART_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Item Types qualified as Part Types defined by BO constant Fnd0PartDesignQualifier. This is a system managed preference and should not be edited manually. Use bmide_modeltool utility for populating the values.

preference.name: FND0_PRODUCTEBOMREVISION_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of ItemRevision Types qualified as ProductEBOM Types defined by BO constant Fnd0PartDesignQualifier. This is a system managed preference and should not be edited manually. Use bmide_modeltool utility for populating the values.

preference.name: FND0_PRODUCTEBOM_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Item Types qualified as ProductEBOM Types defined by BO constant Fnd0PartDesignQualifier. This is a system managed preference and should not be edited manually. Use bmide_modeltool utility for populating the values.

preference.name: PSM_Skip_Unload_PublishedPartAssembly_OnViewer
preference.preference_description: Controls if unload should be performed for published part structure from product graphic viewer or not. Valid Values: - true: When user un-checks a published part BOMLine, make part structure invisible on graphic viewer, but skip unload part structure behind the scene. This is the default value. - false: When user un-checks a published part BOMLine, make part structure invisible on graphic viewer and also unload part structure behind the scene.

preference.name: PSM_enable_PLMXML_Assembly
preference.preference_description: Controls the generation of PLMXML assembly file, when design assembly published with shape option in the Multi Structure Manager and MPP application. The default value is true which will enable the PLMXML assembly generation and attach it to Part revision with rendering relation.

preference.name: PartStructureDepthForCompletenessCheck
preference.preference_description: Determines how many levels Teamcenter traverses when you perform a completeness check of the part structures resulting from CAD BOM alignment. Valid Values: Accepts any numeric value. If you enter 0 or a negative value, a completeness check is not performed.

category.name: Product Structure.Collaboration Context
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: ACTLine_AutoSelect_UsageAddress
preference.preference_description: Indicates Collaboration Context application to load a corporate part by auto-selecting a Usage Address from usage server. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ALLOC_Group_Allocation_Types
preference.preference_description: For use with allocation functionality. Specifies the allocation types that can be used in the specified allocation map. For example, ensure the Allocation_One allocation type is created only in association with the AllocationMap_one allocation map by setting this preference to:AllocationMap_one:Allocation_One Valid Values: Allocation map type:Allocation type,Allocation type Where Allocation map type is a valid Teamcenter allocation map type, and all Allocation type entries are valid Teamcenter allocation types.

preference.name: ALLOC_Product_Representation_Types
preference.preference_description: For use with allocation functionality. Specifies which BOM view types can be used to create allocations in the specified allocation map. For example, ensure allocations are created only between MEProcess and View types for the AllocationMap_one allocation context by setting this preference to:AllocationMap_one:MEProcess,View Valid Values: Allocation map type:View type1,View type2 Where Allocation map type is a valid Teamcenter allocation map type, and all View type entries are valid subtypes of Teamcenter views.

preference.name: ALLOC_Source_Occurrence_Types
preference.preference_description: For use with allocation functionality. Specifies the components that can be used as source components for a given allocation type. Valid values are Allocation type::Source component type Where Allocation type is a valid Teamcenter allocation type, and Source component type is a valid Teamcenter object type used in a product structure.

preference.name: ALLOC_Target_Occurrence_Types
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of components that can participate as target components for a given Allocation type. The components in this preference are the valid Sub-Types of Allocations and valid sub-types of objects that can be instantiated in the Product Structure Editor.

preference.name: ALLOC_map_copy_allocations
preference.preference_description: For use with allocation functionality. Determines whether the allocation set is carried forward when the allocation map is saved as a new allocation map, or revised. By default, the allocation set is carried forward during either of these actions. To prevent the allocation set from being carried forward, remove from preference values the names of the revision action (copy, SaveAs, or Revise) for which you do not want to carry forward the allocation set. Valid Values: saveAs - The allocation set is carried forward when the allocation map is saved as a new allocation map. Revise - The allocation set is carried forward when the allocation map is revised.

preference.name: ALLOC_source_target_cardinality
preference.preference_description: For use with allocation functionality. Specifies the cardinality permitted between a given allocation type and other product structure object types.Specify valid target components for a particular allocation type using the ALLOC_Target_Occurrence_Types preference. Specify valid source components for a particular allocation type using the ALLOC_Source_Occurrence_Types preference.The system supports multiple sources and targets for allocation using cardinality functionality. The system supports the following allocation relationships:One-to-one, Many-to-one, One-to-many, Many-to-many. For example, you can use this preference to enforce a cardinality allowing the Network_Port type allocation to participate only in one-to-one relationships. Allocations using this type can contain only a single source and a single target. To do so, set this preference to:Network_Port::1,1 Valid Values: Allocation subtype::1,1 - Where Allocation subtype specifies the allocation type; this specified allocation type can only be used in one-to-one relationships. Allocation subtype::1,n - Where Allocation subtype is a valid Teamcenter object type; this specified object type can be used in one-to-many relationships. Allocation subtype::n,1 - Where Allocation subtype is a valid Teamcenter object type; this specified object type can be used in many-to-one relationships. Allocation subtype::n,n - Where Allocation subtype is a valid Teamcenter object type; this specified object type can be used in many-to-many relationships.

category.name: Product Structure.Configurator Context
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: Item_Cfg0ProductItem_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between a Configurator Context and the Item under which it is pasted.

preference.name: PSEConfiguratorFeaturePropertyMapping
preference.preference_description: Indicates for what Occ Notes or Property on which mapped properties are authored, so that the system reads the mapped properties and displays the corresponding feature selection for each corresponding configured BOMlines.For example, the preference value can be AIE_OCC_NAME. The mapped property exmaples are bl_occurrence_name=[Teamcenter]family1 bl_quantity=[Teamcenter]family2

preference.name: PSESolutionVariantAutoCreate
preference.preference_description: Enables automatic ID generation for the new solution variant Item creation. This is supported for single level solution variant creation only. Valid Values: * true: An auto generated ID will be assigned to the new solution variant Item and the Item creation wizard will not be shown. * false: Item creation wizard will be shown.

preference.name: PSM_PCA_enable_default_variant_configuration
preference.preference_description: Enables default configuration to consider Product Configurator authored constraints while opening the Product structure Valid values are: * false: Product Structure will not be configured using Product Configurator authored constraints, while opening. This is the default value. * true: Product Structure will be configured using Product Configurator authored constraints, while opening.

preference.name: PSM_default_configurator_context
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default Configurator Context used in the Structure Management application to configure the variability of Product Structures. This is an internal preference used by Product Structure and should not be modified manually.

preference.name: PSM_enable_product_configurator
preference.preference_description: Enables the use of Teamcenter Product Configurator to configure the variability of Product Structure. Any modification to the preference value requires restart of Structure Manager application to avoid data integrity issues. The PSEVariantsMode preference will be ignored and Variants will be authored/configured using Configurator Context via association or setting the Default Configurator Context. Valid values are: * true: Product Structure will use the Configurator Context for Variability. This is the default value. * false: Product Structure will refer to the PSEVariantsMode preference for Variability.

preference.name: SolutionVariantProviderAvailable
preference.preference_description: If this preference is set to true, it will show the "Solution Variants" section in the "Overview" tab of Active Workspace. This is an internal preference and not to be modified by the admin.

category.name: Product Structure.Design Context Clearance Integration
category.category_description: Defines preferences for clearance proxies in a site

preference.name: RDVClearanceProxyServers
preference.preference_description: Specifies the database connection used by the clearance proxy server to connect to the clearance database. Valid Values: DATASOURCE=System-running-clearanceDB-proxy: Port-for-clearanceDB-proxy-server:CONNECT_DATA=Oracle-connection-name:FILTER_NAME=blank An example value is cleardb:7206:CLDB:xyzFilter.

category.name: Product Structure.Design Context Context Definition
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextAllowNoWorkParts
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Design Context requires users to enter at least one work part in the Work Part list in the Context Definition window before displaying the Context Configuration window.When Design Context is used only for modifying assemblies or components, you may want to require users to have at least one work part in the Context Definition window before the Context Configuration window displays; this may help inexperienced users to work with the application.Experienced users may use Design Context for design review sessions of large pieces of the product model or for product model reviews. This requires users to use filters to configure a product context on the second window that they have yet to specify on the third window. Valid Values: 0 - Requires at least one work part in the Work Parts list to continue. Design Context displays a warning that no work parts are provided and displays the initial window again. 1 - Allows users to continue to the Context Configuration window without work parts in the Work Parts list.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextECObject.TYPE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the workspace object type used to authorize design changes. Typically this is an Change Item type, but this preference also allows you to integrate custom change strategies, for example, using a form to authorize design changes.If the type corresponds to objects extending from the item revision class, the primary property displayed in Design Context is the item ID that has an input field for the item revision ID. In all other cases, the primary property is the name of the object. Valid Values: Any Teamcenter change object type.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextECObject.WorkPartProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of change object relationship properties for finding associated work parts when a user adds or selects a new change object. Work parts are the components the user intends to modify or to be the focus of a design session. The list should specify all properties referencing related work parts that are to be added or selected in the Work Parts list. Valid Values: Any property on the change object specified in the PortalDesignContextECObject.TYPE preference, typically, relationships available as properties. The relationships specified on this preference are often the same as the properties specified on the PortalDesignContextECObject.WorkPartRelationships preference. However, this is not the case if you use the standard Change Viewer.For new change (Change Manager) objects, possible values are: CMHasSolutionItem CMHasProblemItem CMHasImpactedItem CMReferences CMImplementedBy CMImplements CMHasWorkBreakdown For classic change objects, possible values are: solution_items problem_items affected_items reference_items addressed_by

preference.name: PortalDesignContextECObject.WorkPartRelationships
preference.preference_description: Specifies Teamcenter relationships between work parts and the change objects that authorize changes on these work parts. These relationships are used to find the change objects when users add or select work parts. Valid Values: Any relationships on the change object specified in the PortalDesignContextECObject.TYPE preference that reference work parts. The relationships specified in this preference are often the same as the properties specified on the PortalDesignContextECObject.WorkPartProperties preference. This is not true, however, for the standard Change Viewer.For new change (Change Manager) objects, possible values are: CMHasSolutionItem CMHasProblemItem CMHasImpactedItem CMReferences CMImplements CMHasWorkBreakdown For classic change objects, possible values are: EC_affected_item_rel EC_solution_item_rel EC_problem_item_rel EC_reference_item_rel EC_addressed_by_rel

preference.name: PortalDesignContextExcludedWorkPart.Types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the item types excluded from the Work Part list in Design Context. For sites that have not yet migrated to Teamcenter Change Viewer, Siemens PLM Software recommends excluding EngChange items. Valid Values: Any Teamcenter item type.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextFindInstallationTreeWalkIncrement
preference.preference_description: Specifies the direction the tree is maneuvered through to find the installation assembly for the specified BOM line. Valid Values: -1 - Traverses down from the top of the tree towards the BOM line. 1 - Traverses up from the BOM line towards the root.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod
preference.preference_description: Specifies the standard for identifying an installation assembly, that is, the assembly that defines the existence and purpose of a component in a product structure. Each appearance of a part can be defined in only one installation assembly at a time.The values specify the name of a Teamcenter Java API method for the DesignContextApplication class. The standard methods are listed below. Your enterprise can create custom Java methods for use with this preference.Siemens PLM Software recommends setting this preference. Valid Values: hasIRType - Returns the closest parent assembly up the tree that has a specific item type. If you specify this value, you must also specify the required item type using the PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.hasIRType.Type preference. has_bomline_prop - Returns the closes parent assembly up the tree that has a BOM line property. isPrecise - Returns the first assembly down the path, beginning at the product item that has a precise BOM View revision. transformsComponents - Returns the first assembly down the path, beginning at the product item that transforms components below it into product space.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.hasIRType.Type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the item type used to identify an installation assembly using the hasIRType method. Setting this preference is required when using the hasIRType method. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Can be any valid Teamcenter item type.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.has_bomline_prop.name
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM line property name used to identify an installation assembly using the has_bomline_prop method. Use this preference with the PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.has_bomline_prop.value preference to identify installation assemblies by BOM line name and value. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Can be any valid property name or run-time property name on a BOM line.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.has_bomline_prop.value
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM line property value used to identify an installation assembly using the has_bomline_prop method. Use this preference with the PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.has_bomline_prop.name preference to identify installation assemblies by BOM line name and value. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. Can be any valid property value or run-time property value on a BOM line.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemQuery
preference.preference_description: Identifies a query that corresponds to the configurable definition of product item characteristics. Specifies the name of a saved query that allows Teamcenter to find product items based on configurable criteria. You can use the Query Builder application to create and save this query.Siemens PLM Software recommends that you create a query with built-in constraints according to the settings of the PortalDesignContextProductItemProperties preference.Teamcenter refers to this preference to find or filter for product items in one of the following applications:Product Configurator (Teamcenter variant and effectivity configurators)Design ContextPlatform Designer Valid Values: Name of any saved query. Use Query Builder to list available saved queries.

category.name: Product Structure.Design Context Filter Configuration
category.category_description: No description available for this category.
