Valid values are true - Parts inside the 3D bounding box are searched by default. false - Parts outside the 3D bounding box are searched by default.

preference.name: RDV_default_find_intersecting_parts
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether parts intersecting with the 3D bounding box during a spatial search are excluded from or included in the results by default. Applies to spatial searches in the Structure Manager, Multi Structure Manager, and Manufacturing Process Planner applications. Valid Values: true - Intersecting parts are included by default. false - Intersecting parts are excluded by default.

preference.name: RDV_design_audit_info
preference.preference_description: Contains a list of BOM lines, user can see in AuditReport.

preference.name: RDV_install_configuration_rules
preference.preference_description: Defines the revision rules used to configure the installation assembly in a product.The Add Design To Product wizard creates new occurrences in the Installation Assembly revision that is configured by the revision rule defined in this preference.If your site chooses to grant write access only to Work In Process (WIP) revisions this would be a WIP revision rule. For example, Latest Working. This includes user-defined revision rules set with the RDV_authoring_override_user preference. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings; each string must be a valid Teamcenter revision rule.

preference.name: RDV_modify_item_desc_on_rdip
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the Item revision's description needs to be modified during Replace Design in product. Valid Values: true : Modify description. false : Do not modify description. This is the default value.

preference.name: RDV_part_occ_note_mappings
preference.preference_description: Specifies a multivalue property that contains the lists of values that prepopulate the notes displayed in the Enter Part Data step of the Add Part to Product wizard or the Replace Part in Product wizard. The note types are specified in RDV_auto_populate_occ_notes preference. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values.

preference.name: RDV_platformdesigner_assign_bulk_variability
preference.preference_description: Determines if the user can add and remove variability on the product context in bulk with Platform Designer. Valid Values: true - The user can add and remove variability on the product context in bulk. false - The user cannot add and remove variability on the product context in bulk.

preference.name: RDV_product_code_mapping
preference.preference_description: Specifies a single-value mapping property that contains the value to prepopulate the Usage_Product note displayed in the Enter Part Data step of the Add Part to Product wizard. Valid Values: Accepts a string as a value.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_3DBox_dimensions
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for 3D box dimensions. It applies to spatial searches. It applies to spatial searches in the Structure Manager, Multi Structure Manager, and Manufacturing Process Planner applications. Valid Values: 0 - Centroid and size. 1 - Origin and size. 2 - Maximum and minimum extents.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_3DBox_search
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option type for spatial searches. Applies to spatial searches in the Structure Manager, Multi Structure Manager, and Manufacturing Process Planner applications. Valid Values: true Sets the 3D box search option as default. false Sets the proximity search option as default.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_3D_Manipulator_ON
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option type for 3D manipulators. Valid Values: true - 3D manipulators are on by default. false - 3D manipulators are off by default.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_slider_increment
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default increment of the slider. Valid Values: Any positive floating value.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_true_shape_filtering_ON
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for TruShape filtering. Valid Values: true - TruShape filtering is on by default. false - TruShape filtering is off by default.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_use_selections_from_tree
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for the target part selections. Applies to spatial searches in the Structure Manager, Multi Structure Manager, and Manufacturing Process Planner applications. Valid Values: true - Use selections from the tree. false - Use selections from the table.

preference.name: RDV_uneditable_part_occ_notes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the occurrence notes that are not editable in the Enter Part Data screen of the Add Part to Product wizard or the Replace Part in Product wizard. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values.

preference.name: RDV_usage_audit_info
preference.preference_description: Contains a list of Occurrence Notes of LOUs, user can see in AuditReport.

preference.name: RDV_usage_occurrence_notes
preference.preference_description: Defines the occurrence note names that are displayed in the Enter Part Data step of the Add Part to Product wizard or the Replace Part in Product wizard. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter occurrence note.

preference.name: RDV_user_defined_units_of_measure
preference.preference_description: Specifies a single-value mapping property that contains the value to prepopulate the Usage_Product note displayed in the Enter Part Data pane of the Add Part to Product wizard. Valid Values: METERS MILLIMETERS INCHES UNKNOWN

preference.name: RDV_variant_overlays_mode
preference.preference_description:
Valid values for this preference are 0/1/2/4. 0 - Indicates dynamic mode which is the default mode. 1 - Indicates static mode. 2 - Indicates hybrid mode. Static if the number of variable options is greater that PortalDesignContextSetVariantRulesMaxVariantRules else dynamic. 4 - Indicates tabular mode. Use the X-O Chart to calculate variant rules dynamically.
When set to static mode valid overlay variant rules are taken as the (static) subset of all variant rules available for the top-level for which the target BOMLines configure. This can be useful if the set of saved variant rules covers all or close enough to all valid option value combinations. In this case static overlay variant rules produce acceptable results without having rule checks available in PSE. When set to dynamic, valid overlay variant rules are dynamically computed based on the variabilty model in PSE (options affecting the target BOMLines, option defaults, rule checks). The default value is dynamic mode (0).

preference.name: TCAllowedParentTypes_Fnd0Workset
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid parent item types.

category.name: Product Structure.RDV Configuration
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: Fnd0AppSession_default_workflow_template
preference.preference_description: Defines the default workflow template to be used for submitting Session to the workflow.

category.name: Product Structure.Variant Administration
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: Fnd0ItemLineLite_bl_line_name_expression
preference.preference_description: Defines the property expression used for evaluation of the line name for objects of the Fnd0ItemLineLite business object type. Valid Values: The valid value is a string that contains property internal names (always preceded with the $ character), the character + to signal concatenation, and strings surrounded by double quotation marks.

preference.name: PS_VariantCondition_option_prefix
preference.preference_description: Sets the display format for option name in Variant Condition dialog. Valid Values: * true: Shows a string in the format "[ItemId]Option_name". * false: Shows a string in the format "[object_string]Option_name" where object string is the display name of the Item in user interface.

preference.name: PersistFullyExpandedSVR
preference.preference_description: Activates the capture of all the values of a Variant Rule (which includes Default, Derived Default) when setting a Saved Variant Rule (creation or update). This is required if the Saved Variant Rule is used in Active Workspace BOM Indexing generation. Valid Values: * true: all values are captured. * false: only user set values are captured in a Saved Variant Rule during creation or update. This is the default value.

category.name: Product Structure.Where Used
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: IsWhereUsedConfiguredModeEnabled
preference.preference_description:
Monitors the Where Used Configured Parent option in the Impact Analysis view.
Note: This preference is not for customer customization. The value for this preference is set by the system at the user level. This preference informs the Graphics Panel the state of "Configure Parent And Child" option.

category.name: ProductView
category.category_description: Preferences affecting the behavior of Product views

preference.name: Vis_PV_AllowLateLoading
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the late loading of ProductViews is enabled. Valid Values: * true: Allows the late loading of ProductViews. This is the default value. * false: Does not allow the late loading of ProductViews.

preference.name: Vis_PV_BlockingViewToggles
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of view toggles preventing the creation of a Product view. Please refer to the description of the preference "Vis_PV_InvalidConfigWarnLevel" for more details. Valid Values: show_unconfigured_variants show_unconfigured_changes show_unconfigured_assignment fnd0show_uncnf_occ_eff show_suppressed_occurrences fnd0show_gcs_cps

preference.name: Vis_PV_CheckOutOnOpen
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the ProductView should be checked out on open. Valid Values: * true: The ProductView is checked out when opened and remains checked out until the document is closed. This is the default value. * false: The ProductView is not checked out when opened.

preference.name: Vis_PV_Geometry_Asset
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether a 3D Geometry Asset should be captured when a Product View is created. It also specifies if an Outline Capture should be included with the 3D Geometry Asset. Valid values are "NoGeoAsset", "GeoAssetWithOutline", "GeoAssetWithoutOutline".

preference.name: Vis_PV_HowTo_Configure_BOM
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the BOM Window is to be configured before a Product View is applied to it. This configuration is captured in the Product View with the use of the VisStructureContext object. This object records the Revision Rule, Variant Rules, Assembly Arrangements and Occurrence Effectivity. Valid values are "UseCurrent" or "UsePV".

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCapture
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether an Image Capture should be added when a Product View is created. It also specifies how the Image Capture options will be obtained if one is created. Valid values are "NoImageCapture", "CaptureUsingPrefs" or "CaptureUsingDialog".

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCaptureHeight
preference.preference_description: Defines the height in pixel of the preview image created when saving a Product View from the Lifecycle Visualization application. This is only used if "Image Capture" is enabled for Product View save, and if the "Use Image Export Dialog" option is unchecked. Valid values are positive integer from 1 to 1040. Specifying a value of 0 for either width or height will result in both values being calculated automatically.

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCaptureResolution
preference.preference_description: Defines the resolution of the preview image created when saving a Product View from the Lifecycle Visualization application. A valid value is any positive integer from 1 (lowest) to 1040 (highest resolution).

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCaptureType
preference.preference_description: Defines the format of the preview image created when saving a Product View from the Lifecycle Visualization application. This is only used if "Image Capture" is enabled for Product View save, and if the "Use image export dialog" option is unchecked. Valid values are "BMP 24bit", "BMP 8bit", "BMP BW", "JPEG 24bit", "PNG 24bit", "PNG 8bit", "PNG BW", "TIFF 24bit", "TIFF 8bit", "TIFF BW".

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCaptureWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the preview image created when saving a Product View from the Lifecycle Visualization application. This is only used if "Image Capture" is enabled for Product View save, and if the "Use Image Export Dialog" option is unchecked. Valid values are positive integer from 1 to 1040. Specifying a value of 0 for either width or height will result in both values being calculated automatically.

preference.name: Vis_PV_InvalidConfigWarnLevel
preference.preference_description: Specifies the intervention level provided when user tries to capture a Product view in a view toggle enabled environment. Valid Values: *Off: The user is allowed to create/update the Product view without any intervention. This is the behavior prior to Tc10.0.0. *Warning: A warning message is displayed to the user alerting the presence of active view toggles on the BOM window. This is the default value. *Prevent: The user shall not be allowed to proceed with creation of the Product view.

preference.name: Vis_PV_LateLoadSaveOp
preference.preference_description: Specifies how late loaded ProductViews are to be handled during a save operation. Valid Values: * Ask - The user is prompted for their desired handling of late loaded ProductViews during save operation. * Ignore - All late loaded ProductViews are ignored for the save operation. * Abort - The save operation is aborted if any late loaded ProductView is present. * LoadAll - All late loaded ProductViews are loaded and included in the save operation. This is the default value.

preference.name: Vis_PV_Play_Motion
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the motion file (if one exists) should be played automatically using the current view when the Product View is applied. Valid values are true (default value) or false.

preference.name: Vis_PV_Show_Name_Dialog
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the dialog used to name a Product View during Product View creation should be shown. If set to false then a name for the Product View will be generated automatically. Valid values are true (default value) or false.

preference.name: Vis_PV_ThumbnailHeight
preference.preference_description: Defines the height in pixels of thumbnails created for Product view in the Lifecycle Visualization application. Valid values are positive integer from 1 to 1040.

preference.name: Vis_PV_ThumbnailQuality
preference.preference_description: Defines the resolution of thumbnail created for Product view in the Lifecycle Visualization application. A valid value is any positive integer from 1 (lowest) to 1040 (highest resolution).

preference.name: Vis_PV_ThumbnailWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixels of thumbnails created for Product view in the Lifecycle Visualization application. Valid values are positive integer from 1 to 1040.

preference.name: Vis_PV_capture3DGeomAssetAsOutline
preference.preference_description: Activates the creation of outline capture during Product view save in the Lifecycle Visualization application. This is only used if 3D Geometry Asset Capture is enabled for Product View save with no menus. Starting with Teamcenter 10.0 this preference is no longer used but remains in order to maintain backwards compatibility with Teamcenter Visualization 9 releases. Valid values are true or false (default value).

category.name: Project Level Security
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: TC_WSO_check_read_priv_for_project_list
preference.preference_description: Activates the evaluation of the "Read" privilege for the logged-in user for each project in the "project_list" property of a Workspace Object when accessing this property. If set to true, the projects for which the logged-in user does not have "Read" privilege are filtered out. If set to false (default value), all the projects to which a Workspace Object is assigned are returned.

preference.name: TC_allow_dba_modify_all_projects
preference.preference_description: Determines whether DBA users can modify all TC_Project objects and the Project Teams, or only the projects in which they are administrators * true: The DBA users can modify all TC_Project objects and the Project Teams. * false: (Default) The DBA users can modify the TC_Projects that they own, and the Project Teams in which they are either Project Administrator or Project Team Administrator.

preference.name: TC_allow_overwriting_owning_program
preference.preference_description: Clears the current owning project (program) from the given workspace object and replaces it with a new owning project (program) by obtaining the owning project from the parent (container) object, assuming that the following conditions are met: - The parent (container) object is related by a relation to the given workspace object. - There is a propagation rule defined to propagate security data from the parent to the secondary using that relation. Valid values are: * true: Replacing the owning program is enabled. * false: This functionality is disabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_allow_project_admins_modify_rules
preference.preference_description: Allows project administrators (who are not a member of the dba group) to edit project related access rules in the Project Administration application. Valid values are: * true: all project administrators are allowed to edit the access rules. * false: only project administrators who are part of dba group are allowed to edit the access rules. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_allow_remove_owning_project
preference.preference_description: Allows the removal of a project from the owning_project property of the workspace object in which the object is assigned if the preference value is set to true. The user must create this preference; it does not exist in Teamcenter by default. If the preference does not exist or has a value of false, the project cannot be removed even though the project can be removed from the project_list property. If you use the autoAssignToProject extension, you must create this preference and set its value to true to allow automatic project assignment. Valid values are: * true: Allows removal of a project from the owning_project property. * false: Prevents removal of a project from the owning_project property. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_assign_to_source_object_projects_on_revise
preference.preference_description: Enables auto-assignment of projects to source objects upon a "Revise" operation.

preference.name: TC_assign_to_source_object_projects_on_save_as
preference.preference_description: Enables auto-assignment of projects to source objects upon a "Save As" operation.

preference.name: TC_copy_security_data_exclusion_list
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of security properties that are not copied over to the new object during the "Save As", "Revise" and "Baseline" operations. The default values are "project_list" and "owning_project".

preference.name: TC_enable_on_the_fly_projectobjectrelation_migration
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the ProjectObjectRelation object from legacy data i.e. data from previous releases should be migrated on the fly or not. The default value is set to false and system will handle the co-existance of new ProjectObjectRelation and un-migrated ProjectObjectRelation objects and will not have any functional impact on the system. Valid values are: * true: migration of ProjectObjectRelation is enabled this will trigger migration of ProjectObjectRelation whenever it is encountered. * false: no migration of ProjectObjectRelation will be performed when legacy ProjectObjectRelation is encountered.

preference.name: TC_multi_site_project_member_bypass
preference.preference_description: Determines the assignment rule to a defined project for objects replicated during an import operation to a remote site. Valid values are: * true: The replicated object is assigned to the defined project regardless of whether the importing user is a project member. This is the default value. * false: The replicated object is assigned to the defined project if the importing user is a privileged project member. If the importing user is a regular project member then TC_project_validate_condition preference determines the project assignment on replicated object.

preference.name: TC_program_project_differentiator
preference.preference_description: Enables users to differentiate between Programs and Projects visually by prepending an extra character to the project id. Users will not be able to use the character given in the value in the project id or project name. If preference does not exist or does not have any value there will not be any visual differentiation. Valid values are: * Any single character

preference.name: TC_project_propagate_from_dataset
preference.preference_description:
Specifies the relation types available for level two propagation in the "update_project_bom" utility.
Level-two propagation processes dependent objects related to the datasets associated with level one objects. The following data model is supported for level-two propagation: * Item * Item revision * Dataset Item Revision (associated with the dataset by a specified relation type) * Dataset Dataset (associated with the dataset by a specified relation type) * Dataset Item (associated with the dataset by a specified relation type) Dependent objects assigned through level-two propagation are explicitly assigned to the project. Objects that are explicitly assigned to projects must also be explicitly removed. If the BOM object to which the secondary object is removed from the project, the dependent object remains.
Valid values are valid Relation types.
Note: For detailed information about assigning objects to projects using propagation rules, and the differences between level-one propagation and level-two propagation, see Project and Program.

preference.name: TC_project_validate_conditions
preference.preference_description:
Determines how the ASSIGN_TO_PROJECT and REMOVE_FROM_PROJECT access privileges are validated in conjunction with privileged membership validation. The behavior of this preference is overruled by the value of the "TC_multi_site_project_member_bypass" preference Valid values are: * 0: The system confirms the user is a privileged member of the project before allowing the user to assign/remove objects to/from a project. This is the default value. * 1: The system confirms the user is either a privileged member of the project, or that the user is a regular project member who is granted the ASSIGN_TO_PROJECT privilege before allowing the user to assign object to a project. Likewise, a user must be either a privileged member of the project or be a regular project member and who is granted the REMOVE_FROM_PROJECT privilege to remove an object from a project. * 2: The system confirms the user is a regular project member and has the ASSIGN_TO_PROJECT privilege before allowing the user to assign object to a project. Likewise, a user must have the REMOVE_FROM_PROJECT privilege to remove an object from a project. * 3: The system confirms the user is a privileged member of the project and that the user has the ASSIGN_TO_PROJECT privilege before allowing the user to assign object to a project. Likewise, a user must be a privileged member of the project and have the REMOVE_FROM_PROJECT privilege to remove an object from a project. * 4: Allows the current user to assign users to a project if the current user is not a member of the project team. This must be done programmatically using ITK. You cannot do this through the user interface. The system confirms that the user has ASSIGN_TO_PROJECT privilege before allowing the user to assign objects to a project. Likewise, the user must have REMOVE_FROM_PROJECT privilege to move an object from a project.
Note: This preference has no effect on which projects are displayed in the Teamcenter interface. Therefore, it is possible that users see projects displayed in the interface, for example, in the User Settings dialog box, that they do not have access to.

preference.name: TC_propagation_exclusion_list
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid workspace object types which are excluded from propagation i.e. data from this objects will not be propagated to or from where this objects are referenced.

preference.name: TC_propagation_security_group_style
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of security groups and associated styles.

preference.name: TC_set_current_project
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the project saved in the previous Teamcenter session for a particular user is set as the current project in a new session for the same user. Valid values are: * true: The project saved in the previous Teamcenter session is set as the current project in the new Teamcenter session. This is the default value. * false: The project saved in the previous Teamcenter session is not set as the current project in the new Teamcenter session.

preference.name: TC_show_all_user_projects
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the projects in which a user is a team member are displayed for selection in the Teamcenter interface or whether only the projects that correlate to the user's current group and role are displayed for selection. Valid values are: * true: Displays all the projects in which the user is a team member, regardless of the user's current group and role. This is the default value. * false: Displays only those projects in which the user is a team member based on the user's current group and role.

preference.name: TC_use_strict_program_project_hierarchy
preference.preference_description:
Enables strict hierarchical representation of programs and projects where a program can have projects. Valid values are: * true: Users can only select programs in the user session. The program selected in user session and the projects under that program will be displayed for project assignment * false: All programs and projects are available for selection in the user session. All programs and projects are displayed for project assignment. This is the default value.
Note: It is recommended that data assigned to programs and projects be migrated to hierarchical configuration before setting this preference to true.

preference.name: TC_UI_SmartFolder_JoinOperator
preference.preference_description: Determines the criteria to apply when the filters on data-driven folders are evaluated. Valid values are: * AND: Applies AND criteria on the filters on data-driven folders. * OR: Applies OR criteria on the filters on data-driven folders. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_UI_SmartNavigator_Pagination_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Indicates if pagination is enabled inside the Smart Navigator tree. The default value for this Site preference is false.

preference.name: TC_UI_SmartNavigator_Pagination_Size
preference.preference_description: Indicates the size of each pagination node inside the Smart Navigator tree. This User preference applies only when TC_UI_SmartNavigator_Pagination_Enabled preference is set to true. Its default value is 250.

The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source Awp0Tile and the target Awp0TileCollection.

preference.name: Awp0TileCollection_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type (i.e Awp0TileCollection).

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Tooltip_Max_Row
preference.preference_description: Defines the node tooltip maximum number of rows displayed in the Relationship Viewer application in the Active Workspace client.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Tooltip_Max_Width
preference.preference_description: Defines the node tooltip maximum character length for each row displayed in the Relationship Viewer application in the Active Workspace client.

preference.name: WRKFLW_Hide_Perform_Task_Command_ToolAndInfo
preference.preference_description: Deactivates the visibility of the "Perform Task" command in the "Tool and Information" area in Active Workspace for Workflow types for which the associated stylesheet defines the command presentation in the middle area (out-of-the-box for Tasks and Task Signoffs). Valid values are: * true: the command is only visible in the middle area for the above-mentioned Workflow types. This is the default value. * false: the command is visible in the middle area and also in the "Tool and Information" area.

preference.name: TC_reactive_logging_file_delete
preference.preference_description: The PJL and JNL files will be removed from the temporary directory. This preference is only meant for reactive logging. Valid values are: * true: Deletes the PJL and JNL files from the temporary directory. * false: Does not delete the PJL and JNL file from the temporary directory.

preference.name: TC_reactive_logging_file_download
preference.preference_description: This preference defines if the fms ticket download link are supposed to be sent to the client. Valid values are: * true: Link to download the log files are sent to the client. * false: Link to download the log files are not sent to the client.

preference.name: TC_reactive_logging_notification_list
preference.preference_description: List of email addresses that are supposed to receive mail notification about the location of teamcenter logfiles(jnl/pjl/syslog), the teamcenter user and the machine on which the log files are located.

Preference to show/hide Swing AbstractAIFDialog for single file drag and drop. The value can be true/false. If the value is set to "false", then the multiple file drag and drop JFace Dialog will be displayed for single file drag and drop event. If the value is set to "true" then the Swing AbstractAIFDialog will be displayed for the single file drag and drop event. Default value is false.

preference.name: Select IR
preference.preference_description: At any time one of the two preferences 'Selection Criteria'or "Select IR" must be set, else Check-In/Out of Item revisions will not work. The values set by the user interactively in an Teamcenter session take precedence over values set by these two preferences. If this preference is set to 'Yes', the Item revision is selectedand is not selected if it is set to 'No'.If this preference is not set (or commented) and the"Selection Criteria" preference is set, then the ItemRevision willnot get selected, but the ItemRevision attachments get selectedbased on the specified Selection criteria.

preference.name: Selection Criteria
preference.preference_description: Sets the criteria used for pre-selection of attachments for Item Revision objects for Check-in/Out in the Explore Dialog. For example, for the below case, all the objects of type UGMASTER having a IMAN_specification relation with the Item Revision object will be pre-selected in the Explore Dialog. Valid values are in the format TypeInternalName followed by 10 spaces and then, RelationInternalName. At all times, one of the two preferences "Selection Criteria" or "Select IR" must be set, otherwise the "Check-In/Check-Out" of Item Revision objects will not work. However, this preference's values take precedence over values of these other two preferences. If this preference is not set and "Select IR" preference is set ,then only the Item Revision objects are selected and not their attachments.

preference.name: TC_Enable_Implicit_CO
preference.preference_description: Specifies if a user can edit an object without explicitly checking out an object. Allows different users to simultaneously edit the same object. In such a concurrent editing scenario, when saving the changes, if changes by another user have already been committed, then the TC_overwrite_protection,preference determines if the changes by the current user should overwrite the other user's changes or if the current user must redo the changes. Valid Values: True - Enables users to edit an object without using the Check-out menu. False - Enables users to edit an object by clicking Check-Out and Edit.

If a value is not listed, the new (starting Tc10.1.0) generic dialog is used for that menu command. Valid values are "Item", "Folder" and "Form".

preference.name: TC_Enable_Legacy_Revise
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the Legacy Revise dialog for all types in the Teamcenter Rich Client. Starting Teamcenter 11.6 new generic dialog will be used for revise menu command.

preference.name: TC_Fnd0SoaConfigFilterCriteria_AutoCheckinRevisable
preference.preference_description: Activates the automatic check-out/check-in of POM revisable objects whenever needed by Teamcenter. Valid Values: * true: POM revisable objects can be checked-out and then checked-in whenever needed, causing the revision number to increase. This causes changes to be immediately visible to other users (provided they have READ access). If the object is already in a "Private Edit" state beforehand, it will not be checked-in. This is the default value. * false: No check-in is made. Users can accumulate more changes for revisable objects before performing a manual check-in so that to commit all "Private Edit" changes and to publish these changes to other users (provided they have READ access).

preference.name: TC_GROUP_PFILE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the directory where the group preference files are located.

preference.name: TC_Generate_Markup_Name
preference.preference_description: Indicates newly created markup dataset name use generated name or hard-coded name. Valid values are TRUE for using generated markup name in format of user ID plus current datetime stamp plus user display name, this format is same as used in standalone TcVis; and FALSE for using hard-coded markup name (default).

preference.name: TC_Graph_Node_Thumbnail_Shown
preference.preference_description: Indicates if existing preview thumbnail image is shown with type icon and object name representing each graph node in Generic Relation Browser. True means showing the image; False means not showing the image.

preference.name: TC_ImpactAnalysis_Display_Limit
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of objects that can be displayed in the Teamcenter Rich Client "Impact Analysis" view when users perform a "Where Referenced" all level search. Increasing from the default value (500) may cause Rich Client to fail displaying due to its current memory allocation.

preference.name: TC_Project.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of stylesheet for TC_Project objects.

preference.name: TC_Project_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the TC_Project type. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: TC_Project_PseudoFolder
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of properties that can be displayed as a pseudo-folder under a node for TC_Project object.

preference.name: TC_Project_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation between source and target when an object is pasted under a TC_Project object.

preference.name: TC_ROLE_PFILE
preference.preference_description: Specify the directory in which to find role preference files This is a Site Preference Only.

preference.name: TC_RelationBrowser_Context
preference.preference_description: Defines the default context to be selected in the "Relation Browser" view of the Rich client. The valid value can be found in "Context" tag of graph_config.xml. The default is "com.teamcenter.rac.tcgrb.ctx.Default".

preference.name: TC_ReviseRenderingInheritTypeList
preference.preference_description: Defines the Business Object types that can inherit the "Revise Stylesheet" status from their parent types.

preference.name: TC_SaveAsRenderingInheritTypeList
preference.preference_description: Defines the Business Object types that can inherit the "Save As Stylesheet" status from their parent types.

preference.name: TC_Text_Default_View_Tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default tool to be used when datasets of this type are viewed. Format is TC_AE_<datasettype>_Default_View_Tool.

preference.name: TC_Text_Tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default tool to be used when datasets of this type are opened. Format is TC_<datasettype>_Tool

preference.name: TC_UGMASTER_Tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default tool to be used when datasets of this type are opened. Format is TC_<datasettype>_Tool

preference.name: TC_UGPART_Tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default tool to be used when datasets of this type are opened. Format is TC_<datasettype>_Tool

preference.name: TC_UI_DisplayMaxColumnsForItemIDNameFields
preference.preference_description: Specifies if max length should be used for item id and name text field length in new item wizard.

preference.name: TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingBasedOn
preference.preference_description: Specifies parameter for the calculation of the threshold width for LOVComboBox objects in the Rich client. This preference value is only taken into account if the TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingPolicy preference is set to "FitToLength". Supported values are: - ScreenSize: The dimension of the primary monitor is used to determine the threshold width. - ParentSize: The dimension of the Rich client window is used to determine the threshold width. The default value for this user preference is "ScreenSize"

preference.name: TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingPolicy
preference.preference_description: Specifies the sizing policy of the LOVComboBox in the Rich client. Valid Values: - Default: Uses a default width of 32 characters - FitToLength: The size of the LOVComboBox is determined based on the width of the selected value. If the width required to accomodate the selected value exceeds the threshold width, the system uses the threshold width. The threshold width is defined to be 70 percent of the ScreenSize or ParentSize which is specified in the preference TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingBasedOn. The default value for this user preference is "FitToLength"

preference.name: TC_UI_LOVControl_SizingPercentage
preference.preference_description: Specifies the percentage to be used for the calculation of the threshold width for LOV Controls in the Rich client. This percentage is applied against the ScreenSize or ParentSize which is specified in the preference TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingBasedOn. Valid values should be between 30 and 100 (inclusive). If the specified value is outside this range, a default percentage of 70 would be used. The default value for this user preference is "70"

preference.name: TC_USER_PFILE
preference.preference_description: Specify the directory in which to find user preference files.

preference.name: TC_Web_Browser_Home_URL
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default home page for the rich client's Web Browser view. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. URL must be valid.

preference.name: TC_auto_delete_folder_references
preference.preference_description: Deactivates the display of error messages when deleting an Item referenced anewhere else present under any folder. By default its value is "true" and that means, user does not want to get any error message when he delets any Item present under Folder even tough Item has some references.

preference.name: TC_auto_login
preference.preference_description: Administrators can use this preference to enable auto-login facility. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. TRUE - Auto login via OS user name is in effect. FALSE - Auto login via OS user name is not in effect. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: TC_check_out_dir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the directory where files will be exported when a dataset is checked-out. The value must match the path format for the client operating system (OS).

preference.name: TC_checkout_and_export
preference.preference_description: Indicates if Teamcenter has to export the file to an OS directory at the time of checking out a dataset. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not export the files to the OS on Check-Out. 1 - Export files on Check-Out.

preference.name: TC_confirm_paste_operation
preference.preference_description: Enables the confirmation dialog for every "Paste" operation in the Rich Client.

preference.name: TC_control_wildcard
preference.preference_description: Control the number of required characters before a wildcard character is allowed. The default is 0, which allows wildcard as the first character. For example, set to 2 means "AB*" is allowed and "A*" or "*" is not allowed. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_control_wildcard_exception
preference.preference_description: The wildcard exceptions specified here take precedence over TC_control_wildcard preference. This preference can be used to control the number of required characters before a wildcard for a specified class and attribute. Format of the preference value is: <Class name>.<Real attribute name>:<Number>. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_days_non_login_timeout
preference.preference_description: Used to disable the inactive use accounts. This option determines whether to allow user logon, based on the number of days that have passed since the user's last recorded logon. This is used as a security method to disable logon for users who have not logged into the system for a specified number of days. This is site preference only.

preference.name: TC_display_group_names_limit
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_display_real_prop_names
preference.preference_description: Indicates if Teamcenter has to display the real property names.

preference.name: TC_display_thumbnail_in_UI
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Thumbnail view is enabled in Teamcenter Rich client.

preference.name: TC_ignore_case_on_search
preference.preference_description: Determines if object searches are case sensitive. Valid Values: 0 - Object searches are case sensitive. 1 - Mapped attribute searches and saved query searches are case insensitive when using an appearance set-based search engine (see ).Work part, engineering change, and workflow process searches are case insensitive when using the Context Definition pane in Design Context.

preference.name: TC_inbox_interval
preference.preference_description: How often to check the In-Box for new tasks (in minutes). 1 - Disable the checking. 0 - Check at the time of logging in. X - Check every X minutes.

preference.name: TC_markup_named_ref
preference.preference_description: Defines all the named references that have viewable image file. For a dataset that needs to do View/Markup, its named references must be defined in this list.

preference.name: TC_max_display_thumbnails
preference.preference_description: Indicates the maximum number of thumbnails that will be displayed in the Viewer tab when selecting multiple objects.

preference.name: TC_max_number_of_retries
preference.preference_description: Retry Control. If Teamcenter cannot lock an object, how may times should it try before reporting an error.

preference.name: TC_name_delimiter
preference.preference_description: The delimiter used in the Person.name. Example: in Smith, John, the delimiter is ,. This is a STEP preference.

preference.name: TC_name_sequence
preference.preference_description: Name sequence.

preference.name: TC_pattern_match_style
preference.preference_description: Indicates the pattern matching style to use. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - use "%" for multi-char replacement, use "_" for single char replacement. 2 - use "*" for multi-char replacement, use "." for single char replacement. 3 - use "*" for multi-char replacement, use "?" for single char replacement.

preference.name: TC_remove_file_on_check_in
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the system has to delete the exported files in the OS while performing a Check-in on a dataset which has been checked-out with "Export" option. This preference is also used to determine if the exported files in the OS should be deleted if the user cancels the Check-Out. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not remove the exported OS files on Check-In. 1 - Remove the exported OS files on Check-In.

preference.name: TC_retry_time
preference.preference_description: Indicates the number of seconds to pause between each retry of locking an object.

preference.name: TC_runtimeTypeToExpand
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of runtime properties to be expanded in the deep copy tree. Valid values are runtime properties internal names. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_show_checkedout_icon
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of the checked-out icon in BOM trees, Attachment trees, Activity trees and Occurrence Group trees.

preference.name: TC_suppress_Edit_Latest_Menu
preference.preference_description: Following preference is used to suppress the Latest command

preference.name: TC_suppress_inactive_group_members
preference.preference_description: Used to suppress inactive group members. This is a user preference and it will be considered only from Group Administrators and System Administrators. In the case of normal users, the value of the preference will not be considered. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - SA/GA can see both active and inactive group members. 1 - SA/GA cannot see the inactive group members in Group Members dialog in SA applications. The default value is 1.

preference.name: TC_thumbnail_tooltip_properties
preference.preference_description: Lists the name of properties to be displayed in the tool tip in the Thumbnail view in Rich client.

preference.name: TC_user_delimiters
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delimiters used between the user name and ID in the Organization application of the rich client.

preference.name: TC_wc_allow_subgroup_default
preference.preference_description: Defines the default setting for the Subgroup Members Allowed checkbox in the New Work Context dialog window.This option determines whether sub-group members of the selected group are allowed to perform a task.

preference.name: TC_wc_setting_modifiable_default
preference.preference_description: Defines the default setting for the "User Settings Modifiable" checkbox in the New Work Context dialog.This option is used to specify if the user settings defined via the work context can be changed once the work context is set as Current Work Context.

preference.name: TC_wc_show_all
preference.preference_description: Defines the content of the list of Work Contexts associated to a user. Valid values for this site preference are: - FALSE (default) to display only Work Contexts related to the tasks in the user's Task to Perform folder. - TRUE to display Work Contexts related to the tasks in the user's Task to Perform folder, followed by any other Work Contexts created by the user.

preference.name: TIF_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type TIF. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target TIF.

preference.name: UGPART_DefaultChildProperties

preference.name: WHERE_REFERENCED_RELATIONS_FILTER
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations displayed in the "Where-Referenced" relation filter combo box, which is used to select relation filter criteria. This enables showing such relations in the combo box, while preventing them to be displayed in the "Paste As" dialog or in defined as child relations. Vertical industry solutions can leverage this preference by adding relations. Valid value of relations are relation internal names (e.g. CP_Has_Has_Copy_Element, CP_Has_Package_Concept).

preference.name: WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_columns_hidden
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of hidden columns for workspace object.

preference.name: WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_columns_shown
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names to be used for displaying the workspace objects.

preference.name: WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_widths_hidden
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns (identified by WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_columns_hidden).

preference.name: WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_widths_shown
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns (identified by WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_columns_shown).

preference.name: WSColumnsHiddenPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of workspace columns not displayed.

preference.name: WSColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Workspace columns to be displayed (left-to-right order).

preference.name: WSDisplayTypePref
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type of display that the users see in the workspace. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - Vertical Tree. 2 - Horizontal Tree. 3 - Indented BOM.

preference.name: WSOM_find_editUserList
preference.preference_description: Specifies the users for whom the Edit button is displayed on the My Teamcenter search panel. This button provides access to the feature for extending existing queries. Valid Values: Any valid Teamcenter user ID.

preference.name: WSOM_find_list_separator
preference.preference_description: Defines the character used to separate multiple entries for queries.No setting for this preference disables multiple entries.If your search criteria includes a semicolon (;) as part of the search value, change the default value of this preference to another value, for example a comma (,) or a pipe (|) character. Otherwise, your search results in incorrect results. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a valid value.

preference.name: WSOM_find_set_pff_displaydata_limit
preference.preference_description: Limits the number of objects displayed in the Print dialog box that Teamcenter displays when a user selects a property finder formatter (PFF) object in the Search Results view, right-clicks, and chooses Print Table (HTML/TEXT).For information about PFF objects, see Teamcenter Basics. Valid values are Any positive integer.Performance may become unacceptable if you enter a value exceeding 1000.

preference.name: WSOM_find_set_search_limit
preference.preference_description: Determines the number of objects loaded to workspace after performing a Find action before asking for user confirmation. Valid Values: Accepts a positive integer as a value.Performance may become unacceptable if you enter a value exceeding 1000.

preference.name: WSOM_find_set_total_limit
preference.preference_description: Determines the total number of objects that can be returned in My Teamcenter for any given search operation. This site-wide preference limits the total return count, not the per-page count determined by the WSOM_find_set_search_limit user preference. Valid Values: 0 - No limit A single positive integer. - The total number of objects to be returned to My Teamcenter for any given search operation.

preference.name: WSOM_only_edit_effectivity_in_ecm
preference.preference_description: Allow editing of effectivity data outside an ECM process. Valid values are yes/no.

preference.name: WSShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the shown workspace columns (WSColumnsShownPref).

preference.name: WS_icon_placement
preference.preference_description: Indicates the position of the Icon to be placed with the workspace display. Valid values are 1/2/3/4. 1 - Above. 2 - Right. 3 - Below. 4 - Left.

preference.name: WeldPointRevision_Cps0ProjectionInfo_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation between an object of type "Cps0ProjectionInfo" and the WeldPoint Revision under which this object is pasted.

preference.name: WeldPointRevision_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type i.e. WeldPointRevision. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: WhereUsedReportPropertyList
preference.preference_description: Stores the name of the properties selected while creating a "Where Used" report. Values for this preference are set automatically by the code.

preference.name: Where_Ref_Avoid_Duplicate_Expansion
preference.preference_description: Simplifies the tree view resulting from the Where referencedSearch command. The subtree of duplicate notes is not displayed. Valid Values: true - Simplifies the tree view by not displaying the subtree of duplicate notes. false - Displays the subtree of duplicate notes.

preference.name: Word_Export_TcTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Revision types displayed in the "Export To Word" dialog

preference.name: WsoFolderSavePref
preference.preference_description: Indicates when to save changes in Workspace. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 = Save on every change. 2 = Only save when manually prompted. 3 = Prompt the user on close if they want to save.

preference.name: WsoInsertNoSelectionsPref
preference.preference_description: When no object selected, which folder/object should have a reference to it. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - Newstuff folder. 2 - RootFolder. 3 - None (place in database, but with no references to it).

preference.name: WsoInsertSelectionsPref
preference.preference_description: When a new object is created, which folders/objects should have a reference to it. Valid values are 1/3/4. 1 - All selected Folders. 3 - Newstuff folder. 4 - None (place in database, but with no references to it).

preference.name: browserWindowMode
preference.preference_description: Determines how the browser window will be displayed (e.g. from QuickLinks open a weblink). Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - Launch externally (default). 2 - Launch in a single internal browser window. 3 - Launch in a separate internal browser window.

preference.name: defaultViewerConfig.VIEWERCONFIG
preference.preference_description:
Defines the default viewer configuration. This is a user preference.
Valid values are in the following format: DATATYPE.VIEWERID=OPTIONAL_NAMED_REF_TYPES.
Entries are in order of priority, with the exception of SEARCHORDER.ITEMREV2DATASET.
In order to enable Viewing NX .prt files please add the following lines: UGMASTER.DirectModelViewer=UGPART UGPART.DirectModelViewer=UGPART UGALTREP.DirectModelViewer=UGPART

preference.name: search_automatic_wildcard
preference.preference_description: To enhance local metadata searches, automatically adds the asterisk (*) character as a prefix, suffix, or both for search criteria for all string attributes. This feature is available in all Teamcenter clients. Valid values are 0 - Search criteria are not altered. 1 - The asterisk (*) character is added as a suffix. 2 - The asterisk (*) character is added as a prefix. 3 - The asterisk (*) character is added as both a suffix and a prefix.

category.name: Rich Client.Effectivity
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: APS_Effectivity_Mode
preference.preference_description: Specifies if only units, dates or both are to be displayed in the "Range Effectivity" view. Valid values are "DateOnly", "UnitOnly" or "All". The default value is "UnitOnly".

preference.name: APS_Effectivity_View_Column_Property
preference.preference_description: Contains the object property name to be shown as a first column in the Effectivity View. Valid value is internal name of the any property. The default value is "object_string".

preference.name: APS_Show_Effectivity_Tabular_View
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to show the "Tabular Effectivity" view (true) or the "Range Effectivity" view (false; default value). The "Tabular Effectivity" view supports only Unit effectivities. This preference is not applicable for Date effectivities, and the "Range Effectivity" view is used.

preference.name: APS_Tabular_Effectivity_View_Default_Units_Column
preference.preference_description: Contains the range of unit columns ("From" and "To" units) to be shown in the "Effectivity Tabular" view. The first value is used for "From Units" and second value is used for "To Units". If the number of unit columns specified in From-To range is greater than the value specified in the preference "Tabular_Effectivity_View_Max_Units_Column", the default unit columns to be created would be "From Unit value" - "From Unit value" + value defined in the preference "Tabular_Effectivity_View_Max_Units_Column". The default values are 1 and 10.

preference.name: APS_Tabular_Effectivity_View_Max_Units_Column
preference.preference_description: Contains the maximum number of unit columns to be shown in the "Effectivity Tabular" view. The default value is 10.

preference.name: SOA_MaxOperationBracketInactiveTime
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum time in seconds for an operation bracket without active server requests. Valid Values: Single positive integer.

category.name: Schedule Manager
category.category_description: Allows configuring of Schedule Manager functionality.

preference.name: CombinedAvailableAttributes
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of common Schedule and Schedule Task object attributes displayed in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a Program View is opened. Valid Values: Combined.object_desc - Displays object description in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Combined.start_date - Displays start date in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Combined.finish_date - Displays finish date in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Combined.fnd0status - Displays status in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Combined.priority - Displays priority in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened.

preference.name: DefaultActualToSystemDate
preference.preference_description: Determines whether system date or scheduled date is used when initially setting actual start date or actual end date, when the user marks a task as in progress or complete, respectively. This preference is used with Schedule Manager. Valid Values: True - system date is used as the default date set in actual start date or actual end date. False - scheduled date is used as the default date set in actual start date or actual end date.

preference.name: Default_Base_Calendar_Preference
preference.preference_description: Determines the internal name of the default calendar when a schedule is created in Schedule Manager. The value for this preference also affects workflow task due date calculations. Valid Values: Standard Night Shift 24 Hours

preference.name: ProgramViewFilterProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of attributes for schedule and schedule task objects displayed in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Valid Values: Schedule Task.complete_percent - Displays complete percent in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.actual_start_date - Displays actual start date in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.actual_finish_date - Displays actual finish date in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.work_complete - Displays work complete in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.ResourceAssignment - Displays resource assignment in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.object_desc - Displays object description in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.duration - Displays duration in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.object_name - Displays object name in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.priority - Displays priority in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.start_date - Displays start date in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.finish_date - Displays finish date in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.work_estimate - Displays work estimate in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.fnd0state - Displays state in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.fnd0status - Displays status in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule.object_name - Displays object name in the Filter dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened.

preference.name: ProgramViewGroupProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of attributes for schedule and schedule task objects displayed in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Valid Values: Schedule Task.complete_percent - Displays complete percent in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.actual_start_date - Displays actual start date in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.actual_finish_date - Displays actual finish date in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.work_complete - Displays work complete in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.ResourceAssignment - Displays resource assignment in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.object_desc - Displays object description in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.duration - Displays duration in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.object_name - Displays object name in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.priority - Displays priority in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.start_date - Displays start date in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened.
