Schedule Task.fnd0state - Displays state in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. Schedule Task.fnd0status - Displays status in the Grouping dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened.

preference.name: SM_ALLOW_INPROCESS_REMOVAL_OF_SUB_SCHEDULE
preference.preference_description: Prevents removal of started subschedules.The value of this preference is overridden by the value of the SM_PREVENT_DELETE_STATES preference for subschedules. In other words, if a subschedule's state is one of the set values of SM_PREVENT_DELETE_STATES, it cannot be deleted or removed, even if this preference is set to true.For example, the subschedule cannot be removed or deleted if the following conditions exist:SM_ALLOW_INPROCESS_REMOVAL_OF_SUB_SCHEDULE is set to true.SM_PREVENT_DELETE_STATES is set to in_progress, complete, aborted.The subschedule state is set to aborted.After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: true false

preference.name: SM_ALLOW_USER_ABORT
preference.preference_description: Specifies if schedule participants can abort schedule tasks. After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: true false

preference.name: SM_AUTO_EXTEND_MASTER_SCHEDULE_DATE
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to extend the start and finish dates of the master schedule based on the sub-schedule being inserted. The valid values are: * true: Extend the start date and finish date of the master schedule. * false: Do not extend the start date and finish date of the master schedule. This is the default value.

preference.name: SM_CREATE_ORPHAN_TASK
preference.preference_description: Activates the conversion of a Schedule Task to an Orphan Task if the deletion of Schedule Task has failed. If set to false, Schedule Task do not convert to an Orphan Task. The default value is "true".

preference.name: SM_Copy_Schedule_Async
preference.preference_description: Determines the default selection when the user performs the Save As or Create a Schedule from Template command. Valid Values: True - Asychronously determines the default selection. False - Synchronously determines the default selection.

preference.name: SM_CriticalPath_Color
preference.preference_description: Sets the color for display of critical path. Valid Values: A user can set any value to this preference. The value specified must be a valid comma-separated integer code specified using three 8-bit unsigned integers (0 through 255) representing the intensities of red, green, and blue.

preference.name: SM_DEFERRED_NOTIFICATION_TIME
preference.preference_description: Specifies the notification time in minutes before the user is warned that the deferred session is about to expire. After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: Any numerical value indicating the number of minutes until deferred session expires.

preference.name: SM_DEFERRED_SHOW_TIMEOUT
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the timer button is displayed or not.After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: True - Displays the timer button. false - Hides the timer button.

preference.name: SM_DEFERRED_TIMEOUT
preference.preference_description: Specifies the time-out in minutes before the deferred session expires. After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: Any numerical value indicating the time-out in minutes until deferred session expires.0 turns off the time-out.

preference.name: SM_DISPLAY_GANTT_SI
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the Gantt status indicator in the Schedule Manager application. Valid Values: True - Shows the Gantt status indicator. False - Hides the Gantt status indicator.

preference.name: SM_Delete_Schedule_Async
preference.preference_description: Determines the behavior when you choose to delete a schedule. Valid Values: true - Asynchronously determines the default selection. false - Synchronously determines the default selection.

preference.name: SM_ENFORCE_ASSIGNMENT_CRITERIA
preference.preference_description: Determines if Schedule Manager enforces assignment criteria, such as discipline, placeholder, or qualification, when assigning resources to schedule tasks. Valid Values: true - Enforces the assignment criteria. false - Specifies that any user can be assigned regardless of the assignment criteria defined on schedule tasks.

preference.name: SM_EVM_Calc_Labels
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether earned value management (EVM) calculations are displayed as EVM labels or C/SCSC (cost/schedule control systems criteria) labels. Valid Values: EVM C/SCSC

preference.name: SM_EVM_Calc_Preference
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether earned value management (EVM) calculations are based on cost or hours. Valid Values: Cost Hours

preference.name: SM_EVM_Export_Units
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether units are displayed in the Microsoft Excel spreadsheet upon export. Valid Values: True - Exports the units to the Microsoft Excel spreadsheet. False - Does not export the units to the Microsoft Excel spreadsheet.

preference.name: SM_EVM_Work_Complete
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether earned value management (EVM) calculations are based on percent of work completed or actual hours of work completed. Valid Values: Percent_Complete Actual_Hours

preference.name: SM_EXEC_VIEW_PROPERTIES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the properties displayed in the execution view and the order in which they are displayed. Valid Values are internal attribute names of a schedule task object. The code retrieves the value for this preference in this property order: user, role, group, or site. Valid Values: Accepts one or more of the following strings as valid values. Each string must provide a valid internal property name of a schedule task object.

preference.name: SM_EnforceActualDatesBeforeNow
preference.preference_description: In Schedule Manager, determines if dates must be set to a date prior to the current date, or if they can be set to any date. Valid Values: true - Forces the use of a date prior to current date. false - Specifies that any date can be used.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_MONTH_ZM_B_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format at the bottom of the Gantt chart for viewing the month. Valid Values: MM/dd/yyyy Format using a combination of the valid characters that make up the date pattern, for example, MM for month character, dd for day number, and yyyy for year. The month character MM allows you to enter the number of the month. For example, enter 01 for January, 02 for February, and so on. Values for month, day, and year are enclosed in quotation marks. The default separator is the forward-slash character (/). The information is specific to iconographic languages.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_MONTH_ZM_T_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format at the top of the Gantt chart for viewing the month. Valid Values: MMMM/dd/yyyy Format using a combination of the valid characters that make up the date pattern, for example, MMMM for month character, dd for day number, and yyyy for year. The month character MMMM allows you to enter four letters for the month. For example, enter Janu for January, Febr for February, and so on. Values for month, day, and year are enclosed in quotation marks. The default separator is the forward slash character (/). The information is specific to iconographic languages.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_QTR_STRT
preference.preference_description: Specifies the starting month of the first quarter of the year. Valid Values: Any number between 1 (January) and 12 (December).

preference.name: SM_GANTT_QTR_ZM_B_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format at the bottom of the Gantt chart for viewing the quarter of the year. Valid Values: n/yyyy Format using a combination of the valid characters that comprise the date pattern, for example, n for quarter character and yyyy for year. Values for quarter and year are enclosed in quotation marks. The default separator is the forward slash character (/). The information is specific to iconographic languages.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_QTR_ZM_T_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format at the top of the Gantt chart for viewing the quarter of the year. Valid Values: MMM/dd/yyyy Format using a combination of the valid characters that comprise the date pattern, for example, MMM for month character, dd for day number, and yyyy for year. The month character MMM allows you to enter three letters for the month. For example, enter Jan for January, Feb for February, and so on. Values for month, day, and year are enclosed in quotation marks. The default separator is the forward slash character (/). The information is specific to iconographic languages.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_USE_ISO_8601_FOR_DATE
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the calendar display in Gantt should follow the ISO 8601 standard to display the week numbers. The ISO 8601 standard denotes that the number of days to call a week as first week of the year should be greater than or equal to 4. Valid Values: True - The week number will be as per the ISO 8601 standard. In addition, the Start Of Week preference should be set to Monday, which is the start day of the week as per the ISO 8601 standard. False - The week number will be as per the locale in which Teamcenter is running.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_WEEK_ZM_T_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format at the top of the Gantt chart for the viewing the week. Valid Values: MMM/dd/yyyy Format using a combination of the valid characters that make up the date pattern, for example, MMM for month character, dd for day number, and yyyy for year. The month character MMM allows you to enter three letters for the month. For example, enter Jan for January, Feb for February, and so on. Values for month, day, and year are enclosed in quotation marks. The default separator is the forward slash character (/). The information is specific to iconographic languages.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_YEAR_ZM_T_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format at the top of the Gantt chart for viewing the year. Valid Values: MM/dd/yyyy Format using a combination of the valid characters that make up the date pattern, for example, MM for month character, dd for day number, and yyyy for year. The month character MM allows you to enter the number of the month. For example, enter 01 for January, 02 for February,and so on. Values for month, day, and year are enclosed in quotation marks. The default separator is the forward slash character (/). The information is specific to iconographic languages.

preference.name: SM_Hours_Per_Day_Preference
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of work hours per day, as used for calculating calendar end dates. The value can vary depending on the site (e.g 8 hours for the US, 7.5 hours for the UK). The default value is 8.

preference.name: SM_Hours_Per_Week_Preference
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of work hours per week, as used for calculating calendar end dates. The value can vary depending on the site (e.g 5 days * 8 hours for the US, 5 days * 7.5 hours for the UK). The default value is 40.

preference.name: SM_Hours_Per_Year_Preference
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of work hours per year, as used for calculating calendar end dates. The value can vary depending on the site (e.g 52 weeks * 40 hrs for the US, 52 weeks * 37.5 hrs for the UK). The default value is 2080.

preference.name: SM_LIMIT_SINGLE_MASTER_SCHED
preference.preference_description: Limits the schedule to one master schedule. Valid Values: true false

preference.name: SM_MPP_CUSTOM_MAP
preference.preference_description: Map of custom schedule task properties to the microsoft project task fields. Please use the format ScheduleTask.CustomProperty=CustomField

preference.name: SM_MPP_OOTB_MAP
preference.preference_description: Map of out of the box schedule task properties to the microsoft project task fields. Please use the format ScheduleTask.CustomProperty=CustomField

preference.name: SM_NEW_TASK_DIALOG_CLOSE_ON_FINISH
preference.preference_description: Determines if the New Task dialog box is closed after the user clicks the Finish button. Valid Values: True - Closes the dialog box. False - Leaves the dialog box open.

preference.name: SM_PLMXML_EXPORT_SUB_SCHEDULE
preference.preference_description: Enables exporting of subschedules when exporting a master schedule. Valid Values: true - Exports subschedules with the master schedule. false - Exports the master schedule without the subschedules.

preference.name: SM_PLMXML_IMPORT_EXISTING_SCHEDULE
preference.preference_description: Allows re-importing a schedule that is already in the system. Set to False to block the import of the schedule that is already in the system. Valid Values: True - Re-imports the schedule after deleting all of its related data. False - Blocks import operation if the schedule is already present in the system.

preference.name: SM_PREVENTION_OVERRIDE
preference.preference_description: Determines if execution updates are allowed despite the value of the SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES preference. After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: ALWAYS_ON - Execution data updates are always allowed. ALWAYS_OFF - Execution data updates are prevented for the states specified by the SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES preference, but allowed for other states. Schedule Based - Execution data updates are always allowed if the schedule's Enable Execution Override flag is set to on. Otherwise, the setting of the SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES preference is enforced.

preference.name: SM_PREVENT_DELETE_STATES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the states in which schedules and tasks cannot be deleted. The value of this preference takes precedence over the value of the SM_ALLOW_INPROCESS_REMOVAL_OF_SUB_SCHEDULE preference for subschedules. In other words, if a subschedule's state is one of the set values of this preference, it cannot be deleted or removed, even if the SM_ALLOW_INPROCESS_REMOVAL_OF_SUB_SCHEDULE preference is set to true.After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: Accepts one or more of the following internal state values: in_progress complete closed aborted

preference.name: SM_PREVENT_TASK_START_UPDATE_STATES
preference.preference_description: Prevents the changing of the start date of the tasks with the specified state. After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: Accepts one or more of the following internal state values: in_progress complete closed aborted

preference.name: SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES
preference.preference_description: Locks the schedules and tasks that have the specified states, which prevents updates to them. After you change this preference's value, you must log off and then log on for it to take effect. Valid Values: Accepts one or more of the following internal state values: in_progress complete closed aborted

preference.name: SM_PV_FILTER_SHOW_SCHEDULES_ON_EMPTY
preference.preference_description: Determines if schedule nodes are displayed when no tasks are returned from a filter-only criteria in the Program View. This preference comes into play when a filter is applied but has no grouping condition. Valid Values: true false

preference.name: SM_RESOURCE_GRAPH_VIEWER_ROLE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the role of the logged in user for which access to view the resource graph for other users will be granted. The default value is Resource Graph Viewers. Any "Role" created in the Organization is a valid value.

preference.name: SM_SCHEDULE_DATE_LINKED_TO_ACTUAL
preference.preference_description: Link planned and actual schedule dates.If you select ALWAYS_ON, the planned schedule dates and actual schedule dates are linked as follows: Changing the actual start or finish date changes the scheduled start or finish date. Changing the scheduled start or finish date does not change the actual start or finish date, respectively. The Gantt chart always reflects the scheduled start and finish dates, not the actual start and finish dates. If this option is selected, the dates default to the scheduled date regardless of how the system is configured. If this option is not selected, the actual start and finish dates are set to the configured default (either today or scheduled) set up by the system administrator. Valid Values: ALWAYS_ON - Enables date linking. ALWAYS_OFF - Disables date linking. SCHEDULE_BASED - Disables date linking unless the schedule Are Dates Linked option is selected.

preference.name: SM_SCHEDULING_ENGINE_DATE
preference.preference_description: Sets the default behavior for new schedules determining if they are scheduled from the start or end date of the schedule. Valid Values: Start Finish

preference.name: SM_SchedulingEngineOptions
preference.preference_description: Manages the deactivation of scheduling and execution validations. Valid Values: * 0: Both scheduling and execution validations are disabled. This is the default value. * 1: Only the scheduling validation is disabled. The default value is 1. If the preference does not have any value, both scheduling and execution validations are enabled. System throws an error if the preference value is set to anything other than 0 or 1.

preference.name: SM_SetDefaultScheduleAsExternal
preference.preference_description: Manages the ownership of validation in a schedule. Valid Values: * true: Validation ownership is managed by an external application. * false: Validation ownership by the Schedule Manager application. This is the default value. If the preference does not have any value, validation ownership falls on the Schedule Manager. System throws an error if the preference value is set to anything other than true or false.

preference.name: SM_Structure_Partial_Context
preference.preference_description: Specifies the load behavior for loading subschedules in a master schedule context. Valid Values: 0 - Loads the full schedule, including all of the sub schedules. This value results in slower loading than other values. 1 - Partially loads all subschedules and loads them inline on demand. This value yields the best performance if there are subschedules. When you insert a schedule only the schedule summary is inserted. For Costing and EVM, if the subschedules have not been loaded, the system loads them and continues.

preference.name: SM_TEMPLATE_DATE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the start date of schedules created from a template. Valid Values: true - Specifies the start date of the template is used as the start date of the new schedules created from it. This is the default value. false - Specifies the current date is used as the start date of the new schedules.

preference.name: SM_Use_Milestone_Wizard
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to launch the New Milestone wizard when you create a milestone. Valid Values: True False

preference.name: SM_View_CriticalPath
preference.preference_description: Sets the default display of critical path. Valid Values: True - Critical path is displayed. False - Critical path is not displayed.

preference.name: SM_WBS_CODE_PREF
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the work breakdown structure (WBS) code is generated and validated in schedules. Valid Values: true - WBS code is generated and validated. false - WBS code is not generated nor validated. The user can define any WBS code without character format restrictions.

preference.name: SM_WBS_FORMAT_PREF
preference.preference_description:
Specifies the default work breakdown structure (WBS) format to be used by schedules when they are created. The format used by the individual schedules can be changed at the schedule level.For more information on setting the default format for new schedules, see Schedule Manager Guide. Valid Values:
[?N,?A,?a]{[.,-,/,+][?N,?A,?a]}* ? - Whole number representing the minimum character length of a given section. If no number is provided, then 1 is assumed. N - Whole number. A - Uppercase English alphabet character (A-Z). a - Lowercase English alphabet character (a-z). . - Valid separation character. - - Valid separation character. / - Valid separation character. + - Valid separation character.

preference.name: SM_WBS_INITIAL_PREF
preference.preference_description: Specifies the initial starting point for work breakdown structure (WBS) codes, based on the default WBS format. Valid Values: Some examples of valid values include: 1 1.2 2.2 The values must comply with the format.

preference.name: SM_WORKFLOW_STATUS_MAP
preference.preference_description: Defines the workflow status rules mapping between the Workflow Task and Schedule Task statuses. Valid Values: workflow-task-status.schedule-task-status Valid values for workflow-task-status: In Process Completed Late Aborted Valid values for schedule-task-status: in_progress complete late aborted

preference.name: ScheduleAvailableAttributes
preference.preference_description: Site Preference Used for Listing Schedule Attributes in Column Chooser Dialog in ProgramView.

preference.name: ScheduleDeliverableWSOTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the types allowed for the schedule deliverables within Schedule Manager. When adding a type, subtypes are not considered. For example, adding the Dataset type allows you to use Microsoft Word, Microsoft WordX, and Microsoft Excel.However, adding the Item type does not allow you to use the Document subtype of Item. If you have custom submittal types, add them as values to this preference so they are associated with schedule tasks in the schedule. Valid Values: The type of internal storage class names for any subtype of (and including) WorkspaceObject business object.

preference.name: ScheduleTaskAvailableAttributes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Schedule Task object attributes displayed in the Available Columns list in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a Program View is opened. Valid Values: ScheduleTask.object_desc - Displays Description in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.start_date - Displays Start Date in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.finish_date - Displays Finish Date in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.duration - Displays Duration in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.priority - Displays Priority in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.task_type - Displays Task Type in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.constraint - Displays Constraint in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.actual_start_date - Displays Actual Start Date in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.actual_finish_date - Displays Actual Finish Date in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.work_complete - Displays Work Complete in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.complete_percent - Displays Work Complete Percent in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.fnd0state - Displays State in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.fnd0status - Displays Status in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.schedule_tag - Displays Schedule in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened. ScheduleTask.ResourceAssignment - Displays ResourceAssignment in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application when a program view is opened.

preference.preference_description: Specifies the Schedule Task object attributes displayed in the Available Columns list in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. Valid Values: ScheduleTask.object_desc - Displays Description in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. ScheduleTask.start_date - Displays Start Date in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. ScheduleTask.work_complete - Displays Work Complete in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. ScheduleTask.complete_percent - Displays Work Complete Percent in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. ScheduleTask.fnd0state - Displays State in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. ScheduleTask.fnd0status - Displays Status in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. ScheduleTask.ResourceAssignment - Displays ResourceAssignment in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. predecessors - Displays Predecessors in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. successors - Displays Successors in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. baseline_start - Displays Baseline Start in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. baseline_finish - Displays Baseline Finish in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. baseline_duration - Displays Baseline Duration in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. baseline_workestimate - Displays Baseline Work Estimate in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. baseline_workcomplete - Displays Baseline Work Complete in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. baseline_workcompletepercent - Displays Baseline Work Complete Percent in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager application. ScheduleTask.fdp0AssociatedProcesses - Displays Associated Processes in the Column Chooser dialog box of the Schedule Manager applicat

preference.name: SiteTimeZone
preference.preference_description: Stores the time zone of the server. Use this preference to determine the time zone used by the TCCalendars in the scheduling logic. This preference is used with Schedule Manager. Valid Values: Accepts a single value pair indicating a time zone ID from the zoneinfo database (also known as the Olson database) in the following format:region/cityFor example:Europe/ParisRefer to the zoneinfo database (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zoneinfo) for the complete list of zone IDs. The system checks for a valid value and displays an error message when Schedule is created if an invalid value is detected.

preference.name: cost_default_currency
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default currency to use for costs in the system. The value must be a valid currency code based on the ISO-4217 standard. Set this preference to the current value listed in the CostCurrency LOV. The default value is USD (United States dollars). If you want to use EUR as your default currency, change the one value in the CostCurrency LOV from USD to EUR. Then, specify EUR when using the cost_default_currency preference. Siemens PLM Software recommends using only one currency in Teamcenter because there is no support for currency conversion. Valid Values: Accepts one of the values listed in the CostCurrency LOV.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_dataSource
preference.preference_description: Specifies data source for resource graph. When set to randomSample, the system uses a random sample generator. When set to TeamcenterDB (default), the system uses the Teamcenter database. This preference must be set to TeamcenterDB in a production environment. Valid Values: randomSample - The system uses a random sample generator as the data source for resource graphs. TeamcenterDB - The system uses the Teamcenter database as the data source for resource graphs.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_dataSource_filter
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Specifies the filtering method used when creating resource graphs. Valid Values: none - No filter is applied. selection - Users can select which schedules are used to create the resource graph. current - The current schedule is used to create the resource graph.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_date_format
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines the date and time display in resource graphs. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. The string can be any pattern that describes date and time format.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_domain_interval
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines the marked intervals on the domain axis. Set this preference with any segmented time line value such as day (default) or week, or with integer values such as 1 for a day or 7 for a week. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a segmented time line value or positive integer. For example: day week 1440 10080

preference.name: scheduling_graph_domain_label_vertical
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines whether domain labels are vertical or horizontal. Valid Values: True - Domain labels are vertical. False - Domain labels are horizontal.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_font_name
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines the font displayed in resource graphs. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. The string must be a valid font type.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_font_size
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines the font size displayed in resource graphs. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. The string must be a positive integer, representing a reasonable font size.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_font_style
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines the font style displayed in resource graphs. Valid Values: 0 - Normal font. 1 - Bold font. 2 - Italic font. 3 - Bold and italic font.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_histogram_single_color
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines whether single or multiple colors bars are used in resource graphics. If this preference is set to True, the bar tool tip display depends on the value of the scheduling_graph_task_legend preference. If this preference is set to False, the bar tool tip is truncated to show only the task name, schedule name, and date. Valid Values: True - A single color bar is used. False - Multiple color bars are used.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_reference_calendar
preference.preference_description: Specifies the calendar type to use for domain (x = days) and range (y = availability/work allocation) axes in the resource graph. Valid Values: resource_calendar_type - Specifies the domain for the resource calendar. system_calendar_type - Specifies the domain for the system calendar.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_task_legend
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines whether legends are displayed for stacked bars. If this preference is set to True, the bar tool tip is truncated to show only the task name, schedule name, and date.If this preference is set to False, the bar tool tip is expanded, displaying additional task and assignee information, such as work, capacity, availability, load, and calendar.However, if the scheduling_graph_histogram_single_color preference is set to False, the bar tool tip is truncated even if this preference is set to False. Valid Values: True - Legends are displayed for stacked bars. False - Legends are not displayed for stacked bars.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_view
preference.preference_description: Used with Schedule Manager resource graphs. Determines whether scroll bars are included in resource graphs. Valid Values: Classic - Resource graphs display with scroll bars. Native - Resource graphs display without scroll bars.

category.name: Search
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: GeolusServer
preference.preference_description: Specifies Geolus Server used to execute Shape Search. For Example: http://hostname:port/geolus

preference.name: MSS_set_display_limit
preference.preference_description: Specifies the number of saved searches shared by others displayed in the My Saved Searches in the navigation pane. Valid Values: Zero and any positive integer.

preference.name: Open_previous_open_search
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the previous search result is open when closing the current search result in the search results view. Valid Values: 0 - Does not open the previous search result. 1 - Opens the previous search result.

preference.name: QRY_allow_modification_before_run_mss
preference.preference_description: Allows modification of search criteria before running query from "My Saved Search". The default value is false (modifications are not allowed).

preference.name: QRY_latest_ItemRevision_limit
preference.preference_description: Controls the maximum number of objects that can be loaded for Revision check to retrieve the latest Item Revision of the search results. The default value is 3000. If defined too large, more memory is required to load all objects and process the Revision check.

preference.name: QRY_lov_show_inactive_user_projects
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of inactive projects in the LOV "Fnd0UserProjectsLOV" (User Projects List Of Values) in the Search panel of the rich and thin clients. The default value is false.

preference.name: QRY_pff_merge_multiple_lines
preference.preference_description: Activates the function for pff to merge multiple lines of a single object to a single line. The default value is true (merge multiple lines).

preference.name: Search_result_load_all_limit
preference.preference_description: Determines the maximum number of found objects for "Load All" operation in "Search Result" view. Setting a larger value will have performance impact when clicking "Load All" button in "Search Result" view.

preference.name: TC_QRY_display_latest_dataset_only
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of only the latest version of dataset objects in results of queries with search class as the super class of dataset or its descendant classes (for example, queries with search class as WorkspaceObject). preference.preference_description: Defines a switch to turn on/off the tag suggestions while creating tags. All the available tag names are cached when the user tries to create a tag for the first time. As the number of tags grows over a period of time, caching the tag names might pose a performance bottleneck. Set this preference to false to turn off caching.

preference.name: S2cl_SocialTileHeightInLines
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of lines to show while rendering the Social Object Cell used for showing Commentary in grouped view. A value of -1 or 0 displays entire commentary text in Social Object cell. A value greater than zero limits the display of the commentary text to that many lines in Social Object cell. For example: if the value is set to 5 then commentary text is displayed on the Social Object Cell will not exceed 5 lines. If the commentary text is small and fits in less than 5 lines then only appropriate number of lines are displayed in the Social Object Cell.

preference.name: S2cl_SocialTileHeightInLinesInThreadedDisplay

Defines the number of lines to show while rendering the Social Object Cell used for showing Commentary. A value of -1 or 0 displays entire commentary text in Social Object cell. A value greater than zero limits the display of the commentary text to that many lines in Social Object cell. For example: if the value is set to 5 then commentary text is displayed on the Social Object Cell will not exceed 5 lines. If the commentary text is small and fits in less than 5 lines then only appropriate number of lines are displayed in the Social Object Cell.

preference.name: BOM_objects_excluded_from_split
preference.preference_description: Contains a list of object types and subtypes that are excluded from a Split Occurrence operation. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter object type or subtype.

preference.name: Connected_ToRules
preference.preference_description: Defines any supported valid primary/secondary object combination allowed for the Connected_To Generic Relationship Management (GRM) relation. GRM rules contain a primary type, a relation type, and multiple secondary types. If no rule is specified for a given primary type, its supertype is searched until PSConnection is found for which the secondary is considered as interface. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list OR add rules for their particular primary types. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values.Constraints are defined in the following format: primaryObjectType:secondaryObjectType1,secondaryObjectType2 primaryObjectType is any type or subtype of PSConnection or GDELink class/subclass, and secondaryObjectType is any valid ImanType type.

preference.name: GDE_exclude_list
preference.preference_description: Defines the hierarchical object types and subtypes the system excludes when generating a list of types to display in the Item Element creation dialog box. Any valid Teamcenter mechatronics process management general design elements (GDE) type defined in this preference will not display in the drop-down list of possible types to create. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid, domain-specific Teamcenter GDE type.

preference.name: GDE_objects_with_integer_quantity
preference.preference_description: Contains a list of general design element (GDE) objects or subclasses for which the user can specify only an integer value as the quantity. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid GDE object or subclass.

preference.name: ITEM_SAVEAS_GDE_COPYAsReference
preference.preference_description: When a Save As operation is performed on an item that has GDE objects, new GDE objects are created for the new item. This is the default behavior. Use this preference to reference the GDE objects in the existing item instead of creating new GDE objects as a result of the Save As of an item. Specify the item types in the preference. When Save As operation is performed, existing GDE objects are referenced for these item types. For other item types, new GDE objects are created.

preference.name: Implemented_ByRules
preference.preference_description: Defines any supported valid primary/secondary object combination allowed for the Implemented_By Generic Relationship Management (GRM) relation. GRM rules contain a primary type, a relation type, and multiple secondary types. If no rules are found for any of the super types, the primary-secondary combination is considered invalid for Implemented_By relationship. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list OR add rules for their particular primary types. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values.Constraints are defined in the following format: primaryObjectType:secondaryObjectType1,secondaryObjectType2 The object types are any valid ImanType type.

preference.name: MECH_domain_list
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Mechatronics Domains to which a Design Artifact object can belong. These Domain values are used in preferences named MECH_domain_types_"value" to define the list of Design Artifact types which belong to that Domain.

preference.name: MECH_domain_types_Automation
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Design Artifact types, like "ItemRevision", which belong to the Automation Domain.

preference.name: MECH_domain_types_Mechanical
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Design Artifact types, like "ItemRevision", which belong to the Mechanical Domain.

preference.name: Realized_ByRules
preference.preference_description: Defines any supported valid primary/secondary object combination allowed for the Realized_By Generic Relationship Management (GRM) relation. GRM rules contain a primary type, a relation type, and multiple secondary types. If no rule is specified for a given primary type, its supertype is searched. If no rules are found for any of the supertypes, the primary-secondary combination is considered invalid for Realized_By relationship. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list OR add rules for their particular primary types. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values.Constraints are defined in the following format: primaryObjectType:secondaryObjectType1,secondaryObjectType2 The object types are any valid ImanType type.

preference.name: SIG_asystem_source_rules
preference.preference_description: Defines which Teamcenter types and/or classes can be associated with a frame or a signal as a source system. When a class is specified, subtypes are included. If this preference is not set, users can associate a frame or signal to any Teamcenter object that can participate in a relation. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter class or type. Values are set in the following format : frame or signal: class or type For example: Frame:Item Signal:Interfaces

preference.name: SIG_asystem_target_rules
preference.preference_description: Defines which Teamcenter types can be associated with the signal as a target system. If this preference is not set, users can associate a signal to any Teamcenter object that can participate in a relation. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter type corresponding to the secondary object for the desired association. For example, to restrict valid targets for a frame to item and its subtypes, and for the signal to Interfaces and its subtypes, set the values as: Frame:Item Signal:Interfaces

preference.name: SIG_asystem_transmitter_rules
preference.preference_description: Defines which Teamcenter types can be associated with the signal as a transmitter system. If this preference is not set, users can associate a signal to any Teamcenter object that can participate in a relation. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter type corresponding to the secondary object for the desired association. For example, to restrict valid transmitters for a PSSignal subtype or subclass to PSConnection and its subtypes, set the values as: PSSignal:Connection

preference.name: SIG_pvariable_rules
preference.preference_description: Defines which Teamcenter types can be associated with the signal as a process variable. If this preference is not set, users can associate a signal to any Teamcenter object that can participate in a relation. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter type corresponding to the secondary object for the desired association. For example, to restrict valid process variables for a signal or subtype to ProcessVariable and its subtypes, set the values as: Signal:ProcessVariable

preference.name: SIG_redundant_rules
preference.preference_description: Defines which Teamcenter types can be associated with the signal as a redundant signals (or frames) type. If this preference is not set, users can associate a signal to any Teamcenter object that can participate in a relation. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter type corresponding to the secondary object for the desired association. For example, to restrict valid redundants for a frame and its subtypes to Frame and its subtypes, and valid redundants for a signal and its subtypes to Signal and its subtypes, set the values as: Frame:Frame Signal:Signal

preference.name: TC_releasable_logical_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies which releasable logical types are displayed in the Process Selector dialog box. The dialog box lists unreleased logical components of a selected assembly. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid release type.

preference.name: RDV_variant_expression_overlap_checking_mode
preference.preference_description: Determines the mode used to check overlap between variant expressions. Architecture breakdown structures may be configured to check for named variant expression (NVE) consistency. This consistency check rejects NVEs that overlap with other NVEs. Valid Values: 1 - The system assumes an unlimited continuum of values in the product variability. For example, the system assumes an unlimited number of intermediate values between Length = 2 meter and Length = 3 meter, such as a length of 2.50 meters. 2 - The system uses the defined variability, with exactly and only those values allocated. 5 - Same as setting 1, but NVEs are permitted on architecture elements even when they go beyond the variability specified for this element. 6 - Same as setting 2, but NVEs are permitted on architecture elements even when they go beyond the variability specified for this element.

preference.name: TCAE_installation_level
preference.preference_description:
Used to decide whether to check for TcAE/GMO licenses or not. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - No license. 2 - TcAE license. 3 - GMO license.
If this preference is not set, default value is 1.

category.name: Subscription Manager
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: Create_Subscription_mru_list
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of the most recently used types for Subscription creation.

preference.name: Create_Subscription_mru_max
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of the list of most recently used types for Subscription creation, as captured in the preference "Create_Subscription_mru_list". A valid value is a strictly positive integer.

preference.name: SCM_execution_day
preference.preference_description: Determines the day when the event will be processed by the daemon. Applies when value of preference SCM_execution_frequency is Weekly. Valid Values: Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday Friday Saturday Sunday

preference.name: SCM_execution_frequency
preference.preference_description: Specifies the frequency when the event will be processed by the daemon. Valid Values: Immediately Daily Weekly

preference.name: SCM_execution_time
preference.preference_description: Specifies the time when the event will be processed by the daemon. Applies when value of preference SCM_execution_frequency is either Daily or Weekly. Valid Values: hh:mm 00:00 24:00

preference.name: SCM_expiration_date
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default number of days before the subscription expires. A valid value is a positive integer. If the value is empty (default value), Subscriptions never expire.

preference.name: SCM_newsfeed_purge_threshold
preference.preference_description: Defines the purge threshold in number of days for managing the deletion of Newsfeed. Messages older than configured days will be deleted. A valid value is a positive integer. If the value is empty (default value) or 0 (zero), newsfeed messages will not be deleted.

preference.name: SCM_notification_digest
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delivery of Subscription notifications as periodic digest collating notifications for daily and weekly Subscription respectively. This is not applicable to immediate notifications. Valid Values: *1 : Periodic Digest is disabled. This is the default value. *2 : Periodic Digest is enabled. Collated notifications are delivered.

preference.name: SCM_notification_digest_file_size_limit
preference.preference_description: Specifies the limit to Digest notification file size in MB. The default value is set to 1 MB. When the size of collated Digest notification is more than this specified size limit, digest is sent in multiple parts.

preference.name: SCM_notification_mode
preference.preference_description: A user level preference that specifies whether a subscription notification is delivered via SMTP email, Teamcenter inbox, or both. Valid Values: 1 - SMTP email 2 - Teamcenter inbox 3 - Both

preference.name: SCM_notify_new_recipients
preference.preference_description: Activates sending e-mails or Message notifications to users added as recipients to Subscriptions. The preference SCM_notification_mode indicates the method of notification. The default value is false (nothing sent).

preference.name: TC_notification_msg_ext
preference.preference_description: Specifies the file extension for the notification file in the Subscription Manager application. For notifications to be sent as html formatted emails, valid values are txt, htm, html, HTM and HTML.

preference.name: TC_subscription_limit_class_based_notifications
preference.preference_description: Restricts notification of events by class-based subscription objects only when one of the criteria properties is modified as part of an event action. This restriction only applies to Modify events. When set to "false", posting of events is not limited. This is the default value. Valid Values: true - Notifications are sent only when properties in the criteria are changed. false - Notifications are sent when any property is changed.

preference.name: TC_subscription_limit_nocriteria_notification
preference.preference_description: Restricts posting of events by class-based Subscriptions when the criteria is not defined. When the value is "false", posting of events is not restricted.

preference.name: WRKFLW_notification_mode
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the failure of Workflow background process notification is delivered via SMTP email or Active Workspace alert or both. Note: Active Workspace client must be installed Valid Values: *1 : Delivered as SMTP email. This is the default value. *2 : Delivered in the user's Active Workspace alerts. *3 : Delivered in both.

category.name: Subscription Monitor
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: SCM_notification_WorkspaceObject_props
preference.preference_description: Defines the default properties to be included in notification e-mails. Valid Values: Any attributes available on Subscribed object in the Teamcenter schema

preference.name: SCM_notification_history
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the notification history audit record is enabled or disabled. Audit logs with event type Email_Send and Email_Not_Send shows email was sent or not respectively. Valid Values: true: Enables auditing of email sent or not. false: Suppresses auditing of email sent or not.

preference.name: TC_subscription
preference.preference_description: Enables or suppresses subscription functionality. Valid Values: ON - Enables subscription functionality. OFF - Suppresses subscription functionality.

preference.name: TC_subscription_available_subscription_handlers
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Action Handlers that the user can select when creating a Subscription object from a client. If the handler does not appear in this list, the user cannot select it as part of a Subscription. Valid values are the IDs of the handlers. If no handlers are specified, the handler "IMAN_Smtp_Mail_Notify" will be used by default. This handler will always be included even if it is not present in the list.

preference.name: TC_subscription_log_event_and_action_status
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to log the status of TcEvent and TcAction objects via the subscriptionmgrd and actionmgrd process daemons. Valid Values: ON - The subscriptionmgrd process daemon logs the status of each TcEvent object that it processes. The actionmgrd process daemon logs the status of each TcAction object that it processes. OFF - Neither process daemon logs the status of their respective objects as they are processed.

preference.name: CmplExAutoPost
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Auto Post" in the Substance Compliance Exchange view opened by clicking the menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Substance Compliance Exchange -> Send Selected" in the Teamcenter application. The default value is true.

preference.name: CmplExAutoPublish
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Auto Publish" in the Substance Compliance Exchange view opened by clicking the menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Substance Compliance Exchange -> Send Selected" in the Teamcenter application. The default value is true.

preference.name: CmplExCategoryRootClass
preference.preference_description: Specifies the root class for searching Vendor Contacts allowed to participate in Substance Compliance Exchange.

preference.name: CmplExDefaultPartition
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Partition" in the Substance Compliance Exchange view opened by clicking the menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Substance Compliance Exchange -> Send Selected" in the Teamcenter application. The default value is "sample partition".

preference.name: CmplExDefaultTemplate
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Template" in the Substance Compliance Exchange view opened by clicking the menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Substance Compliance Exchange -> Send Selected" in the Teamcenter application. The default value is "Substance_Compliance_Sample_Exchange".

preference.name: CmplExReviewResponseWorkflow
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the Workflow Template used for starting Workflow Process upon the submission of Response by the Recipient for Substance Compliance Exchnage. The default value is "Review Substance Compliance Exchange Response".

preference.name: CmplExSendEmailNotification
preference.preference_description: Sends an Email to the Sponsor User when the Substance Declarations Exchange is initiated or when its response is approved or rejected. The default value is true.

preference.name: CmplExSendToSupplierWorkflow
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the Workflow Template used for starting a Workflow Process through the command "Send to Supplier" for Substance Compliance Exchange in the Exchange view of the Teamcenter application. The default value is "Substance Compliance Data Exchange Process".

preference.name: CmplExVendorContactRoles
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Vendor Contact roles which are allowed to participate in Substance Compliance Exchange.

preference.name: ComplianceTemplates
preference.preference_description: Specifies the values for Supplier Collaboration Templates for Substance Compliance Exchange.

preference.name: DesExAutoPost
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Auto Post" in the Design Exchange view opened by clicking menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Design Exchange -> Send Selected". The default value is true.

preference.name: DesExAutoPublish
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Auto Publish" in the Design Exchange view opened by clicking menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Design Exchange -> Send Selected". The default value is true.

preference.name: DesExCategoryRootClass
preference.preference_description: Specifies the root class for searching Vendors and Vendor Contacts allowed to participate in Design Exchange.

preference.name: DesExDefaultImportOptionSet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Import Option Set" in the Design Exchange view opened by clicking menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Design Exchange -> Send Selected". The default value is "TIEImportOptionSetDefault".

preference.name: DesExDefaultOptionSet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Option Set" in the Design Exchange view opened by clicking menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Design Exchange -> Send Selected". The default value is "TIEConfiguredExportDefault".

preference.name: DesExDefaultPartition
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Partition" in the Design Exchange view opened by clicking menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Design Exchange -> Send Selected". The default value is "sample partition".

preference.name: DesExDefaultTemplate
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value associated to the option "Template" in the Design Exchange view opened by clicking menu item "Supplier Exchange -> Design Exchange -> Send Selected". The default value is "Design_Data_Exchange_Sample_Template".

preference.name: DesExReviewResponseWorkflow
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the Workflow Template used for starting a Workflow Process upon the submission of a response by the Respondent in the Supplier Collaboration Foundation application. The default value is "Review Supplier Response".

preference.name: DesExSendEmailNotification

preference.name: SC_ECNRev_ItemRev_Relation_Names

preference.preference_description: Determines if line items or splits(BidPackageLineItem) to be created automatically based on projects (assigned to selected ChangeRequestRevision or ChangeNoticeRevision) and plants (associated with Impacted or Solution ItemRevision of selected ChangeRequestRevision or ChangeNoticeRevision) in Supplier Collaboration application. The default value is false

preference.name: SC_auto_split_project_attribute_name

Valid value is internal name of the projects (List of TypedReference to TC_Project object or its subtype) attribute. Default value is project_list.

preference.name: SC_briefcase_pkg_file_name
preference.preference_description: Defines the name format for Briefcase packages (named references attached to Dataset objects). The format is based on the keywords ItemID (Item ID), ItemName (Item Name), RevID (Revision ID), VariantRule (Variant Rule ID), RevRule (Revision Rule), PkgType (Package Type), TargetSite (Remote Site) and TimeStamp (Time Stamp) of the object being exported. The format is any combination of one or more of the above specified keywords. Any other word specified in the format will be treated as a constant. For example a value "ItemID:RevID:TargetSite:TimeStamp" would result in the following generated file name "00001_A_Site1_31-Sep-2011_19-48-30.bcz".

preference.name: SC_close_date_offset_hours

preference.name: SC_search_contacts_using_item_classes

preference.name: SC_selfserviceSponsor

preference.name: SC_traverse_BOM

The Request Data command is visible only when the selected oject is of the type mentioned in this preference. Valid values are type internal names.

preference.name: SC_valid_types_for_revise_data

preference.name: SrcExCategoryRootClass
preference.preference_description: Specifies the root class for searching Vendors and Vendor Contacts allowed to participate in Sourcing.

preference.name: SrcExDefaultBaseCurrency

preference.name: SrcExDefaultTemplate

preference.name: SrcExPrepareBidPackageExTask
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the Workflow task the Sourcing Manager needs to perform to prepare Direct Materials Sourcing Data. The default value is "Direct Materials Sourcing Review Task".

preference.name: SrcExReviewResponseWorkflow

preference.name: SrcExSendEmailNotification
preference.preference_description: Sends an email to the Sponsor User when the workflow "Direct Materials Sourcing" is initiated or when its response is approved or rejected. The default value is true.

preference.name: SrcExSendToSupplierWorkflow

preference.name: SrcExUpdateDoTaskWorkflow
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the Workflow Template used for updating a rejected Direct Materials Sourcing Revisiona by Program buyer in the Supplier Collaboration Foundation application. The default value is "Update Direct Materials Sourcing".

preference.name: SrcExVendorContactRoles
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Vendor Contact roles which are allowed to participate in Sourcing. Valid values are the values of the classification Key-LOV that is attached to the classification attribute specified by the preference "SC_VendorRolesAttributeID".

preference.name: Use_DataShare_Manager
preference.preference_description: Activates the use of the Data Share Manager for uploading and downloading files. The Data Share Manager is an asynchronous file upload and download async application for File Management System (FMS) transactions. Valid Values: true - Perform asynchronous file uploads and downloads and monitor them with the Data Share Manager. false - Use the File Management System (FMS) to perform synchronous file uploads and downloads. This is the default value.

preference.name: ValidVendorStatuses
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Vendor statuses which are allowed to participate in Design or Sourcing Exchange.

preference.name: VisStructureContext.SUMMARYRENDERING

preference.name: VisStructureContextSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the VisStructureContextSummary summary stylesheet can be applied.

category.name: Systems Engineering
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: CrossProbing_AllowedRelationTypes
preference.preference_description: Lists all relation types and subtypes that users can select as targets for cross-domain tracing. This master list is displayed in the Available Relations pane of the Options dialog box. From the Available Relations pane, the user adds selections to the Shown Relations pane, which lists the specific relations that are designated for the current cross-domain tracing operation. The selections in the Shown Relations pane are stored in the CrossProbing_SelectedRelationTypes preference. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid trace link relation type or subtype that can be used as a search keyword.

preference.name: CrossProbing_RelationTraversalType
preference.preference_description: Defines the direction of the current cross-domain tracing operation. The user sets the direction with the Relations Traversal Type option in the Options dialog box. Valid Values: 0 - Specifies that the source is the primary (defining) object in a relation. The trace highlights related objects downstream. 1 - Specifies that the source is secondary (complying) object in a relation. The trace highlights related objects upstream. 2 - Specifies that the source is both a primary (defining) and a secondary (complying) object in a relation. The trace highlights related objects downstream and upstream.

preference.name: CrossProbing_SelectedRelationTypes
preference.preference_description: Lists the specific relation types and subtypes that are designated as targets for the current cross-domain tracing operation. These relations are displayed in the Shown Relations pane of the Options dialog box. Users select the target relations from the Available Relations pane, which lists all relation types and subtypes that can be selected for cross-domain tracing. This master list is controlled by the CrossProbing_AllowedRelationTypes preference. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid trace link relation type or subtype that can be used as a search keyword.

preference.name: DefiningTraceReportTable_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the width of the columns for the properties listed in the DefiningTraceReportTable_ColumnPreferences preference. The width values are modified as the user resizes the columns in a traceability report. Valid Values: Accepts one or more integers as values. Each integer defines the column width in characters.

preference.name: IconShownColumnProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the columns where an icon is displayed on BOM structure instead of a string value. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid BOM line property.

preference.name: Import_Spec_Info_EXCLUDETYPES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the specification subclasses that are restricted from the Spec type list of the Import Spec wizard. These list of types are also excluded from the types specified in the TcAllowedImportExportPeakSpecObject preference. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be the internal name of a valid subclass of the Specification business object.

preference.name: Indirect_Tracelink_Report
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the current cross-domain tracing operation includes indirect trace links. Indirect trace links are implicitly inherited by the item revisions of target objects. Valid Values: true - The trace follows both direct and indirect trace links. The value is set to true when the user selects the ON checkbox in the Options dialog box. false - The trace follows only explicit trace links that are directly associated with target object items. The value is reset to false when the user clears the ON checkbox in the Options dialog box.

preference.name: MultilineColumnProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the columns where data can be shown on multiple lines. The columns wrap the words into as many lines as needed. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid BOM line property.

preference.name: NE_default_application_domain_template
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default application domain and Visio diagram template for the specified types of BOM line, which is used in Systems Engineering. Default application domains are defined in the Business Modeler IDE by the Fnd0TcApplication list of values. Valid Values: ObjectTypeName:valid_application_domain_name,default_visio _template

preference.name: NE_relation_rule_grm_list
preference.preference_description: Lists all Generic Relationship Management (GRM) relations that can appear in the Available GRMs list of the New Diagram Template and Edit Diagram Template dialog boxes. These selections determine which relations can be represented in diagrams based on the diagram template. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be the valid model name of a relation, not the display name.

preference.name: REQ_ExportToExcel_add_level_column
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Teamcenter inserts the Level column in Microsoft Excel output files for structures that exceed eight levels. In these files, Excel's Outline features are disabled and all objects occupy the same level. The Level column references each object's structure level in Teamcenter. Valid Values: false - The Level column is suppressed. true - The Level column is inserted in the leftmost position.

preference.name: REQ_checkout_objects_before_export
preference.preference_description: Sets the default condition of the Check out objects before export check box under Live options in the Export to Word dialog box. Valid Values: default - The check box can be selected and cleared. default_hide - The check box is cleared and unavailable. Objects are exported to live Word but not checked out. default_checkout - The check box is selected and unavailable. Objects exported to live Word are explicitly checked out before the output document is generated.

preference.name: SE_Trace_Report_Layout
preference.preference_description: Controls the arrangement of the panes in the Traceability view. Valid Values: true - Panes are arranged horizontally, with the Defining Object pane on the left and the Complying Object pane on the right. false - Panes are arranged vertically, with the Defining Object pane on top and the Complying Object pane at bottom.

preference.name: TC_setProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the overall behavior of object properties setting from Excel Live and Word Live. VALID VALUES - SET_PROPERTIES: indicates that all properties are set without any query or confirmation from the user regarding properties that have been overwritten since the export. This is the default value. - QUERY_AND_SET_ALL: indicates that all objects will be queried to check if they have been overwritten since the export. This option behaves like SET_PROPERTIES if no objects are found to be have been overwritten. If objects have been found, values for ALL objects will be set only after confirmation from the user. This option will work only when the preference TC_overwrite_protection is turned on. - QUERY_AND_SET_OVERWRITTEN: indicates that all objects will be queried to check if they have been overwritten since the export. This option behaves like SET_PROPERTIES if no objects are found to have been overwritten. If objects have been found, values for OVERWRITTEN objects will be set only after confirmation from the user. Values that have not been overwritten will be automatically updated without confirmation. This option will work only when the preference TC_overwrite_protection is turned on.

preference.name: TcAllowedImportExportPeakSpecObject
preference.preference_description:
Specifies which business object subclasses can occupy the top level in Systems Engineering structures that are imported and exported. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must contain the following: The name of a valid subclass of the Item business object. One of the following parameters: true - The subclass and its child subclasses can occupy the top level. false - Only the subclass can occupy the top level.
For example: subclass_name:true Do not enter multiple values from the same subclass hierarchy. Otherwise, only the parent's value is recognized. For example, assume that the following values are entered: Document:true Specification:false
Because the Document subclass is the parent of the Specification subclass, the Specification value is ignored.

preference.name: TcNotesAllowedType_DesignReq
preference.preference_description: Specifies the types of custom notes that can be attached with the Quick Create bar to selected design requirements. Valid Values: Accepts the internal names of user-defined subtypes of the Fnd0CustomNote business object.

preference.name: TcNotesAllowedType_Fnd0LogicalBlock
