preference.name: ME_skip_bvr_check_on_assign_for_types
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of item types for which the BOM View Revision (BVR) check will be skipped. BVR check is necessary to assign top line of BOM structure to BOP structure, and it ensures that the assigned BOM line behaves like a consumed line. This preference is recommended in special case to skip BVR check on certain types of lines to prevent access rights problem. Valid values are Teamcenter type internal names. For each type defined in the list, its sub types will be also included. Teamcenter needs to be restarted for any value change to take effect. By default the list is empty.

preference.name: MfgValidationFramework_EP_ObjectType_Workflow_Tests_Mapping
preference.preference_description: Defines the workflow the Manufacturing Validation Test Framework will associate with the validation tests. The format of this preference is as follows: "MfgValidationTestFramework_<ClientIdentifier>_ObjectType_Workflow_Tests_Mapping" "ClientIdentifier" is a unique client identifier that communicates with the Mfg Validation Test Framework. The preference value is a ':' delimited list of the following format: <Item Type>,<Workflow Name>,<Validation Test Type> The value (<Validation Test Type> is the value used during the validation test callback registration for -type. Example validation test callback registration: 'install_callback -u=%1 -p=%1 -g=dba -mode=create -type=MyMfgValidationsType -library=libmfgvalidationsamples -function=MfgValidationTestSuiteA -name="My Validation Suite A" ' The "Item Type" entry is based on the Item subtype hierarchy. Therefore, if there are two entries of the same item subtype then the highest subtype entry wins. For example if "Process:Release1:Tests" and "Item:Release2:Tests" are both entries then the Process entry will win if the input object is a Process type. This preference is optional. If not defined the validation test suites defined in preference 'MfgValidationTestFramework_Client_<ClientIdentifier>_ValidationTestTypes' are used.

preference.name: MfgValidationFramework_EP_TestResultTypesForSubmitWorkflow
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of test status types the Manufacturing Validation Test Framework will count as equivalent to 'Pass'. The format of this preference is as follows: "MfgValidationTestFramework_<ClientIdentifier>_TestResultTypesForSubmitWorkflow" "ClientIdentifier" is a unique client identifier that communicates with the Mfg Validation Test Framework. Valid Values: One or more strings from the following list: 'Pass','Warning','Caution'. This preference is only used when 'MfgValidationTestFramework_EP_ForceValidationPassForSubmitWorkflow' is 'true'.

preference.name: MfgValidationFramework_EP_TestResultTypesForSummary
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of test status types the Manufacturing Validation Test Framework will count as equivalent to 'Pass' when calculating the Validation Test Summary column value. The format of this preference is as follows: "MfgValidationTestFramework_<ClientIdentifier>_TestResultTypesForSummary" "ClientIdentifier" is a unique client identifier that communicates with the Mfg Validation Test Framework. Valid Values: One or more strings from the following list: 'Pass','Warning','Caution'.

preference.name: MfgValidationTestFramework_Client_EP_ValidationTestTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the validation test types this client can handle. The format of this preference is as follows: "MfgValidationTestFramework_Client_<ClientIdentifier>_ValidationTestTypes" This preference needs to be an entry in the preference: "MfgValidationTestFramework_Clients". Each entry is a Manufacturing Validation Test Type that this client can present and handle. Each entry must match the -type argument used during the 'install_callback' for a Validation Test Suite. Required if specified in "MfgValidationTestFramework_Clients".

preference.name: MfgValidationTestFramework_Client_EP_WI_ValidationTestTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the validation test types this client can handle. The format of this preference is as follows: "MfgValidationTestFramework_Client_<ClientIdentifier>_ValidationTestTypes" This preference needs to be an entry in the preference: "MfgValidationTestFramework_Clients". Each entry is a Manufacturing Validation Test Type that this client can present and handle. Each entry must match the -type argument used during the 'install_callback' for a Validation Test Suite. Required if specified in "MfgValidationTestFramework_Clients".

preference.name: MfgValidationTestFramework_Clients
preference.preference_description: Defines the clients that will be communicating with the Manufacturing Validation Test Framework. Each entry is the name of another preference of this form. "MfgValidationTestFramework_Client_<ClientIdentifier>_ValidationTestTypes" where "ClientIdentifier" is a unique client identifier that communicates with the Manufacturing Validation Test Framework. For example: See preference MfgValidationTestFramework_Client_EP_ValidationTestTypes. Currently, a single tcserver instance can handle 'one' validation test client.

preference.name: MfgValidationTestFramework_EP_ClosureRules
preference.preference_description:
Defines the closure rule the Manufacturing Validation Test Framework will use before executing the validation tests. The format of this preference is as follows: "MfgValidationTestFramework_<ClientIdentifier>_ClosureRules" "ClientIdentifier" is a unique client identifier that communicates with the Mfg Validation Test Framework.
The value is a pair tuple delineated by a ':' of the form "Item Type:Closure Rule Name". The "Item Type" entry is based on the Item subtype hierarchy. Therefore, if there are two entries of the same item subtype then the highest subtype entry wins. For example if "Process:ClosureRule1" and "Item:ClosureRule2" are both entries then the Process entry will win if the input object is a Process type.

preference.name: MfgValidationTestFramework_EP_ForceValidationPassForSubmitWorkflow
preference.preference_description: Defines that the submit to work flow button enablement is associated with the validation test results. The submit to work flow button will only be enabled if all the associated validation test results are pass or equivalent to pass. The format of this preference is as follows: "MfgValidationTestFramework_<ClientIdentifier>__VisibleSubmitWorkflowButton" "ClientIdentifier" is a unique client identifier that communicates with the Mfg Validation Test Framework. The default value is false.

preference.name: MfgValidationTestFramework_EP_VisibleSubmitWorkflowButton
preference.preference_description: Makes visible the submit to work flow button on the EasyPlan Manufacturing Validation Page. The default value is false.

preference.name: MfgValidationTestFramework_EP_WI_MyMfgValidationsType_ClosureRule
preference.preference_description: Defines the closure rule the Manufacturing Validation Test Framework will use before executing the validation tests. The format of this preference is as follows: "MfgValidationTestFramework_<ClientIdentifier>_<ValidationTestSuiteTypeName>_ClosureRule" "ClientIdentifier" is a unique client identifier that communicates with the Mfg Validation Test Framework. "ValidationTestSuiteTypeName" must match the -type argument used during the 'install_callback' for a Validation Test Suite. The value is the name of a Closure Rule. This closure rule is associated with all the manufacturing test suites of this type. This closure rule will be run by the Mfg Test Framework before executing a Validation Test Suite. This is a closure rule that is relevant across all validation test suites within a registered type. Of course, each Mfg Validation Test suite can do any further traversal refinements within its own implementation.

When you resolve part assignments, you can set a state for the assignment allowing it to go through a manual review and approval process. Valid Values: true - Teamcenter assigns a state to the resolved part. false - Teamcenter does not assign a state to the resolved part.

Valid Values: Accepts one of the following values: No State Pending Accepted Rejected

preference.name: MEAutomaticOwnershipTransferClosureRules
preference.preference_description: Specifies the closure rule to be used in recursive ownership transfer of "Export To Briefcase" functionality for CC Objects. The default value of the preference is MfgDefaultOTCR.

preference.name: MEConstraintViewPreloadedPredecessorLevels
preference.preference_description: Specifies the level of predecessors that are loaded automatically when a new scope is set in the Line Balancing Constraints view. Valid Values: Accepts a single positive integer or 0.

preference.name: MEConstraintViewPreloadedSuccessorLevels
preference.preference_description: Specifies the level of successors that are loaded automatically when a new scope is set in the Line Balancing Constraints view. Valid Values: Accepts a single positive integer or 0.

preference.name: MEDefaultExportTransferOptionSet
preference.preference_description:
Specifies the list of valid transfer option set values in "Export to Briefcase" dialog's transfer option set dropdown. The values shown in the transfer option set dropdown are dependent on: 1. Values in this preference 2. Values of transfer mode in preference "TC_gms_export_default_transfermode".
With value of preference "TC_gms_export_default_transfermode" as "TIEExportDefaultTM" there will be two cases: 1. Only those transfer option set will be displayed in "Export to Briefcase" dialog's transfer option set dropdown that are specified in this preference and have transfer mode value as "TIEExportDefaultTM". 2. All the transfer option set with transfer mode value as "TIEExportDefaultTM" will be displayed in "Export to Briefcase" dialog's transfer option set dropdown, if none of the transfer option set names specified in this preference have transfer mode value as "TIEExportDefaultTM".
Default values for the dropdown are: * MfgConfiguredExportDefault_LL: Use this transfer option set for briefcase configured LowLevel export. * MfgConfiguredExportDefault: Use this transfer option set for briefcase configured export. * MfgUnconfiguredExportDefault: Use this transfer option set for briefcase unconfigured export. The first value specified in this preference defaults to selected transfer option set on the export to briefcase dialog.

preference.name: MEDesignToBom_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables the Design to BOM alignment commands and disables existing Structure Alignment commands. The default value is false.

preference.name: MEDesignToBom_check_maturity
preference.preference_description: Enables the Design to BOM alignment maturity check. The default value is false.

preference.name: MEDesignToBom_keep_rep_by_relation
preference.preference_description: Enables keeping the "TC_Is_Represented_By" relation during the removal of a Design to BOM alignment. If set false then the "TC_Is_Represented_By" relation is deleted if it exists. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEIdGenerationAllowDuplicates
preference.preference_description: Allows duplicate values for IDs generated for BOM line properties based on the value of the MEIdGenerationPropertySetting preference. Valid Values: true - The value of the property created by the recipe found in the MEIdGenerationPropertySetting preference must not be unique. false - The value of the property created by the recipe found in the MEIdGenerationPropertySetting preference must be unique.

preference.name: MEIdGenerationOnAssignEnabled
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the MEIdGenerationPropertySetting preference is used to generate absolute occurrence values (in-context IDs) during the assign action. Valid Values: true - The smart IDIC is generated when assigning from one structure to another. false - The smart IDIC is not generated when assigning from one structure to another. Teamcenter creates IDICs based on the values of the MECopyIdInContextToAssignedLine and MECopyIdInContextLowerLevels preferences.

preference.name: MEIdGenerationPropertySetting
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of BOM line properties for which values are to be formulated using specified property values from other BOM lines. This is customizable based on item type. If a rule is independent of the item type, use Item for the item type. If there is no exact match for the specified item type, Teamcenter uses the closest parent type. Valid Values: Accepts a string with the following format: type:item-type,key:property-being-set,prop:first-property-to-concatenate,prop:second-property-to-concatenate...

preference.name: MEMBOMAllowInContextAssign
preference.preference_description:
Enables considering the active context line of the Manufacturing Bill Of Material (MBOM) window during assignment the BOMLine from Engineering BOM to MBOM. When set to "true", the ID In Context (IDIC) value is created in context of the active context line and not the default top line. The default value is false.
Teamcenter needs to be restarted for any value change to take effect.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_AlignProperties
preference.preference_description: Enables the alignment of properties on Make items and revisions created in a manufacturing BOM (MBOM) during a mirror operation through the me_create_mbom utility. These Make nodes are of different types compared to the original engineering BOM (EBOM) nodes. Valid Values: Formats use the character : as a separator. Relation:InternalRelationName:list of secondary types separated by comma:Skip/Reference Example: Relation:IMAN_Rendering:DirectModel:Reference These relation types are skipped or referenced on items and revisions of the exact specified secondary types and do not apply to subtypes. If secondary types are not specified, all relations of that type are referenced. Use * for a relation type or secondary type wildcard. The relation elements are ordered. Item:InternalEBOMItemType,InternalMBOMItemType:(EBOMInternalPropertyName, MBOMInternalPropertyName)+ Example: Item:Item,Document:fnd0is_monolithic,fnd0is_monolithicEBOM and MBOM items with matching underlying property types have their values aligned. Revision:InternalEBOMItemType,InternalMBOMItemType:(EBOMInternalPropertyName, MBOMInternalPropertyName)+ Example: Revision:ItemRevision,DocumentRevision:ebomRevProp,mbomRevProp

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_Align_Existing_Mbom_Items
preference.preference_description: Defines the alignment of top-level context IDs (IDICs) of manufacturing BOM (MBOM) lines based on their corresponding engineering BOM (EBOM) lines. Valid Values: 0 - No alignment. 1 - Alignment of IDIC values of MBOM lines only for EBOM lines that have an IDIC value. 2 - Alignment of IDIC values of MBOM lines using the EBOM lines. If no IDIC value exists on an EBOM node, the item ID and transform values are used for equivalence.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_IgnoreRules
preference.preference_description: Defines the BOM line properties and corresponding values used to determine the action to take on Engineering BOM nodes when the me_create_mbom utility is invoked for each BOM line that matches the criteria. Valid Values: KEY:BOM-line-property-internal-name,VALUE:property-value,ACTION:Skip/Traverse.KEY:GCS CP,VALUE:Phantom,ACTION:TraverseIf more than one value for a given property can determine the action, the OR| operator can be used:KEY:BOM-line-property-internal-name,VALUE:PropertyValue1,ACTION:Skip/Traverse [|VALUE:PropertyValue2,ACTION:Skip/Traverse]The ACTIONSkip keyword (default ) skips an EBOM node, while Traverse traverses below an EBOM node and ignores that EBOM node. The children of the EBOM node become children of the corresponding MBOM parent. KEY:GCS CP,VALUE:Phantom,ACTION:Skip|VALUE:Phantom1,ACTION:Traverse

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_MakeRules
preference.preference_description: Defines the key/value pairs of BOM line properties and their corresponding values used to determine if a new manufacturing BOM node is to be created when the me_create_mbom utility is invoked, for each BOM line that matches the criteria. Valid Values: KEY:BOM-line-property-internal-name,VALUE:property-value1[|VALUE:property-value2]KEY:GCS CP,VALUE:Make

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_RemoveLineWithIDIC
preference.preference_description: Enables the deletion of manufacturing bill of material (MBOM) lines whose in-context ID (top level) values do not match existing engineering BOM (EBOM) lines during MBOM update from the EBOM using the me_create_mbom utility. Valid Values: TRUE - Teamcenter deletes the MBOM line if its value does not match its corresponding EBOM line. FALSE - Teamcenter does not delete any lines based on a mismatch of in-context ID.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_ReplaceMakeOnChange
preference.preference_description: When running the me_create_mbom utility, enables the replacement of manufacturing BOM (MBOM) lines that were changed from Make to Buy in the engineering BOM (EBOM) during the MBOM update from the EBOM. Valid Values: TRUE - Teamcenter replaces the Make part in the MBOM with a Buy part from the EBOM during the update. FALSE - Teamcenter does not replace the Make part with a Buy part from the EBOM. It adds the EBOM Buy part to the MBOM structure without removing the original Make part.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_TypePrefixSuffix
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of item to be used when creating an item in a manufacturing BOM through the me_create_mbom utility. It also defines the prefix and suffix for the name of the item instance. Valid Values: Valid values are in the format ItemType,Prefix,Suffix, in which the character (,) is the separator. The prefix or suffix are optional.

preference.name: MEMaxOpenViewsSameType
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of structures of any given type that you can open at the same time. Valid Values: Accepts a positive integer value.

preference.name: MEOperationWeldReportPartsOcc
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of occurrence types for which parts table in the Process Weld report (Operation page) will be populated.

preference.name: MEOperationWeldReportResourceOcc
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of occurrence types for which resources table in the Process Weld report (Operation page) will be populated.

preference.name: MEProcessResourcesViewColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixels of the columns displayed in the Process Resources view of Manufacturing Process Planner, as defined by the MEProcessResourcesViewDisplayNameColumnsShownPref preference. This setting affects each column defined in the MEProcessResourcesViewDisplayNameColumnsShownPref preference. Valid Values: Accepts one or more integers as values. The number of integers should match the number of columns in the MEProcessResourcesViewDisplayNameColumnsShownPref preference.

preference.name: MEProcessWeldReportPartsOcc
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of occurrence types for which parts table in the Process Weld report (Index page) will be populated.

preference.name: MEProcessWeldReportResourceOcc
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of occurrence types for which resources table in the Process Weld report (Index page) will be populated.

preference.name: MEReplaceAssemblyInContext_AlignProperties
preference.preference_description: Enables the alignment of properties on Items and Revisions created in Manufacturing BOM (MBOM), during a replace assembly with any item type operation. The following formats are allowed (the character ':' is the separator in each of them): * "Item:[InternalEBOMItemType,InternalMBOMItemType:(EBOMInternalPropertyName,MBOMInternalPropertyName)+]" (e.g. "Item:Item,Document:fnd0is_monolithic,fnd0is_monolithic"): The EBOM and MBOM Items for which the underlying property types match, will have their values aligned. * "Revision:[InternalEBOMItemType,InternalMBOMItemType:(EBOMInternalPropertyName,MBOMInternalPropertyName)+]" (e.g. "Revision:ItemRevision,DocumentRevision:ebomRevProp,mbomRevProp"): The EBOM and MBOM Item Revisions for which the underlying property types match, will have their values aligned.

preference.name: MEResolveBypassICForReleaseStatus
preference.preference_description: Bypasses the changes to be tracked in Incremental Change (IC) context during resolve command in Enterprise Bill of Process (EBOP) structures in the Manufacturing application. Valid values are all the release statuses for which IC needs to be turned off. If the value is "No_Status", IC will be turned off for all structures that are not released. If there is no value or an empty value for this preference, IC will be turned on for every release status and for structures with no release status.

preference.name: MEShowPartPositionDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Determines if the default state of the 'Use Reference Frame Position' toggle button is 'toggled ON' when Graphic view is opened on a PlantBOP structure in the Manufacturing application. The default value is false.

preference.name: MEStudyMaturityStatusforBriefcaseExport
preference.preference_description: Defines the maturity statuses of the Study objects to use during a briefcase export of a Collaboration Context (CC). By default the value is "Approved", which means that only the studies in a CC with release status "Approved" will be exported.

preference.name: ME_CHECHOUT_EXCLUDED_DATASET_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Indicates which datasets will not be checked out when running Manufacturing Checkout command. Valid values are the pairs of dataset types and relations separated by a ":" character.

preference.name: ME_CHECHOUT_EXCLUDED_FORM_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Indicates which forms will not be checked out when running Manufacturing Checkout command. Valid values are the pairs of form types and relations separated by a ":" character.

preference.name: ME_angular_tolerance
preference.preference_description: Defines the tolerance value (in degrees) under which small variations in the rotation section of a transform are considered equal. This value is used to normalize Euler angles of the rotation vector to the closest integer (floor). For example, if the rotation angle is changed from 1.11 to 1.12 and this preference is set to 0.1, the calculation is as follows:floor (1.11/0.1)=11 and floor (1.12/0.1)=11Because these results are equal (11), the angles are not flagged as different. Lowering the preference value to .01 results in the following calculation:floor (1.11/0.01)=111 and floor (1.12/0.01)=112These results are no longer equal meaning that the rotation between 1.11 and 1.12 are considered two different positions. Valid Values: Accepts a double value representing a degree amount.

preference.name: ME_reuse_assm_xform_precision
preference.preference_description: Sets the precision of transform comparisons in reused assembly. Transform values with differences smaller than the specified precision are treated as identical when comparing. Valid Values: A floating point number.

preference.name: ME_translation_tolerance
preference.preference_description: Defines the tolerance value (in millimeters) under which small variations in the translation section of a transform are considered equal. This value is used to normalize translation vectors to the closest integer (floor). For example, if the part is moved from 1.11 to 1.12 and this preference is set to 0.1, the calculation is as follows:floor (1.11/0.1)=11 and floor (1.12/0.1)=11Because these results are equal (11), the positions are not flagged as different. Lowering the preference value to .01 results in the following calculation:floor (1.11/0.01)=111 and floor (1.12/0.01)=112These results are no longer equal meaning that the translation from 1.11 to 1.12 constitutes two different positions. Valid Values: Accepts a double value representing a millimeter amount.

preference.name: OccurrenceGroup_Expansion_EXCLUDETYPES
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types not to be displayed in Manufacturing "Expand To Type" dialog when the structure is of type "Occurrence Group". For a given value, its associated subtypes will also to be considered for the exclusion.

preference.name: ProcessStationForAutomatedMfgAssignment
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types and their properties that are supported by the Automatic MFG Assignment menu command in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts a list of any valid process type and property with a double format separated by a colon. TypeInternalName:PropertyInternalName

preference.name: ProductStructure_Expansion_EXCLUDETYPES
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types not to be displayed in Manufacturing "Expand To Type" dialog when the structure is of type "Product Structure". For a given value, its associated subtypes will also to be considered for the exclusion.

preference.name: WeldTimeForAutomatedMfgAssignment
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of manufacturing feature object types and their properties that are supported by the Automatic MFG Assignment menu command in Manufacturing Process Planner. Valid Values: Accepts a list of any valid feature type and property with a double format separated by a colon. internal-name-of-feature-type:internal-property-name

preference.name: Baseline_precondition_validation_rule_item_revision
preference.preference_description: Specifies the validation rule item revision for baseline pre-action handler. Valid Values: A valid item revision.

preference.name: NXCMValData.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the create style sheet for NXCMValData objects. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: NXCMValData.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary style sheet for NXCMValData objects. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.preference_description: Registers the summary style sheet for NXCheckMate objects. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: NXCheckMateRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary style sheet for NXCheckMateRevision objects. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: NXRDDV.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary style sheet for NXRDDV objects. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: NXRDDVRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary style sheet for NXRDDVRevision objects. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: NXRDDVValData.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary style sheet for NXRDDVValData objects. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: NXRDDVValDataRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary style sheet for NXRDDVValDataRevision objects. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_CLI_file_spec_separator
preference.preference_description: Defines the separator used to separate fields in the NX Manager CLI part file specification format.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_FILE_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Determines the types of files that can be associated as datasets to validation data or validation results objects.This preference is applicable for the NX Check-Mate and NX RDDV (Requirement-Driven Design Validation) validation agents only. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must contain three string values: dataset name, RefName and references (which are file extensions in the following example), defining the types of files that can contain rules or validation results. For example: TC_VALIDATION_FILE_TYPES= Text Text *.mqclog MSExcel excel *.xls

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_RULE_SET_ITEM_REVISIONS
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of item revisions that contain validation rule datasets, and which are displayed in the Rule Setlist of the Rule Set Evaluation tab in the Validation Manager. You can always type in or paste items and item revisions into the list. Register them into this preference list after creation. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid item revision.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_STYLESHEET_DATASETNAME
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of style sheet datasets information. This is a blank separated list containing the dataset type, reference type name, named reference name, style sheet file name, and validation result log file extension that is used to match this style sheet dataset.For example, the NX Check-Mate result log is in PLM XMLformat with .xml as an extension. It needs a style sheet (checkmat_log.xsl) for a tool (Internet Explorer for instance) to display its contents in a pre-defined format.This preference is also used to import style sheet files into the database as style sheet datasets during installation or the upgrade (post schema) process. Valid Values: The format is: dataset-type dataset-reference-type-name dataset-name stylesheet-name.extension validation-result-file-extension.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_TIMESTAMP_NREFS
preference.preference_description: Timestamp on a validation result and dataset is compared to decide whether the result is up-to-date. The following list is an extension to this logic. The list gives the Namedref list against each dataset type. For the following dataset types, instead of the dataset timestamp, the named reference timestamp is used to compare the dates. Valid Values: TRUE - Enables the named reference timestamp. FALSE - Disables the named reference timestamp.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_ViewValidationWithRuleSetColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of property names to be displayed as columns in the View Validation table. Valid Values: Accepts string array.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_ViewValidationWithRuleSetColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of columns displayed in the View Validation table. Valid Values: Accepts string array.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_duplicate_nx_valdata_error_on_import
preference.preference_description: Indicates if an error should be returned when importing an NX validation checker that has the same checker name as an existing NX validation checker. Valid Values: TRUE FALSE

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_include_validation_checker_for_site_transfer
preference.preference_description: Defines if the Validation Checker object referenced by a Validation Result will be included for export when the Validation Result is being exported with site ownership transfer. Valid values for this site preference are true and false (default value).

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_mandatory_checkers_required
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the mandatory checkers are required to be run when performing validation. Valid Values: true - Mandatory checkers are required. false - Mandatory checkers are not required.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_override_approval_roles
preference.preference_description: Specifies the roles that can approve or reject validation result override requests. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values. Each string must be a valid Teamcenter role.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_requirement_expressions_separator
preference.preference_description: Defines the string used to separate two requirement expressions for display. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. The following special characters are recommended values: . , ; / #

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_requirement_formula_expressions_separator
preference.preference_description: Defines the string used to separate the requirement formula and the requirement expressions for display. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_run_validation_hidden_agents
preference.preference_description: List of Validation Agent class names to be hidden in the list in the Run Validation dialog box. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as value.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_unify_itemrev_validation_form_ownership
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the owner of the Validation Results Summary form and associated report datasets is changed to the same owner of their associated item revision after its owner is changed. Valid Values: true - Sets the owner of the Validation Results Summary form and validation report datasets to the new owner of their associated item revision after the item revision's owner is changed. false - Leaves the owner of the Validation Results Summary form and validation report datasets unchanged following a change in their associated item revision's owner.

preference.name: TC_Validation_Datasettype
preference.preference_description: This preference will be used by the CM to set the datasettype for file validation and Conversion

preference.name: TC_Validation_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Displays validation results under the specified item revision types.All relation_business_object_relation_primary preferences are obsolete and are replaced by relation properties. Use the Business Modeler IDE to create and manage relation properties. Valid Values: Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be a valid item revision type.

preference.name: ValToolAgentRevision_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: Determines which properties are children of the ValToolAgentRevision business object. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid Teamcenter property name.

preference.name: ValToolAgentRevision_Tool_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Defines the default relation for associating a Tool object in context of a ValToolAgentRevision object. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. It must be a valid Teamcenter relation business object.

preference.name: ValidationAgent_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: Determines which properties are children of the ValidationAgent business object. Valid Values: Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid Teamcenter property name.

preference.name: ValidationMasterFormColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of property names to be displayed as columns in the ValidationMasterForm table. Valid Values: validation_target validation_name validation_application validation_utility_name validation_user validation_date result_state_flag validation_result override_to_state override_request_state

preference.name: ValidationMasterFormColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the shown columns in the ValidationMasterForm table. Valid Values: 10 25 15 10 10 15 10 10 10 15

preference.name: ResourceAssignment.resource_level.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Defines the string formatter for the property "resource_level" from ResourceAssignment objects. Use the string "%" (double quotes included) in order to represent the property value.

preference.name: ScheduleTask.complete_percent.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Specifies the format for the "complete_percent" property of ScheduleTask.

preference.name: g4mClassViewer.VIEWERCONFIGTOLOAD
preference.preference_description: Defines the viewer configuration name to load for the G4M Class Viewer. This is a user preference.

preference.name: g4mInstanceViewer.VIEWERCONFIGTOLOAD
preference.preference_description: Defines the viewer configuration name to load for the G4M Product Vision Viewer. This is a user preference.

preference.name: g4mProductVisionViewer.VIEWERCONFIGTOLOAD
preference.preference_description: Defines the viewer configuration name to load for the G4M Product Vision Viewer. This is a user preference.

preference.name: g4mViewerConfig.VIEWERCONFIG
preference.preference_description: Specifies an alternate Viewer view configuration to use for the Classification (g4m) application, and is used in place of the viewer_config_id.VIEWERCONFIG preference. This preference defines which Generic Relationship Management (GRM) rules to expand for the Classification application only.The Classification application provides a key to Teamcenter Services so that it can use the g4mKey.VIEWERCONFIGTOLOAD preference to load the viewer configuration set in this preference. Valid Values: teamcenter-type.viewer-ID = named-references Indicates the viewer to use for each Teamcenter type. SEARCHORDER.ITEMREV2DATASET = GRMs-list Specifies the Generic Relationship Management rules (GRMs) to expand from item revision to dataset. SEARCHORDER.ITEMREV2ITEMREV = item-revision-type-for-primary-side-of-relation . GRM-relation- name.item-revision-type-for-secondary-side-of-relation Specifies the Generic Relationship Management rules (GRMs) to expand from item revision to item revision, for example: SEARCHORDER.ITEMREV2ITEMREV = Part Revision.TC_Primary_Design_Representation.Design Revision The limitation with this value is that only a single hop from an item revision to another item revision is allowed. Indefinite expansion is not supported because there could be issues with circular rules.

category.name: Volume Management.Hierarchical Storage Management
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: HSM_secondary_tier_capacity
preference.preference_description: Sends an e-mail alert when the capacity of the second tier volume reaches capacity. Set this preference to the estimated capacity level of the second tier volume. Compute this estimate by totalling all storage capacities of all disks mounted on the secondary tier.The hsm_capacity_alert utility estimates the capacities of the volumes and uses the values defined in this preference to send e-mail alerts when the secondary tier capacity exceeds alert levels. Valid Values: Accepts a single string as a value. The value must be the estimated capacity of the second tier volume. For example:HSM_secondary_tier_capacity= 16.9

category.name: Workflow
category.category_description: No description available for this category.

preference.name: CR_allow_alternate_procedures
preference.preference_description:
Manages the visibility of workflow templates in the "New Process" panel of the Workflow application in the rich client. Valid Values: * any : The "All" option is pre-selected in the "All/Assigned" radio button group, which means that all templates are listed. * Assigned: The "Assigned" option is pre-selected in the "All/Assigned" radio button group, which means that only the templates assigned to the group and selected target object type are listed. This is the default value. * none: The options "All/Assigned" are not visible. Furthermore, only the templates assigned to the group and selected target object type are displayed (behaviour similar to the "Assigned" option). When no templates are assigned for the target group/type, the displayed list is empty. If no object was selected when initiating the workflow, all the templates assigned to the group are listed.
Process templates assigned to a group and a target object type are defined through the "Process designer->Edit->Template Filter" command.

preference.name: ENABLE_invoke_system_handlers
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to enable/disable invoke-system-rule and invoke-system-action workflow handlers. Valid values are YES/NO. YES (which is the default setting) - Enables these handlers and are displayed in handler selection dialog. NO - Disables these handlers and will not be displayed in handler selection dialog.

preference.name: EPM_ARG_target_user_group_list_separator
preference.preference_description: Indicates what separator to user when a list of groups or users are returned. This preference is related to $TARGETGROUP/$TARGETOWNER keywords used in the handlers such as CR-fill-in-reviewers. Default value is ",".

preference.name: EPM_adhoc_signoffs
preference.preference_description: Enables the adhoc signoffs functionality in the Workflow application in the rich client. Valid Values: * ON: Enables adhoc signoffs. This is the default value. * OFF: Disables adhoc signoffs.

preference.name: EPM_enable_apply_template_changes
preference.preference_description: Enables template changes to all active workflow processes in the client. Valid Values: NONE: template changes will not be applied to active workflow processes and no option will be presented in the client. This is the default value. OPTIONAL: a) in Workflow Designer when the template stage is being changed to Available, a follow-up dialog will be displayed prompting the user if the template changes should be applied to all active workflow processes. b) an additional checkbox will be displayed in the "Workflow Template Import" dialog to determine if the template changes should be applied to all active workflow processes. AUTOMATIC: template changes will be automatically applied to all active workflow processes. The user will not be prompted to specify if the template changes should be applied.

preference.name: EPM_multiple_processes_targets
preference.preference_description: Enables/Disables multiple processes for same objects in the Workflow application. Valid Values: * ON: Enables Multiple processes. This is the default value. * OFF: Disables Multiple processes.

preference.name: EPM_notify_url_format
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of client connection for URL generation by notify and CR-notify handlers. The valid values are "rich", "dhtml", "activeworkspace" and "none".

preference.name: EPM_resource_pool_restrict_subscription
preference.preference_description: Restricts the resource pools available for subscription based on user membership in the "Resource Pool Subscription" dialog. Valid Values: ON - the user can subscribe only to groups and roles for which he/she is a member. OFF - the users can subscribe to all groups and roles. This is the default value.

preference.name: EPM_skip_dataset_purge
preference.preference_description: Determines if dataset versions are purged when the EPM-set-status workflow handler adds a status to a dataset. Valid values are true/false: true - Dataset versions are not purged false - Dataset versions are purged. This is a site preference.

preference.name: EPM_sub_process_target_inheritance
preference.preference_description: Defines the default setting of the 'Inherit Targets' checkbox in the 'New Workflow Sub-Process' dialog. Valid values are ON/OFF: ON - the 'Inherit Targets' checkbox will be ticked. OFF - the 'Inherit Targets' checkbox will not be ticked. This is a site preference.

preference.name: EPM_task_execution_mode
preference.preference_description: Determines which task execution mode should be used to process a Workflow task. Valid Values: * FOREGROUND: Processes all tasks in foreground mode. This is the default value. * BACKGROUND: Processes all tasks in background mode. * CONFIGURABLE: Processes a task according to its task template's "ExecuteAsync" property setting. If the property is set to "ON", the task will be processed in background mode. If the property is set to "OFF", the task will be processed in foreground mode.

preference.name: EPM_valid_roles_to_assign_responsible_party
preference.preference_description: Determines the list of privileged users allowed to reassign the Responsible Party responsibility of a task. Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be one of the following values: responsible_party - Allows the current Responsible Party. active_surrogate - Allows the current surrogate user. task_owner - Allows the owning user of the workflow process. task_owning_group - Allows all users belonging to the group of the owning user. world - Allows all users. privileged - Allows the following users: Current task owner, Responsible Party, All Administrative users group::role - Allows members of a specific group and role. Accepts following format: group::role where group is valid group name and role is a valid role name. This preference will be deprecated from 10.1.2.2 and the assign action will be performed on bmide condition 'Fnd0AssignAccessPrivilege' evaluation.

preference.name: EPM_valid_user_to_apply_assignment_list
preference.preference_description: Lists all the values to determine the authorized users to to use Assign All Tasks functionality that assigns the resources to all tasks of the workflow process This preference takes the following values owner - Owning User of the Process owning_group - Workflow Process Owning Group Users world - all users privileged - All site admin users and the group admin users of the process owning group group::role - Group and Role Name to specify resource pool.

preference.name: ForciblyMakeDesignPrimary
preference.preference_description: Bypasses the write permission on Part Revisions for creating TC_Primary_Design_Representation relations between Part Revisions and Design Revisions. The default value is false. Please note that this preference applies only when PS-make-mature-design-primary handler is used to make a Design Revision primary through a Workflow Process.

preference.name: Global_transfer_access
preference.preference_description: Setting for global_transfer utilityall users regardless of this preference settings can use the Global transferfunctionality to transfer their own tasks to someone else. This preferenceconfigures who can assign other users task to someone else.0--> System Administrator can also transer tasks assigned to other users1--> System & Group Administrators can also transfer tasks assigned to others, for group admin it'll only enable this for users within the respective group2--> Every body can transfer tasks assigned to others.

preference.name: INBOX_hide_suspended_tasks
preference.preference_description: Valid values are 0/1/2/3. 0 - Default condition to show Started & suspended tasks in the tasks to perform. 1 - Condition to show Only Started tasks in the tasks to perform. 2 - Suspend All Started Tasks of this job. Show Started & suspended tasks in the tasks to perform. 3 - Suspend All Started Tasks of this job. Show Only Started tasks in the tasks to perform. Also suspend all other started tasks of the job.

preference.name: SIGNOFF_adhoc_quorum
preference.preference_description:
Indicates if the task quorum modifiable by Teamcenter user in select-signoff-team can be set lower than that defined by the task template when adhoc signoffs functionality is enabled (EPM_adhoc_signoffs=ON). Valid values are 1/2. 1 - User can set signoff quorum value either less than or greater than that set by task template. 2 - User can set signoff quorum value only greater that that set by task template.
NOTE: For setting 2, if the signoff-quorum is set as -1 (ALL), in that case, the user cannot modify the signoff quorum through select-signoff-team task.
This is a site preference.

preference.name: SIGNOFF_fill_in_reviewers
preference.preference_description: Determines how group members are selected by the EPM-fill-in-reviewers handler when attempting to assign un-staffed sign-off profiles. Preference values 1, 2 or 3 only effect the behavior of the $USER handler argument. Preference value 4 effects the behavior of all the arguments, and in organizations with many group memberships per user will perform better as it does not exhaustively attempt to match the user to an un-staffed sign-off profile using all their group memberships. 1 --> For the $USER handler argument only,it will first attempt to assign un-staffed sign-off profiles using group member from the user's current log-in setting. If no match is found, it will next attempt to assign group member from the user's default group setting.If then also no match is found, it will exhaustively attempt to assign a single group member from any other group membership to which the user belongs. 2 --> For the $USER handler argument only,it will first attempt to assign un-staffed sign-off profiles using group member from the user's current log-in setting. If no match is found, it will next attempt to assign group member from the user's default group setting. 3 --> For the $USER handler argument only,it will attempt to assign un-staffed sign-off profiles using group member from the user's current log-in setting. 4 --> For the $USER handler argument only,it will attempt to assign un-staffed sign-off profile using group member from the user's current log-in setting.For all other handler arguments, It will use the group member the handler argument resolves to.But for cases where the handler argument resolves to a user only, It will use the default group member for that user to assign un-staffed sign-off profiles.

preference.name: SIGNOFF_required_group_and_role
preference.preference_description: Setting for SIGNOFF_required_group_and_role 0--> User must be a registered member of the signoff required group and role, but doesn't have to be logged in as a member of that group or role to perform the signoff. (Default) 1--> User must be a registered member of the signoff required group and role, and must be currently logged in as a member of that group or role to perform the signoff.

preference.name: SKF_EBOM_CM_SignOffProfileRoles
preference.preference_description: This preference is used to assign the specific role members for EBOM Change Management Notification.

preference.name: TASK_MONITOR_SLEEP_TIME
preference.preference_description: Used to set the sleep time for the task monitor daemon. Sleep time should be an integer specifying the desired number of minutes. e.g. 30 for 30 minutes, 60 for 1 hour and 120 for 2 hours.

preference.name: TCVIEWER_default_workflow_view
preference.preference_description: Specifies what the users want to see as default viewer for viewing process tasks. Valid values are task/process.

preference.name: User.is_out_of_office.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Defines the property formatter for the "is_out_of_office" boolean property on User business object. Using this property formatter, the boolean property is displayed as the localized values of the keys "k_yes" for "True" and "k_no" for "False".

preference.name: WORKFLOW_adhoc_process
preference.preference_description: Site preference flag indicating if adhoc process functionalities are enabled. Valid values are 0/1/2. 0 - Enabled for all users. 1 - Enabled only if the user is a system administrator or user granted edit access to Workflow Designer. 2 - Enabled for System Adminitrators and Group admins or user granted edit access to Workflow Designer(default).

preference.name: WORKFLOW_advanced_paste
preference.preference_description: Preference to display the Advanced Paste icon in File New Process dialog. Valid values are ON/OFF. If it is set to ON, the icon will be visible. If it is set to OFF, the icon will not be displayed.

preference.name: WORKFLOW_new_route_task_panel
preference.preference_description: Site Preference to display the new route task panel with action column instead of route task panel with radio buttons. Valid values are ON/OFF. If it is set to ON, the new route task panel will be displayed.If it is set to OFF, the old route task panel with radio buttons will be displayed.

preference.name: WRKFLW_access_level_for_handlers_execution
preference.preference_description: Indicates access level that will be used for all handlers. By default some handlers will execute with system access and some handlers will execute with user access, but if this preference is set to "system" then all handlers will execute with system access regardless of the handler's default access. Valid Values: * system: All handlers will execute with system access. * regular: Handlers will execute with their default access. This is the default setting.

preference.name: WRKFLW_add_template_name_for_new_process
preference.preference_description: Defines whether the template name is prepended to the item when submitting to workflow. Valid Values: true: The template name will appear before the item name when submitting the item to workflow. false: Only the item name will be given when submitting to workflow.

preference.name: WRKFLW_admin_for_inactive_user
preference.preference_description: Defines the mailing list to be notified when the workflow automatically reassigns a task or signoff to a resource pool if the user is inactive. It is a single value string type preference. Valid Values: * Any valid email address. For multiple email addresses use semicolon (;) to separate two email addresses.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_adding_target_behavior
preference.preference_description: Preference to decide whether to allow adding/pasting target(s) based on "fnd0FilterCondition" condition. Valid Values: 0 - Allow specific target(s) which satisfies "fnd0FilterCondition" condition when the value of "CR_allow_alternate_procedures" preference is set to "none". 1 - Allow any target(s). This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_quorum_override
preference.preference_description: Preference to enable/disable "Quorum" settings. Valid Values: * true will enable the numeric box * false will disable the numeric box

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_replica_targets
preference.preference_description: Defines whether replica objects should be allowed as replica proposed targets for workflows. Valid Values: true: The replica objects will be attached to the workflow as replica proposed targets. This is the default value. false: The replica proposed targets attachments will be used.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_wait_for_undecided_override
preference.preference_description: Preference to enable/disable "Wait for Undecided" check box in RAC and "Require Full Participation" in AWC. Valid Values: * true will enable the check box * false will disable the check box

preference.name: WRKFLW_async_error_notifyees
preference.preference_description:
This preference is used to determine the recipients of an asynchronous Workflow error notification. When an error occurs in a background session a notification is sent to inform the recipients of the error.
Any combination of the values described below may be used to identify the notification recipients. Invalid values will be ignored. If there are no values or all values are invalid or this preference is missing then the recipient will default to $USER.
The Valid Values: * $USER - The current user. This is the default setting. * user:<user ID> - The user specified by the Teamcenter user ID. * allmembers:<group>::<role> - All members of the group/role combination. May be defined in the form of allmembers:<group>::, allmembers:<group>::<role>, or allmembers:<role>. * $PROCESS_OWNER - The Workflow process owner. * $RESPONSIBLE_PARTY - The Workflow task responsible party.

preference.name: WRKFLW_change_target_lmu
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the value of "last modified user" information for the workflow targets should be modified when modifying their release statuses during workflow. Valid Values: * true: the last modified user should be set to the current user. This is the default value. * false: the last modified user should not be modified.

preference.name: WRKFLW_convert_backward_path_representation
preference.preference_description: Indicates if a checkbox option to convert backward branching paths will be displayed when a Process template is taken offline. Valid Values: * false: the checkbox option is not displayed when a Process template is taken offline. This is the default value. * true: the checkbox option is displayed when a Process template is taken offline and backward branching paths are present.

preference.name: WRKFLW_create_remote_workflow
preference.preference_description: Defines whether the workflow should be created at the remote site. Valid Values: true: An asynchronous request will be submitted to create the workflow at the remote site. This is the default value. false:Workflow will be created at the local site.

preference.name: WRKFLW_display_participants
preference.preference_description: Decides which participant types will be shown while assigning dynamic participants for an object. Valid Values: * allowable: Show all the dynamic participant types associated with the target object type. This is the default value. * assignable: Show all the dynamic participant types which are assignable by the current user and used in any of the in-progress workflows on the target object. If there is no in-progress workflow; all the assignable dynamic participant types will be shown.

preference.name: WRKFLW_error_on_invalid_dynamic_participant
preference.preference_description: Decides whether the workflow handlers will report an error if a dynamic participant is empty or reassign task to resource pool in case of inactive user. The following handlers would use this preference: * EPM-auto-assign * EPM-auto-assign-rest * EPM-assign-team-selector * EPM-adhoc-signoffs * EPM-fill-in-reviewers * EPM-assign-signoff-dynamic-participant * EPM-assign-responsible-party-dynamic-participant Valid Values: * true: The handlers will report an error in case of empty dynamic participant or reassigns the task to resource pool in case of inactive user. * false: The handlers will not report an error in case of empty dynamic participant or reassigns task to resource pool. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_fnd0Instructions_available
preference.preference_description: Preference to enable/disable "fnd0Instructions" property in stylesheet. Valid Values: * true: Enables the "fnd0Instructions" property and disables property "object_desc"in stylesheets.This is the default value. * false: Disables the "fnd0Instructions" property and enables property "object_desc".

preference.name: WRKFLW_inbox_content_mechanism
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the tasks seen in the user's inbox are to fetched using inbox queries or the TaskInbox folder contents. Valid values are: * query : Uses Inbox queries to fetch the tasks to be displayed in task inbox. The insertion and removal of tasks and signoffs in the inbox are also supressed. This is the default value * folder_contents : Uses the "contents" property of task inbox to display tasks.

preference.name: WRKFLW_modify_completed_workflow
preference.preference_description: Allows removing targets from completed Workflows. Valid Values: * true: Removal is allowed. * false: Removal is disabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_modify_target_list_access_privilege
preference.preference_description: Indicates the access privilege to be used in order to enforce permission on modification of the Workflow target list. Valid values are any access privilege. The default value is the CHANGE access privilege.

preference.name: WRKFLW_multisite_apply_template_changes
preference.preference_description: Controls the application of template changes in a replica site after synchronization. If a replica template has active workflow processes, this preference will be consulted before applying the template changes to the active workflow processes when the replica template is synchronized with changes made to the master template. Valid Values: true: Template changes will be applied to the active workflow processes after synchronizing the template changes. false:Template changes will not be applied to the active workflow processes after synchronizing the template changes. This is the default value. This is a site preference.

preference.name: WRKFLW_parent_behavior_on_sub_process_abort
preference.preference_description: 1. Trigger dependent parent task to complete. (default value) 2. No action on dependent parent task. User will decide what action to take.

preference.name: WRKFLW_retain_ACL_objects_on_release
preference.preference_description: Determines the state of Access Control List objects on a target when a release status is applied. Valid Values: true: Any pre-existing ACL objects will not be removed when the release status is applied. false:Any pre-existing ACL objects will be removed when the release status is applied. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_show_deferred_participant_assignments
preference.preference_description: Indicate whether to show deferred participant assignments in Active Workspace client. This feature is specifically designed to work with Teamcenter platform release 13.1 and higher. Valid Values: * true: User will be able to see deferred participant assignments. This is the default value. * false: User will not be able to see deferred participant assignments.

preference.name: WRKFLW_show_non_condition_templates
preference.preference_description: Controls the results of Condition based Workflow Template filtering shown in the Workflow create/submit panels, specifically whether we show or hide Workflow Templates that have no associated BMIDE Condition filter. Valid Values: * true: Show workflow templates on which condition is not defined. * false: Hide workflow templates on which condition is not defined. This is default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_show_user_assignment_options
preference.preference_description: Decides which participant tabs will be shown while assigning users to dynamic participants or workflow tasks. Valid Values: * org_default: The organization tree as well as project team list will be shown for assigning users. The organization tree will be the initially selected tab. This is the default value. * project_default: The organization tree as well as project team list will be shown for assigning users. The project team list will be the initially selected tab. * org_only: Only the organization tree will be shown and project team list will be hidden. * project_only: Only the project team list will be shown and organization tree will be hidden.

preference.name: WRKFLW_signoff_report_show_sub_process
preference.preference_description: Controls the details of Signoff, for the parent process and sub-processes, shown in the Signoff report in the Workflow application. Valid Values: 0 - Shows signoff details for the parent process as well as dependent or independent sub-processes. 1 - Shows signoff details for the parent process and only dependent sub-processes. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_task_assignee_dynamic_participant_sync
preference.preference_description: Controls synchronization between a Task Assignee and Dynamic Participants of a Task's target object. When such synchronization is enabled, task reassignment will result in the reassignment of Dynamic Participants of the Task's target object, and vice versa. This synchronization behavior is possible only when the initial task assignment is based on a Dynamic Participant of the Task's target object. Valid Values: * true: Task assignments are synchronized with assignment of Dynamic Participants on the Task's target object. This is the default value. * false: Task assignments are not synchronized with assignment of Dynamic Participants on the Task's target object.

preference.name: WRKFLW_task_complete
preference.preference_description:
Defines the default selection some key components, in order to enable single-click in the "Perform" action for Tasks in the Workflow application in the rich client. The preference applies only to "Do" Tasks and "select-signoff-team" for Review and Route Tasks. If the value is true: - "Do" Tasks: the "Complete" value is selected by default in the "Done" radio buttons. - "select-signoff-team" for Review and Route Tasks: the "Ad-hoc done" checkbox is selected by default.
If the value is false, no value is pre-selected for either Tasks.
IMPORTANT: Setting the value to true also sets the associated Task result value (task_result property) to "complete" by default.

preference.name: WRKFLW_use_legacy_template_filter
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether to use the legacy Type and Group based Template Filter or the new Condition based Template Filter. Valid Values: * true: Use the legacy Type and Group based Template Filter. * false: Use the new Condition based Template Filter. This is the default value.

category.name: epwi
category.category_description: epw0workinstructions template preferences

preference.name: WI_DocumentRelationsInfo
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties/relations data to be shown in the Document view in the EasyPlan Work Instructions (EPW) solution in the EasyPlan. The valid format for the values is "<property/relation name>[:<type names>]" where: * <property/relation name> is the property or the relation name of the step object (sub-type of BOMLine). * <type names> is a comma separated list of internal type names of the secondary objects to show for the given property/relation. This argument is optional. In case the type names are not provided, all of the secondary objects information will be shown.

preference.name: WI_ImageRelationsInfo
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties/relations data to be shown in the Image view in the EasyPlan Work Instructions (EPW) solution in the EasyPlan. The valid format for the values is "<property/relation name>[:<type names>]" where: * <property/relation name> is the property or the relation name of the step object (sub-type of BOMLine). * <type names> is a comma separated list of internal type names of the secondary objects to show for the given property/relation. This argument is optional. In case the type names are not provided, all of the secondary objects information will be shown.

preference.name: WI_InstructionRelationsInfo
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties/relations data to be shown in the Ref Instructions view in the EasyPlan Work Instructions (EPW) solution in the EasyPlan. The valid format for the values is "<property/relation name>[:<type names>]" where: * <property/relation name> is the property or the relation name of the step object (sub-type of BOMLine). * <type names> is a comma separated list of internal type names of the secondary objects to show for the given property/relation. This argument is optional. In case the type names are not provided, all of the secondary objects information will be shown. Note: If the instructions are simple string property values, only specify the <property/relation name> parameter. In this case, if the <type names> parameter is specified then it will be ignored.

preference.name: WI_SavedPresets
preference.preference_description: Defines the saved presets for notes shown in Graphics Viewer in the Work Instructions (WI) solution in the EasyPlan. The valid format for the values is "color": "#FF0000", "font-family": "Courier New", "font-size":"30px" where: * color: is the color of the font in hex code format * font-family: is the font name * font-size: is the size of font in pixels

preference.name: WI_Support
preference.preference_description: Defines if the Work Instructions solution is installed.

category.name: mfgcore
category.category_description: mbc0mfgbvrcore template preferences

preference.name: AWC_Mfg0BvrOperation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the stylesheet for the Mfg0BvrOperation objects.

preference.name: AWC_Mfg0BvrPlantBOP.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the stylesheet for the Mfg0BvrPlantBOP objects.

preference.name: AWC_Mfg0BvrProcess.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the stylesheet for the Mfg0BvrProcess objects.

preference.name: AWC_Mfg0BvrProcessArea.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the stylesheet for the Mfg0BvrProcessArea objects.

preference.name: AWC_Mfg0BvrProcessLine.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the stylesheet for the Mfg0BvrProcessLine objects.

preference.name: AWC_Mfg0BvrProcessStation.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the stylesheet for the Mfg0BvrProcessStation objects.

preference.name: AWC_Mfg0BvrProductBOP.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the stylesheet for the Mfg0BvrProductBOP objects.

preference.name: EP_BackgroundPartsEbomColumnConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Column configuration for EBOM tree and Background Parts Tree on Background Parts Management page - EasyPlan. Value Format: objectType.propertyName.columnWidth

preference.name: EP_BopBreakdownAssemblyTreeColumnConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Column configuration for Assembly Tree on BOP Breakdown page - EasyPlan. Value Format: objectType.propertyName.columnWidth

preference.name: EP_BopBreakdownProcessTreeColumnConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Column configuration for Process Tree on BOP Breakdown page - EasyPlan. Value Format: objectType.propertyName.columnWidth

preference.name: EP_CloneAlternativeTemplateName
preference.preference_description: The name of the preference used for cloning the objects while cloning an alernative from alternative workpackage. The default value is EP_ProjectCloneAlternativeTemplate. That means, while cloning an alternative,the objects will be cloned according to rules specified by the preference EP_ProjectCloneAlternativeTemplate. The administrator can create a new preference, specify the cloning rules for various objects in it and then name that preference here.

preference.name: EP_CreateAlternativeTemplateName
preference.preference_description: The name of the preference used for cloning the objects while creating an alernative from work package. The default value is ProjectPlantBOPTemplate. That means, while creating an alternative, the objects will be cloned according to rules specified by the preference ProjectPlantBOPTemplate. The administrator can create a new preference, specify the cloning rules for various objects in it and then name that preference here.

preference.name: EP_CreateSubtypesForType_BOPFolder
preference.preference_description: List of types of the processes to be used as folder processes. These process types will be allowed to be created when user tries to Create Folder from BOP Breakdown page in Easy Plan. Depending on the value of type constant Mbc0BOPQualifier, a folder icon will be displayed for the created process. Set the value of type constant Mbc0BOPQualifier as BOPFolder for the revision object of process listed here. If not set, the process will be displayed as normal process. In any case, the processes created from this preference will be treated as folder. Please see the documentation of type constant Mbc0BOPQualifier.

preference.name: EP_CreateSubtypesForType_Item
preference.preference_description: List of subtypes to show when creating an item

preference.name: EP_CreateSubtypesForType_Mfg0ProcResource
preference.preference_description: List of subtypes to show when creating a process resource

preference.name: EP_DependenciesTabColumnConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Column Configuration for dependencies tab on Process area page - EasyPlan. Value Format: objectType.propertyName.columnWidth

preference.name: EP_DisplayAutoBOPGenerationCommand
preference.preference_description: Preference to govern the visibility of the command "Autogenerate Structures" in manage work package page. The value should be set to True if the "Rule Stream Engineering" And "Rule Stream architect" applications are installed on the system.

preference.name: EP_DisplayLegacyPlanningPage
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to display the legacy planning page or the new planning page in Easy Plan application. The default value is 'false'.

preference.name: EP_EffectivityMode
preference.preference_description: The type of effectivity to be considered while configuring the structure in WorkInstruction application. Default value is UNIT. Other value can be DATE.

preference.name: EP_FileTypesForLayoutDataset
preference.preference_description: Defines the allowed file types to be attached as layout dataset to process area or line.

preference.name: EP_LayoutRelation
preference.preference_description: Defines the relation type to be used while attaching a layout dataset.

preference.name: EP_OperationsTypes
preference.preference_description: Define the types of operation for each operation persistent type including sub-types. The type can be None, Human or Machine. Default values are None for MEOP, Human for Mbc0HumanOp and Machine for Mbc0MachineOp.

preference.name: EP_PlanningForSmallProduct
preference.preference_description: This will be used in ETO workspace. The default value is false. That means the user will see the "BOP Breakdown task" in the Easy Plan application. The value is expected to be set as true for the customers who have small MBOM structures up to 2500 lines. When the value is set to true then the "BOP Breakdown task" will be bypassed in easy plan.

preference.name: EP_ProductTabTreeGridColumnConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Column configuration for 'Product Tab' tree showing MBOM or Available Target Assemblies. Value Format: objectType.propertyName.columnWidth

preference.name: EP_ProjectCloneAlternativeTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules to be used when cloning a alternative from alternative workpackage. The "Origin" relation "Mfg0MEProjectOriginRel" is created between objects of new alternative plantBop and master plantBop. The default cloning rules of this preference are such that - If an alternative work package say Alt1 is created from a master work package say Master and then if the Alt1 is cloned to another workpackage Alt2 then - The objects in Alt2 will be related to the objects in Master workpackage. There will be no relation in between the objects from Alt2 and Alt1. Thus the accountability check can be run in between Master and Alt2. The accountability check will not be run in between Alt1 and Alt2. There will be no effect on relationship of objects from Alt1 and Master. All of this can be achieved through the cloning rule - *:*:Relation.Mfg0MEProjectOriginRel:EBOPReference The action EBOPReference is must. If it is not specified as EBOPReference in this rule, the above mentioned behavior can not be achieved.

preference.name: EP_SplitChangeNotice
preference.preference_description: To indicate when to split the existing change notice and to create a new change notice

preference.name: EP_TargetAssembliesTabTableColumnConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Column configuration for 'Target Assemblies Tab' table showing Assigned Target Assemblies. Value Format: objectType.propertyName.columnWidth

preference.name: EP_WorkPackageContentType
preference.preference_description: This preference defines the list of structures which will be displayed in the manage work package page. For each structure it defines the type of object to be stored in the corresponding work package, in case that the structure is added in Easy Plan. Syntax is StructureType1:ContentType1, StructureType2:ContentType2. Valid values for StructureType are - EBOM, MBOM, BOP, Plant, PlantBOP, ProductBOP and ProductionProgram. Valid values for ContentType are - Item, ItemRevision, PSBOMView and PSBOMViewRevision.

preference.name: EP_bop_type
preference.preference_description: This preference determines the bop type the EP application handles - plantBop or legacyBop.

preference.name: EP_domainUrl
preference.preference_description: Easy Plan site URL

preference.name: MBC_AllowedDatasetTypes
preference.preference_description: Allowed dataset types in create dataset UI and quick overview UI.The value is in the format <relation_type>.<dataset_type>.

preference.name: MBC_RelationTypeAssignedDocuments
preference.preference_description: This preference defines the occurrence types that indicate assignment of a document item. Any item assigned to a BOPLine with this occurrence types will be treated as a document item.

preference.name: MBC_VAColor
preference.preference_description: This preference is used to define the color that will be used in the application for each time category

preference.name: MBC_VisibleDatasetTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies which dataset types are visible in files panel.The value is in the format <relation_type>.<dataset_type>.

preference.name: MERelationTypePartsBackground
preference.preference_description: Defines the relation (occurrence) types that Teamcenter interprets as assignment of background parts to processes. Valid Values: An array of strings, where each string represents a relation (occurrence) type.

preference.name: Mbc0OperatorAction.mbc0estimatedTime.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Formatting the walk time property of an operation.

preference.name: Mfg0BvrOperation.mbc0walkTime.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Formatting the walk time property of an operation.

preference.name: Mfg0BvrOperation.mbc0workTime.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Formatting the work time property of an operation.

preference.name: Mfg0BvrPlantBOP.mbc0allowance.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Formatting plant allowance time

preference.name: Mfg0BvrPlantBOP.mbc0performanceRatingFactor.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Formatting plant PRF

preference.name: Mfg0BvrProcessArea.elb0taktTimeConverted.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Formatting the TAKT time of a process area.

preference.name: Mfg0BvrProductVariant.Mfg0productionRate.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Formatting product variant production rate
